{"type":"text","timestamp":1783915517097,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"id":"prt_f59a68fbd001TdfHLJHBE347sq","messageID":"msg_f59a67e81001hLZDigWbA2Eahr","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","type":"text","text":"The context trigger lookup timed out, so continuity retrieval is unavailable through that path. `SKILL ROUTING: User directed -> deep-review; executor directed -> cli-opencode.` I will proceed from the explicit packet and detached-lineage bindings rather than infer missing context.","time":{"start":1783915515837,"end":1783915517095},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_09eda0dc789b5e39016a5463fbd7e08191b9673ece12533eda","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915517158,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_QcAumeKKyfrCz1wOTx4xGAWO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"deep-review"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"deep-review\">\n# Skill: deep-review\n\n<!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n\n<!-- Keywords: deep-review, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n\nIterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n\nConvergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### When to Use This Skill\n\nUse this skill when:\n- Code quality audit requiring multiple rounds across different review dimensions\n- Spec folder validation requiring cross-reference checks between docs and implementation\n- Release readiness check before shipping a feature or component\n- Finding misalignments between spec documents and actual code\n- Verifying cross-references across documentation, agents, commands, and code\n- Iterative review where each dimension's findings inform subsequent dimensions\n- Unattended or overnight audit sessions\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- Simple single-pass code review (use `sk-code`'s code-review mode instead)\n- Known issues that just need fixing (go directly to implementation)\n- Implementation tasks (use `sk-code` or `/speckit:implement`)\n- Quick one-file checks (use direct Grep/Read)\n- Fewer than 2 review dimensions needed (single-pass suffices)\n\n### FORBIDDEN INVOCATION PATTERNS\n\nThis skill is invoked EXCLUSIVELY through the `/deep:review` command. The command's YAML workflow owns state, dispatch, and convergence.\n\n**NEVER:**\n- Write a custom bash/shell dispatcher to parallelize iterations (ad-hoc shell fan-out)\n- Invoke cli-opencode / cli-claude-code directly in a loop to simulate iterations\n- Manually write iteration prompts to `/tmp` and dispatch them via `copilot -p`\n- Dispatch the `@deep-review` LEAF agent via the Task tool for iteration loops (the agent is LEAF, a single iteration, and MUST be driven by the command's workflow)\n- Skip the state machine: `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-config.json`, `deltas/`, `prompts/`, `logs/`\n- Manage iteration state outside the resolved local review packet under `{spec_folder}/review/`\n\n**COMMAND-DRIVEN FAN-OUT IS SUPPORTED:** use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on `/deep:review`. The command's YAML `step_fanout_spawn` owns multi-lineage dispatch; `fanout-merge.cjs` applies strongest-restriction (any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL). This is not ad-hoc shell dispatch — it is the canonical fan-out path. Intra-lineage wave orchestration remains deferred.\n\n**ALWAYS:**\n- Invoke via `/deep:review :auto` or `/deep:review :confirm`\n- Let the command's YAML workflow own dispatch (auto: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`)\n- Let `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` be the SINGLE state writer\n- Require every iteration to produce BOTH the markdown narrative AND the JSONL delta (dispatch scripts must fail if either is missing)\n- Use `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` to locate the canonical review root\n\n### Trigger Phrases\n\n- \"review code quality\" / \"audit this code\"\n- \"audit spec folder\" / \"validate spec completeness\"\n- \"release readiness check\" / \"pre-release review\"\n- \"find misalignments\" (between spec and implementation)\n- \"verify cross-references\" (across docs and code)\n- \"deep review\" / \"iterative review\" / \"review loop\"\n- \"quality audit\" / \"convergence detection\"\n\n### Keyword Triggers\n\n`deep review`, `convergence review`, `iterative review`, `review loop`, `release readiness`, `spec folder review`, `convergence detection`, `quality audit`, `find misalignments`, `verify cross-references`, `pre-release review`, `audit spec folder`\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level | When to Load | Resources |\n|-------|-------------|-----------|\n| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop protocol, convergence, state format, review contract |\n| ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full protocol docs, detailed specifications |\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards markdown paths, checks `inventory`, and uses `seen`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - `get_routing_key()` derives the review phase from dispatch context.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` returns review disambiguation and missing phases return a \"no review resources\" notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/protocol/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"deep review\", \"review mode\", \"convergence review\", \"iterative review\", \":review\", \"audit spec\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"review iteration\", \"dimension review\", \"review findings\", \"P0\", \"P1\", \"P2\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review convergence\", \"coverage gate\", \"verdict\", \"binary gate\", \"all dimensions\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review report\", \"remediation\", \"verdict\", \"release readiness\", \"planning packet\"]},\n}\n\nNOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"audit code\": 2.0, \"review spec folder\": 1.8, \"release readiness\": 1.5, \"pre-release\": 1.5},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"review dimension\": 1.5, \"check correctness\": 1.4, \"check security\": 1.4, \"check alignment\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"all dimensions covered\": 1.6, \"coverage complete\": 1.5, \"stop review\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"review results\": 1.5, \"what to fix\": 1.4, \"ship decision\": 1.6, \"final report\": 1.5},\n}\n\n# RESOURCE_MAP: local markdown assets + local review-specific protocol docs\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_strategy.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": [\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/protocol/completion_criteria.md\",\n        \"references/protocol/loop_state_and_gates.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      [\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\":            [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all templates\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep review\", \"deep-review wave\", \"review artifact\", \"release-readiness audit\", \"convergence-tracked\", \"same session lineage\", \"P0\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\":         [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nPHASE_RESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"init\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n    \"iteration\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n    \"stuck\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n    \"synthesis\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\", \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\"],\n}\n\nNON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES = {\n    \"review_contract\": \"assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\",\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm the review target or spec folder\",\n    \"Confirm the review phase\",\n    \"Provide one concrete file, diff range, or expected finding class\",\n    \"Confirm the verification command set before final review\",\n]\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n\ndef get_routing_key(dispatch_context) -> str:\n    phase = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"phase\", \"\")).strip().lower()\n    if phase:\n        return phase\n    text = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if \"recovery\" in text:\n        return \"stuck\"\n    if \"convergence\" in text or \"synthesis\" in text:\n        return \"synthesis\"\n    if \"iteration\" in text or \"dimension\" in text:\n        return \"iteration\"\n    return \"init\"\n\ndef route_review_resources(task, dispatch_context):\n    inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n    routing_key = get_routing_key(dispatch_context)\n    scores = score_intents(task, INTENT_SIGNALS, NOISY_SYNONYMS)\n    intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n\n    loaded = []\n    seen = set()\n\n    def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n        if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n            load(guarded)\n            loaded.append(guarded)\n            seen.add(guarded)\n\n    for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n        return {\n            \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    phase_resources = PHASE_RESOURCE_MAP.get(routing_key, [])\n    if routing_key == \"unknown\" or not phase_resources:\n        return {\n            \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n            \"notice\": f\"No review resources found for routing key '{routing_key}'\",\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    for intent in intents:\n        for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    for relative_path in phase_resources:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    task_text = str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if any(keyword in task_text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n        for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    return {\n        \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n        \"intents\": intents,\n        \"resources\": loaded,\n        \"non_markdown_references\": NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES,\n    }\n```\n\n### Phase Detection\n\nDetect the current review phase from dispatch context to load appropriate resources:\n\n| Phase | Signal | Resources to Load |\n|-------|--------|-------------------|\n| Init | No JSONL exists in `review/` | Loop protocol, state format, state outputs, review contract |\n| Iteration | Dispatch context includes dimension + iteration number | Loop protocol, convergence, convergence signals, review contract |\n| Stuck | Dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY\" | Convergence, convergence signals, loop protocol, reducer registry |\n| Synthesis | Convergence triggered STOP | Review contract, state format, state outputs, reducer registry |\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Resource Map Coverage Gate\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init, deep review treats it as a mandatory audit input: `resource_map_present` is persisted in config, a map snapshot seeds `Known Context`, at least one iteration audits `target_files` coverage against the map (touched / not-touched `expected-by-scope`-vs-`gap` / absent-from-map, findings tagged `resource-map-coverage`), and synthesis adds the `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` report section plus a converged `resource-map.md` (disable via `--no-resource-map`). Absent at init, the gate and section are skipped without failing the loop. Full sequencing: `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` (init 9a, iteration 3b, synthesis 4); schema: `references/state/state_format.md`.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot Replacement\n\nDuring initialization, capture a bounded, pointer-based context snapshot in `deep-review-strategy.md` `Known Context` before the first dimension runs: target pointers (files, specs, symbols, resource-map entries), claimed behavior/acceptance criteria to verify, reuse/convention pointers, and risk areas, missing context, stale-graph caveats, and out-of-scope areas. It must not create a context-loop report or widen scope beyond the declared target; use `@context` for quick retrieval and `/speckit:plan` only when findings require implementation planning.\n\n### Architecture\n\n`/deep:review` owns the loop. The YAML workflow initializes state, dispatches one LEAF review iteration at a time, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `review-report.md`, and saves continuity. The LEAF agent reads state, reviews one dimension, writes `iteration-NNN.md`, updates strategy, and appends JSONL. Full 4-phase lifecycle: `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`.\n\n### State Packet Location\n\nThe review state packet always lives under the target spec's local `review/` folder. Root-spec targets use `{spec_folder}/review/` directly; child-phase and sub-phase targets use **flat-first** placement (first run writes flat, a `pt-NN` sibling packet is allocated only when prior content already exists for a different target). Full resolution rule and worked examples: `references/state/state_format.md` §1.\n\nCore artifacts: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, `.deep-review-pause`, `resource-map.md`, `review-report.md`, and `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n\n### Core Innovation: Fresh Context Per Iteration\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window; state continuity comes from files, not memory, preventing accumulated findings from biasing later dimensions. Init writes config/strategy/JSONL; each loop reads state, checks convergence, dispatches one dimension, records findings, and reduces state; synthesis compiles the report and saves continuity.\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\nThe four primary review dimensions (configured in `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml`):\n\n| Dimension | Focus | Key Questions |\n|-----------|-------|---------------|\n| **Correctness** | Logic, behavior, error handling | Behavior matches claims? Edge cases handled? |\n| **Security** | Vulnerabilities, exposure, trust boundaries | Inputs validated? Credentials exposed? |\n| **Spec-Alignment / Traceability** | Spec vs. implementation fidelity | Code matches spec.md? Planned items present? |\n| **Completeness / Maintainability** | Coverage, dead code, documentation | TODOs resolved? Code self-documenting? |\n\n### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n\nReview mode is lineage-aware. Supported lifecycle modes are `new`, `resume`, and `restart`. Required lineage fields include `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, and `releaseReadinessState`. The reducer consumes the latest JSONL delta, the new iteration file, and prior reduced state, then emits finding registry, dashboard metrics, and strategy updates.\n\n### Severity Classification\n\n| Severity | Criteria | Blocking |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| **P0** | Correctness failure, security vulnerability, spec contradiction | Yes, blocks PASS verdict |\n| **P1** | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation | Conditional, triggers CONDITIONAL verdict |\n| **P2** | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps | No, PASS with advisories |\n\n### Verdicts\n\n| Verdict | Condition |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **PASS** | No P0/P1 findings, P2 findings recorded as advisories (`hasAdvisories: true`) |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | P1 findings present, remediation plan included in report |\n| **FAIL** | Any P0 finding confirmed after adversarial self-check |\n\n### Acceptance-Coverage Signal\n\nWhen the review target is a spec folder, deep review reflects the `AC_COVERAGE` validation signal in synthesis for Level 2+ folders, and only once `checklist.md` exists and `implementation-summary.md` is in-progress or later (Level 1 folders and fresh scaffolds are exempt). The signal is advisory while the validation rule stays INFO/default-off -- it can add traceability context and planning-seed work, but must not alter the iteration final-line contract below unless a later enforcement rollout explicitly changes severity.\n\n### Iteration Final-Line Contract (MANDATORY)\n\nEvery `iteration-NNN.md` MUST end with exactly one of the following plain-text lines as the **absolute final line** (no trailing whitespace, no variation), and every review MUST emit exactly one parseable verdict:\n\n```\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\n**Mapping rule:** PASS if no P0 or P1 findings in this iteration. CONDITIONAL if any P1 (but no P0) findings. FAIL if any P0 findings. P2-only findings → PASS.\n\n**VERDICT_LOCK:** Any confirmed active P0 forces the exact final line `Review verdict: FAIL` -- never relabel that state as conditional, partial, mixed, or advisory, and truncated/partial output is not a valid substitute for the final line. An optional advisory `riskScore` may appear in narratives/JSONL for relative risk calibration but never changes the `PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` mapping.\n\nDownstream automation (including the synthesis phase and CI gate parser) parses this final line via exact string match, do not vary the format.\n\n### Executor Selection Contract\n\nExecutor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack -- never hand-dispatch review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta. Full contract (per-iteration invariants, failure modes, JSONL audit field, config surface/precedence, TrustState surface): `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS\n\n1. Read JSONL and strategy before review action.\n2. Review one dimension per iteration and write findings to `iteration-NNN.md`.\n3. Append JSONL with severity counts, finding detail, and `newInfoRatio`.\n4. Cite every finding with `[SOURCE: file:line]`. Reject inference-only findings.\n5. Re-read cited code before recording any P0.\n6. Keep target files read-only.\n7. Use `generate-context.js` for continuity saves. **Owner**: the YAML workflow (`deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) calls it at the save phase, not the reducer (`scripts/reduce-state.cjs`) directly — don't expect continuity-save side effects from the reducer alone.\n8. Emit setup `BINDING:` lines before workflow output.\n9. Refuse nested dispatch with: `REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.`\n\n### ❌ NEVER\n\n1. **Dispatch sub-agents**, `@deep-review` is LEAF-only. It cannot dispatch additional agents. When dispatch is requested, use the canonical REFUSE wording (ALWAYS rule 14).\n2. **Hold findings in context**, Write everything to iteration files. Context is discarded after each dispatch.\n3. **Exceed TCB**, Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle.\n4. **Ask the user**, Autonomous execution. The agent makes best-judgment decisions without pausing.\n5. **Skip convergence checks**, Every iteration must be evaluated against convergence criteria before the next dispatch.\n6. **Modify config after init**, `deep-review-config.json` is read-only after initialization.\n7. **Modify files under review**, The review loop is observation-only. No code changes during audit.\n8. **Use WebFetch**, Review is code-only. No external resource fetching is permitted.\n9. **Implement fixes during review**, Report findings only. Implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n\n### Iteration Status Enum\n\n`complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight`\n\n- `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but important finding that changes the verdict trajectory.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n\n1. **3+ consecutive timeouts**, Infrastructure issue. Pause loop and report to user.\n2. **State file corruption**, Cannot reconstruct iteration history from JSONL or iteration files.\n3. **All dimensions covered with P0 findings remaining**, Human sign-off required before shipping.\n4. **Security vulnerabilities discovered in production code**, Escalate immediately. Do not defer to report synthesis.\n5. **All recovery tiers exhausted**, No automatic recovery path remaining in convergence protocol.\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/protocol/quick_reference.md`, `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`, `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`, `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md`, `assets/deep_review_strategy.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n\nScripts: `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, `scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`.\n\nDetailed contracts: `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` (executor invariants, failure modes, config surface), `references/protocol/loop_state_and_gates.md` (state transitions, error handling, STOP-decision gates), `references/protocol/completion_criteria.md` (full loop-completion/quality-gate/validation-success checklist), and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` (two-tier content-hash dedup).\n\nRelated skills: `deep-research` for investigation loops, `sk-code`'s code-review mode for single-pass review doctrine, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state and continuity saves.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\nA review loop is complete only when convergence and every quality gate agree: the composite stop score clears `compositeStopScore` (or `maxIterations` is hit without a false-positive STOP), every configured dimension plus required traceability protocols (`spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`) have at least one full iteration of coverage, all canonical state files exist and parse cleanly (`deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, one `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` per dispatched iteration), `review-report.md` carries all 9 core sections plus the conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate`, and continuity is saved via `generate-context.js`.\n\nNine binary quality gates must all pass before STOP is legal: config validity + lineage match, strategy initialization completeness, state/registry consistency, iteration completeness (markdown + JSONL delta), severity-field coverage on every finding (`severity`/`category`/`file:line`/`content_hash`), the advisory-only `riskScore` never gating verdict logic, adversarial P0 replay, dimension/protocol coverage stability, acceptance-coverage (advisory `AC_COVERAGE` signal when the spec-folder lifecycle predicate is active), and the security-sensitive override (`minStabilizationPasses=2` + fix-completeness replay) when the target touches security, path handling, env precedence, schema boundaries, persistence, or shared policy. Full gate-by-gate criteria and rationale: `references/protocol/completion_criteria.md`.\n\nValidate a completed run with `skill_advisor.py \"run a deep review loop\" --threshold 0.8` (skill still surfaces) and `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` (exits 0).\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in the active runtime's root doc (CLAUDE.md or AGENTS.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py` (keywords: deep review, convergence review, iterative review)\n- **Gate 3**: File modifications require spec folder question per the root doc Gate 3. The spec folder determines the `{spec_folder}/review/` state packet location\n- **Continuity**: `/speckit:resume` is the operator-facing recovery surface, resolving context in the order `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`. During review, the agent writes iteration, strategy, and JSONL state; after synthesis, run `generate-context.js` to write canonical packet continuity\n- **Command**: `/deep:review` is the primary invocation point\n\n### Code Graph Integration\n\n`code_graph_query + Grep` is available to `@deep-review` for semantic code search when Grep/Glob exact matching is insufficient: finding usages by concept/intent, locating implementations when exact symbol names are unknown, and cross-referencing behavior across unfamiliar code paths.\n\nBase directory for this skill: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/baselines/claude-baseline.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-007-delegation-route-proof.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-004-concise-natural-ask.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-005-orchestrate-handoff.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-008-absorption-probe.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-006-auto-missing-inputs.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-001-auto-run-specified.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-002-bare-command-halt.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-003-vague-natural-ask.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/behavior_benchmark.md</file>\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"deep-review","dir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: deep-review","time":{"start":1783915517140,"end":1783915517149}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09eda0dc789b5e39016a5463fd16288191abe2cb7be8aeb20f"}},"id":"prt_f59a694a8001Lba5vW9M0qgmd1","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a67e81001hLZDigWbA2Eahr"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915517187,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_dNABcZZDJPOfidRnvmlx1dNp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"system-spec-kit"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"system-spec-kit\">\n# Skill: system-spec-kit\n\n<!-- Keywords: spec-kit, speckit, documentation-workflow, spec-folder, template-enforcement, context-preservation, progressive-documentation, validation, mk-spec-memory, mk-goal, goal-plugin, active_goal, session-goal, vector-search, hybrid-search, bm25, rrf-fusion, fsrs-decay, constitutional-tier, checkpoint, importance-tiers, cognitive-memory, co-activation, tiered-injection -->\n\n# Spec Kit - Mandatory Conversation Documentation\n\nOrchestrates mandatory spec folder creation for all conversations involving file modifications. Ensures proper documentation level selection (1-3+), template usage, and context preservation through AGENTS.md-enforced workflows.\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### What is a Spec Folder?\n\nA **spec folder** is a numbered directory (e.g., `007-auth-feature/`) that contains documentation for a single feature/task or a coordinated packet of related phase work:\n\nSpec folders may also be nested as coordination-root packets with direct-child phase folders (e.g., `specs/02--track/022-feature/011-phase/002-child/`).\n\n- **Purpose**: Track specifications, plans, tasks, and decisions for one unit of work\n- **Location**: Under `specs/` using either `###-short-name/` at the root or nested packet paths for phased coordination\n- **Contents**: Markdown files (spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, and implementation-summary.md when work is complete) plus optional support folders such as `scratch/`, `research/`, or `review/`\n\nThink of it as a \"project folder\" for AI-assisted development - it keeps context organized and enables session continuity.\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\n**MANDATORY for ALL file modifications:**\n- Code files: JS, TS, Python, CSS, HTML\n- Documentation: Markdown, README, guides\n- Configuration: JSON, YAML, TOML, env templates\n- Templates, knowledge base, build/tooling files\n\n**Request patterns that trigger activation:**\n- \"Add/implement/create [feature]\"\n- \"Fix/update/refactor [code]\"\n- \"Modify/change [configuration]\"\n- Positive keywords include add, implement, fix, update, create, modify, rename, delete and configure. The authoritative Gate 3 classifier intentionally omits `analyze`, `decompose` and `phase` from positive triggers; `analyze` is a read-only disqualifier unless a real write, memory-save or resume trigger is also present.\n\n**Example triggers:**\n- \"Add email validation to the signup form\" → Level 1-2\n- \"Refactor the authentication module\" → Level 2-3\n- \"Fix the button alignment bug\" → Level 1\n- \"Implement user dashboard with analytics\" → Level 3\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- Pure exploration/reading (no file modifications)\n- Single typo fixes (<5 characters in one file)\n- Whitespace-only changes\n- Auto-generated file updates (package-lock.json)\n- User explicitly selects Option D (skip documentation)\n\n**Rule of thumb:** If modifying ANY file content → Activate this skill.\nStatus: ✅ This requirement applies immediately once file edits are requested.\n\n### Distributed Governance Rule\n\nAny agent writing authored spec folder docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `decision-record.md`, `handover.md`, `review-report.md`, `debug-delegation.md`, `resource-map.md` (optional)) MUST use contract-backed templates through `create.sh` or the inline renderer. This is a workflow-required gate, not a runtime hook: run `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` after authored spec-doc writes and before completion claims, then route continuity updates through /memory:save. Deep-research workflow-owned packet markdown (`research/iterations/*.md`, `research/deep-research-*.md`, and progressive `research/research.md` loop updates) is exempt from that generic per-write rule; `/deep:research` must instead run targeted strict validation after every `spec.md` mutation it performs. @deep-research retains exclusive write access for `research/research.md`; @debug retains exclusive write access for `debug-delegation.md`.\n\n- `handover.md` stays in the canonical recovery ladder and is maintained through `/memory:save` handover_state routing using the handover template for initial creation.\n- `review-report.md` remains owned by `@deep-review` when deep review workflows synthesize findings.\n- `resource-map.md` is a peer cross-cutting template under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/`; it remains optional at any level and gives reviewers a lean file ledger alongside `implementation-summary.md`.\n\n### Utility Template Triggers\n\n| Template              | Trigger Keywords                                                                                                              | Action                    |\n| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------- |\n| `handover.md`         | \"handover\", \"next session\", \"continue later\", \"pass context\", \"ending session\", \"save state\", \"multi-session\", \"for next AI\"  | Suggest `/memory:save` handover maintenance |\n| `debug-delegation.md` | \"stuck\", \"can't fix\", \"tried everything\", \"same error\", \"fresh eyes\", \"hours on this\", \"still failing\", \"need help debugging\" | Suggest Task-tool debug delegation |\n\n**Rule:** When detected, proactively suggest the appropriate action.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n### Resource Domains\n\nThis skill uses simple intent/domain routing, not keyed runtime resource routing. It does not select whole `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` subtrees from project, mode, stack, or model signals. Instead, the router discovers markdown resources recursively from `references/` and `assets/`, then applies intent scoring from `RESOURCE_MAP` to load real, guarded resources from the current inventory. Keep this section domain-focused rather than static file inventories.\n\n- `references/memory/` for context retrieval, save workflows, trigger behavior, and indexing.\n- `references/templates/` for level selection, template selection, and structure guides.\n- `references/validation/` for checklist policy, verification rules, decision formats, and template compliance contracts.\n- `references/structure/` for folder organization and sub-folder versioning.\n- `references/workflows/` for command workflows, shared intake, rename procedures, and worked examples.\n- `references/debugging/` for troubleshooting and root-cause methodology.\n- `references/cli/` for daemon CLI parity, shared smart-router behavior, and memory handback contracts.\n- `references/config/` for runtime environment configuration and launcher/lease contracts.\n- `references/hooks/` for prompt-time advisor hooks, the OpenCode goal plugin, runtime hook parity, and hook validation playbooks.\n- `assets/*.md` for shared decision matrices, template mapping, and parallel dispatch support.\n\n### Template and Script Sources of Truth\n\n- Level definitions and template size guidance: level specifications reference\n- Template usage and composition rules: [template_guide.md](./references/templates/template_guide.md)\n- Use the Level contract for operational templates; `create.sh` and the Level contract resolver share the same template index.\n- Use `templates/changelog/` for packet-local nested changelog generation at completion time.\n- Script architecture, build outputs, and runtime entrypoints: [scripts/README.md](./scripts/README.md)\n- Memory save JSON schema and workflow contracts: [save_workflow.md](./references/memory/save_workflow.md)\n- Nested packet changelog workflow: [nested_changelog.md](./references/workflows/nested_changelog.md)\n\nPrimary operational scripts:\n- `spec/validate.sh`\n- `spec/create.sh`\n- `spec/archive.sh`\n- `spec/check-completion.sh`\n- `spec/recommend-level.sh`\n- `mcp_server/lib/templates/level-contract-resolver.ts`\n\nSpec-script exit codes (`spec/*.sh`; distinct from the daemon-backed memory CLI taxonomy in §3):\n- `0`: success.\n- `1`: user error such as bad flags or invalid input.\n- `2`: validation error.\n- `3`: system error such as missing folders, missing manifests, or file I/O failures.\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level       | When to Load               | Resources                    |\n| ----------- | -------------------------- | ---------------------------- |\n| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation     | Shared patterns + SKILL.md   |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match   | Intent-mapped references     |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request   | Deep-dive quality standards  |\n\n`references/workflows/quick_reference.md` is the primary first-touch command surface. Keep the compact `spec_kit` and `memory` command map there, including `/speckit:plan --intake-only` as the standalone intake entry, `/speckit:plan` and `/speckit:complete` smart delegation notes, and the pointer from `/deep:research` to `../system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`, and use this file only to point readers to it rather than duplicating the full matrix.\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\nThe authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, and ambiguity handling. Because this skill is an intent/domain router, Pattern 3 is adapted to extensible intent labels over discovered resources rather than keyed resource subdirectories.\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards, de-duplicates with `seen`, and checks `inventory`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - command and intent signals select domain labels and resource maps without forcing `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` subtrees.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` asks for disambiguation and missing-resource cases return a \"no knowledge base\" notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/workflows/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"PLAN\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"plan\", \"design\", \"new spec\", \"level selection\", \"option b\"]},\n    \"RESEARCH\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"investigate\", \"explore\", \"analyze\", \"prior work\", \"evidence\"]},\n    \"IMPLEMENT\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"implement\", \"build\", \"execute\", \"workflow\"]},\n    \"DEBUG\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"stuck\", \"error\", \"not working\", \"failed\", \"debug\"]},\n    \"COMPLETE\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"done\", \"complete\", \"finish\", \"verify\", \"checklist\"]},\n    \"MEMORY\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"memory\", \"save context\", \"resume\", \"checkpoint\", \"context\"]},\n    \"HANDOVER\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"handover\", \"continue later\", \"next session\", \"pause\"]},\n    \"PHASE\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"phase\", \"decompose\", \"split\", \"workstream\", \"multi-phase\", \"phased approach\", \"phased\", \"multi-session\"]},\n    \"RETRIEVAL_TUNING\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"retrieval\", \"search tuning\", \"fusion\", \"scoring\", \"pipeline\"]},\n    \"INTAKE\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"intake\", \"folder_state\", \"start_state\", \"repair-mode\", \"intake-only\"]},\n    \"HOOKS\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"hook\", \"skill advisor hook\", \"advisor hook\", \"prompt-time advisor\", \"advisor_validate\", \"goal plugin\", \"mk-goal\", \"/goal\", \"active_goal\", \"session goal\"]},\n    \"LAUNCHER\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"launcher\", \"lease\", \"pid file\", \"single-writer\", \"lease_held_by\"]},\n    \"RENAME\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"rename\", \"mechanical refactor\", \"rename pattern\", \"git mv\", \"case variants\"]},\n    \"EVALUATION\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"evaluate\", \"ablation\", \"benchmark\", \"baseline\", \"metrics\"]},\n    \"SCORING_CALIBRATION\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"calibration\", \"scoring\", \"normalization\", \"decay\", \"interference\"]},\n    \"ROLLOUT_FLAGS\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"feature flag\", \"rollout\", \"toggle\", \"enable\", \"disable\"]},\n    \"GOVERNANCE\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"governance\", \"tenant\", \"retention\", \"audit\"]},\n}\n\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"PLAN\": [\n        \"references/templates/template_guide.md\",\n        \"references/workflows/intake_contract.md\",\n        \"references/validation/template_compliance_contract.md\",\n        \"assets/level_decision_matrix.md\",\n        \"assets/complexity_decision_matrix.md\",\n    ],\n    \"RESEARCH\": [\n        \"references/workflows/quick_reference.md\",\n        \"references/workflows/worked_examples.md\",\n        \"references/memory/epistemic_vectors.md\",\n    ],\n    \"IMPLEMENT\": [\n        \"references/validation/validation_rules.md\",\n        \"references/validation/template_compliance_contract.md\",\n        \"references/templates/template_guide.md\",\n        \"assets/template_mapping.md\",\n    ],\n    \"DEBUG\": [\n        \"references/debugging/troubleshooting.md\",\n        \"references/debugging/universal_debugging_methodology.md\",\n        \"references/workflows/quick_reference.md\",\n    ],\n    \"COMPLETE\": [\n        \"references/validation/validation_rules.md\",\n        \"references/workflows/nested_changelog.md\",\n        \"references/workflows/intake_contract.md\",\n        \"references/workflows/spec_folder_write_recipe.md\",\n        \"references/workflows/spec_folder_authoring_checklist.md\",\n    ],\n    \"MEMORY\": [\n        \"references/memory/memory_system.md\",\n        \"references/memory/save_workflow.md\",\n        \"references/memory/trigger_config.md\",\n    ],\n    \"HANDOVER\": [\n        \"references/workflows/quick_reference.md\",\n    ],\n    \"PHASE\": [\n        \"references/structure/phase_definitions.md\",\n        \"references/structure/sub_folder_versioning.md\",\n        \"references/validation/phase_checklists.md\",\n    ],\n    \"RETRIEVAL_TUNING\": [\n        \"references/memory/embedder_architecture.md\",\n        \"references/memory/embedding_resilience.md\",\n        \"references/memory/embedder_pluggability.md\",\n        \"references/memory/trigger_config.md\",\n    ],\n    \"INTAKE\": [\n        \"references/workflows/intake_contract.md\",\n        \"references/templates/template_guide.md\",\n        \"references/validation/template_compliance_contract.md\",\n    ],\n    \"HOOKS\": [\n        \"references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md\",\n        \"references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook_validation.md\",\n        \"references/hooks/goal_plugin.md\",\n        \"references/config/hook_system.md\",\n    ],\n    \"LAUNCHER\": [\n        \"references/config/launcher_lease.md\",\n        \"references/memory/memory_system.md\",\n    ],\n    \"RENAME\": [\n        \"references/workflows/rename_pattern.md\",\n    ],\n    \"EVALUATION\": [\n        \"references/memory/epistemic_vectors.md\",\n        \"references/config/environment_variables.md\",\n    ],\n    \"SCORING_CALIBRATION\": [\n        \"references/config/environment_variables.md\",\n    ],\n    \"ROLLOUT_FLAGS\": [\n        \"references/config/environment_variables.md\",\n    ],\n    \"GOVERNANCE\": [\n        \"references/config/environment_variables.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nCOMMAND_BOOSTS = {\n    \"/speckit:plan\": \"PLAN\",\n    \"/speckit:implement\": \"IMPLEMENT\",\n    \"/speckit:complete\": \"COMPLETE\",\n    \"/speckit:plan --intake-only\": \"INTAKE\",\n    \"/speckit:plan :with-phases\": \"PHASE\",\n    \"/memory:search\": \"MEMORY\",\n    \"/memory:save\": \"MEMORY\",\n    \"/memory:manage\": \"MEMORY\",\n    \"/memory:learn\": \"MEMORY\",\n    \"/speckit:resume\": \"MEMORY\",\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\": [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"deep dive\", \"full validation\", \"full checklist\", \"full template\", \"save context\", \"/memory:save\", \"/speckit:resume\", \"implementation-summary\", \"tasks.md\", \"spec folder\", \"phase folder\", \"description metadata\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\": [\n        \"references/validation/phase_checklists.md\",\n        \"references/templates/template_guide.md\",\n        \"references/workflows/intake_contract.md\",\n        \"references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook_validation.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm whether this is planning, memory, validation, phase, debug, or completion work\",\n    \"Confirm the target spec folder or command surface\",\n    \"Provide one concrete file, error, or expected output\",\n    \"Confirm which verification gate must pass\",\n]\n\ndef _task_text(task) -> str:\n    parts = [\n        str(getattr(task, \"query\", \"\")),\n        str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")),\n        \" \".join(getattr(task, \"keywords\", []) or []),\n        str(getattr(task, \"command\", \"\")),\n    ]\n    return \" \".join(parts).lower()\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Allow markdown loads only within this skill folder.\"\"\"\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef _guard_resource_map(resource_map: dict[str, list[str]]) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Reject compatibility stubs as router targets while allowing them to preserve old links.\"\"\"\n    for intent, resources in resource_map.items():\n        for relative_path in resources:\n            guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n            if guarded.startswith(\"references/\"):\n                tail = guarded.removeprefix(\"references/\")\n                if \"/\" not in tail and \"-\" in Path(tail).stem:\n                    raise ValueError(f\"RESOURCE_MAP must target canonical references, not compatibility stubs: {intent} -> {guarded}\")\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    \"\"\"Recursively discover routable markdown docs for this skill only.\"\"\"\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(p for p in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if p.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n\ndef score_intents(task) -> dict[str, float]:\n    \"\"\"Weighted scoring from request text, keywords, and explicit command boosts.\"\"\"\n    text = _task_text(task)\n    scores = {intent: 0.0 for intent in INTENT_SIGNALS}\n\n    for intent, cfg in INTENT_SIGNALS.items():\n        for keyword in cfg[\"keywords\"]:\n            if keyword in text:\n                scores[intent] += cfg[\"weight\"]\n\n    command = str(getattr(task, \"command\", \"\")).lower()\n    for prefix, intent in COMMAND_BOOSTS.items():\n        if command.startswith(prefix):\n            scores[intent] += 6\n\n    return scores\n\ndef select_intents(scores: dict[str, float], ambiguity_delta: float = 1.0, max_intents: int = 2) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Return primary intent and secondary intent when scores are close.\"\"\"\n    ranked = sorted(scores.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse=True)\n    if not ranked or ranked[0][1] <= 0:\n        return []\n\n    selected = [ranked[0][0]]\n    if len(ranked) > 1:\n        primary_score = ranked[0][1]\n        secondary_intent, secondary_score = ranked[1]\n        if secondary_score > 0 and (primary_score - secondary_score) <= ambiguity_delta:\n            selected.append(secondary_intent)\n\n    return selected[:max_intents]\n\ndef route_speckit_resources(task):\n    \"\"\"Scoped, recursive, weighted, ambiguity-aware routing.\"\"\"\n    _guard_resource_map(RESOURCE_MAP)\n    _guard_resource_map({\n        \"ALWAYS\": LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"],\n        \"ON_DEMAND\": LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"],\n    })\n    inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n    scores = score_intents(task)\n    intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n    loaded = []\n    seen = set()\n\n    def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n        if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n            load(guarded)\n            loaded.append(guarded)\n            seen.add(guarded)\n\n    # ALWAYS: base references for every invocation\n    for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n        return {\n            \"intents\": intents or [\"UNKNOWN\"],\n            \"intent_scores\": scores,\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    # CONDITIONAL: intent-scored resources\n    matched_intents = []\n    for intent in intents:\n        before_count = len(loaded)\n        for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n        if len(loaded) > before_count:\n            matched_intents.append(intent)\n\n    # ON_DEMAND: explicit deep-dive requests\n    text = _task_text(task)\n    if any(keyword in text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n        for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if not loaded:\n        load_if_available(DEFAULT_RESOURCE)\n\n    result = {\"intents\": intents, \"intent_scores\": scores, \"resources\": loaded}\n    if not matched_intents:\n        result[\"notice\"] = f\"No knowledge base found for intent(s): {', '.join(intents)}\"\n    return result\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Core Workflow\n\n1. Gate 3 selects an existing, new, related, skipped, or phase spec folder before file changes.\n2. For new folders, estimate level from LOC, risk, affected systems, and verification needs; create from contract-backed templates.\n3. Keep phase parents lean: parent folders hold `spec.md`, `description.json`, and `graph-metadata.json`; child phases hold working docs.\n4. Use checklist priority as the completion gate: P0 cannot defer, P1 requires completion or approved deferral, and P2 is optional.\n5. Preserve continuity in `implementation-summary.md` or through canonical `/memory:save` with `generate-context.js`.\n\n### Spec Kit Memory\n\nSpec Kit Memory provides context retrieval, search, save, checkpoint, health, and indexing surfaces. Use `memory_context()` or `/speckit:resume` for recovery; use `memory_search()` for targeted retrieval; use `generate-context.js` for canonical saves.\n\nThe surface is dual-stack: alongside the `mk-spec-memory` MCP registration, all 41 tools are callable through the full-parity daemon-backed CLI `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool_name> [--json '{...}' | --param value]` against the same daemon. MCP remains the primary in-session transport today; use the CLI when MCP transport is missing, failed or not reconnecting while the daemon is warm, and for hooks, cron, CI and operator shell diagnostics. Recovery example: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_context --json '{\"input\":\"resume previous work\",\"mode\":\"resume\"}' --format json --timeout-ms 3000`. CLI exit taxonomy: `0` success, `1` runtime, `64` usage/schema, `69` protocol/dist mismatch or stale dist, `75` retryable daemon error. Prompt-time callers must pass `--warm-only` (probe-only, exit `75` instead of cold-spawning); non-prompt contexts auto-spawn the daemon through the launcher. Because this CLI already has full parity, a later evolution could make it the primary or sole transport without breaking existing MCP workflows; that is a possible direction, not a committed plan. `--format jsonl` renders one complete JSON payload on one stdout line; it is not streaming JSON Lines. Full cross-daemon CLI behavior, recovery, stale-dist build commands, per-command `--help`, offline smoke, and safety rules live in [`references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md`](references/cli/daemon_cli_reference.md). See `mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md` (\"CLI front door\") for the warm-only/prompt-time env flags. Detailed behavior, flags, scoring, and MCP tool reference live in `references/memory/memory_system.md`, `references/memory/save_workflow.md`, and `mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md`. Launcher/daemon reliability is operator-tunable via the `SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_LOG`, `SPECKIT_LEASE_PROBE_RETRIES`, `SPECKIT_STOP_HOOK_ORPHAN_SWEEP`, and `SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION` (default-on in the runtime configs: a disposing owner releases the shared daemon for a live secondary, and a fresh session reaps the released daemon before respawn for a single writer) flags, all documented in `mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md`.\n\n`memory_index_scan` is self-maintaining: overlapping scan calls return a `coalesced:true` success envelope instead of a raw E429 error. Rows become BM25/FTS-searchable immediately as `pending` while vectors drain (`complete_with_pending_vectors` with a `pendingVectors` count). Move reconciliation heals renamed spec folders by packet identity without re-embedding. Each scan also runs a bounded global orphan sweep. `memory_health` now includes an `index` block with a summary enum (`healthy_fresh`, `healthy_lagging_vectors`, `stale_needs_scan`, `degraded_needs_repair`, `unavailable`) and counts for indexed/pending/failed rows.\n\n`memory_embedding_reconcile` is a net-new public MCP maintenance tool on the `mk-spec-memory` surface. It converges `embedding_status` for vector-present stale rows and resets genuinely missing-vector retry rows inside one guarded `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` transaction. It runs dry-run by default so operators can inspect the proposed changes before committing them.\n\nThe current memory baseline is schema v41. The hardening features ship behind conservative defaults: semantic-trigger shadow matching, session-trace causal inference, feedback-retention reducers, soft-delete tombstones, memory idempotency receipts, authored continuity snapshots, and completion freshness all stay opt-in. `source_kind` provenance, retrieval observability, stale-audit signals, and tool-ownership linting are documented in the memory and ENV references rather than duplicated here.\n\n### Reranking\n\nModel-based cross-encoder/local-GGUF reranking was removed in the 014 deprecation: the spec-memory local model path was removed in phase 003 and the local rerank sidecar skill was deleted in phase 004 (cloud rerankers were removed earlier in 022/013). Memory search still has a Stage 3 rerank step: MMR diversity reranking plus MPAB chunk collapse, with the `memory_search` `rerank` option defaulting to true. The `SPECKIT_CROSS_ENCODER`/`RERANKER_LOCAL` flags are no longer wired.\n\n### Security\n\n- `VOYAGE_API_KEY` is read from the process environment only. It must never be logged, written into spec docs, or persisted to disk by Spec Kit. Operators should set it in shell init files owned by the operator with mode `600`.\n- Tests may mutate env vars, but must restore them in `afterEach`. Production code paths should not treat mutable process env as request-time configuration.\n\n### Validation and Recovery\n\nRun `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` before completion claims. Validation errors block completion; warnings must be addressed or documented. Startup, resume, hook, goal plugin, code graph, and Code Graph readiness details live in `references/config/hook_system.md`, `references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md`, `references/hooks/goal_plugin.md`, `mcp_server/hooks/README.md` (Claude and OpenCode hook folders; OpenCode uses plugin-backed delivery), and the code graph references.\n\n### OpenCode Goal Plugin\n\nThe local `/goal` surface is `.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js` plus `.opencode/commands/goal_opencode.md`. It is not an MCP daemon bridge: it stores per-session JSON state under `.opencode/skills/.goal-state/`, injects the active goal with `experimental.chat.system.transform`, observes lifecycle events through the plugin `event` hook, and exposes `mk_goal` / `mk_goal_status` plugin tools. Use [`references/hooks/goal_plugin.md`](./references/hooks/goal_plugin.md) for the operator contract, restart requirement, environment variables, validation commands, and boundary between raw `objective` and generated `goalPrompt`.\n\n### Code Graph and Search Routing\n\nUse Grep/Glob for semantic/token discovery, Code Graph for structural relationships, and Spec Kit Memory for prior decisions and continuity. The `system-code-graph` skill owns the 8-tool `mcp__mk_code_index__*` surface: read tools (`code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `detect_changes`) return blocked/degraded payloads under the readiness contract, `code_graph_status` is always answerable, `code_graph_classify_query_intent` is text-only, and maintenance tools (`code_graph_scan`, `code_graph_apply`, `code_graph_verify`) handle recovery and verification, with verify blocking when graph state is not fresh.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n1. **Determine level (1/2/3/3+) before ANY file changes** - Count LOC, assess complexity/risk\n2. **Scaffold from contract-backed templates** - Use `create.sh` or `inline-gate-renderer`, NEVER create from scratch\n3. **Fill ALL placeholders** - Remove placeholder markers and sample content\n4. **Ask A/B/C/D/E when file modification detected** - Present options, wait for selection\n5. **Prefer coordinated related packets before new top-level folders** - Check active and related specs, their scope, status, and Phase Documentation Map. When related work qualifies for phase decomposition, recommend one phased packet rather than separate single-spec folders.\n6. **Get explicit user approval before changes** - Show level, path, templates, approach\n7. **Use consistent folder naming** - `specs/###-short-name/` format\n8. **Use checklist.md to verify (Level 2+)** - Load before claiming done\n9. **Mark items `[x]` with evidence** - Include links, test outputs, screenshots\n10. **Complete P0/P1 before claiming done** - No exceptions\n11. **Suggest handover.md on session-end keywords** - \"continue later\", \"next session\"\n12. **Run validate.sh before completion** - Completion Verification requirement\n13. **Create implementation-summary.md at end of implementation phase (Level 1+)** - Document what was built\n14. **Suggest /memory:save when session-end keywords detected OR after extended work (15+ tool calls)** - Proactive context preservation\n15. **Suggest Task-tool debug delegation after 3+ failed fix attempts on same error** - Do not continue without offering a fresh debugging pass\n16. **Apply the phased-packet preference without bypassing qualification** - Suggest `/speckit:plan :with-phases` only when phase complexity score >= 25 AND documentation level >= 3. If either condition fails, use a standard packet; if the work is new or unrelated, create a separate packet and evaluate that packet independently.\n17. **Route all code creation/updates through `sk-code`** - Full surface alignment is mandatory before claiming completion\n   - **Authoring-time vs review-time load**: `sk-code` is loaded at TWO distinct points in `/speckit:complete`. (a) Authoring-time (Step 10 development): when the implementation target is under `.opencode/skills/`, `.opencode/agents/`, `.opencode/commands/`, or `.opencode/specs/`, load the matching sk-code authoring checklist (`assets/opencode/checklists/{surface}_authoring.md`) and, for `.opencode/specs/` targets, the system-spec-kit spec-folder docs (`references/workflows/spec_folder_authoring_checklist.md` + `references/workflows/spec_folder_write_recipe.md`) BEFORE the first write. (b) Review-time (Step 11 review): the existing `sk-code` code-review mode (findings-first baseline + router-selected surface evidence) overlay runs after writes complete. Authoring-time load surfaces invariants the writer needs to honor; review-time load catches drift the writer didn't honor. See `cross_skill_authoring_load` block in `speckit_complete_auto.yaml` and `speckit_complete_confirm.yaml` for the YAML contract.\n18. **Route all documentation creation/updates through `sk-doc`** - Full alignment is mandatory before claiming completion\n19. **Enforce ToC policy from validation rules** - Only `research/research.md` may include a Table of Contents section; remove ToC headings from standard spec artifacts\n20. **Literal naming for AI-derived spec folders and phases** - When the AI (not the user) picks a spec-folder or phase slug, the name MUST describe the concrete work being built or fixed. Names must include a specific subject token (the component, behavior, or bug being addressed). Forbidden as standalone slugs: `remediation`, `cleanup`, `fix`, `phase-N`, `review-remediation`, `round-N`. Good remediation-packet examples: `fix-deep-review-p1-p2-findings-for-sk-doc-skill`, `harden-mcp-server-startup-races`, `fix-singleton-leak-in-launcher`. Good phase-decomposition examples: `data-model-design`, `api-implementation`, `ui-integration`. **Remediation-packet source/target rule** - remediation slugs MUST follow `NNN-fix-<source>-for-<target>` where: **Source** = the event or evidence that triggered the packet (e.g. `deep-review-p0-p1-findings`, `verdict-fail`, `audit-finding-NN`); **Target** = the specific component being remediated (e.g. `skill-local-benchmarks-format`, `mk-spec-memory-handler`, `launcher-cache`). The source names WHERE the work comes from; the target names WHAT is being fixed. Do not conflate them: the thing being remediated is the target, not the source. Worked example: `007-fix-deep-review-p0-p1-findings-for-skill-local-benchmarks-format` (source=`deep-review-p0-p1-findings`, target=`skill-local-benchmarks-format`). This rule is documentation-layer guidance; `validate.sh` does not lint slugs today (operator decision; may be lifted in a follow-on packet).\n\n### NEVER\n\n1. **Create documentation from scratch** - Use templates only\n2. **Skip spec folder creation** - Unless user explicitly selects D\n3. **Make changes before spec + approval** - Spec folder is prerequisite\n4. **Leave placeholders in final docs** - All must be replaced\n5. **Decide autonomously update vs create** - Always ask user\n6. **Claim done without checklist verification** - Level 2+ requirement\n7. **Proceed without spec folder confirmation** - Wait for A/B/C/D/E\n8. **Skip validation before completion** - Completion Verification hard block\n9. **Add ToC sections to standard spec artifacts** - `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `handover.md`, `debug-delegation.md`, and `resource-map.md` must not contain ToC headings\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n1. **Scope grows during implementation** - Run `upgrade-level.sh` to add higher-level templates (recommended), then auto-populate all placeholder content:\n   - Read all existing spec files (spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, implementation-summary.md) for context\n   - Replace every placeholder marker pattern in newly injected sections with content derived from that context\n   - For sections without sufficient source context, write \"N/A - insufficient source context\" instead of fabricating content\n   - Run `check-placeholders.sh <spec-folder>` to verify zero placeholders remain (see level specifications reference for the full procedure)\n   - Document the level change in changelog\n2. **Uncertainty about level <80%** - Present level options to user, default to higher\n3. **Template doesn't fit requirements** - Adapt closest template, document modifications\n4. **User requests skip (Option D)** - Warn about tech debt, explain debugging challenges, confirm consent\n5. **Validation fails with errors** - Report specific failures, provide fix guidance, re-run after fixes\n\n---\n\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\nSuccess means the selected spec folder uses the right template set, placeholders and sample content are removed, links between packet docs work, continuity is saved or updated, Level 2+ checklist P0/P1 items are verified with evidence, and `validate.sh --strict` has no blocking errors.\n\n---\n\n## 6. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\nP0 blocks, P1 requires completion or approved deferral, and P2 is optional. Code updates route through `sk-code`; documentation updates route through `sk-doc`; git handoff routes through `sk-git`.\n\n### Quick Reference Commands\n\n| Command | Usage |\n| --- | --- |\n| Canonical intake | `/speckit:plan --intake-only \"Description\"` |\n| Create spec folder | `./scripts/spec/create.sh \"Description\" --short-name name --level 2` |\n| Validate | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh specs/007-feature/` |\n| Verify code alignment drift | `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py --root .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit` |\n| Save context | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json specs/007-feature/` |\n| Memory CLI (dual-stack) | `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --format json` calls any of the 41 memory tools over the live daemon; `list-tools` enumerates them offline; `--warm-only` for prompt-time contexts |\n| Next spec number | `ls -d specs/[0-9]*/ \\| sed 's/.*\\/\\([0-9]*\\)-.*/\\1/' \\| sort -n \\| tail -1` |\n| Upgrade level | `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/upgrade-level.sh specs/007-feature/ --to 2` |\n| Completeness | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/calculate-completeness.sh specs/007-feature/` |\n| Worktree isolation | `.opencode/bin/worktree-session.sh` creates a per-session git worktree with isolated `SPEC_KIT_DB_DIR` / `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR` / `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR`. Pair with `worktree-reaper.sh` for teardown and `worktree-guard.sh` for lock enforcement |\n| Session cleanup | `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` (renamed from `claude-session-cleanup.sh` with a back-compat shim retained) resolves PIDs across claude/opencode/opencode runtimes |\n\nCanonical command lifecycle: `/speckit:plan --intake-only` establishes or repairs the packet when standalone intake is needed, `/deep:research` follows `../system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` when research needs bounded `spec.md` anchoring, and `/speckit:plan` or `/speckit:complete` continue from the same folder while reusing the shared intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`) only when the local `folder_state` still needs repair. When intake runs, the returned `start_state` is the canonical downstream field.\n\n**Remember**: This skill is the foundational documentation orchestrator. It enforces structure, template usage, context preservation, and workflow-required validation for all file modifications. Every conversation that modifies files MUST have a spec folder.\n\n---\n\n## 7. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/workflows/quick_reference.md`, `references/templates/template_guide.md`, `references/validation/validation_rules.md`, `references/memory/save_workflow.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n\nScripts: `scripts/spec/validate.sh`, `scripts/spec/create.sh`, `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`, `scripts/spec/check-completion.sh`.\n\nRelated skills: `sk-doc` for authored documentation quality, `sk-code` for code changes, `sk-git` for git handoff, and `system-deep-loop` for iterative research and audit (its `research` and `review` modes).\n\nBase directory for this skill: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/context-server.ts</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/eslint.config.mjs</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/embedder-status.ts</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud-types.ts</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-ingest.ts</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-bulk-delete.ts</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-triggers.ts</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-crud.ts</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/db-helpers.ts</file>\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"system-spec-kit","dir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: system-spec-kit","time":{"start":1783915517170,"end":1783915517185}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09eda0dc789b5e39016a5463fd164c8191aa6259a90e8cced4"}},"id":"prt_f59a694f0001qJ2Zb4nOlj4KtU","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a67e81001hLZDigWbA2Eahr"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915517192,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_xLWwfwRlDqjLZGTRqjHkLSFf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"cli-opencode"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"cli-opencode\">\n# Skill: cli-opencode\n\n<!-- Keywords: opencode, opencode-cli, opencode-run, cross-ai, spec-kit-runtime, plugin-runtime, parallel-sessions, share-url, detached-session, agent-delegation, deepseek, openai, minimax, minimax-coding-plan, minimax-m3, token-plan, xiaomi, xiaomi-token-plan, xiaomi-token-plan-ams, xiaomi-api, xiaomi-direct, mimo, mimo-v2.5-pro, mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed, ultraspeed, glm-5.2, zai-coding-plan, z.ai-coding-plan, glm-coding-plan -->\n\n# OpenCode CLI Orchestrator - Full-Runtime Cross-AI Dispatch\n\n> **CRITICAL — SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED**\n>\n> This skill dispatches to the OpenCode CLI binary (`opencode`). If the agent currently reading this skill is itself running inside OpenCode (TUI / acp / serve / run modes — detection signals listed in §2), the skill MUST refuse to load and return the documented error message instead of generating any `opencode` invocation. The only exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory.\n>\n> A running CLI skill never dispatches itself. The cli-X skills are for **cross-AI delegation only** — never self-invocation.\n\nOrchestrate OpenCode's `opencode run` from external AI assistants (Claude Code, OpenCode, raw shell) AND from inside an existing OpenCode session for parallel detached workers. Three documented use cases keep the cycle risk explicit while giving every dispatch path a copy-paste invocation shape.\n\n**Core Principle**: The calling AI stays the conductor. Delegate to OpenCode for what it does best — full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime in a one-shot dispatch. Validate and integrate the output.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\n- **Full plugin / skill / MCP runtime** (use case 1) — calling AI is Claude Code / OpenCode / Copilot / raw shell AND the task needs the project's full Spec Kit Memory database, Code Graph semantic index, structural code graph, or every plugin/skill/MCP tool in a one-shot dispatch. Includes `@deep-research` / `@deep-review` agent loops with externalized state under `.opencode/specs/`.\n- **Parallel detached session** (use case 2) — operator already inside OpenCode (TUI / web / serve / acp) AND wants a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory for ablation, worker farm, or parallel research. Prompt explicitly mentions \"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", or \"share URL\".\n- **Cross-AI orchestration handback** (use case 3) — calling AI is non-Anthropic (OpenCode / Copilot), task targets a project-specific subsystem (spec-kit, memory, code-graph, advisor), and the non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugin/skill/MCP runtime on its own and needs OpenCode as a bridge. When the caller only needs a daemon-backed tool call, prefer the shipped front doors (`spec-memory.cjs`, `code-index.cjs`, `skill-advisor.cjs`) over a full `opencode run` delegation.\n- **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate primary: `context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`, `ai-council`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n- **Cross-repo dispatch** — session in repo A dispatches into repo B's plugin/skill/MCP runtime via `--dir <path>` or remote OpenCode server via `--attach <url>`.\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- **You ARE OpenCode already.** If your runtime is OpenCode (detection signal: `$OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` or any `OPENCODE_*` env var set, `opencode` in process ancestry, or `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` present), this skill refuses to load. Self-invocation creates a circular dispatch loop and burns tokens for no value. The cli-X family is exclusively for cross-AI delegation. The single legitimate exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session id and state directory (use case 2); without that qualifier, the smart router refuses per ADR-001.\n- Simple, quick tasks where `opencode run` overhead is not worth it.\n- Tasks that only need a raw model dispatch — use a sibling cli-* skill.\n- Tasks requiring interactive TUI or web UI (use `opencode` directly instead of `opencode run`).\n- Context already loaded and understood by the calling AI.\n- Tasks where the OpenCode binary is not installed at the expected path.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Prerequisite Detection\n\n```bash\n# Verify OpenCode CLI is available\ncommand -v opencode || echo \"Not installed. Run: brew install opencode (macOS) or curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash\"\n\n# SELF-INVOCATION GUARD (ADR-001 layered detection)\n# Layer 1: env var lookup — any OPENCODE_* variable\nenv | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: OPENCODE_* env detected — already inside OpenCode.\"\n# Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\nps -o command= -p \"$PPID\" | grep -q opencode && echo \"ERROR: opencode parent process detected.\"\n# Layer 3: state lock-file probe\nls ~/.opencode/state/*/lock 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q lock && echo \"ERROR: live OpenCode session lock detected.\"\n```\n\n### Self-Invocation Guard (ADR-001)\n\n```python\ndef detect_self_invocation():\n    \"\"\"Returns a non-None signal when the orchestrator is already running inside OpenCode.\"\"\"\n    # Layer 1: env var lookup — OpenCode sets OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR and OPENCODE_* vars\n    for key in os.environ:\n        if key == 'OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR' or key.startswith('OPENCODE_'):\n            return ('env', key)\n    # Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\n    try:\n        ancestry = subprocess.check_output(['ps', '-o', 'command=', '-p', str(os.getppid())]).decode()\n        if '/opencode' in ancestry or 'opencode ' in ancestry:\n            return ('ancestry', 'opencode')\n    except subprocess.SubprocessError:\n        pass\n    # Layer 3: state lock-file probe\n    state_dir = os.path.expanduser('~/.opencode/state')\n    if os.path.isdir(state_dir):\n        for entry in os.listdir(state_dir):\n            if os.path.exists(os.path.join(state_dir, entry, 'lock')):\n                return ('lockfile', entry)\n    return None\n\nif detect_self_invocation():\n    # Single legitimate exception: explicit \"parallel detached\" keywords (use case 2)\n    # spawn a SEPARATE session id and state directory, not a self-dispatch.\n    if not has_parallel_session_keywords(prompt):\n        refuse(\n            \"Self-invocation refused: this agent is already running inside OpenCode. \"\n            \"Use a sibling cli-* skill or a fresh shell session in a different runtime to dispatch a different model. \"\n            \"For a parallel detached session, restate with explicit parallel-session keywords.\"\n        )\n```\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level       | When to Load            | Resources                      |\n| ----------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------ |\n| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation  | `references/cli_reference.md`, `assets/prompt_quality_card.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Intent-mapped reference docs   |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request| Extended templates and patterns |\n\n### Smart Router\n\nIntent-specific dictionaries (used by the shared helper functions in [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md`](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md)):\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans existing `references/` and `assets/` folders with `base.exists()` safeguards.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` uses `_guard_in_skill()`, `inventory`, and `seen` so raw loads, missing files, duplicate loads, and path escapes are rejected.\n- Pattern 3: Not applicable here - `cli-opencode` has flat resource folders, not keyed `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` subdirectories. Routing selects from `RESOURCE_MAP` by intent signal rather than by runtime resource key.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - low-confidence intent scores return `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` with a disambiguation checklist; missing intent resources still return always-load baseline docs plus a clear notice.\n\n```python\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate to opencode\", \"opencode run\", \"from claude code\", \"from opencode\", \"from copilot\", \"external runtime\", \"full plugin runtime\", \"hand this off to opencode\", \"hand off to opencode\", \"send this to opencode\", \"dispatch to opencode\", \"run this through opencode\", \"let opencode handle this\", \"opencode's full runtime\", \"full runtime dispatch\", \"one-shot dispatch\", \"invoke opencode\", \"kick this off in opencode\", \"have opencode take care of this\", \"get opencode to run this\", \"pass this over to opencode\", \"opencode has access to every tool\", \"opencode has the whole toolchain\", \"since opencode has all the plugins\", \"opencode can load every skill\", \"ask opencode to handle this\", \"opencode should handle this\", \"offload this to opencode\", \"outsource this to opencode\", \"forward this to opencode\", \"route this to opencode\", \"push this to opencode\", \"opencode has everything loaded\", \"opencode has the whole toolset\", \"opencode cli\", \"run externally\", \"full toolset\", \"handle this externally\", \"external ai assistant\", \"run in opencode\", \"hand off externally\"]},\n    \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", \"share url\", \"share-url\", \"detached session\", \"separate session id\", \"own state directory\", \"spin up a new session\", \"background opencode session\", \"run this in the background\", \"fan out workers\", \"concurrent sessions\", \"isolated session\", \"run these in parallel\", \"spin off a few workers\", \"kick off several sessions at once\", \"run copies side by side\", \"fire off multiple runs at the same time\", \"farm this out to multiple workers\", \"run a bunch of these concurrently\", \"distribute the work across sessions\", \"batch this across sessions\", \"start several sessions at once\", \"spin up another instance\", \"new opencode instance\", \"run it as its own session\", \"own separate session\", \"side session\", \"run this independently\", \"additional worker\", \"background job\", \"separate instance\", \"own instance\", \"parallel run\", \"concurrent run\", \"session of its own\", \"spin up a worker\", \"worker pool\", \"run in parallel\"]},\n    \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"spec kit\", \"spec-kit\", \"spec_kit\", \"code graph\", \"memory_search\", \"session_bootstrap\", \"skill advisor\", \"cross-ai handback\", \"hand back to opencode\", \"bridge back to opencode\", \"opencode as a bridge\", \"non-anthropic cli\", \"project's memory database\", \"structural code index\", \"use the skill advisor\"]},\n    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate\", \"agent\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-review\", \"ai-council\", \"review agent\", \"context agent\", \"dispatch an agent\", \"spawn an agent\", \"run a subagent\", \"invoke a subagent\", \"specialized subagent\", \"debug agent\", \"write agent\"]},\n    \"CROSS_REPO\":         {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"cross-repo\", \"different repo\", \"--dir\", \"another repository\", \"remote opencode\", \"different repository\", \"target repo\", \"other codebase\", \"separate repository\", \"remote opencode server\", \"--attach\"]},\n    \"TEMPLATES\":          {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"template\", \"prompt\", \"how to ask\", \"opencode prompt\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\", \"prompt framework\", \"prompt template\", \"how do i phrase this\", \"copy-paste template\", \"prompt quality\", \"prompt craft\", \"costar framework\", \"example prompt\"]},\n    \"PATTERNS\":           {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"pattern\", \"workflow\", \"orchestrate\", \"session continue\", \"resume session\", \"integration pattern\", \"dispatch pattern\", \"continue the session\", \"resume a session\", \"session continuation\"]},\n    # WHY: DESIGN is an intent signal only — a deliberate cross-skill handoff to sk-design,\n    # not a same-skill resource bundle. It intentionally has NO RESOURCE_MAP entry: this skill\n    # hands design work off rather than owning design reference docs. The durable sk-design\n    # loading contract lives in the always-fires Design Standards Loading rule and the dispatch\n    # manifest (see ALWAYS rules 13-14); RESOURCE_MAP stays limited to same-skill markdown paths.\n    \"DESIGN\":             {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"sk-design\", \"interface design\", \"frontend design\", \"visual design\", \"redesign the ui\", \"design foundations\", \"design tokens\", \"motion design\", \"micro-interactions\", \"design audit\", \"ui critique\", \"extract design system\", \"generate design.md\"]},\n}\n\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  [\"references/cli_reference.md\", \"references/integration_patterns.md\"],\n    \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  [\"references/integration_patterns.md\", \"assets/prompt_templates.md\"],\n    \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  [\"references/integration_patterns.md\", \"references/opencode_tools.md\"],\n    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     [\"references/agent_delegation.md\", \"assets/prompt_templates.md\"],\n    \"CROSS_REPO\":         [\"references/cli_reference.md\", \"references/opencode_tools.md\"],\n    \"TEMPLATES\":          [\"assets/prompt_templates.md\", \"references/cli_reference.md\"],\n    \"PATTERNS\":           [\"references/integration_patterns.md\", \"references/cli_reference.md\"],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\": [\"references/cli_reference.md\", \"assets/prompt_quality_card.md\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full reference\", \"all templates\", \"deep dive\", \"complete guide\", \"opencode agent\", \"opencode prompt\", \"share url\", \"ablation\", \"worker farm\", \"self-invocation\", \"memory handback\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\": [\"references/opencode_tools.md\", \"assets/prompt_templates.md\"],\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Is the user asking about OpenCode CLI specifically?\",\n    \"Does the task need the project's full plugin / skill / MCP runtime?\",\n    \"Is a parallel detached session what they want?\",\n    \"Is a non-Anthropic CLI handing back to OpenCode for a spec-kit workflow?\",\n]\n```\n\n**Call sequence** (using shared helpers from `shared_smart_router.md`):\n\n1. `discover_markdown_resources()` — recursively enumerate current `.md` files under existing `references/` and `assets/` folders at routing time.\n2. `_guard_in_skill()` + `load_if_available()` — sandbox paths to this skill, reject non-markdown loads, skip missing files, and suppress duplicates.\n3. `score_intents(task)` and `select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)` — preserve provider-specific weighted intent scoring and top-2 ambiguity handling.\n4. ALWAYS-load `LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]`, then return `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` with `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST` when max score is 0.\n5. CONDITIONAL-load existing `RESOURCE_MAP[intent]` entries via `load_if_available()`, ON_DEMAND-load keyword matches, and return a notice when no intent-specific knowledge base is available beyond always-load resources.\n\nThe `route_opencode_resources(task)` function body lives in [`shared_smart_router.md`](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md) — substitute `<PROVIDER>` = `opencode`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n```bash\n# Verify installation (cli-opencode v1.0.0 is pinned to opencode v1.3.17)\nopencode --version | grep -q '^1\\.' || echo \"Not installed or version drift. See references/cli_reference.md §9.\"\n\n# Self-invocation guard\nenv | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: Already inside OpenCode session\"\n\n# Authentication — providers configured via opencode providers (alias auth)\nopencode providers\n```\n\n**Authentication options**: `opencode providers login <provider>` (and `opencode auth login` for subscription plans) for OAuth and API key flows. Configured providers on a typical install: `deepseek` (api, DEFAULT), `minimax-coding-plan` (MiniMax Token Plan subscription — **DEFAULT MiniMax path**; `opencode auth login`; model `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`), `minimax` (MiniMax Direct API, pay-per-token — `opencode providers login minimax`; model `minimax/MiniMax-M3`), `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API, pay-per-token — `opencode providers login xiaomi`; models `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` and the low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe; `opencode auth login`; model `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead), `openai` (api, premium alternative — full GPT-5.6 catalog: a bare tier (`gpt-5.6`/`gpt-5.6-fast`/`gpt-5.6-pro`) plus three named families Sol/Terra/Luna, each in base/Fast/Pro model tiers (`gpt-5.6-sol`/`gpt-5.6-sol-fast`/`gpt-5.6-sol-pro`, `gpt-5.6-terra`/`gpt-5.6-terra-fast`/`gpt-5.6-terra-pro`, `gpt-5.6-luna`/`gpt-5.6-luna-fast`/`gpt-5.6-luna-pro`); `gpt-5.6-sol` is the flagship default).\n\n### Provider Auth Pre-Flight (Smart Fallback)\n\n**MANDATORY before any first dispatch in a session.** The default provider may not be logged in on this machine — silently failing with `provider/model not found` or `401 Unauthorized` mid-dispatch wastes a round-trip. Run this check once per session, cache the result, and re-run it only if a dispatch fails with an auth error.\n\n```bash\n# One-shot pre-flight: list configured providers, capture for routing\nPROVIDERS=$(opencode providers list 2>&1)\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"deepseek\"            && DEEPSEEK_OK=1       || DEEPSEEK_OK=0\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"minimax-coding-plan\" && MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=1  || MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0   # MiniMax Token Plan (default MiniMax path)\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"minimax([^-]|$)\"    && MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1 || MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0  # MiniMax Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the coding-plan provider\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams\" && XIAOMI_OK=1       || XIAOMI_OK=0          # Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"xiaomi([^-]|$)\"     && XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1 || XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0   # Xiaomi Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the token-plan-ams provider\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"openai\"              && OPENAI_OK=1         || OPENAI_OK=0\n```\n\n**Decision tree** (apply in order — first match wins):\n\n| State | DEEPSEEK_OK | OPENAI_OK | Action |\n|-------|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| Default available | 1 | * | Proceed with `--model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` |\n| Default missing, openai ready | 0 | 1 | **ASK user** before substituting to OpenAI — surface options A/B/C/D below; OpenAI is a paid premium fallback. |\n| All missing | 0 | 0 | **ASK user** to configure a provider — surface the login commands, do NOT dispatch. |\n\n**MiniMax routing** (default = Token Plan; Direct API is the pay-per-token alternative — first match wins):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiniMax requested (default) | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` — **omit `--agent`** (rejected on opencode 1.15.13) |\n| Token Plan not configured | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → MiniMax Token Plan — never substitute silently |\n| Direct API explicitly requested | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax/MiniMax-M3` (pay-per-token; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax`) |\n| Direct API requested, not configured | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login minimax` (needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`) — never substitute silently |\n\n**MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (high reasoning is the standing default — opencode maps low/medium/high to MiMo's reasoning effort) — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13); confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n| MiMo speed variant requested (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive checks/smokes) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro serving tier, same COSTAR prompt contract as the standard model |\n| Direct API not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n| Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n| Token Plan requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n\n**User prompt template — default missing, fallback configured:**\n\n```text\nThe skill default `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` is not configured on this machine.\nA configured fallback is available. Pick one:\n  A) Use `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro --variant high` (OpenAI premium, configured now — paid)\n  B) Use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API, configured now) — or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` for latency-sensitive runs\n  C) Use `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (Kimi For Coding plan, configured now — subscription)\n  D) Run `opencode providers login deepseek` first, then retry the original dispatch\n  E) Name a different model — paste the `--model <provider/model>` you want to use\n```\n\n**User prompt template — all providers missing:**\n\n```text\nNo supported providers are configured on this machine. Run one:\n  - `opencode providers login deepseek`     (recommended — default for cli-opencode)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path; pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\" → provider minimax-coding-plan; model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3)\n  - `opencode providers login minimax`      (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token; needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; model minimax/MiniMax-M3)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Xiaomi Token Plan — default Xiaomi path; pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\" → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams; model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro)\n  - `opencode providers login xiaomi`       (Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; models xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro and xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Kimi For Coding plan — Kimi/Moonshot coding subscription; provider kimi-for-coding; model kimi-for-coding/k2p7)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription; provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2)\n  - `opencode providers login openai`       (OpenAI premium alternative — paid)\nWhich would you like to set up? Confirm when login finishes; the skill will retry the original dispatch.\n```\n\n**Error-recovery contract.** If a dispatch returns an auth error after pre-flight passed (credential expired or rotated), invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n\n### Default Invocation (Skill Default)\n\n**Default model + variant + format + dir**: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` · `--variant high` · `--format json` · `--dir <repo-root>`. The repo root pin avoids CWD ambiguity. Direct DeepSeek is the default provider — it gives elevated reasoning at low cost for routine cli-opencode dispatches.\n\nUse `opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"<prompt>\"`.\n\n> **The `--agent` flag (read this):** Do NOT pass `--agent` on a top-level `opencode run`. Current opencode treats named agents like `general` as **subagents** and rejects them at the top level, so `--agent general` fails the dispatch outright. When no `--agent` is given, the default agent runs — which is what you want for almost every dispatch. **To run as a specific agent profile, describe the role in the prompt body** (for example, open the prompt with \"Act as a code-review agent: …\"), not via `--agent`. Only pass `--agent <name>` if you have confirmed against `opencode run --help` on the installed version that it accepts that agent at the top level.\n\nHonor explicit user model, port, and handback phrasing verbatim; otherwise use the default invocation above.\n\n### Core Invocation Pattern\n\nCore flags: `--model`, `--agent`, `--variant`, `--format json`, `--dir`, continuation/session/fork flags, `--share` and `--port` for detached sessions, `--file`, `--thinking`, `--pure`, and log flags.\n\n> **Non-interactive invocation stdin**: always append `</dev/null` to any non-interactive `opencode run` invocation. Without it, opencode can inherit parent-terminal stdin and trigger the reactive-EOF exit path when that stream closes. See `references/integration_patterns.md` §6.\n\n> **Registered command dispatch (`--command`)**: slash-command text inside a `run` message is NOT expanded — `opencode run \"/memory:search query\"` delivers the slash text to the model as raw prose, and the command template (router contract, presentation assets, MUST-render envelopes) never enters the session. To execute a registered command non-interactively: `opencode run --command <family>/<name> [flags] \"<args>\"` — the message becomes `$ARGUMENTS`. Registry names are slash-namespaced: `memory/search` for `/memory:search` (a wrong `--command` name fails with the full registry list). Verified on opencode 1.17.4. Consequences: (a) any behavior/adherence probe of a slash command MUST use `--command`, and the raw-text form is only valid as a labeled negative control; (b) inside `` !`…` `` template injections `$ARGUMENTS` expands like `\"$@\"` — one word per argument — so renderer scripts must join argv themselves.\n\n### Model Selection\n\nRun `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API); the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (omit `--agent`), the pay-per-token `minimax/MiniMax-M3` (Direct API), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo; high reasoning preset; omit `--agent`), `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo; pay-per-token) and `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` (low-latency MiMo tier, same prompt contract) remain available. The Kimi For Coding plan model `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (\"Kimi K2.7 Code\"; 256k / 262,144-token context; subscription billing — dispatch cost 0; omit `--agent`; `--variant high` accepted but effect benchmark-unverified) is the coding-optimized large-context Kimi path. **Operational caveat (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`. The Z.AI GLM Coding Plan model `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (\"GLM-5.2\"; flagship long-horizon coding; 1,000,000-token context / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs; subscription billing; omit `--agent`; `--variant`↔`reasoning_effort` mapping unverified — GLM has native high/max, smoke-test before relying on it; thinking on by default + preserved on the Coding Plan endpoint) is the Z.AI direct-provider GLM path, superseding the gateway-only `glm-5.1` removed in v1.3.15.0; confirm the live slug via `opencode models zai-coding-plan`. **Operational (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45 transient dispatch failures (retry the cell). Empirical prompt framework: COSTAR (benchmark 008). **Vision (image input):** `glm-5.2` is natively multimodal (vision-to-code), but `opencode run --file <image>` does NOT deliver images to this provider — upstream #20802 for custom OpenAI-compatible providers (confirmed 2026-06-28: `--file` → `NO_IMAGE_RECEIVED`). For image input use the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 `image_url` at `https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions`) — a deviation from this skill's dispatch path justified only by the verified #20802 breakage; see `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md` §7. OpenAI chat models — the full GPT-5.6 catalog spans a bare tier plus three named families (Sol, Terra, Luna), each offered in three model tiers (base / Fast / Pro) for twelve slugs total (`openai/gpt-5.6`, `openai/gpt-5.6-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-pro`) — usable when explicitly requested; **`gpt-5.6-sol` is the flagship default OpenAI model** for this skill. The model tier (base / Fast / Pro) is orthogonal to reasoning effort, which is the separate `--variant` lever up to **`xhigh`** (e.g. `--model openai/gpt-5.6-sol --variant xhigh`; per-tier effort ranges in `references/cli_reference.md` §5). **The `-fast` model tiers** (e.g. `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra-fast`) are the low-latency Fast variants (OpenAI `priority` service tier). Confirm live slugs via `opencode models openai`.\n\nShared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n\n### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n\nThe calling AI is the conductor. OpenCode distinguishes **primary agents** (directly invokable via `--agent <slug>`) from **subagents** (dispatched as Task-tool subagents from a primary).\n\n#### Primary agents — directly invokable via `--agent`\n\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n\n#### Subagents — dispatched as Task subagents from a primary\n\nThese live at `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` with `mode: subagent` and are NOT directly invokable via `opencode run --agent`. Three dispatch surfaces are legal under the single-hop NDP contract:\n\n1. **Generic subagents** (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) — dispatched by a primary (`orchestrate`) using the Task tool. To exercise via the opencode CLI, route through `--agent orchestrate` and let it dispatch the relevant subagent.\n2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n3. **Command-owned loop executors** (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) — LOOP-OWNED by their parent commands (`/deep:research`, `/deep:review`, `/deep:agent-improvement`, `/prompt`), which own iteration state, convergence detection, and continuity. Never dispatch these directly via raw `--agent <slug>` from the CLI. `orchestrate` is an authorized **caller/coordinator only** for these agents (e.g. its registry-backed `/deep:review` Priority row) — it may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to the resolved leaf, but MUST NOT re-implement the loop (no iterating, no convergence checks, no continuity tracking); that remains the parent command's job.\n\nGeneric subagents (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) and `ai-council` route through `orchestrate` for full Task-tool dispatch; loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are loop-owned by their parent commands, with `orchestrate` limited to a single bounded hand-off when it recognizes one of these as the target.\n\nSee [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md) for the complete agent roster and dispatch patterns.\n\n### Unique OpenCode Strengths\n\nOpenCode dispatch provides full project runtime loading, detached sessions, JSON event streams, agent routing, cross-repo/server dispatch, session continuation, and plugin-disable debugging.\n\n### Essential Commands\n\nUse the default invocation for external runtime handback, append `--share --port <N>` only for explicit detached sessions, select `--agent orchestrate` for generic subagent routing, and change `--dir` for cross-repo dispatch.\n\n### Error Handling\n\nInstall missing binaries, refuse ambiguous self-invocation, run provider pre-flight for model/auth errors, check version drift for unknown flags, force `--format json` for empty streams, add `</dev/null` for background loops, confirm `--share`, use `--pure` only for plugin crashes, and inspect state logs for stuck sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS\n\n1. Verify OpenCode CLI is installed before first invocation; confirm version baseline against v1.3.17 (drift handling per `references/cli_reference.md` §9).\n2. **Run the self-invocation guard before dispatch** (ADR-001): Layer 1 env-var lookup for any `OPENCODE_*`, Layer 2 process-ancestry probe for `opencode` parent, Layer 3 `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` probe. Trip on ANY positive — refuse unless prompt has explicit parallel-session keywords.\n3. Pin model + variant + format + dir explicitly — **no `--agent`** (see the Default Invocation note: current opencode rejects a top-level `--agent general`; put any agent-profile request in the prompt body). Default: `--model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root>`. Honor user overrides verbatim (e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`, `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`, `minimax/MiniMax-M3`, `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro`).\n4. Pass `--format json` unless the calling AI explicitly wants formatted output — JSON event stream is what external runtimes parse incrementally.\n5. **Append `</dev/null` to every non-interactive `opencode run` invocation** that redirects stdout and/or stderr to files OR runs inside `while read` loops. opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation; without explicit closed stdin, automation hangs forever at 0% CPU after the `+60s service=snapshot prune=7.days cleanup` log line. Position: AFTER the prompt positional argument, BEFORE the `> stdout 2> stderr` redirects. Foreground `| tail` happens to provide closed stdin (pipe stage upstream is empty) and accidentally bypasses the bug, but `> stdout.log 2> stderr.log` does not. The 9-character `</dev/null` redirect provides immediate EOF on stdin, unblocking the dispatch. **DO NOT auto-kill external operator-owned opencode sessions** when sweeping orphans between dispatches; exclude `opencode run` from pkill (per 2026-05-23 operator directive captured in memory `feedback_proactive_orphan_cleanup.md`). See `references/integration_patterns.md` §6 + memory `feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md` + CHANGELOG-2026-05-08-tool-name-regex-fix.md §Fix 4.\n6. **Pass the spec folder to the dispatched session** in the prompt: if the calling AI has an active Gate-3 spec folder, include `Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)`. If none, ASK the user before delegating — the dispatched session cannot answer Gate 3 interactively in non-interactive `run` mode.\n7. **Prompt construction & model-craft (cli-* family precedence).** Compose every dispatch prompt via the 3-tier rule canonical in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli_prompt_quality_card.md`:\n   1. **Fast path (default).** Build from the local `assets/prompt_quality_card.md`, which delegates the framework table + CLEAR check to the canonical card.\n   2. **Model override (mandatory for a profiled model).** If the target model has a profile at `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/<id>.md`, that profile OVERRIDES the cross-model default. The **sk-prompt/prompt-models** hub owns per-model prompt-craft (framework + scaffold + gotchas, mirroring `sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json` `recommended_frameworks`); consult it before composing for any small model.\n   3. **Deep path (escalation).** Dispatch `@prompt-improver` via the Task tool (never load full `sk-prompt` inline) when any canonical **Tier 3** trigger applies — the trigger list lives in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli_prompt_quality_card.md` under \"Tier 3 — Deep path\"; do not re-enumerate it here.\n8. Validate dispatched session output: parse JSON events incrementally (tool calls, partial messages, final summary), run syntax checks if code generated, and cross-reference against project standards via `sk-code` surface detection plus its code-review mode when findings-first review is requested (see ALWAYS rule 12).\n9. Capture stderr (`2>&1`) to catch tool errors and warnings.\n10. Classify the use case (1 / 2 / 3) before dispatching — the smart router refuses dispatches that do not map to one of the three.\n11. **Run the Provider Auth Pre-Flight once per session** (see §3 Provider Auth Pre-Flight). Cache the configured-providers list. If the default `deepseek` is missing, ASK the user — never silently substitute the model. If a later dispatch returns an auth error, invalidate the cache and rerun the pre-flight before retrying.\n12. **Code Standards Loading (surface-aware contract)** — When dispatching for code review or code generation, instruct the dispatched session to: (1) load `sk-code`; (2) let `sk-code` emit a surface tag matching the detected stack from markers and target files; (3) load the selected surface resources and run its verification commands; (4) load `sk-code`'s code-review mode only for formal findings-first review output. Fallback: if the surface cannot be determined confidently, ask for the runtime surface and verification command set. NEVER hardcode obsolete sibling code skills in dispatch prompts.\n13. **Design Standards Loading (surface-aware contract)** — When dispatching for design or UI work, instruct the dispatched session to: (1) load `sk-design` (the hub); (2) let the hub resolve a `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json` (interface / foundations / motion / audit / md-generator / design-mcp-open-design); (3) load the selected mode packet, set the design register, and run that mode's design verification; (4) if the work feeds Open Design, carry the `design-mcp-open-design` pairing (a nested transport packet of the hub) — the transport never decides taste. Fallback: if the design mode cannot be determined confidently, ask for the surface and design intent. NEVER treat `mcp-figma` or `design-mcp-open-design` as the taste authority, or hardcode obsolete flat design skills in dispatch prompts.\n14. **Pass the design dispatch manifest to the dispatched session** — when dispatching design or UI work, inline a `DESIGN_DISPATCH_MANIFEST v1` block in the prompt (the child cannot resolve skill paths, so the manifest travels in the payload, not by reference): `skDesignLoaded` true, `register` resolved to `Brand` or `Product` (never `unknown`), registry-valid `workflowModes`, `dials`, `loadedFiles`, and `proofDemandBack`. If the manifest cannot be assembled — `sk-design` not loaded, register unresolved, or no registry-valid mode — ASK before launching the child rather than starting a silent design dispatch. The child returns the demanded proof; the parent reconciles it on the return path.\n15. **Destructive-scope-violation prevention (RM-8) for deep-loop dispatches** — The structured permissions-matrix gate (`permissions-gate.ts`; schema and design in `references/permissions-matrix.md`) is built and unit-tested but has ZERO production callers today — no `opencode run` dispatch path invokes it, so a loaded `--permissions-matrix <path>` config or recipe field is NOT currently enforced and does NOT bypass anything. Regardless of whether a matrix config is present, any non-interactive `opencode run` with `--dangerously-skip-permissions` against a populated worktree MUST apply the four-layer mitigation — it is the only active protection today: (L1) rendered prompt contains literal `BANNED OPERATIONS` and `ALLOWED WRITE PATHS`; (L2) `--dir` points at a fresh `git worktree`; (L3) main `git status` clean OR committed, recovery-baseline commit hash recorded; (L4) for multi-phase / phase-parent targets, prefer `cli-copilot` + `gpt-5.6-sol --reasoning-effort high` (verify `gpt-5.6-sol` availability on the Copilot surface — unverified, carried over from a gpt-5.5-era check; if absent, pick an available Copilot model, don't silently fall back to the risky default) over `deepseek-v4-pro`. Background: on 2026-05-04 an `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` dispatch under `/deep:review:auto` deleted 44 files across two phase folders because the only safeguard was prose and `--dangerously-skip-permissions` granted unrestricted FS write. Full incident + root cause + checklist: `references/destructive_scope_violations.md`.\n16. **Single-dispatch discipline (operator-gated, session-scoped)** — Default: launch ONE cli-* dispatch at a time across the cli-* family (cli-opencode, cli-claude-code). Wait for the dispatched agent's work to return, verify outputs exist, then SIGKILL only the dispatch THIS skill started: capture its PID at launch (`opencode run ... & OC_PID=$!`) and kill that captured PID directly plus its own orphan children (`kill -9 \"$OC_PID\" 2>/dev/null; pkill -9 -P \"$OC_PID\" 2>/dev/null`), then apply the same PID-scoped `gtimeout` / `positional_scoring_fallback:app` cleanup. (A backgrounded `opencode run &` is NOT a process-group leader unless launched with `setsid`/`set -m`, so a negative-PID group kill would target a nonexistent group and miss the process — kill the captured PID directly.) **Kill only the dispatch you started, by captured PID; never a blanket `pkill -9 -f \"opencode run\"` pattern — see Rule 5** (a blanket match kills operator-owned `opencode run` sessions too). Only launch the next dispatch (this skill OR a sibling) after the prior one is dead and RSS has dropped. **Within a deep-flow session** (deep-review / deep-research): the operator authorizes the whole multi-iteration session at start — iterations chain back-to-back with kill-between as the safety mechanism, NOT a per-iteration operator confirmation prompt. **Exception (cross-skill parallel)**: when the operator explicitly authorizes N parallel dispatches, run N concurrently — but still SIGKILL each by its own captured PID as its work returns.\n17. **Set `AI_SESSION_CHILD=1` in the dispatched session's env** when sessions may be launched through the per-session worktree wrapper (`.opencode/bin/worktree-session.sh`). A dispatched `opencode run` is an orchestrated sub-session, not a new top-level session, so it must SHARE the parent's worktree rather than allocate its own. The wrapper checks `AI_SESSION_CHILD` (plus a `git --git-common-dir` structural backstop) and exec's in place when set. Pattern: `AI_SESSION_CHILD=1 opencode run ... </dev/null`. Harmless when the wrapper is not in use. See `.opencode/bin/README.md` → \"Worktree session isolation\". Prepend `MK_SPEC_GATE_ENFORCE=0` next to it so a dispatched child never inherits an enforced spec-gate from the parent shell (belt-and-suspenders alongside the wrapper's own neutralization and the core's `AI_SESSION_CHILD` deny-narrowing): `MK_SPEC_GATE_ENFORCE=0 AI_SESSION_CHILD=1 opencode run ... </dev/null`.\n\n### ❌ NEVER\n\n1. Invoke this skill from within OpenCode itself for a self-dispatch — refuse with the documented error message; use a sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords.\n2. Pass `--share` without operator confirmation (CHK-033) — share URL exposes session contents.\n3. Trust dispatched session output blindly for security-sensitive code, send sensitive data (API keys, passwords, credentials) in prompts, or hammer the API with rapid sequential calls.\n4. Use `--pure` outside of plugin debugging (disabling plugins removes the entire point of cli-opencode dispatch).\n5. Nest `opencode run` inside a dispatched session's tool calls — use OpenCode's native Task tool for sub-agent dispatch.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n\n1. OpenCode CLI is not installed and user has not acknowledged (provide `brew install opencode` or `curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash`).\n2. Operator wants to publish a `--share` URL — get explicit confirmation per CHK-033.\n3. Binary version differs from the v1.3.17 baseline — run `opencode --version` and `opencode run --help`; surface drift and fall back or require approval.\n4. Smart router cannot map the prompt to one of the three use cases — surface the disambiguation checklist from UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n5. Self-invocation guard trips AND the prompt is ambiguous — surface the refusal with three remediation options (sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords).\n\n### Memory Handback Protocol\n\nWhen the calling AI needs to preserve session context from an OpenCode CLI delegation, run the canonical 7-step procedure (extract `MEMORY_HANDBACK` section → build structured JSON → scrub secrets → invoke `generate-context.js` via `--stdin`/`--json`/temp-file → `memory_index_scan`). Full procedure and caveats: [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md`](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md).\n\nFor read-only or hook-style recovery, use the daemon-backed CLI front doors instead of spawning OpenCode: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool>`, `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool>`, or `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs <tool>`. Prompt-time paths must probe warm sockets or pass `--warm-only`; exit `75` is retryable daemon/IPC unavailability, not a model failure.\n\nOpenCode-specific Memory Epilogue template: see [assets/prompt_templates.md](./assets/prompt_templates.md) §14.\n\nExample invocation:\n```bash\nprintf '%s' \"$JSON_PAYLOAD\" | node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --stdin [spec-folder]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [cli_reference.md](./references/cli_reference.md) - Full subcommand and flag reference, models, version drift handling\n- [integration_patterns.md](./references/integration_patterns.md) - 3 use cases, decision tree, self-invocation guard, silent stdin\n- [opencode_tools.md](./references/opencode_tools.md) - Unique value props vs sibling cli-* skills\n- [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md) - Agent routing matrix, leaf-agent constraints\n- [destructive_scope_violations.md](./references/destructive_scope_violations.md) - RM-8 incident (2026-05-04, 44 files deleted), root cause analysis, four-layer prevention playbook\n\n### Templates and Assets\n\n- [prompt_templates.md](./assets/prompt_templates.md) - 13 numbered copy-paste templates per use case + agent + handback\n- [prompt_quality_card.md](./assets/prompt_quality_card.md) - Executor-specific model overrides (MiniMax, MiMo); delegates shared framework table and CLEAR check to canonical card\n\n### Shared (cli-* family)\n- [shared_smart_router.md](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md) - Helper-function bodies for the smart router.\n- [memory_handback.md](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md) - Canonical 7-step Memory Handback procedure.\n\n### External\n- [OpenCode GitHub](https://github.com/sst/opencode) - Official repository\n- [OpenCode Install](https://opencode.ai/install) - Standalone installer entry point\n- [OpenCode Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs) - Official docs\n\n### Reference Loading Notes\n\n- Load only references needed for current intent.\n- Smart Routing (Section 2) is the single routing authority.\n- `cli_reference.md` and `prompt_quality_card.md` are ALWAYS loaded as baseline.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Task Completion\n\n- OpenCode CLI invoked with the correct subcommand, flags, model, agent, variant, format, and dir.\n- Self-invocation guard checked before dispatch — refused when appropriate.\n- Use case (1 / 2 / 3) classified explicitly before invocation.\n- JSON event stream captured, parsed incrementally, validated, integrated.\n- No security vulnerabilities introduced from generated code.\n- `--share` URLs opt-in with operator confirmation per CHK-033.\n- Background dispatches in `while read` loops include `</dev/null` redirect.\n- Memory Handback extracted and saved through `generate-context.js` when applicable.\n\n### Skill Quality\n\n- All 8 sections present with proper anchor comments.\n- Smart routing covers all intent signals with UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n- Reference files provide deep-dive content without duplication.\n- Self-invocation guard pseudocode reproduced in Section 2 mirrors ADR-001.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in [AGENTS.md](../../../../AGENTS.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via the Skill Advisor Hook (or `skill_advisor.py` fallback)\n- **Tool Routing**: Per AGENTS.md Section 6 decision tree\n- **Memory**: Context preserved via Spec Kit Memory MCP (`generate-context.js`)\n- **Validation**: `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh` for spec-folder workflows\n\n**Tool roles**: Bash dispatches the CLI; Read/Glob/Grep validate output and probe `~/.opencode/state/` for session locks.\n\n---\n\n## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/cli_reference.md`, `references/integration_patterns.md`, `assets/prompt_quality_card.md`, `assets/prompt_templates.md`, `references/agent_delegation.md`, `references/opencode_tools.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n\n\n...2188 bytes truncated...\n\nThe tool call succeeded but the output was truncated. Full output saved to: /Users/michelkerkmeester/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_f59a695030015AYuLLk9QgDJAn\nUse the Task tool to have explore agent process this file with Grep and Read (with offset/limit). Do NOT read the full file yourself - delegate to save context.","metadata":{"name":"cli-opencode","dir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode","truncated":true,"outputPath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_f59a695030015AYuLLk9QgDJAn"},"title":"Loaded skill: cli-opencode","time":{"start":1783915517167,"end":1783915517189}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09eda0dc789b5e39016a5463fd16448191b3836a739edef9c6"}},"id":"prt_f59a694e2001kw36559xf3baSp","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a67e81001hLZDigWbA2Eahr"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783915517849,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"id":"prt_f59a6979700148xc3GAHLy15M2","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","messageID":"msg_f59a67e81001hLZDigWbA2Eahr","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":31055,"input":655,"output":126,"reasoning":66,"cache":{"write":0,"read":30208}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783915520532,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"id":"prt_f59a6a213001iZjwnH0Yd7JF6q","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915533991,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bRKTUry7J0rGAJi8GmqbRVWC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n5: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n6: role: Deep Review Loop Manager\n7: purpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\n8: action: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\n9: operating_mode:\n10:   workflow: iterative_loop\n11:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n12:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n13:   approvals: none\n14:   tracking: progressive_review_state\n15:   validation: convergence_detection\n16: \n17: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n18: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: operating_principles:\n21:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n22:   approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n23:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n24: \n25: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n27: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n28: user_inputs:\n29:   review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n30:   review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n31:   review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n32:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n33:   session_id: \"[SESSION_ID] - Optional caller-supplied session id for fan-out lineages. Default: timestamp.\"\n34:   lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n35:   max_iterations: 7\n36:   convergence_threshold: 0.10\n37:   convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n38:   stop_policy: \"[convergence|max-iterations] - Stop behavior. Default: convergence. max-iterations treats convergence as telemetry until the hard iteration ceiling.\"\n39:   config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: \"[optional internal path] - Fan-out lineage artifact override for command-owned single-lineage execution.\"\n40: \n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: # CONTEXT LOADING\n43: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n44: context_loading:\n45:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n46:   purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n47:   mcp_integration:\n48:     tool: memory_context\n49:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n50:     parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n51:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n52:   behavior:\n53:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n54:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n55: \n56: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n57: # SKILL REFERENCE\n58: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n59: skill_reference:\n60:   skill: system-deep-loop\n61:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md\n62:   references:\n63:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n64:     state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n65:     convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n66:   templates:\n67:     config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n68:     strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n69: \n70: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n71: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n72: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n73: agent_config:\n74:   agent: deep-review\n75:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n76:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n77:   mode: subagent\n78:   model: opus\n79:   leaf_only: true\n80:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n81:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n82:   tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n83: \n84: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n85: # STATE FILE PATHS\n86: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n87: state_paths:\n88:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n89:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n90:   # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n91:   # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n92:   # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n93:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n94:   local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n95:   legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n96:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n97:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n98:   findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n99:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n100:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n101:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n102:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n103:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n104:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n105:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n106:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n107:   # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n108:   # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n109:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n110:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n111:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n112:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n113:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n114: \n115: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n116: # WORKFLOW\n117: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n118: workflow:\n119: \n120:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n121:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n122:     note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n123:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n124:     if_present:\n125:       bind:\n126:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n127:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n128:         artifact_subfolder: null\n129:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n130:     if_absent:\n131:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n132:       outputs:\n133:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n134:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n135:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n136:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n137: \n138:   step_apply_lifecycle_request:\n139:     description: \"Honor explicit auto-mode restart before fan-out or normal initialization\"\n140:     skip_when: \"lineage_mode != 'restart'\"\n141:     instructions: |\n142:       This is the autonomous equivalent of the confirm-mode restart choice. Run it\n143:       immediately after artifact resolution and before fan-out so old packet files\n144:       cannot be merged with fresh lineage outputs. A restart request must never\n145:       fall back to auto-resume. In auto mode, the explicit restart flag is operator\n146:       authorization to archive the resolved review packet, so do not ask for a\n147:       second confirmation. Rollback is to move the timestamped archive back to\n148:       the packet directory.\n149:     command: \"if [ -d \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" ]; then mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}\\\" && mv \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\\\"; fi; mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\"\"\n150:     outputs:\n151:       - archived_path: \"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug} when a prior packet existed, else null\"\n152:       - lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n153:     on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL; do not continue as resume or auto.\"\n154: \n155:   step_fanout_spawn:\n156:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n157:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n158:     instructions: |\n159:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n160:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n161:       A cli-opencode lineage inside this fan-out is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode\n162:       session with a separate lineage directory and session id; it is not the single-executor\n163:       self-invocation path. fanout-run.cjs owns the stack-only recursion guard for that\n164:       first-level detached lineage and still blocks recursive same-kind dispatch from inside it.\n165:       fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n166:       deep/review command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n167:       deep-review agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n168:       sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n169:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n170:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n171:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n172:     sub_steps:\n173:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n174:         description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n175:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n176:         command: |\n177:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n178:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n179:             --loop-type review \\\n180:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n181:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n182:             --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold} \\\n183:             --stop-policy {stop_policy}\n184:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n185:         wait_for_completion: true\n186: \n187:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n188:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n189:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n190:   phase_init:\n191:     purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n192:     steps:\n193: \n194:       step_preflight_contract:\n195:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n196:         verify:\n197:           - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, lineage_mode, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode, stop_policy]\n198:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n199:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n200:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n201:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n202: \n203:       step_create_directories:\n204:         action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n205:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n206: \n207:       step_detect_resource_map:\n208:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n209:         inspect:\n210:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n211:         classify:\n212:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n213:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n214:         outputs:\n215:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n216:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n217: \n218:       step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n219:         action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n220:         detect:\n221:           canonical_review_state:\n222:             - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n223:             - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n224:             - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n225:             - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n226:           legacy_review_state:\n227:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n228:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n229:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n230:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n231:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n232:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n233:             - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n234:             - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n235:           legacy_review_markers:\n236:             - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n237:             - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n238:         migrate_only:\n239:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n240:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n241:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n242:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n243:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n244:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n245:           - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n246:           - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n247:         on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n248:         on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n249:         on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n250:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n251: \n252:       step_acquire_lock:\n253:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n254:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n255:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n256:         note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n257:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n258:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n259:         on_halt:\n260:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n261:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n262:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n263:         on_cancel:\n264:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n265:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n266:         on_workflow_exit:\n267:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n268:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n269: \n270:       step_classify_session:\n271:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n272:         inspect:\n273:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n274:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n275:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n276:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n277:         classify:\n278:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n279:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n280:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n281:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n282:         outputs:\n283:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n284:         lifecycle_routing:\n285:           - \"If lineage_mode == restart and session_state is resume or completed-session, execute on_restart before on_resume or on_completed_session.\"\n286:           - \"If lineage_mode == auto or lineage_mode == resume, preserve the existing resume/completed/fresh behavior.\"\n287:         on_resume:\n288:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n289:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n290:           skip_to: phase_loop\n291:         on_restart:\n292:           action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n293:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n294:           set:\n295:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n296:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n297:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n298:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n299:           skip_to: step_create_config\n300:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n301:         on_completed_session:\n302:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n303:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n304:         on_invalid_state:\n305:           halt: true\n306:           message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n307:         on_fresh:\n308:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n309: \n310:       step_scope_discovery:\n311:         action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n312:         resolve:\n313:           spec-folder: |\n314:             1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n315:             2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n316:             3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n317:             4. Set scope = all discovered files\n318:           skill: |\n319:             1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n320:             2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n321:             3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n322:             4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n323:             5. Set scope = all discovered files\n324:           agent: |\n325:             1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/)\n326:             2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n327:             3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n328:           track: |\n329:             1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n330:             2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n331:             3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n332:           files: |\n333:             1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n334:             2. Validate all files exist\n335:             3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n336:             4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n337:         outputs:\n338:           - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n339:           - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n340: \n341:       step_order_dimensions:\n342:         action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n343:         algorithm: |\n344:           1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n345:           2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n346:              correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n347:           3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n348:           4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n349:              - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n350:              - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n351:           5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n352:           6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n353:         outputs:\n354:           - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n355:           - inventory_pass: true\n356: \n357:       step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n358:         action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n359:         outputs:\n360:           - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n361:           - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n362:         normalize: |\n363:           Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n364:             - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n365:             - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n366:             - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n367:           Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n368: \n369:       step_resolve_session_id:\n370:         action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve timestamp fallback\"\n371:         branch_on: \"session_id\"\n372:         if_present:\n373:           bind:\n374:             session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n375:         if_absent:\n376:           bind:\n377:             session_id_init: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n378: \n379:       step_create_config:\n380:         action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n381:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n382:         populate:\n383:           topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n384:           mode: \"review\"\n385:           sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n386:           parentSessionId: null\n387:           lineageMode: \"new\"\n388:           generation: 1\n389:           continuedFromRun: null\n390:           reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n391:           reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n392:           # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n393:           reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n394:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n395:           reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n396:           severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n397:           crossReference:\n398:             core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n399:             overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n400:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n401:           # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n402:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n403:           antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n404:           antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n405:           stopPolicy: \"{stop_policy}\"\n406:           stuckThreshold: 2\n407:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n408:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n409:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n410:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n411:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n412:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n413:           status: \"initialized\"\n414:           releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n415:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n416:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n417: \n418:       step_create_state_log:\n419:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n420:         note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n421:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n422:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"stopPolicy\":\"{stop_policy}\",\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n423:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n424: \n425:       step_create_findings_registry:\n426:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n427:         content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n428:         output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n429: \n430:       step_create_strategy:\n431:         action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n432:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n433:         populate:\n434:           review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n435:           review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n436:           dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n437:           scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n438:           cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n439:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n440:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n441:           stop_policy: \"{stop_policy}\"\n442:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n443: \n444:       step_seed_coverage_graph:\n445:         action: \"Seed the review coverage graph before the first convergence check\"\n446:         transform: |\n447:           1. Convert review_scope_files into FILE nodes.\n448:           2. Convert review target groupings into coarse SLICE nodes only; do not expand SYMBOL\n449:              or DEPENDENCY nodes in review mode.\n450:           3. Emit COVERS edges from SLICE nodes to FILE nodes when the grouping is known.\n451:           4. Bind coverage_seed_source to \"scope_discovery\" and coverage_seed_confidence to 0.50.\n452:           5. When scope discovery yields no files, emit [] for both arrays; the upsert script\n453:              returns a warning and review continues with an empty graph.\n454:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{coverage_seed_nodes_json}' --edges '{coverage_seed_edges_json}' --seed-source \\\"{coverage_seed_source}\\\" --seed-confidence \\\"{coverage_seed_confidence}\\\"\"\n455:         outputs:\n456:           - coverage_seed_nodes_json: \"Seed nodes for review SLICE and FILE kinds only\"\n457:           - coverage_seed_edges_json: \"Seed COVERS edges where review target groupings resolved\"\n458:           - coverage_seed_warning: \"Warning emitted when the seed batch inserts zero nodes, else empty\"\n459:         on_warning:\n460:           log: \"Coverage graph seed inserted zero nodes; continuing with an empty graph.\"\n461:           proceed: true\n462: \n463:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n464:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n465:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n466:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n467:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n468: \n469:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n470:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n471:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n472:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n473: \n474:       step_init_complete:\n475:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n476:         set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n477: \n478:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n479:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n480:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n481:   phase_loop:\n482:     purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n483:     repeat: true\n484:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n485:     steps:\n486: \n487:       step_read_state:\n488:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n489:         read:\n490:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n491:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n492:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n493:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n494:         extract:\n495:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n496:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n497:           - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n498:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n499:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n500:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n501:           - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n502:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n503:           - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n504:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n505:           - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n506:           - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n507:           - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n508:           - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n509:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n510:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n511:           - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n512:           - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n513:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n514:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n515:           - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n516:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n517:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n518:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n519:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n520:           - stop_policy: \"Extract stopPolicy from deep-review-config.json, default 'convergence'. Valid values: convergence, max-iterations.\"\n521:           - convergence_mode: \"Extract antiConvergence.convergenceMode when it is one of 'default', 'off', 'sliding-window', or 'divergent'; default to 'default'\"\n522:           - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when antiConvergence.convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n523:           - pivot_lineage: \"Summarize registry.divergence.completed and registry.divergence.overrides with pivot ids, source iterations, and selected review direction; else 'none yet'\"\n524:           - saturated_directions: \"List registry.divergence.saturatedDirections; else 'none yet'\"\n525: \n526:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n527:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n528:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n529:         if_exists:\n530:           set:\n531:             pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n532:             pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n533:             pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n534:           skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n535:         if_not_exists:\n536:           proceed: true\n537: \n538:       step_validate_convergence_config:\n539:         action: \"Validate convergence mode when loading config\"\n540:         if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n541:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"field\":\"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n542:           log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n543: \n544:       step_graph_convergence:\n545:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n546:         inspect:\n547:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n548:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n549:         transform: |\n550:           1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n551:           2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n552:           3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n553:           4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n554:           5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n555:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\" --convergence-mode \"{convergence_mode}\"'\n556:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n557:         append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n558:         outputs:\n559:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n560:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n561:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n562:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n563:           - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n564: \n565:       step_check_convergence:\n566:         action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n567:         algorithm: |\n568:           0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n569:              claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n570:              If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n571:                candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n572:                stop_blocked = true\n573:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n574:                blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n575:                recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n576:                Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n577:           1. HARD STOPS:\n578:              a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n579:              b) if stop_policy == \"max-iterations\" AND iteration_count < max_iterations: do not allow all-dimensions-clean or composite convergence to stop; treat convergence signals as telemetry, set decision = \"CONTINUE\", and broaden the next review angle.\n580:              c) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n581:              Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n582:           2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n583:              if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n584:           3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n585:                graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n586:                Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n587:                If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n588:           4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n589:                signals = []\n590:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n591:                   avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n592:                   stop if avg <= 0.08\n593:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n594:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n595:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n596:                c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n597:                   coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n598:                   stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n599:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n600:                if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n601:                if stop_policy == \"max-iterations\" AND iteration_count < max_iterations: convergence votes are telemetry only; set weighted_stop_score for diagnostics, keep decision = \"CONTINUE\", and choose a broader next focus.\n602:                else if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n603:           5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n604:                a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n605:                b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n606:                c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n607:                d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n608:                e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n609:                f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n610:                g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n611:                h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n612:                i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n613:              if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n614:                decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n615:                stop_blocked = true\n616:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n617:                blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n618:                blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n619:                convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n620:                convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n621:                dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n622:                dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n623:                dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n624:                p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n625:                active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n626:                evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n627:                avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n628:                hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n629:                claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n630:                claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n631:                fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n632:                security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n633:                fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-633. Use offset=634 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n  session_id: \"[SESSION_ID] - Optional caller-supplied session id for fan-out lineages. Default: timestamp.\"\n  lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n  max_iterations: 7\n  convergence_threshold: 0.10\n  convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n  stop_policy: \"[convergence|max-iterations] - Stop behavior. Default: convergence. max-iterations treats convergence as telemetry until the hard iteration ceiling.\"\n  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: \"[optional internal path] - Fan-out lineage artifact override for command-owned single-lineage execution.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: system-deep-loop\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-review\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  mode: subagent\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n  # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n  # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n  # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n  legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n  findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n  # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n  # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_apply_lifecycle_request:\n    description: \"Honor explicit auto-mode restart before fan-out or normal initialization\"\n    skip_when: \"lineage_mode != 'restart'\"\n    instructions: |\n      This is the autonomous equivalent of the confirm-mode restart choice. Run it\n      immediately after artifact resolution and before fan-out so old packet files\n      cannot be merged with fresh lineage outputs. A restart request must never\n      fall back to auto-resume. In auto mode, the explicit restart flag is operator\n      authorization to archive the resolved review packet, so do not ask for a\n      second confirmation. Rollback is to move the timestamped archive back to\n      the packet directory.\n    command: \"if [ -d \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" ]; then mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}\\\" && mv \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\\\"; fi; mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\"\"\n    outputs:\n      - archived_path: \"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug} when a prior packet existed, else null\"\n      - lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n    on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL; do not continue as resume or auto.\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      A cli-opencode lineage inside this fan-out is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode\n      session with a separate lineage directory and session id; it is not the single-executor\n      self-invocation path. fanout-run.cjs owns the stack-only recursion guard for that\n      first-level detached lineage and still blocks recursive same-kind dispatch from inside it.\n      fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n      deep/review command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n      deep-review agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n      sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n            --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold} \\\n            --stop-policy {stop_policy}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, lineage_mode, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode, stop_policy]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n        action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n        detect:\n          canonical_review_state:\n            - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          legacy_review_state:\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n            - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n          legacy_review_markers:\n            - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n            - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n        migrate_only:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n        on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n        on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n        on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        lifecycle_routing:\n          - \"If lineage_mode == restart and session_state is resume or completed-session, execute on_restart before on_resume or on_completed_session.\"\n          - \"If lineage_mode == auto or lineage_mode == resume, preserve the existing resume/completed/fresh behavior.\"\n        on_resume:\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_scope_discovery:\n        action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n        resolve:\n          spec-folder: |\n            1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n            2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n            3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n            4. Set scope = all discovered files\n          skill: |\n            1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n            2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n            3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n            4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n            5. Set scope = all discovered files\n          agent: |\n            1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/)\n            2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n            3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n          track: |\n            1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n            2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n            3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n          files: |\n            1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n            2. Validate all files exist\n            3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n            4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n        outputs:\n          - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n          - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n\n      step_order_dimensions:\n        action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n          2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n             correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n          3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n          4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n             - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n             - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n          5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n          6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n        outputs:\n          - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n          - inventory_pass: true\n\n      step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n        action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n        outputs:\n          - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n          - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n        normalize: |\n          Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n            - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n            - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n            - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n          Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n\n      step_resolve_session_id:\n        action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve timestamp fallback\"\n        branch_on: \"session_id\"\n        if_present:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n        if_absent:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n          mode: \"review\"\n          sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n          parentSessionId: null\n          lineageMode: \"new\"\n          generation: 1\n          continuedFromRun: null\n          reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n          reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n          reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n          crossReference:\n            core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n            overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n          antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n          stopPolicy: \"{stop_policy}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n        note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"stopPolicy\":\"{stop_policy}\",\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_findings_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n          review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n          scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stop_policy: \"{stop_policy}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_seed_coverage_graph:\n        action: \"Seed the review coverage graph before the first convergence check\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Convert review_scope_files into FILE nodes.\n          2. Convert review target groupings into coarse SLICE nodes only; do not expand SYMBOL\n             or DEPENDENCY nodes in review mode.\n          3. Emit COVERS edges from SLICE nodes to FILE nodes when the grouping is known.\n          4. Bind coverage_seed_source to \"scope_discovery\" and coverage_seed_confidence to 0.50.\n          5. When scope discovery yields no files, emit [] for both arrays; the upsert script\n             returns a warning and review continues with an empty graph.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{coverage_seed_nodes_json}' --edges '{coverage_seed_edges_json}' --seed-source \\\"{coverage_seed_source}\\\" --seed-confidence \\\"{coverage_seed_confidence}\\\"\"\n        outputs:\n          - coverage_seed_nodes_json: \"Seed nodes for review SLICE and FILE kinds only\"\n          - coverage_seed_edges_json: \"Seed COVERS edges where review target groupings resolved\"\n          - coverage_seed_warning: \"Warning emitted when the seed batch inserts zero nodes, else empty\"\n        on_warning:\n          log: \"Coverage graph seed inserted zero nodes; continuing with an empty graph.\"\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n          - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n          - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n          - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n          - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n          - stop_policy: \"Extract stopPolicy from deep-review-config.json, default 'convergence'. Valid values: convergence, max-iterations.\"\n          - convergence_mode: \"Extract antiConvergence.convergenceMode when it is one of 'default', 'off', 'sliding-window', or 'divergent'; default to 'default'\"\n          - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when antiConvergence.convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n          - pivot_lineage: \"Summarize registry.divergence.completed and registry.divergence.overrides with pivot ids, source iterations, and selected review direction; else 'none yet'\"\n          - saturated_directions: \"List registry.divergence.saturatedDirections; else 'none yet'\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          set:\n            pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n          skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_validate_convergence_config:\n        action: \"Validate convergence mode when loading config\"\n        if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"field\":\"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n          2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n          3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n          4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n          5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\" --convergence-mode \"{convergence_mode}\"'\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n        append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n          - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n        algorithm: |\n          0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n             claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n             If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n               candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n               recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n               Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n          1. HARD STOPS:\n             a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n             b) if stop_policy == \"max-iterations\" AND iteration_count < max_iterations: do not allow all-dimensions-clean or composite convergence to stop; treat convergence signals as telemetry, set decision = \"CONTINUE\", and broaden the next review angle.\n             c) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n             Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n          2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n             if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n               graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n               Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n               If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n          4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n               signals = []\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n                  stop if avg <= 0.08\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n                  coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n                  stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n               if stop_policy == \"max-iterations\" AND iteration_count < max_iterations: convergence votes are telemetry only; set weighted_stop_score for diagnostics, keep decision = \"CONTINUE\", and choose a broader next focus.\n               else if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n          5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n               a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n               b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n               c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n               d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n               e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n               f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n               g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n               h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n               i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n             if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n               decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n               blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n               convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n               convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n               dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n               dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n               p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n               active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n               evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n               avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n               hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n               fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n               security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n               fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":633,"totalLines":634,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783915533979,"end":1783915533989}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f7bdebefd030b5016a54640de9348191be392b844c6c2941"}},"id":"prt_f59a6d673001pMOwADSzo0LRRw","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915534022,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9So6E9vRi1sievhr7j2FS0Uk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","offset":1,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Quick Reference\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review quick reference\"\n6:   - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n7:   - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n8:   - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n9:   - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\n10: importance_tier: normal\n11: contextType: general\n12: version: 1.11.0.16\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review Quick Reference\n16: \n17: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Use this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: - Looking up the canonical `/deep:review` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n30: - Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n31: - Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n32: - Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n33: \n34: ### Commands\n35: \n36: | Command | Description |\n37: |---------|-------------|\n38: | `/deep:review:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n39: | `/deep:review:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n40: | `/deep:review \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n41: \n42: ### Parameters\n43: \n44: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n45: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n46: | `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n47: | `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n48: | `--stop-policy` | convergence | Use `max-iterations` when convergence must not end the run before the iteration ceiling |\n49: | `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n50: | `--restart` | off | Archive the current review packet and start a fresh lineage |\n51: | `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 2. WHEN TO USE\n56: \n57: | Scenario | Use |\n58: |----------|-----|\n59: | Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:review` |\n60: | Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code` (code-review mode) |\n61: | Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:review:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n62: | Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:review:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n63: | Deep technical investigation | `/deep:research` (different skill) |\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n68: \n69: ```\n70: /deep:review  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n71:     |                    |                      |\n72:     |                    |                      +-- Read state\n73:     |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n74:     |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n75:     |                    |                      +-- Update state\n76:     |                    |\n77:     |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n78:     |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n79:     |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n80:     |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## 4. STATE FILES\n86: \n87: Review mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n88: \n89: | File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n90: |------|----------|--------|---------|\n91: | Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n92: | State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n93: | Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n94: | Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n95: | Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n96: | Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n97: | Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n98: | Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n99: \n100: ### Lifecycle Modes\n101: \n102: | Mode | Effect |\n103: |------|--------|\n104: | `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n105: | `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n106: | `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n107: | `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n112: \n113: | ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n114: |----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n115: | D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n116: | D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n117: | D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n118: | D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n123: \n124: | Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n125: |---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n126: | FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n127: | CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n128: | PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n129: \n130: ### Release Readiness\n131: \n132: `releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n133: \n134: | State | Meaning |\n135: |-------|---------|\n136: | `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n137: | `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n138: | `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n143: \n144: | Gate | Rule |\n145: |------|------|\n146: | Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n147: | Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n148: | Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n153: \n154: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n155: |--------|--------|-------------|\n156: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n157: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n158: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n159: \n160: **Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n161: \n162: **P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n167: \n168: Each @deep-review iteration:\n169: 1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n170: 2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n171: 3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n172: 4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n173: 5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n174: 6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n175: 7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n180: \n181: | # | Section | Purpose |\n182: |---|---------|---------|\n183: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n184: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n185: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n186: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n187: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n188: | 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n189: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n190: | 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n191: | 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n196: \n197: | Goal | Adjustment |\n198: |------|------------|\n199: | Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n200: | Forced iteration ceiling | Set `--stop-policy=max-iterations` with the desired `--max-iterations` |\n201: | Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n202: | Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n203: | Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n208: \n209: | Problem | Fix |\n210: |---------|-----|\n211: | Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05, or use `--stop-policy=max-iterations` when early convergence is unacceptable |\n212: | Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n213: | P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n214: | Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n215: | Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## 13. RELATED\n220: \n221: | Resource | Purpose |\n222: |----------|---------|\n223: | `deep-research` | Investigation/research (not review) |\n224: | `sk-code` (code-review mode) | Single-pass code review |\n225: | `@deep-review` | Single review iteration agent (LEAF) |\n226: | `@context` | Single-pass codebase search |\n227: | `generate-context.js` | Memory save script |\n228: \n229: For review-specific protocol documentation, see local `references/`:\n230: - `loop_protocol.md`, Review loop lifecycle (4 phases)\n231: - `../state/state_format.md`, Review state file schemas\n232: - `../convergence/convergence.md`, Review convergence algorithms\n\n(End of file - total 232 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review quick reference\"\n  - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n  - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n  - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.11.0.16\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review quick reference\"\n  - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n  - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n  - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.11.0.16\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nUse this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Looking up the canonical `/deep:review` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n- Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n- Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n- Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n\n### Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:review:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n| `/deep:review:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n| `/deep:review \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n| `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n| `--stop-policy` | convergence | Use `max-iterations` when convergence must not end the run before the iteration ceiling |\n| `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n| `--restart` | off | Archive the current review packet and start a fresh lineage |\n| `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n\n---\n\n## 2. WHEN TO USE\n\n| Scenario | Use |\n|----------|-----|\n| Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:review` |\n| Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code` (code-review mode) |\n| Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:review:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n| Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:review:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n| Deep technical investigation | `/deep:research` (different skill) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n```\n/deep:review  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n    |                    |                      |\n    |                    |                      +-- Read state\n    |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n    |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n    |                    |                      +-- Update state\n    |                    |\n    |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n    |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n    |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n    |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE FILES\n\nReview mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n\n| File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n|------|----------|--------|---------|\n| Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n| State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n| Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n| Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n| Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n| Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n| Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n| Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n\n### Lifecycle Modes\n\n| Mode | Effect |\n|------|--------|\n| `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n| `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n| `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n| `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n\n| ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n|----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n| D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n| D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n| D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n\n---\n\n## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n|---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n| FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n| CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n| PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n\n### Release Readiness\n\n`releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n\n| State | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n| `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n| `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n\n---\n\n## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n\n| Gate | Rule |\n|------|------|\n| Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n| Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n| Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n\n---\n\n## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n\n**Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n\n**P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n\n---\n\n## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n\nEach @deep-review iteration:\n1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n\n---\n\n## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n\n| # | Section | Purpose |\n|---|---------|---------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n| 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n| 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n\n---\n\n## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n| Forced iteration ceiling | Set `--stop-policy=max-iterations` with the desired `--max-iterations` |\n| Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n| Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n| Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n\n---\n\n## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05, or use `--stop-policy=max-iterations` when early convergence is unacceptable |\n| Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n| P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n| Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n| Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n\n---\n\n## 13. RELATED\n\n| Resource | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `deep-research` | Investigation/research (not review) |\n| `sk-code` (code-review mode) | Single-pass code review |\n| `@deep-review` | Single review iteration agent (LEAF) |\n| `@context` | Single-pass codebase search |\n| `generate-context.js` | Memory save script |\n\nFor review-specific protocol documentation, see local `references/`:\n- `loop_protocol.md`, Review loop lifecycle (4 phases)\n- `../state/state_format.md`, Review state file schemas\n- `../convergence/convergence.md`, Review convergence algorithms","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":232,"totalLines":232,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","time":{"start":1783915534017,"end":1783915534021}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f7bdebefd030b5016a54640de9488191b56650b4e002b494"}},"id":"prt_f59a6d69d001M2Lx8HshLV6vZ3","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915534032,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ACHcbOrYPG4BNEOZBpoe5Efs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n6:   - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n7:   - \"review loop initialization\"\n8:   - \"review auto resume\"\n9:   - \"review synthesis phase\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.11.0.29\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\n16: \n17: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n30: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n31: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n32: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n33: \n34: ```\n35: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n36: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n37: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n38: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n39: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n40: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n41: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n42: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n43: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n44: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n45: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n46: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n47: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n48: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n50: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n51: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ### Core Innovation\n55: \n56: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n57: \n58: ### Key References\n59: \n60: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\n61: |----------|------|---------|\n62: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n63: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n64: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n65: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n66: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n71: \n72: ### Purpose\n73: \n74: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n75: \n76: ### Steps\n77: \n78: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n79:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n80:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n81:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n82:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n83: \n84: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n85: \n86: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n87: \n88:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n89:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n90:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n91:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n92:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n93:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n94:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n95: \n96:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n97: \n98: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n99: \n100:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n101:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\n102:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n103:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n104:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n105:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n106: \n107:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n108: \n109: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n110: \n111:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n112:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n113:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n114:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n115:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n116:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n117:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n118:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n119: \n120:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n121: \n122: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n123: \n124: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n125: \n126: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n127: \n128: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n129:    - Topic (review target description)\n130:    - Review Dimensions checklist\n131:    - Files Under Review table\n132:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n133:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n134:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n135:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n136:    - Review Boundaries from config\n137: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n138:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n139:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n140: \n141: 10. **Validate review charter**:\n142:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n143:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n144:    - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n145: \n146: 11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n147: \n148: ### Outputs\n149: \n150: | File | Location | Purpose |\n151: |------|----------|---------|\n152: | Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n153: | State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n154: | Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n155: | Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n160: \n161: ### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n162: \n163: #### Step 1: Read State\n164: \n165: - Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n166: - Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n167: - Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n168: \n169: Reducer contract for every loop refresh:\n170: \n171: | Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n172: |--------------|-----------------|-------|\n173: | Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n174: | Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n175: | Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n176: \n177: #### Step 2: Check Convergence\n178: \n179: Run `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n180: \n181: - Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n182: - Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n183: - Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n184:   - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n185:   - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n186:   - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n187:   - Required traceability protocols are covered\n188:   - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n189: - Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n190: \n191: If convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n192: \n193: - `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n194: - `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n195: - `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n196: \n197: The blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n198: \n199: Convergence signals and weights:\n200: \n201: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n202: |--------|--------|-------------|\n203: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n204: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n205: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n206: \n207: **P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n208: \n209: #### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n210: \n211: Before dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n212: \n213: 1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n214: 2. If present:\n215:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n216:    - Halt the loop with message:\n217:      ```\n218:      Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n219:      Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n220:      ```\n221:    - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n222: 3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n223:    - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n224:    - Continue from step_read_state\n225: \n226: **Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n227: \n228: Normalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n229: \n230: #### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n231: \n232: Generate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n233: \n234: ```\n235: STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\n236: Iteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\n237: Target: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\n238: Dimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\n239: Findings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\n240: Traceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\n241: Last 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n242: Provisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\n243: Next focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n244: ```\n245: \n246: This summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n247: \n248: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n249: \n250: Dispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n251: \n252: ```\n253: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n254: \n255: Review Target: {config.reviewTarget}\n256: Review Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\n257: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n258: Focus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\n259: Focus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\n260: Remaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}\n261: Traceability Protocols:\n262:   - Core: {core_protocols}\n263:   - Overlay: {overlay_protocols}\n264: Active Findings: {findingsSummary}\n265: State Files:\n266:   - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\n267:   - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\n268:   - Registry: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\n269:   - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\n270: Output: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n271: CONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n272: CONSTRAINT: Target files are READ-ONLY -- never modify code under review\n273: ```\n274: \n275: #### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n276: \n277: Before dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n278: \n279: - `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-review` agent with model Opus.\n280: - `cli-opencode` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y]`. **This grants full OS-level workspace write access.** There is no `--sandbox workspace-write` flag in the live command, and `sandboxMode='read-only'` is NOT currently honored/enforced by opencode (no opencode equivalent exists). The only real containment is (a) the prompt-level \"ALLOWED WRITE PATHS\" / \"BANNED OPERATIONS\" contract rendered into the iteration prompt (`assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`), which relies on the model obeying instructions rather than an OS-level sandbox, and (b) post-dispatch validation (`validateIterationOutputs`) catching some violations after the fact. Because review targets are arbitrary code/spec files, they MUST be treated as potentially adversarial content (untrusted) for prompt-injection purposes — the same containment posture as untrusted fetched content in deep-research.\n281: - `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only). We override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n282: \n283: All branches share:\n284: 1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n285: 2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n286: 3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n287: \n288: Per-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n289: \n290: Cross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope. See the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n291: \n292: Failure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n293: \n294: **Agent constraints**:\n295: - `@deep-review` is LEAF-only: it cannot dispatch sub-agents\n296: - No WebFetch: review is code-only and read-only\n297: - Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle\n298: - Tools available: Read, Grep, Glob, Edit (state files only), code_graph_query + Grep\n299: \n300: #### Step 3a: Cross-Reference Protocol Execution\n301: \n302: During iterations focused on the Traceability dimension, the agent executes applicable cross-reference protocols. Each protocol produces a structured result appended to the JSONL `traceabilityChecks.results[]` array.\n303: \n304: | Protocol | Execution | Expected Output |\n305: |----------|-----------|-----------------|\n306: | `spec_code` | Compare normative claims in spec.md against shipped implementation | Pass/partial/fail per claim with file:line evidence |\n307: | `checklist_evidence` | Verify every `[x]` mark in checklist.md has supporting evidence | Pass/partial/fail per checked item |\n308: | `skill_agent` | Compare SKILL.md contracts against runtime agent definitions | Agreement/drift/disagreement per capability |\n309: | `agent_cross_runtime` | Compare agent definitions across runtimes (.opencode, .claude, .opencode) | Parity/drift/divergence per runtime pair |\n310: | `feature_catalog_code` | Compare catalog claims against discoverable implementation | Match/stale/missing per feature |\n311: | `playbook_capability` | Validate playbook scenarios against executable reality | Executable/needs-update/impossible per scenario |\n312: \n313: Each protocol result includes:\n314: - `protocolId`: Protocol identifier\n315: - `status`: `pass`, `partial`, or `fail`\n316: - `gateClass`: `hard` or `advisory`\n317: - `applicable`: Whether the protocol applies to this target type\n318: - `counts`: `{ pass, partial, fail, skipped }`\n319: - `evidence`: Array of file:line citations\n320: - `findingRefs`: Array of finding IDs generated from this protocol\n321: - `summary`: Human-readable summary text\n322: \n323: #### Step 3b: Resource Map Coverage Audit\n324: \n325: When `config.resource_map_present == true`, at least one loop iteration MUST audit implementation-vs-resource-map coverage:\n326: \n327: 1. Read `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`\n328: 2. Read applied reports under `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md`\n329: 3. Cross-check `target_files` from the applied reports against resource-map entries\n330: 4. Classify outcomes into:\n331:    - entries touched\n332:    - entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`)\n333:    - implementation paths absent from the map\n334: 5. Emit any resulting findings with category `resource-map-coverage`\n335: \n336: When `config.resource_map_present == false`, skip this audit and rely on the `Known Context` note: `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate`.\n337: \n338: #### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n339: \n340: After agent completes:\n341: \n342: 1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n343: 2. Verify JSONL was appended with review iteration fields:\n344:    - `dimensions` (array of dimensions covered)\n345:    - `filesReviewed` (array of file paths)\n346:    - `findingsSummary` (cumulative P0/P1/P2 counts)\n347:    - `findingsNew` (this iteration's new findings)\n348:    - `traceabilityChecks` (protocol results if applicable)\n349: 3. Verify strategy.md was updated (dimension progress, findings count, protocol status)\n350: 4. Extract `newFindingsRatio` from JSONL record\n351: 5. Update stuck tracking using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`:\n352:    - Skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change)\n353:    - Reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress)\n354:    - Increment if `newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold`\n355:    - Reset otherwise\n356: \n357: #### Step 4a: Claim Adjudication\n358: \n359: Before the next convergence pass, the orchestrator adjudicates every new P0/P1 finding with a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. This step prevents false positives from inflating severity and distorting convergence, AND acts as a hard STOP gate: `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` appends a `claim_adjudication` event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree consults that event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`). A missing or failing packet vetoes STOP even when every other gate passes.\n360: \n361: Each new P0/P1 must carry a typed packet with the following required fields (see `../state/state_format.md` §9 for the full schema and a worked example):\n362: \n363: | Field | Type | Description |\n364: |-------|------|-------------|\n365: | `findingId` | string | Matches the finding ID in the iteration body |\n366: | `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes |\n367: | `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations (≥ 1) |\n368: | `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the orchestrator looked for contradicting evidence |\n369: | `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative explanation, even if rejected |\n370: | `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication |\n371: | `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Orchestrator confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n372: | `downgradeTrigger` | string | Concrete condition that would cause a future downgrade |\n373: | `transitions` | object[] | Optional, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n374: \n375: **Protocol**:\n376: \n377: 1. Re-read the cited evidence at the referenced file:line locations.\n378: 2. Seek counterevidence in adjacent code, docs, or prior iteration history.\n379: 3. Record an alternative explanation even if it is rejected.\n380: 4. Confirm or downgrade severity before the finding becomes convergence-visible.\n381: 5. Emit the typed packet inside the iteration file so `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` can parse it.\n382: \n383: **Failure semantics**: when any new P0/P1 finding is missing a packet or a required field, the workflow records `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. On the next loop, `step_check_convergence` step 0 (universal pre-check) routes STOP to `BLOCKED` with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet. Downgraded findings have their `finalSeverity` updated. The original severity is preserved in the iteration file for audit trail.\n384: \n385: #### Step 4b: Generate Dashboard\n386: \n387: Generate `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md` with review-specific sections:\n388: \n389: | Section | Content |\n390: |---------|---------|\n391: | Status | Provisional verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`/`PENDING`) and `hasAdvisories` flag |\n392: | Findings Summary | P0/P1/P2 counts with deltas from previous iteration |\n393: | Progress Table | Iteration number, focus dimension, `newFindingsRatio`, findings count, status |\n394: | Coverage | Files reviewed, dimensions completed, traceability protocol status |\n395: | Trend | Last 3 `newFindingsRatio` values with direction indicator (ascending/descending/flat) |\n396: | Active Risks | Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings |\n397: \n398: Dashboard behavior:\n399: - Auto-generated only -- never manually edited\n400: - Overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n401: - Non-blocking: if generation fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n402: - In **confirm mode**: displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate\n403: - In **auto mode**: written silently for post-hoc review\n404: \n405: #### Step 5: Loop Decision\n406: \n407: - If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n408: - If STUCK_RECOVERY: apply review-specific recovery strategies (see Section 3a), reset stuck count, continue\n409: - Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n410: \n411: ### Stuck Recovery (Review-Specific)\n412: \n413: **Threshold:** 2 consecutive no-progress iterations (`noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n414: \n415: | Failure Mode | Detection | Recovery Strategy |\n416: |-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n417: | Same dimension stuck | Last 2 iterations reviewed the same dimension with ratios `< 0.05` | **Change granularity**: if reviewing at file level, zoom into functions, if reviewing functions, zoom out to module level |\n418: | Traceability plateau | Required protocols remain partial while ratios stay `< 0.05` | **Protocol-first replay**: re-run the unresolved traceability protocol directly against the conflicting artifacts |\n419: | Low-value advisory churn | Last 2 iterations found only P2 work | **Escalate severity review**: explicitly search for P0/P1 patterns or downgrade unsupported severity claims |\n420: \n421: **Selection logic**:\n422: \n423: ```\n424: function selectReviewRecoveryStrategy(stuckIterations, state, config):\n425:   lastFocuses = [i.focus for i in stuckIterations[-2:]]\n426: \n427:   // Same dimension stuck? Change granularity\n428:   if len(set(lastFocuses)) <= 1:\n429:     return { strategy: \"change_granularity\", dimension: lastFocuses[0] }\n430: \n431:   // Required protocol plateau?\n432:   if hasRequiredProtocolPlateau(state.traceabilityChecks):\n433:     return { strategy: \"protocol_first_replay\" }\n434: \n435:   // Default: escalate severity\n436:   return { strategy: \"escalate_severity_review\" }\n437: ```\n438: \n439: **Recovery evaluation**:\n440: - If recovery iteration finds any new P0/P1 or materially advances required traceability coverage: recovery successful. Reset stuck count. Continue.\n441: - If recovery iteration finds only P2 or nothing: recovery failed. If all dimensions are already covered, exit to synthesis. Otherwise, move to the next unreviewed dimension.\n442: \n443: ---\n444: \n445: ## 4. PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n446: \n447: ### Purpose\n448: \n449: Compile all iteration findings into the final `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md`. The synthesis phase owns the canonical review report output.\n450: \n451: ### Steps\n452: \n453: #### Step 1: Finding Registry Deduplication\n454: \n455: Consolidate findings across all iterations:\n456: \n457: 1. Read all iteration files: `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n458: 2. Group findings by file + line range + root cause\n459: 3. Merge duplicates, keeping the highest severity and all evidence\n460: 4. Assign final finding IDs: `F001`, `F002`, ...\n461: 5. Preserve the audit trail: note which iterations contributed to each merged finding\n462: \n463: #### Step 2: Severity Reconciliation\n464: \n465: Use adjudicated `finalSeverity` for any P0/P1 that was downgraded during claim adjudication (Step 4a of the iteration loop). The original severity from the iteration file is preserved in the audit appendix.\n466: \n467: #### Step 3: Replay Validation\n468: \n469: Recompute the convergence outcome from JSONL state before finalizing the report:\n470: \n471: 1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` and select review-mode iteration records in run order\n472: 2. Recompute `newFindingsRatio`, rolling-average votes, MAD votes, and coverage votes from stored JSONL fields only\n473: 3. Recompute `traceabilityChecks.summary` and confirm required protocol statuses match the recorded coverage vote\n474: 4. Re-run the evidence, scope, and coverage gates against stored findings and scope data\n475: 5. Compare the replayed decision and stop reason to the recorded synthesis event\n476: \n477: This synthesis-stage replay is a **full-history audit replay** over the stored JSONL state. It follows the same full-history replay discipline as the per-iteration reducer refresh above, but runs as an explicit pre-synthesis audit.\n478: \n479: Replay passes only when the recomputed decision, thresholds, and gate outcomes agree with the persisted result. If replay fails, log a warning in the audit appendix but proceed with synthesis.\n480: \n481: #### Step 4: Compile review-report.md\n482: \n483: Generate the 9 core review-report sections (defined in `review_mode_contract.yaml` under `outputs.reviewReport`) and insert `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` between `Traceability Status` and `Deferred Items` when `config.resource_map_present == true`:\n484: \n485: | # | Section | Purpose |\n486: |---|---------|---------|\n487: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` metadata |\n488: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n489: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduplicated active findings with evidence and final severity |\n490: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n491: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n492: | 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n493: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n494: | 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `config.resource_map_present == true`, reports touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n495: | 9 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n496: | 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, convergence evidence |\n497: \n498: #### Step 5: Verdict Determination\n499: \n500: Apply the verdict contract from `review_mode_contract.yaml`:\n501: \n502: | Verdict | Condition | Next Command |\n503: |---------|-----------|--------------|\n504: | **FAIL** | Active P0 remains OR any required binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n505: | **CONDITIONAL** | No active P0, but active P1 remains | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n506: | **PASS** | No active P0/P1 | `/create:changelog` |\n507: \n508: When `PASS` verdict is issued and active P2 findings remain, set `hasAdvisories = true` in the report metadata.\n509: \n510: #### Step 6: Finalize State\n511: \n512: 1. Update config status: Set `status: \"complete\"` in `deep-review-config.json`\n513: 2. Write final JSONL entry:\n514:    ```json\n515:    {\n516:      \"type\": \"event\",\n517:      \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\",\n518:      \"mode\": \"review\",\n519:      \"totalIterations\": N,\n520:      \"verdict\": \"PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL\",\n521:      \"activeP0\": N,\n522:      \"activeP1\": N,\n523:      \"activeP2\": N,\n524:      \"dimensionCoverage\": X,\n525:      \"stopReason\": \"...\",\n526:      \"timestamp\": \"...\"\n527:    }\n528:    ```\n529: \n530: ---\n531: \n532: ## 5. PHASE 4: SAVE\n533: \n534: ### Purpose\n535: \n536: Preserve review context to the memory system for future session recovery and cross-session continuity.\n537: \n538: ### Steps\n539: \n540: 1. **Compose context payload**: Create a structured JSON payload with the review summary, active findings, verdict, next action, and relevant artifacts. Use `specFolder` for the target packet and include curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` when available.\n541: \n542: 2. **Generate context**: Run the memory save script with structured JSON via `--stdin`, `--json`, or a session-scoped JSON file:\n543:    ```bash\n544:    node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --json '{\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"sessionSummary\":\"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict and findings.\"}' {spec_folder}\n545:    ```\n546: \n547: 3. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow.\n548: \n549: 4. **Verify**: Confirm the routed canonical spec document carries the review continuity update. Expected targets are `implementation-summary.md`, `decision-record.md`, or `handover.md`; standalone `memory/*.md` files are retired and should not be created.\n550: \n551: ### On Save Failure\n552: \n553: If memory save fails:\n554: - Preserve the current `review/` packet as backup (the disk state is the ground truth)\n555: - Log the error\n556: - The review results remain intact in `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md` regardless of memory save status\n557: \n558: ---\n559: \n560: ## 6. AUTO-RESUME PROTOCOL\n561: \n562: ### Purpose\n563: \n564: Enable review sessions to resume cleanly from prior state when interrupted by context compaction, process termination, or intentional pause.\n565: \n566: ### Resume Detection\n567: \n568: If state files already exist from a prior session:\n569: \n570: 1. **Verify agreement**: Confirm config, JSONL, findings registry, and strategy all exist and agree on target/spec folder\n571: 2. **Count progress**: Read JSONL, count iteration records, determine last completed iteration\n572: 3. **Read strategy**: Load current dimension progress, findings, and next focus from `deep-review-strategy.md`\n573: 4. **Set counter**: Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n574: 5. **Log resume**: Append the canonical resume event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The reducer requires every field below:\n575:    ```json\n576:    {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-24T14:05:00Z\"}\n577:    ```\n578: 6. **Continue**: Enter the iteration loop from step_read_state\n579: \n580: ### Lifecycle Branches (current release)\n581: \n582: The runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures. Until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n583: \n584: | Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n585: |------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n586: | `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n587: | `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n588: | `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `review/` tree moved under `review_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus non-null `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n589: \n590: **Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n591: \n592: ```json\n593: {\n594:   \"type\": \"event\",\n595:   \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n596:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n597:   \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n598:   \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n599:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n600:   \"generation\": <number>,\n601:   \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n602:   \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n603:   \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n604: }\n605: ```\n606: \n607: Every field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n608: \n609: ### State Validation on Resume\n610: \n611: | Condition | Classification | Action |\n612: |-----------|---------------|--------|\n613: | Config + JSONL + strategy all exist and agree | `resume` | Continue from last iteration + 1 |\n614: | All exist, config says `status: \"complete\"` | `completed-session` | Report completion, ask user if re-review desired |\n615: | Partial files or contradictions | `invalid-state` | Halt for repair, do not guess |\n616: | No files exist | `fresh` | Start new initialization |\n617: \n618: ### State Recovery Cascade\n619: \n620: When state files are missing or corrupted, apply this priority cascade:\n621: \n622: | Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n623: |----------|-----------|----------------|\n624: | 1 | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation |\n625: | 2 | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract dimensions, findings, coverage |\n626: | 3 | JSONL missing, iteration files exist | Scan `review/iterations/iteration-*.md`, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n627: | 4 | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase |\n628: | 5 | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n629: \n630: Each priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next.\n631: \n632: ---\n633: \n634: ## 7. PAUSE/RESUME\n635: \n636: ### Pause Sentinel Behavior\n637: \n638: The pause sentinel provides graceful loop suspension in autonomous mode without killing the process.\n639: \n640: ### Creating a Pause\n641: \n642: Create the sentinel file at any time:\n643: \n644: ```bash\n645: touch {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n646: ```\n647: \n648: The orchestrator checks for this file between iterations (Step 2a). When detected:\n649: - The current iteration is allowed to complete\n650: - The loop halts before dispatching the next iteration\n651: - A paused event is logged to JSONL\n652: - The user is notified with current state (iteration count, dimensions covered, findings)\n653: \n654: ### Resuming After Pause\n655: \n656: Delete the sentinel file and restart the workflow:\n657: \n658: ```bash\n659: rm {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n660: ```\n661: \n662: On the next invocation:\n663: - The auto-resume protocol (Section 6) detects the existing state\n664: - A resumed event is logged to JSONL\n665: - The loop continues from the next iteration\n666: \n667: ### Confirm Mode Approval Gates\n668: \n669: In confirm mode (`deep_review_confirm.yaml`), the workflow adds explicit approval gates instead of relying on the pause sentinel:\n670: \n671: | Gate Location | Behavior |\n672: |---------------|----------|\n673: | After initialization | Show config, strategy, and scope. Wait for approval |\n674: | After each iteration | Show iteration findings, dashboard, and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n675: | Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n676: | After synthesis | Show final review-report.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n677: \n678: ---\n679: \n680: ## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS, ERROR HANDLING, AND QUALITY GATES\n681: \n682: State-transition rules, error handling, and the review quality gates live in `loop_state_and_gates.md` for navigability.\n683: \n684: ---\n685: \n686: ## 11. RELATED RESOURCES\n687: \n688: ### Shared Protocol Documentation\n689: \n690: Protocol documents from `deep-research` are cross-referenced, not duplicated:\n691: \n692: | Document | Path | Purpose |\n693: |----------|------|---------|\n694: | Loop Protocol (research) | `../deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` | Research loop lifecycle (this file adapts Section 9) |\n695: | State Format | `../deep-research/references/state/state_format.md` | JSONL, strategy, and config schemas |\n696: | Convergence | `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` | `shouldContinue_review()` (Section 10), stuck recovery, quality guards |\n697: \n698: ### Review-Specific Resources\n699: \n700: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\n701: |----------|------|---------|\n702: | Review Contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Single source of truth for dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n703: | Quick Reference | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | One-page review cheat sheet |\n704: | Strategy Template | `assets/deep_review_strategy.md` | Template for review strategy files |\n705: | Config Template | `assets/deep_review_config.json` | Template for review config files |\n706: | Dashboard Template | `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md` | Template for auto-generated dashboard |\n707: \n708: ### Workflow Files\n709: \n710: | Mode | Path |\n711: |------|------|\n712: | Auto (unattended) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` |\n713: | Confirm (step-by-step) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` |\n714: \n715: ### Agent\n716: \n717: | Agent | Path Pattern | Constraint |\n718: |-------|-------------|------------|\n719: | `@deep-review` | `{runtime_dir}/deep-review.{ext}` | LEAF-only, no sub-agents, no WebFetch, target files read-only |\n720: \n721: Runtime paths:\n722: - OpenCode / Copilot: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md`\n723: - Claude: `.claude/agents/deep-review.md`\n724: \n725: ---\n726: \n727: ## Executor Selection Contract\n728: \n729: Executor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta.\n730: \n731: ### Invariants\n732: \n733: Every executor path MUST satisfy:\n734: \n735: 1. Produce an iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}` (non-empty).\n736: 2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n737: 3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops. Max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n738: \n739: ### Failure Modes\n740: \n741: - Missing iteration file: `iteration_file_missing` from `post-dispatch-validate.ts`, emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event.\n742: - Empty iteration file: `iteration_file_empty`, same downstream.\n743: - JSONL not appended: `jsonl_not_appended`.\n744: - JSONL missing required fields: `jsonl_missing_fields`.\n745: - JSONL malformed: `jsonl_parse_error`.\n746: - 3 consecutive failures: existing `stuck_recovery` event (unchanged).\n747: \n748: ### JSONL Audit Field\n749: \n750: Non-native executor runs append an `executor` block with model and runtime settings to the iteration's JSONL record via `executor-audit.ts`. Native runs are recoverable from YAML alone.\n751: \n752: ### Template And Config Surface\n753: \n754: The executor-agnostic iteration prompt lives at `assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`, rendered by `prompt-pack.ts` before dispatch and either injected as the agent's context (native) or piped to `opencode run` stdin (cli-opencode). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `runtime//lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\n755: \n756: ### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\n757: \n758: - YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\n759: - `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\n760: - Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\n761: - The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\n762: \n763: ### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\n764: \n765: On this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\n\n(End of file - total 765 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n  - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n  - \"review loop initialization\"\n  - \"review auto resume\"\n  - \"review synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.29\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n  - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n  - \"review loop initialization\"\n  - \"review auto resume\"\n  - \"review synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.29\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThe deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n- Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n- Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n- Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n│  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n│              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n│ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n│ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n│ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n│ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n│ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n│              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n└──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n```\n\n### Core Innovation\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n\n### Key References\n\n| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n| Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n| Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n\n### Purpose\n\nSet up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n   - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n   - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n   - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n   - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n\n2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n\n3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n\n   | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n   |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n   | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n   | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n   | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n   | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n   | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n\n   Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n\n4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n\n   | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n   |----------|-----------|-----------|\n   | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n   | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n   | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n   | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n\n   Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n\n5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n\n   | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n   |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n   | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n   | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n   | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n   | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n   | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n   | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n\n   Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n\n6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n\n7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n\n8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n\n9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n   - Topic (review target description)\n   - Review Dimensions checklist\n   - Files Under Review table\n   - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n   - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n   - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n   - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n   - Review Boundaries from config\n9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n   - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n   - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n\n10. **Validate review charter**:\n   - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n   - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n   - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n\n11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n\n### Outputs\n\n| File | Location | Purpose |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n| State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n| Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n| Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n\n---\n\n## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n\n### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n\n#### Step 1: Read State\n\n- Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n- Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n- Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n\nReducer contract for every loop refresh:\n\n| Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n|--------------|-----------------|-------|\n| Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n| Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n| Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n\n#### Step 2: Check Convergence\n\nRun `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n\n- Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n- Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n- Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n  - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n  - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n  - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n  - Required traceability protocols are covered\n  - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n- Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n\nIf convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n- `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n- `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n\nThe blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n\nConvergence signals and weights:\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n\n**P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n\n#### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n\nBefore dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n\n1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n2. If present:\n   - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n   - Halt the loop with message:\n     ```\n     Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n     Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n     ```\n   - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n   - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n   - Continue from step_read_state\n\n**Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n\nNormalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n\n#### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n\nGenerate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n\n```\nSTATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\nIteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\nTarget: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\nDimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\nFindings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\nTraceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\nLast 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\nProvisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\nNext focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n```\n\nThis summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n\nDispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n\n```\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nReview Target: {config.reviewTarget}\nReview Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\nFocus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\nRemaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}\nTraceability Protocols:\n  - Core: {core_protocols}\n  - Overlay: {overlay_protocols}\nActive Findings: {findingsSummary}\nState Files:\n  - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\n  - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\n  - Registry: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\n  - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\nOutput: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\nCONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\nCONSTRAINT: Target files are READ-ONLY -- never modify code under review\n```\n\n#### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n\nBefore dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n\n- `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-review` agent with model Opus.\n- `cli-opencode` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y]`. **This grants full OS-level workspace write access.** There is no `--sandbox workspace-write` flag in the live command, and `sandboxMode='read-only'` is NOT currently honored/enforced by opencode (no opencode equivalent exists). The only real containment is (a) the prompt-level \"ALLOWED WRITE PATHS\" / \"BANNED OPERATIONS\" contract rendered into the iteration prompt (`assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`), which relies on the model obeying instructions rather than an OS-level sandbox, and (b) post-dispatch validation (`validateIterationOutputs`) catching some violations after the fact. Because review targets are arbitrary code/spec files, they MUST be treated as potentially adversarial content (untrusted) for prompt-injection purposes — the same containment posture as untrusted fetched content in deep-research.\n- `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only). We override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n\nAll branches share:\n1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n\nPer-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n\nCross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope. See the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n\nFailure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n\n**Agent constraints**:\n- `@deep-review` is LEAF-only: it cannot dispatch sub-agents\n- No WebFetch: review is code-only and read-only\n- Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle\n- Tools available: Read, Grep, Glob, Edit (state files only), code_graph_query + Grep\n\n#### Step 3a: Cross-Reference Protocol Execution\n\nDuring iterations focused on the Traceability dimension, the agent executes applicable cross-reference protocols. Each protocol produces a structured result appended to the JSONL `traceabilityChecks.results[]` array.\n\n| Protocol | Execution | Expected Output |\n|----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| `spec_code` | Compare normative claims in spec.md against shipped implementation | Pass/partial/fail per claim with file:line evidence |\n| `checklist_evidence` | Verify every `[x]` mark in checklist.md has supporting evidence | Pass/partial/fail per checked item |\n| `skill_agent` | Compare SKILL.md contracts against runtime agent definitions | Agreement/drift/disagreement per capability |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | Compare agent definitions across runtimes (.opencode, .claude, .opencode) | Parity/drift/divergence per runtime pair |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | Compare catalog claims against discoverable implementation | Match/stale/missing per feature |\n| `playbook_capability` | Validate playbook scenarios against executable reality | Executable/needs-update/impossible per scenario |\n\nEach protocol result includes:\n- `protocolId`: Protocol identifier\n- `status`: `pass`, `partial`, or `fail`\n- `gateClass`: `hard` or `advisory`\n- `applicable`: Whether the protocol applies to this target type\n- `counts`: `{ pass, partial, fail, skipped }`\n- `evidence`: Array of file:line citations\n- `findingRefs`: Array of finding IDs generated from this protocol\n- `summary`: Human-readable summary text\n\n#### Step 3b: Resource Map Coverage Audit\n\nWhen `config.resource_map_present == true`, at least one loop iteration MUST audit implementation-vs-resource-map coverage:\n\n1. Read `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`\n2. Read applied reports under `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md`\n3. Cross-check `target_files` from the applied reports against resource-map entries\n4. Classify outcomes into:\n   - entries touched\n   - entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`)\n   - implementation paths absent from the map\n5. Emit any resulting findings with category `resource-map-coverage`\n\nWhen `config.resource_map_present == false`, skip this audit and rely on the `Known Context` note: `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate`.\n\n#### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n\nAfter agent completes:\n\n1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n2. Verify JSONL was appended with review iteration fields:\n   - `dimensions` (array of dimensions covered)\n   - `filesReviewed` (array of file paths)\n   - `findingsSummary` (cumulative P0/P1/P2 counts)\n   - `findingsNew` (this iteration's new findings)\n   - `traceabilityChecks` (protocol results if applicable)\n3. Verify strategy.md was updated (dimension progress, findings count, protocol status)\n4. Extract `newFindingsRatio` from JSONL record\n5. Update stuck tracking using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`:\n   - Skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change)\n   - Reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress)\n   - Increment if `newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold`\n   - Reset otherwise\n\n#### Step 4a: Claim Adjudication\n\nBefore the next convergence pass, the orchestrator adjudicates every new P0/P1 finding with a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. This step prevents false positives from inflating severity and distorting convergence, AND acts as a hard STOP gate: `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` appends a `claim_adjudication` event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree consults that event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`). A missing or failing packet vetoes STOP even when every other gate passes.\n\nEach new P0/P1 must carry a typed packet with the following required fields (see `../state/state_format.md` §9 for the full schema and a worked example):\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `findingId` | string | Matches the finding ID in the iteration body |\n| `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes |\n| `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations (≥ 1) |\n| `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the orchestrator looked for contradicting evidence |\n| `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative explanation, even if rejected |\n| `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication |\n| `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Orchestrator confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n| `downgradeTrigger` | string | Concrete condition that would cause a future downgrade |\n| `transitions` | object[] | Optional, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n\n**Protocol**:\n\n1. Re-read the cited evidence at the referenced file:line locations.\n2. Seek counterevidence in adjacent code, docs, or prior iteration history.\n3. Record an alternative explanation even if it is rejected.\n4. Confirm or downgrade severity before the finding becomes convergence-visible.\n5. Emit the typed packet inside the iteration file so `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` can parse it.\n\n**Failure semantics**: when any new P0/P1 finding is missing a packet or a required field, the workflow records `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. On the next loop, `step_check_convergence` step 0 (universal pre-check) routes STOP to `BLOCKED` with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet. Downgraded findings have their `finalSeverity` updated. The original severity is preserved in the iteration file for audit trail.\n\n#### Step 4b: Generate Dashboard\n\nGenerate `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md` with review-specific sections:\n\n| Section | Content |\n|---------|---------|\n| Status | Provisional verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`/`PENDING`) and `hasAdvisories` flag |\n| Findings Summary | P0/P1/P2 counts with deltas from previous iteration |\n| Progress Table | Iteration number, focus dimension, `newFindingsRatio`, findings count, status |\n| Coverage | Files reviewed, dimensions completed, traceability protocol status |\n| Trend | Last 3 `newFindingsRatio` values with direction indicator (ascending/descending/flat) |\n| Active Risks | Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings |\n\nDashboard behavior:\n- Auto-generated only -- never manually edited\n- Overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n- Non-blocking: if generation fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n- In **confirm mode**: displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate\n- In **auto mode**: written silently for post-hoc review\n\n#### Step 5: Loop Decision\n\n- If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n- If STUCK_RECOVERY: apply review-specific recovery strategies (see Section 3a), reset stuck count, continue\n- Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n\n### Stuck Recovery (Review-Specific)\n\n**Threshold:** 2 consecutive no-progress iterations (`noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n\n| Failure Mode | Detection | Recovery Strategy |\n|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| Same dimension stuck | Last 2 iterations reviewed the same dimension with ratios `< 0.05` | **Change granularity**: if reviewing at file level, zoom into functions, if reviewing functions, zoom out to module level |\n| Traceability plateau | Required protocols remain partial while ratios stay `< 0.05` | **Protocol-first replay**: re-run the unresolved traceability protocol directly against the conflicting artifacts |\n| Low-value advisory churn | Last 2 iterations found only P2 work | **Escalate severity review**: explicitly search for P0/P1 patterns or downgrade unsupported severity claims |\n\n**Selection logic**:\n\n```\nfunction selectReviewRecoveryStrategy(stuckIterations, state, config):\n  lastFocuses = [i.focus for i in stuckIterations[-2:]]\n\n  // Same dimension stuck? Change granularity\n  if len(set(lastFocuses)) <= 1:\n    return { strategy: \"change_granularity\", dimension: lastFocuses[0] }\n\n  // Required protocol plateau?\n  if hasRequiredProtocolPlateau(state.traceabilityChecks):\n    return { strategy: \"protocol_first_replay\" }\n\n  // Default: escalate severity\n  return { strategy: \"escalate_severity_review\" }\n```\n\n**Recovery evaluation**:\n- If recovery iteration finds any new P0/P1 or materially advances required traceability coverage: recovery successful. Reset stuck count. Continue.\n- If recovery iteration finds only P2 or nothing: recovery failed. If all dimensions are already covered, exit to synthesis. Otherwise, move to the next unreviewed dimension.\n\n---\n\n## 4. PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n\n### Purpose\n\nCompile all iteration findings into the final `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md`. The synthesis phase owns the canonical review report output.\n\n### Steps\n\n#### Step 1: Finding Registry Deduplication\n\nConsolidate findings across all iterations:\n\n1. Read all iteration files: `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n2. Group findings by file + line range + root cause\n3. Merge duplicates, keeping the highest severity and all evidence\n4. Assign final finding IDs: `F001`, `F002`, ...\n5. Preserve the audit trail: note which iterations contributed to each merged finding\n\n#### Step 2: Severity Reconciliation\n\nUse adjudicated `finalSeverity` for any P0/P1 that was downgraded during claim adjudication (Step 4a of the iteration loop). The original severity from the iteration file is preserved in the audit appendix.\n\n#### Step 3: Replay Validation\n\nRecompute the convergence outcome from JSONL state before finalizing the report:\n\n1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` and select review-mode iteration records in run order\n2. Recompute `newFindingsRatio`, rolling-average votes, MAD votes, and coverage votes from stored JSONL fields only\n3. Recompute `traceabilityChecks.summary` and confirm required protocol statuses match the recorded coverage vote\n4. Re-run the evidence, scope, and coverage gates against stored findings and scope data\n5. Compare the replayed decision and stop reason to the recorded synthesis event\n\nThis synthesis-stage replay is a **full-history audit replay** over the stored JSONL state. It follows the same full-history replay discipline as the per-iteration reducer refresh above, but runs as an explicit pre-synthesis audit.\n\nReplay passes only when the recomputed decision, thresholds, and gate outcomes agree with the persisted result. If replay fails, log a warning in the audit appendix but proceed with synthesis.\n\n#### Step 4: Compile review-report.md\n\nGenerate the 9 core review-report sections (defined in `review_mode_contract.yaml` under `outputs.reviewReport`) and insert `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` between `Traceability Status` and `Deferred Items` when `config.resource_map_present == true`:\n\n| # | Section | Purpose |\n|---|---------|---------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` metadata |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduplicated active findings with evidence and final severity |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n| 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `config.resource_map_present == true`, reports touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n| 9 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n| 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, convergence evidence |\n\n#### Step 5: Verdict Determination\n\nApply the verdict contract from `review_mode_contract.yaml`:\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Next Command |\n|---------|-----------|--------------|\n| **FAIL** | Active P0 remains OR any required binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | No active P0, but active P1 remains | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n| **PASS** | No active P0/P1 | `/create:changelog` |\n\nWhen `PASS` verdict is issued and active P2 findings remain, set `hasAdvisories = true` in the report metadata.\n\n#### Step 6: Finalize State\n\n1. Update config status: Set `status: \"complete\"` in `deep-review-config.json`\n2. Write final JSONL entry:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"type\": \"event\",\n     \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\",\n     \"mode\": \"review\",\n     \"totalIterations\": N,\n     \"verdict\": \"PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL\",\n     \"activeP0\": N,\n     \"activeP1\": N,\n     \"activeP2\": N,\n     \"dimensionCoverage\": X,\n     \"stopReason\": \"...\",\n     \"timestamp\": \"...\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## 5. PHASE 4: SAVE\n\n### Purpose\n\nPreserve review context to the memory system for future session recovery and cross-session continuity.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Compose context payload**: Create a structured JSON payload with the review summary, active findings, verdict, next action, and relevant artifacts. Use `specFolder` for the target packet and include curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` when available.\n\n2. **Generate context**: Run the memory save script with structured JSON via `--stdin`, `--json`, or a session-scoped JSON file:\n   ```bash\n   node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --json '{\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"sessionSummary\":\"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict and findings.\"}' {spec_folder}\n   ```\n\n3. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow.\n\n4. **Verify**: Confirm the routed canonical spec document carries the review continuity update. Expected targets are `implementation-summary.md`, `decision-record.md`, or `handover.md`; standalone `memory/*.md` files are retired and should not be created.\n\n### On Save Failure\n\nIf memory save fails:\n- Preserve the current `review/` packet as backup (the disk state is the ground truth)\n- Log the error\n- The review results remain intact in `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md` regardless of memory save status\n\n---\n\n## 6. AUTO-RESUME PROTOCOL\n\n### Purpose\n\nEnable review sessions to resume cleanly from prior state when interrupted by context compaction, process termination, or intentional pause.\n\n### Resume Detection\n\nIf state files already exist from a prior session:\n\n1. **Verify agreement**: Confirm config, JSONL, findings registry, and strategy all exist and agree on target/spec folder\n2. **Count progress**: Read JSONL, count iteration records, determine last completed iteration\n3. **Read strategy**: Load current dimension progress, findings, and next focus from `deep-review-strategy.md`\n4. **Set counter**: Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n5. **Log resume**: Append the canonical resume event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The reducer requires every field below:\n   ```json\n   {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-24T14:05:00Z\"}\n   ```\n6. **Continue**: Enter the iteration loop from step_read_state\n\n### Lifecycle Branches (current release)\n\nThe runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures. Until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n\n| Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n|------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n| `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n| `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n| `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `review/` tree moved under `review_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus non-null `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n\n**Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n  \"generation\": <number>,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n  \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n}\n```\n\nEvery field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n\n### State Validation on Resume\n\n| Condition | Classification | Action |\n|-----------|---------------|--------|\n| Config + JSONL + strategy all exist and agree | `resume` | Continue from last iteration + 1 |\n| All exist, config says `status: \"complete\"` | `completed-session` | Report completion, ask user if re-review desired |\n| Partial files or contradictions | `invalid-state` | Halt for repair, do not guess |\n| No files exist | `fresh` | Start new initialization |\n\n### State Recovery Cascade\n\nWhen state files are missing or corrupted, apply this priority cascade:\n\n| Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n|----------|-----------|----------------|\n| 1 | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation |\n| 2 | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract dimensions, findings, coverage |\n| 3 | JSONL missing, iteration files exist | Scan `review/iterations/iteration-*.md`, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n| 4 | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase |\n| 5 | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n\nEach priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next.\n\n---\n\n## 7. PAUSE/RESUME\n\n### Pause Sentinel Behavior\n\nThe pause sentinel provides graceful loop suspension in autonomous mode without killing the process.\n\n### Creating a Pause\n\nCreate the sentinel file at any time:\n\n```bash\ntouch {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n```\n\nThe orchestrator checks for this file between iterations (Step 2a). When detected:\n- The current iteration is allowed to complete\n- The loop halts before dispatching the next iteration\n- A paused event is logged to JSONL\n- The user is notified with current state (iteration count, dimensions covered, findings)\n\n### Resuming After Pause\n\nDelete the sentinel file and restart the workflow:\n\n```bash\nrm {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n```\n\nOn the next invocation:\n- The auto-resume protocol (Section 6) detects the existing state\n- A resumed event is logged to JSONL\n- The loop continues from the next iteration\n\n### Confirm Mode Approval Gates\n\nIn confirm mode (`deep_review_confirm.yaml`), the workflow adds explicit approval gates instead of relying on the pause sentinel:\n\n| Gate Location | Behavior |\n|---------------|----------|\n| After initialization | Show config, strategy, and scope. Wait for approval |\n| After each iteration | Show iteration findings, dashboard, and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n| Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n| After synthesis | Show final review-report.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n\n---\n\n## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS, ERROR HANDLING, AND QUALITY GATES\n\nState-transition rules, error handling, and the review quality gates live in `loop_state_and_gates.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## 11. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n### Shared Protocol Documentation\n\nProtocol documents from `deep-research` are cross-referenced, not duplicated:\n\n| Document | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Loop Protocol (research) | `../deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` | Research loop lifecycle (this file adapts Section 9) |\n| State Format | `../deep-research/references/state/state_format.md` | JSONL, strategy, and config schemas |\n| Convergence | `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` | `shouldContinue_review()` (Section 10), stuck recovery, quality guards |\n\n### Review-Specific Resources\n\n| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review Contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Single source of truth for dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Quick Reference | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | One-page review cheat sheet |\n| Strategy Template | `assets/deep_review_strategy.md` | Template for review strategy files |\n| Config Template | `assets/deep_review_config.json` | Template for review config files |\n| Dashboard Template | `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md` | Template for auto-generated dashboard |\n\n### Workflow Files\n\n| Mode | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Auto (unattended) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm (step-by-step) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` |\n\n### Agent\n\n| Agent | Path Pattern | Constraint |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| `@deep-review` | `{runtime_dir}/deep-review.{ext}` | LEAF-only, no sub-agents, no WebFetch, target files read-only |\n\nRuntime paths:\n- OpenCode / Copilot: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md`\n- Claude: `.claude/agents/deep-review.md`\n\n---\n\n## Executor Selection Contract\n\nExecutor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta.\n\n### Invariants\n\nEvery executor path MUST satisfy:\n\n1. Produce an iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}` (non-empty).\n2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops. Max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n\n### Failure Modes\n\n- Missing iteration file: `iteration_file_missing` from `post-dispatch-validate.ts`, emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event.\n- Empty iteration file: `iteration_file_empty`, same downstream.\n- JSONL not appended: `jsonl_not_appended`.\n- JSONL missing required fields: `jsonl_missing_fields`.\n- JSONL malformed: `jsonl_parse_error`.\n- 3 consecutive failures: existing `stuck_recovery` event (unchanged).\n\n### JSONL Audit Field\n\nNon-native executor runs append an `executor` block with model and runtime settings to the iteration's JSONL record via `executor-audit.ts`. Native runs are recoverable from YAML alone.\n\n### Template And Config Surface\n\nThe executor-agnostic iteration prompt lives at `assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`, rendered by `prompt-pack.ts` before dispatch and either injected as the agent's context (native) or piped to `opencode run` stdin (cli-opencode). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `runtime//lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\n\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\n\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\n\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\n\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":765,"totalLines":765,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1783915534024,"end":1783915534030}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f7bdebefd030b5016a54640de950819180286e79ab386fd4"}},"id":"prt_f59a6d6c20013oxaw5T3uiYwty","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915534072,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6CFHpI6Ll5ANZ4zdmf08Q4OT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","offset":1,"limit":1800},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review State Format\n3: description: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state format\"\n6:   - \"deep review config schema\"\n7:   - \"review severity weights\"\n8:   - \"file protection levels\"\n9:   - \"review iteration file structure\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.11.0.28\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review State Format\n16: \n17: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: The deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n24: \n25: | File | Format | Mutability |\n26: |------|--------|------------|\n27: | `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n28: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n29: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n30: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n31: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n32: | `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n33: | `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n34: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n35: \n36: ```text\n37: {artifact_dir}/\n38:   deep-review-config.json\n39:   deep-review-state.jsonl\n40:   deep-review-findings-registry.json\n41:   deep-review-strategy.md\n42:   deep-review-dashboard.md\n43:   .deep-review-pause\n44:   review-report.md\n45:   iterations/\n46:     iteration-001.md\n47:     iteration-002.md\n48:     ...\n49: ```\n50: \n51: `{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n52: \n53: Example (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../006-continuity-refactor-gates/003-gate-c-writer-ready/` → `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/` (flat, no subfolder).\n54: \n55: Example (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/003-gate-c-writer-ready-pt-02/` (`pt-NN` allocated as a sibling to the prior content; subfolder name is `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`).\n56: \n57: ### When to Use\n58: \n59: - Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n60: - Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n61: - Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n62: - Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n67: \n68: Created during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n69: \n70: ```json\n71: {\n72:   \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n73:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n74:   \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n75:   \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n76:   \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n77:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n78:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n79:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n80:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n81:   \"generation\": 1,\n82:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n83:   \"maxIterations\": 7,\n84:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n85:   \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n86:   \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n87:   \"crossReference\": {\n88:     \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n89:     \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n90:   },\n91:   \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n92:   \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n93:   \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n94:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n95:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n96:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n97:   \"fileProtection\": {\n98:     \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n99:     \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n100:     \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n101:     \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n102:     \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n103:     \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n104:     \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n105:     \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n106:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n107:   },\n108:   \"reducer\": {\n109:     \"enabled\": true,\n110:     \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n111:     \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n112:     \"metrics\": [\n113:       \"dimensionsCovered\",\n114:       \"findingsBySeverity\",\n115:       \"openFindings\",\n116:       \"resolvedFindings\",\n117:       \"convergenceScore\"\n118:     ]\n119:   }\n120: }\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ### Field Reference\n124: \n125: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n126: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n127: | mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n128: | reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n129: | reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n130: | reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n131: | resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n132: | sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n133: | parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n134: | lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n135: | generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n136: | continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n137: | maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n138: | convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n139: | stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n140: | severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n141: | crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n142: | qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n143: | specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n144: | status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n145: | releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n146: | fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n147: | reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n148: \n149: ### File Protection Levels\n150: \n151: | Level | Meaning |\n152: |-------|---------|\n153: | immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n154: | append-only | New content added at end only |\n155: | mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n156: | write-once | Created once, never modified |\n157: | auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n158: | operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n159: \n160: ### Review Dimensions\n161: \n162: | Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n163: |-----------|----------|---------------------|\n164: | correctness | 1 | Yes |\n165: | security | 2 | Yes |\n166: | traceability | 3 | Yes |\n167: | maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n168: \n169: ### Severity Weights\n170: \n171: | Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n172: |----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n173: | P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n174: | P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n175: | P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ## 3. STATE LOG\n180: \n181: The `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n186: \n187: Updated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n188: \n189: ### Required Sections\n190: \n191: | Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n192: |---------|-----------|---------|\n193: | topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n194: | review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n195: | completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n196: | running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n197: | what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n198: | what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n199: | exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n200: | ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n201: | next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n202: | known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n203: | cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n204: | files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n205: | review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n206: \n207: ### Mapping from Research Mode\n208: \n209: | Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n210: |---------------|-------------------|\n211: | review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n212: | completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n213: | running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n214: | cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n215: | files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n216: | review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n217: \n218: Sections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n219: \n220: ### Update Protocol\n221: \n222: 1. Read current strategy file\n223: 2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n224: 3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n225: 4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n226: 5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n227: 6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n232: \n233: Reducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n234: \n235: ```json\n236: {\n237:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n238:   \"generation\": 1,\n239:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n240:   \"openFindings\": [],\n241:   \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n242:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n243:   \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n244:   \"severityChanged\": [],\n245:   \"repeatedFindings\": [],\n246:   \"dimensionCoverage\": {\n247:     \"correctness\": true,\n248:     \"security\": true,\n249:     \"traceability\": false,\n250:     \"maintainability\": false\n251:   },\n252:   \"findingsBySeverity\": {\n253:     \"P0\": 0,\n254:     \"P1\": 1,\n255:     \"P2\": 2\n256:   },\n257:   \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n258:   \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n259:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n260:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n261:   \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n262:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n263:   \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n264: }\n265: ```\n266: \n267: This file is machine-owned and must stay synchronized with the latest iteration delta, dashboard metrics, and synthesized review report.\n268: \n269: ### Blocked-Stop and Corruption-Tracking Additions\n270: \n271: | Field | Type | Description |\n272: |-------|------|-------------|\n273: | `blockedStopHistory` | array | One entry per `blocked_stop` JSONL event: `{run, blockedBy, gateResults, recoveryStrategy, timestamp}`. Rendered in the dashboard `BLOCKED STOPS` section and can drive the strategy `next-focus` anchor when blocked-stop is the most recent loop event. |\n274: | `persistentSameSeverity` | array | Findings observed in ≥2 iterations with NO severity transitions beyond initial discovery. REQ-018 split of the deprecated `repeatedFindings` bucket. |\n275: | `severityChanged` | array | Findings that went through at least one severity transition (P0↔P1↔P2) in their `transitions` history. |\n276: | `repeatedFindings` | array | **Deprecated.** Union of `persistentSameSeverity` and `severityChanged`. Retained for backward compatibility, new code should read the split arrays. |\n277: | `corruptionWarnings` | array | Per-line corruption reports from `parseJsonlDetailed()`: `{line, raw, error}`. Non-empty means the reducer detected malformed JSONL. |\n278: \n279: ### Default Values\n280: \n281: When no `graph_convergence` event has been recorded yet, defaults are `graphConvergenceScore: 0`, `graphDecision: null`, and `graphBlockers: []`.\n282: When no `blocked_stop` event has been recorded yet, `blockedStopHistory: []`.\n283: When JSONL parses cleanly, `corruptionWarnings: []`.\n284: \n285: ### Fail-Closed Semantics (REQ-015, REQ-016)\n286: \n287: - **Malformed JSONL**: The reducer CLI exits with code `2` and writes a warning to stderr when `corruptionWarnings.length > 0`. Pass `--lenient` (or `lenient:true` to `reduceReviewState`) to escape-hatch out and preserve the v1.2.0.0 fail-open behavior for legacy packets.\n288: - **Missing machine-owned anchors**: `replaceAnchorSection()` throws `Error('Missing machine-owned anchor \"<id>\" in deep-review strategy file.')` when the strategy file is present but lacks one of the required anchors. Pass `--create-missing-anchors` (or `createMissingAnchors:true`) to bootstrap empty strategy files by appending the missing anchor blocks.\n289: - **Dashboard surfaces**: `CORRUPTION WARNINGS` section lists detected lines. `BLOCKED STOPS` section lists `blockedStopHistory` entries. `GRAPH CONVERGENCE` section reports `graphConvergenceScore` / `graphDecision` / `graphBlockers`.\n290: - **Strategy next-focus override**: When the latest `blocked_stop` event timestamp is newer than the latest iteration timestamp, the reducer rewrites the strategy `next-focus` anchor to surface the blocking gates and recovery hint so operators see the blocker before choosing the next iteration direction.\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## 6. ITERATION FILES (review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md)\n295: \n296: Write-once files. One per iteration, zero-padded 3-digit naming.\n297: \n298: ### Structure\n299: \n300: ```markdown\n301: # Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n302: \n303: ## Focus\n304: [Dimension(s), files, scope investigated]\n305: \n306: ## Scorecard\n307: - Dimensions covered: [list]\n308: - Files reviewed: [count]\n309: - New findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n310: - Refined findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n311: - New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n312: \n313: ## Findings\n314: \n315: ### P0, Blocker\n316: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n317: \n318: ### P1, Required\n319: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n320: \n321: ### P2, Suggestion\n322: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n323: \n324: ## Cross-Reference Results\n325: | Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n326: |----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n327: | spec_code | pass/partial/fail | hard | file:line | ... |\n328: \n329: ## Assessment\n330: - New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n331: - Dimensions addressed: [list]\n332: - Novelty justification: [breakdown]\n333: \n334: ## Ruled Out\n335: - [Approach]: [Why], [Evidence]\n336: \n337: ## Dead Ends\n338: - [Direction]: [Why]\n339: \n340: ## Recommended Next Focus\n341: [What to investigate next]\n342: ```\n343: \n344: Every finding must include: unique ID (`F001`...), severity (`P0`/`P1`/`P2`), concrete `file:line` evidence, and dimension tag.\n345: \n346: ---\n347: \n348: ## 7. REVIEW REPORT (review/review-report.md)\n349: \n350: The review synthesis output contains 9 core sections plus a conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present` is true:\n351: \n352: | # | Section | Description |\n353: |---|---------|-------------|\n354: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` flag |\n355: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why result routes to planning or changelog |\n356: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence, severity, dimension |\n357: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Ordered lanes grouped by dependency or area |\n358: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec updates implied by findings |\n359: | 6 | Plan Seed | Initial remediation tasks from findings |\n360: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol outcomes and gaps |\n361: | 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` existed at init, contains touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n362: | 9 | Deferred Items | Advisory findings, blocked items, follow-up checks |\n363: | 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, convergence replay, audit detail |\n364: \n365: **Executive Summary** includes verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`), active finding counts, `hasAdvisories` boolean (PASS + P2 > 0), scope description, and convergence reason.\n366: \n367: **Planning Trigger** routes FAIL/CONDITIONAL to remediation planning, PASS to changelog creation.\n368: \n369: **Active Finding Registry** lists each active finding with findingId, severity, dimension, title, file:line evidence, first/last seen iteration, and status.\n370: \n371: **Remediation Workstreams** group related findings into ordered lanes with constituent finding IDs and execution order.\n372: \n373: **Spec Seed / Plan Seed** provide minimal spec updates and initial remediation tasks referencing finding IDs and target files.\n374: \n375: **Traceability Status** reports per-protocol pass/partial/fail with gating class and evidence.\n376: \n377: **Resource Map Coverage Gate** is emitted only when `resource_map_present` is true and MUST contain exactly three bullets: touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n378: \n379: **Deferred Items** captures advisory findings, blocked protocols, and future follow-up checks.\n380: \n381: **Audit Appendix** contains iteration table, convergence signal replay, file coverage matrix, and dimension breakdown.\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## 8. DASHBOARD (review/deep-review-dashboard.md)\n386: \n387: Auto-generated summary. Never manually edited.\n388: \n389: - **Path**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n390: - **Generated from**: JSONL state log + strategy + findings registry\n391: - **Refresh**: Regenerated after every iteration\n392: - **Protection**: `auto-generated` in fileProtection\n393: \n394: ### Sections\n395: \n396: | Section | Source | Description |\n397: |---------|--------|-------------|\n398: | Findings Summary | JSONL | Active P0/P1/P2 counts, new vs refined |\n399: | Progress Table | JSONL | Run, status, focus, dimensions, ratio, duration |\n400: | Coverage | Strategy + JSONL | Dimension completion, file coverage, protocol status |\n401: | Trend | JSONL signals | Rolling average, composite stop score, trajectory |\n402: \n403: **Rules:** Sole inputs are JSONL + strategy. Overwrite entirely on refresh. Read-only for all agents.\n404: \n405: ---\n406: \n407: ## 9. CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n408: \n409: Every new P0/P1 finding must carry a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. The packet is parsed by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` in the review workflow and its pass/fail result is persisted as a `claim_adjudication` event in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree reads the latest event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`), a missing or failed packet vetoes STOP even if every other gate passes. Prose-only adjudication blocks are no longer accepted.\n410: \n411: ### Typed Packet Schema (required)\n412: \n413: Embed the packet inside the iteration file for each new P0/P1 finding. The orchestrator parses it after evaluation and persists the validation result.\n414: \n415: ```json\n416: {\n417:   \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n418:   \"claim\": \"Coverage-graph upsert identity is bare `id`, so cross-session collisions overwrite prior rows.\",\n419:   \"evidenceRefs\": [\n420:     \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154\",\n421:     \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302\"\n422:   ],\n423:   \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Grepped the module for compound-key upserts, checked migration scripts, and inspected session-isolation.vitest.ts for a collision regression, none found.\",\n424:   \"alternativeExplanation\": \"Could be intentional single-tenant design, but REQ-024 explicitly requires session isolation, so this is rejected.\",\n425:   \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n426:   \"confidence\": 0.86,\n427:   \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If a composite primary key `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` lands and a collision regression covers the ID-reuse path, downgrade to P2 tech-debt.\",\n428:   \"transitions\": [\n429:     { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" }\n430:   ]\n431: }\n432: ```\n433: \n434: ### Required Fields\n435: \n436: | Field | Type | Description |\n437: |-------|------|-------------|\n438: | `findingId` | string | Must match the finding ID in the iteration body and registry |\n439: | `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes (one sentence, evidence-backed) |\n440: | `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations that substantiate the claim (at least one entry) |\n441: | `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the reviewer looked for contradicting evidence (commands, paths, docs), blank string is not acceptable |\n442: | `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative reading of the evidence, even if the reviewer rejects it |\n443: | `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication (may differ from the severity originally asserted) |\n444: | `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Reviewer confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n445: | `downgradeTrigger` | string | The concrete condition under which this finding should be downgraded in a future iteration |\n446: | `transitions` | object[] | Optional severity transition log, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n447: \n448: ### Validation Rules (enforced by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication`)\n449: \n450: 1. A packet MUST exist for every new P0/P1 finding introduced in this iteration. Carried-forward findings reuse the previous packet unless severity transitioned.\n451: 2. All required fields MUST be present and non-empty. `confidence` MUST be a number in `[0, 1]`.\n452: 3. Each `evidenceRefs` entry MUST contain a `:` separating the path from a line or range.\n453: 4. `finalSeverity` MUST match the severity the finding is registered under in the iteration's `Findings` section and in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`.\n454: 5. When any rule fails, the workflow appends `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` to the state log. The next `step_check_convergence` call reads that event and sets `claimAdjudicationGate` = `false`, producing a `blockedStop` event with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet.\n455: \n456: ### Severity Transition Rules\n457: \n458: - **P2 → P1**: confirmed exploitable impact or spec violation with direct evidence\n459: - **P1 → P0**: demonstrated data loss, security breach, or hard-gate failure\n460: - **Downgrade**: requires explicit counterevidence or a confirmed alternative explanation\n461: - Every transition is recorded in the packet's `transitions` array and mirrored into the finding registry's `transitions` field\n462: \n463: ---\n464: \n465: ## 10. FINDING REGISTRY\n466: \n467: Each finding is tracked with a unique identifier enabling deduplication, severity transitions, and status lifecycle.\n468: \n469: ### Schema\n470: \n471: ```json\n472: {\n473:   \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n474:   \"severity\": \"P1\",\n475:   \"category\": \"resource-map-coverage\",\n476:   \"status\": \"active\",\n477:   \"dimension\": \"traceability\",\n478:   \"title\": \"Applied target file missing from resource-map inventory\",\n479:   \"file\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\",\n480:   \"line\": 955,\n481:   \"firstSeen\": 2,\n482:   \"lastSeen\": 4,\n483:   \"transitions\": [\n484:     { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" },\n485:     { \"iteration\": 4, \"from\": \"P2\", \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Confirmed real coverage gap against applied target inventory\" }\n486:   ]\n487: }\n488: ```\n489: \n490: | Field | Type | Description |\n491: |-------|------|-------------|\n492: | findingId | string | Sequential unique ID: `F001`, `F002`, ... |\n493: | severity | `\"P0\"` / `\"P1\"` / `\"P2\"` | Current severity |\n494: | category | `\"correctness\"` / `\"security\"` / `\"traceability\"` / `\"maintainability\"` / `\"resource-map-coverage\"` | Primary audit category for the finding, `resource-map-coverage` is reserved for implementation-vs-map coverage gaps |\n495: | status | `\"active\"` / `\"resolved\"` / `\"deferred\"` / `\"disproved\"` | Current status |\n496: | dimension | string | Primary dimension: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability |\n497: | title | string | Short description |\n498: | file | string | File path |\n499: | line | number | Line number (approximate) |\n500: | firstSeen / lastSeen | number | Iteration where first discovered / last referenced |\n501: | transitions | array | Severity and status change history |\n502: \n503: ### Status Lifecycle\n504: \n505: ```text\n506: [discovered] --> active --> resolved    (fixed or confirmed non-issue)\n507:                   |\n508:                   +--> deferred    (advisory, below threshold)\n509:                   |\n510:                   +--> disproved   (counterevidence invalidated)\n511: ```\n512: \n513: | Status | Counts Toward Verdict |\n514: |--------|----------------------|\n515: | active | Yes |\n516: | resolved | No |\n517: | deferred | No (listed in Deferred Items) |\n518: | disproved | No |\n519: \n520: ### Deduplication\n521: \n522: Same file + line range + root cause as an existing finding = **refinement**, not new. The existing findingId is updated. Refinements count at half weight (`refinementMultiplier: 0.5`) and are tracked via `findingsRefined` in JSONL.\n523: \n524: ### Cross-Reference Protocols\n525: \n526: | Protocol | Level | Applies To | Gate |\n527: |----------|-------|------------|------|\n528: | spec_code | core | all types | hard |\n529: | checklist_evidence | core | all types | hard |\n530: | skill_agent | overlay | skill | advisory |\n531: | agent_cross_runtime | overlay | agent | advisory |\n532: | feature_catalog_code | overlay | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory |\n533: | playbook_capability | overlay | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory |\n534: \n535: Severity for `resource-map-coverage` findings is calibrated to the coverage-gate outcome:\n536: - `P2` when an untouched map entry is explicitly `expected-by-scope`\n537: - `P1` when an untouched or absent path represents a real coverage gap\n538: - `P0` only when the missing coverage masks a release-blocking correctness or security risk\n539: \n540: ### Quality Gates\n541: \n542: | Gate | Rule |\n543: |------|------|\n544: | Evidence | Every active finding backed by concrete file:line evidence |\n545: | Scope | Reviewed files and conclusions stay inside declared scope |\n546: | Coverage | Required dimensions and required protocols covered |\n547: \n548: All three gates must pass before STOP. Gate failure forces `verdict: \"FAIL\"` regardless of finding counts.\n\n(End of file - total 548 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state format\"\n  - \"deep review config schema\"\n  - \"review severity weights\"\n  - \"file protection levels\"\n  - \"review iteration file structure\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.28\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state format\"\n  - \"deep review config schema\"\n  - \"review severity weights\"\n  - \"file protection levels\"\n  - \"review iteration file structure\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.28\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n\n| File | Format | Mutability |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n| `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n| `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n\n```text\n{artifact_dir}/\n  deep-review-config.json\n  deep-review-state.jsonl\n  deep-review-findings-registry.json\n  deep-review-strategy.md\n  deep-review-dashboard.md\n  .deep-review-pause\n  review-report.md\n  iterations/\n    iteration-001.md\n    iteration-002.md\n    ...\n```\n\n`{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\nExample (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../006-continuity-refactor-gates/003-gate-c-writer-ready/` → `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/` (flat, no subfolder).\n\nExample (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/003-gate-c-writer-ready-pt-02/` (`pt-NN` allocated as a sibling to the prior content; subfolder name is `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`).\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n- Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n- Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n- Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n\nCreated during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n  \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n  \"crossReference\": {\n    \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n    \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n  },\n  \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n    \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n    \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n    \"metrics\": [\n      \"dimensionsCovered\",\n      \"findingsBySeverity\",\n      \"openFindings\",\n      \"resolvedFindings\",\n      \"convergenceScore\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Field Reference\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n| reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n| reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n| reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n| resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n| sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n| parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n| lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n| generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n| continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n| maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n| convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n| stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n| crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n| qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n| specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n| status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n| releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n| fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n| reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n\n### File Protection Levels\n\n| Level | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n| append-only | New content added at end only |\n| mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n| write-once | Created once, never modified |\n| auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n| operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\n| Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|---------------------|\n| correctness | 1 | Yes |\n| security | 2 | Yes |\n| traceability | 3 | Yes |\n| maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n\n### Severity Weights\n\n| Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n|----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n| P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n| P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n| P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## 3. STATE LOG\n\nThe `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n\nUpdated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n\n### Required Sections\n\n| Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n|---------|-----------|---------|\n| topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n| review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n| completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n| running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n| what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n| what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n| exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n| ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n| next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n| known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n| cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n| files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n| review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n\n### Mapping from Research Mode\n\n| Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n|---------------|-------------------|\n| review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n| completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n| running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n\nSections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n\n### Update Protocol\n\n1. Read current strategy file\n2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n\nReducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"openFindings\": [],\n  \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n  \"severityChanged\": [],\n  \"repeatedFindings\": [],\n  \"dimensionCoverage\": {\n    \"correctness\": true,\n    \"security\": true,\n    \"traceability\": false,\n    \"maintainability\": false\n  },\n  \"findingsBySeverity\": {\n    \"P0\": 0,\n    \"P1\": 1,\n    \"P2\": 2\n  },\n  \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n  \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n  \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n}\n```\n\nThis file is machine-owned and must stay synchronized with the latest iteration delta, dashboard metrics, and synthesized review report.\n\n### Blocked-Stop and Corruption-Tracking Additions\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `blockedStopHistory` | array | One entry per `blocked_stop` JSONL event: `{run, blockedBy, gateResults, recoveryStrategy, timestamp}`. Rendered in the dashboard `BLOCKED STOPS` section and can drive the strategy `next-focus` anchor when blocked-stop is the most recent loop event. |\n| `persistentSameSeverity` | array | Findings observed in ≥2 iterations with NO severity transitions beyond initial discovery. REQ-018 split of the deprecated `repeatedFindings` bucket. |\n| `severityChanged` | array | Findings that went through at least one severity transition (P0↔P1↔P2) in their `transitions` history. |\n| `repeatedFindings` | array | **Deprecated.** Union of `persistentSameSeverity` and `severityChanged`. Retained for backward compatibility, new code should read the split arrays. |\n| `corruptionWarnings` | array | Per-line corruption reports from `parseJsonlDetailed()`: `{line, raw, error}`. Non-empty means the reducer detected malformed JSONL. |\n\n### Default Values\n\nWhen no `graph_convergence` event has been recorded yet, defaults are `graphConvergenceScore: 0`, `graphDecision: null`, and `graphBlockers: []`.\nWhen no `blocked_stop` event has been recorded yet, `blockedStopHistory: []`.\nWhen JSONL parses cleanly, `corruptionWarnings: []`.\n\n### Fail-Closed Semantics (REQ-015, REQ-016)\n\n- **Malformed JSONL**: The reducer CLI exits with code `2` and writes a warning to stderr when `corruptionWarnings.length > 0`. Pass `--lenient` (or `lenient:true` to `reduceReviewState`) to escape-hatch out and preserve the v1.2.0.0 fail-open behavior for legacy packets.\n- **Missing machine-owned anchors**: `replaceAnchorSection()` throws `Error('Missing machine-owned anchor \"<id>\" in deep-review strategy file.')` when the strategy file is present but lacks one of the required anchors. Pass `--create-missing-anchors` (or `createMissingAnchors:true`) to bootstrap empty strategy files by appending the missing anchor blocks.\n- **Dashboard surfaces**: `CORRUPTION WARNINGS` section lists detected lines. `BLOCKED STOPS` section lists `blockedStopHistory` entries. `GRAPH CONVERGENCE` section reports `graphConvergenceScore` / `graphDecision` / `graphBlockers`.\n- **Strategy next-focus override**: When the latest `blocked_stop` event timestamp is newer than the latest iteration timestamp, the reducer rewrites the strategy `next-focus` anchor to surface the blocking gates and recovery hint so operators see the blocker before choosing the next iteration direction.\n\n---\n\n## 6. ITERATION FILES (review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md)\n\nWrite-once files. One per iteration, zero-padded 3-digit naming.\n\n### Structure\n\n```markdown\n# Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n\n## Focus\n[Dimension(s), files, scope investigated]\n\n## Scorecard\n- Dimensions covered: [list]\n- Files reviewed: [count]\n- New findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n- Refined findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n- New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n\n## Findings\n\n### P0, Blocker\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n### P1, Required\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n### P2, Suggestion\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n## Cross-Reference Results\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n| spec_code | pass/partial/fail | hard | file:line | ... |\n\n## Assessment\n- New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n- Dimensions addressed: [list]\n- Novelty justification: [breakdown]\n\n## Ruled Out\n- [Approach]: [Why], [Evidence]\n\n## Dead Ends\n- [Direction]: [Why]\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n[What to investigate next]\n```\n\nEvery finding must include: unique ID (`F001`...), severity (`P0`/`P1`/`P2`), concrete `file:line` evidence, and dimension tag.\n\n---\n\n## 7. REVIEW REPORT (review/review-report.md)\n\nThe review synthesis output contains 9 core sections plus a conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present` is true:\n\n| # | Section | Description |\n|---|---------|-------------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` flag |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why result routes to planning or changelog |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence, severity, dimension |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Ordered lanes grouped by dependency or area |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec updates implied by findings |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Initial remediation tasks from findings |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol outcomes and gaps |\n| 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` existed at init, contains touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n| 9 | Deferred Items | Advisory findings, blocked items, follow-up checks |\n| 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, convergence replay, audit detail |\n\n**Executive Summary** includes verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`), active finding counts, `hasAdvisories` boolean (PASS + P2 > 0), scope description, and convergence reason.\n\n**Planning Trigger** routes FAIL/CONDITIONAL to remediation planning, PASS to changelog creation.\n\n**Active Finding Registry** lists each active finding with findingId, severity, dimension, title, file:line evidence, first/last seen iteration, and status.\n\n**Remediation Workstreams** group related findings into ordered lanes with constituent finding IDs and execution order.\n\n**Spec Seed / Plan Seed** provide minimal spec updates and initial remediation tasks referencing finding IDs and target files.\n\n**Traceability Status** reports per-protocol pass/partial/fail with gating class and evidence.\n\n**Resource Map Coverage Gate** is emitted only when `resource_map_present` is true and MUST contain exactly three bullets: touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n\n**Deferred Items** captures advisory findings, blocked protocols, and future follow-up checks.\n\n**Audit Appendix** contains iteration table, convergence signal replay, file coverage matrix, and dimension breakdown.\n\n---\n\n## 8. DASHBOARD (review/deep-review-dashboard.md)\n\nAuto-generated summary. Never manually edited.\n\n- **Path**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated from**: JSONL state log + strategy + findings registry\n- **Refresh**: Regenerated after every iteration\n- **Protection**: `auto-generated` in fileProtection\n\n### Sections\n\n| Section | Source | Description |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| Findings Summary | JSONL | Active P0/P1/P2 counts, new vs refined |\n| Progress Table | JSONL | Run, status, focus, dimensions, ratio, duration |\n| Coverage | Strategy + JSONL | Dimension completion, file coverage, protocol status |\n| Trend | JSONL signals | Rolling average, composite stop score, trajectory |\n\n**Rules:** Sole inputs are JSONL + strategy. Overwrite entirely on refresh. Read-only for all agents.\n\n---\n\n## 9. CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n\nEvery new P0/P1 finding must carry a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. The packet is parsed by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` in the review workflow and its pass/fail result is persisted as a `claim_adjudication` event in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree reads the latest event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`), a missing or failed packet vetoes STOP even if every other gate passes. Prose-only adjudication blocks are no longer accepted.\n\n### Typed Packet Schema (required)\n\nEmbed the packet inside the iteration file for each new P0/P1 finding. The orchestrator parses it after evaluation and persists the validation result.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n  \"claim\": \"Coverage-graph upsert identity is bare `id`, so cross-session collisions overwrite prior rows.\",\n  \"evidenceRefs\": [\n    \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154\",\n    \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302\"\n  ],\n  \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Grepped the module for compound-key upserts, checked migration scripts, and inspected session-isolation.vitest.ts for a collision regression, none found.\",\n  \"alternativeExplanation\": \"Could be intentional single-tenant design, but REQ-024 explicitly requires session isolation, so this is rejected.\",\n  \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.86,\n  \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If a composite primary key `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` lands and a collision regression covers the ID-reuse path, downgrade to P2 tech-debt.\",\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Required Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `findingId` | string | Must match the finding ID in the iteration body and registry |\n| `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes (one sentence, evidence-backed) |\n| `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations that substantiate the claim (at least one entry) |\n| `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the reviewer looked for contradicting evidence (commands, paths, docs), blank string is not acceptable |\n| `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative reading of the evidence, even if the reviewer rejects it |\n| `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication (may differ from the severity originally asserted) |\n| `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Reviewer confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n| `downgradeTrigger` | string | The concrete condition under which this finding should be downgraded in a future iteration |\n| `transitions` | object[] | Optional severity transition log, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n\n### Validation Rules (enforced by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication`)\n\n1. A packet MUST exist for every new P0/P1 finding introduced in this iteration. Carried-forward findings reuse the previous packet unless severity transitioned.\n2. All required fields MUST be present and non-empty. `confidence` MUST be a number in `[0, 1]`.\n3. Each `evidenceRefs` entry MUST contain a `:` separating the path from a line or range.\n4. `finalSeverity` MUST match the severity the finding is registered under in the iteration's `Findings` section and in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`.\n5. When any rule fails, the workflow appends `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` to the state log. The next `step_check_convergence` call reads that event and sets `claimAdjudicationGate` = `false`, producing a `blockedStop` event with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet.\n\n### Severity Transition Rules\n\n- **P2 → P1**: confirmed exploitable impact or spec violation with direct evidence\n- **P1 → P0**: demonstrated data loss, security breach, or hard-gate failure\n- **Downgrade**: requires explicit counterevidence or a confirmed alternative explanation\n- Every transition is recorded in the packet's `transitions` array and mirrored into the finding registry's `transitions` field\n\n---\n\n## 10. FINDING REGISTRY\n\nEach finding is tracked with a unique identifier enabling deduplication, severity transitions, and status lifecycle.\n\n### Schema\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n  \"severity\": \"P1\",\n  \"category\": \"resource-map-coverage\",\n  \"status\": \"active\",\n  \"dimension\": \"traceability\",\n  \"title\": \"Applied target file missing from resource-map inventory\",\n  \"file\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\",\n  \"line\": 955,\n  \"firstSeen\": 2,\n  \"lastSeen\": 4,\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" },\n    { \"iteration\": 4, \"from\": \"P2\", \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Confirmed real coverage gap against applied target inventory\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| findingId | string | Sequential unique ID: `F001`, `F002`, ... |\n| severity | `\"P0\"` / `\"P1\"` / `\"P2\"` | Current severity |\n| category | `\"correctness\"` / `\"security\"` / `\"traceability\"` / `\"maintainability\"` / `\"resource-map-coverage\"` | Primary audit category for the finding, `resource-map-coverage` is reserved for implementation-vs-map coverage gaps |\n| status | `\"active\"` / `\"resolved\"` / `\"deferred\"` / `\"disproved\"` | Current status |\n| dimension | string | Primary dimension: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability |\n| title | string | Short description |\n| file | string | File path |\n| line | number | Line number (approximate) |\n| firstSeen / lastSeen | number | Iteration where first discovered / last referenced |\n| transitions | array | Severity and status change history |\n\n### Status Lifecycle\n\n```text\n[discovered] --> active --> resolved    (fixed or confirmed non-issue)\n                  |\n                  +--> deferred    (advisory, below threshold)\n                  |\n                  +--> disproved   (counterevidence invalidated)\n```\n\n| Status | Counts Toward Verdict |\n|--------|----------------------|\n| active | Yes |\n| resolved | No |\n| deferred | No (listed in Deferred Items) |\n| disproved | No |\n\n### Deduplication\n\nSame file + line range + root cause as an existing finding = **refinement**, not new. The existing findingId is updated. Refinements count at half weight (`refinementMultiplier: 0.5`) and are tracked via `findingsRefined` in JSONL.\n\n### Cross-Reference Protocols\n\n| Protocol | Level | Applies To | Gate |\n|----------|-------|------------|------|\n| spec_code | core | all types | hard |\n| checklist_evidence | core | all types | hard |\n| skill_agent | overlay | skill | advisory |\n| agent_cross_runtime | overlay | agent | advisory |\n| feature_catalog_code | overlay | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory |\n| playbook_capability | overlay | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory |\n\nSeverity for `resource-map-coverage` findings is calibrated to the coverage-gate outcome:\n- `P2` when an untouched map entry is explicitly `expected-by-scope`\n- `P1` when an untouched or absent path represents a real coverage gap\n- `P0` only when the missing coverage masks a release-blocking correctness or security risk\n\n### Quality Gates\n\n| Gate | Rule |\n|------|------|\n| Evidence | Every active finding backed by concrete file:line evidence |\n| Scope | Reviewed files and conclusions stay inside declared scope |\n| Coverage | Required dimensions and required protocols covered |\n\nAll three gates must pass before STOP. Gate failure forces `verdict: \"FAIL\"` regardless of finding counts.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":548,"totalLines":548,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1783915534066,"end":1783915534070}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f7bdebefd030b5016a54640de9588191a88ad06d6f86e6a6"}},"id":"prt_f59a6d6e0001gj1qaAAvpKtjG2","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915534111,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BgX8jn6qZXmpATVlI6TInn9h","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","offset":1,"limit":1400},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Convergence\n3: description: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"review convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n7:   - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n8:   - \"review stuck detection\"\n9:   - \"composite convergence vote\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.11.0.22\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review Convergence\n16: \n17: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Convergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n26: \n27: | Outcome | Meaning |\n28: |---------|---------|\n29: | **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n30: | **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n31: | **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n32: \n33: Convergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n34: \n35: Release-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n36: - `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n37: - `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n38: - `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n39: \n40: When the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n41: \n42: ### When to Use\n43: \n44: - Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n45: - Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n46: - Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n47: - Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n48: \n49: ### Key Defaults\n50: \n51: | Setting | Value | Purpose |\n52: |---------|-------|---------|\n53: | `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n54: | `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n55: | `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n56: | `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n57: | `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n58: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n59: | `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n60: \n61: ### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n62: \n63: `convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n64: \n65: **Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n66: \n67: | Skill | Default | Signal |\n68: |---|---|---|\n69: | `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n70: | `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n71: | `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n72: \n73: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n74: \n75: ### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n76: \n77: > **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n78: \n79: For review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n80: \n81: | Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n82: |---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n83: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n84: | `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n85: | `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n86: \n87: When implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n88: \n89: ### Shared Stop Contract\n90: \n91: Every terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n92: \n93: ### Convergence Modes\n94: \n95: The shared convergence runtime accepts four values. Review legality, security gates, target authority, and verdict derivation remain owned by the review workflow rather than the convergence mode.\n96: \n97: | Mode | Live Behavior |\n98: |------|---------------|\n99: | `default` | Uses normal full-history convergence signals and sends a legal STOP to synthesis and verdict derivation. This is the fallback when no mode is supplied. |\n100: | `off` | Is accepted and persisted, but the shipped review YAML has no `off` decision branch; review therefore follows the same legal-stop and synthesis path as `default`. Use `stopPolicy: \"max-iterations\"` when convergence must remain telemetry-only until the iteration ceiling. |\n101: | `sliding-window` | Is accepted and persisted, but windowed graph-novelty telemetry is research-only in the shared runtime; review therefore retains its ordinary full-history signals, legal-stop gates, and synthesis path. |\n102: | `divergent` | After all review gates pass, translates the eligible `all_dimensions_clean` STOP into a read-only three-seat direction-selection pivot and continues with the selected review direction. |\n103: \n104: #### Divergent Pivot Contract\n105: \n106: Review has one eligible reason: the exact internal reason `all_dimensions_clean` with decision `STOP`. The nine legal-stop gates run before the divergent branch and remain unchanged. `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `error`, `manualStop`, and `userPaused` are explicitly excluded. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, unrecoverable error, and any blocked security or quality gate therefore never dispatch a pivot Council.\n107: \n108: Each eligible pivot runs one native, in-process Council round with exactly three distinct seats: analytical, critical, and pragmatic. It does not use an external CLI. The transaction requires all three seat returns to be parse-valid and at least two seats to materially endorse the same candidate without a high-severity blocker. Candidate sources are persisted unswept dimensions, search debt, producer-consumer gaps, negative-test gaps, and traceability gaps. Candidate generation rejects directions without in-scope evidence and directions that imply implementation, a fix, mutation, writing, or target expansion.\n109: \n110: The guarantees are absolute: divergent mode never changes the PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL mapping, never authorizes a fix, and never makes the review target writable. A successful pivot returns to the loop before `phase_synthesis`; verdict computation exists only inside `phase_synthesis`, where active P0 yields FAIL, active P1 yields CONDITIONAL, and no active P0/P1 yields PASS. A failed pivot fails closed to that existing synthesis path.\n111: \n112: Every pivot dispatches three seats, so a run that pivots has proportionally higher model cost and duration than the same run under `default`, `off`, or `sliding-window`. Pivot evidence is isolated under `<artifactRoot>/divergent/pivots/<pivotId>/council/**`, including config, append-only state, three seat artifacts, deliberation, and report. This path is distinct from ordinary planning Council artifacts under a spec packet's `ai-council/**` tree.\n113: \n114: #### stopReason Enum\n115: \n116: | `stopReason` | Meaning |\n117: |--------------|---------|\n118: | `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n119: | `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n120: | `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n121: | `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n122: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n123: | `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n124: | `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n125: \n126: #### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n127: \n128: `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n129: \n130: ```json\n131: {\n132:   \"type\": \"event\",\n133:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n134:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n135:   \"run\": 5,\n136:   \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n137:   \"gateResults\": {\n138:     \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n139:     \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n140:       \"pass\": false,\n141:       \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n142:       \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n143:     },\n144:     \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n145:     \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n146:     \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n147:     \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n148:     \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n149:     \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n150:     \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n151:   },\n152:   \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n153:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n154:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n155:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n156:   \"generation\": 1\n157: }\n158: ```\n159: \n160: - `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n161: - `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n162: - `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n163: - `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n164: - When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n165: \n166: ### Decision Priority\n167: \n168: Checks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n169: \n170: 1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n171: 2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n172: 3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n173: 4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n174: 5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n175: 6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ## 2. HARD STOPS\n180: \n181: Hard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n182: \n183: ### Max Iterations Reached\n184: \n185: ```\n186: if len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n187:   return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n188: ```\n189: \n190: The loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n191: \n192: ### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n193: \n194: ```\n195: if coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n196:   if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n197:     if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n198:       return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: Triggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n206: \n207: Identifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n208: \n209: ```\n210: function countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n211:   count = 0\n212:   for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n213:     if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n214:     if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n215:     if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n216:       count += 1\n217:     else:\n218:       break\n219:   return count\n220: ```\n221: \n222: **Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n223: \n224: **Status exclusions:**\n225: - `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n226: - `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n227: \n228: When `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n229: \n230: The recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n235: \n236: Three independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n237: \n238: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n239: |--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n240: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n241: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n242: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n243: \n244: ### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n245: \n246: Averages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n247: \n248: ```\n249: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n250:   recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n251:   avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n252:   rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n256: \n257: Robust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n258: \n259: ```\n260: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n261:   allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n262:   med = median(allRatios)\n263:   mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n264:   noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n265:   madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n269: \n270: Highest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n271: \n272: ```\n273: dimensionStop =\n274:   dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n275:   AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n276:   AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n277: ```\n278: \n279: The latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n280: \n281: ### Weighted Vote\n282: \n283: ```\n284: stopScore = sum(s.weight * (1 if s.stop else 0) for s in signals) / totalWeight\n285: if stopScore >= 0.60:   // proceed to quality gate evaluation\n286: ```\n287: \n288: Weights are redistributed across active signals only. If only 2 signals have enough data, their weights are normalized to sum to 1.0.\n289: \n290: ### Semantic Convergence Signals\n291: \n292: Two additional signals provide deeper semantic analysis of review iteration quality. These signals are ADDITIONAL to the 3-signal composite vote above and participate in the legal-stop gate evaluation rather than the composite stop-score.\n293: \n294: #### semanticNovelty (0.0-1.0)\n295: \n296: Measures how much genuinely new review insight each iteration contributes beyond surface-level overlap with prior findings. Unlike `newFindingsRatio` (which is severity-weighted), `semanticNovelty` evaluates the conceptual novelty of findings independent of severity weighting.\n297: \n298: | Value | Meaning |\n299: |-------|---------|\n300: | 0.8-1.0 | Iteration uncovered substantially new defect patterns, architectural concerns, or review angles |\n301: | 0.4-0.7 | Mix of new review insights and restatements of prior findings |\n302: | 0.1-0.3 | Mostly refinements or rewordings of previously identified issues |\n303: | 0.0 | No semantically novel findings detected |\n304: \n305: Computation:\n306: ```\n307: function computeSemanticNovelty_review(currentFindings, priorCumulativeFindings):\n308:   newPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings) - extractDefectPatterns(priorCumulativeFindings)\n309:   totalPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings)\n310:   if len(totalPatterns) == 0: return 0.0\n311:   return len(newPatterns) / len(totalPatterns)\n312: ```\n313: \n314: When `semanticNovelty` drops below 0.15 for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations, it provides strong supporting evidence for a legal STOP decision. This signal catches cases where `newFindingsRatio` stays moderate (due to severity weighting of refinements) but the review has exhausted genuinely new defect categories.\n315: \n316: #### findingStability (0.0-1.0)\n317: \n318: Measures how stable the cumulative finding set is across iterations. A high stability score means the finding registry is not materially changing between iterations -- findings are not being added, upgraded, downgraded, or invalidated at a significant rate.\n319: \n320: | Value | Meaning |\n321: |-------|---------|\n322: | 0.9-1.0 | Finding set is highly stable, minimal churn between iterations |\n323: | 0.6-0.8 | Moderate stability, some findings still evolving |\n324: | 0.3-0.5 | Active churn, findings being added, merged, or reclassified frequently |\n325: | 0.0-0.2 | Highly unstable, the review is still in early discovery |\n326: \n327: Computation:\n328: ```\n329: function computeFindingStability(currentRegistry, priorRegistry):\n330:   if priorRegistry is null: return 0.0  // first iteration\n331:   unchangedFindings = count(f for f in currentRegistry\n332:     if f.id in priorRegistry and f.severity == priorRegistry[f.id].severity\n333:     and f.status == priorRegistry[f.id].status)\n334:   totalFindings = max(len(currentRegistry), len(priorRegistry))\n335:   if totalFindings == 0: return 1.0\n336:   return unchangedFindings / totalFindings\n337: ```\n338: \n339: Convergence behavior:\n340: - `findingStability >= 0.85` supports STOP: the finding set has stabilized and further iterations are unlikely to materially change the review outcome.\n341: - `findingStability < 0.50` prevents STOP: the finding set is still in flux and the review has not reached a stable assessment.\n342: \n343: #### Integration with Legal-Stop Gate Bundle\n344: \n345: The two semantic signals integrate with the existing 5-gate legal-stop bundle (Section 6):\n346: \n347: 1. **findingStability gate** (existing): The existing `findingStability` gate already evaluates rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio. The new `semanticNovelty` signal adds a sub-check:\n348:    - `semanticNoveltyPlateau`: `semanticNovelty < 0.15` for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations\n349:    - When this sub-check fails while the existing churn signals pass, the gate records the mismatch as a diagnostic note but does not independently block STOP.\n350: \n351: 2. **findingStability signal** (new): The `findingStability` metric (0.0-1.0) is surfaced alongside the existing convergence signals. It supports the `findingStability` gate evaluation by providing a registry-level stability measure that complements the ratio-based churn signals.\n352: \n353: The gate passes only when both the existing churn-based checks AND the semantic stability checks agree. When a semantic check fails, the persisted `blocked_stop.gateResults.findingStability` payload includes the semantic signal values.\n354: \n355: #### Stop-Decision Trace\n356: \n357: The stop-decision event includes which semantic signals supported or prevented STOP:\n358: \n359: ```json\n360: {\n361:   \"type\": \"event\",\n362:   \"event\": \"stop_decision\",\n363:   \"semanticSignals\": {\n364:     \"semanticNovelty\": { \"value\": 0.06, \"consecutiveLow\": 3, \"supportsStop\": true },\n365:     \"findingStability\": { \"value\": 0.92, \"supportsStop\": true }\n366:   },\n367:   \"semanticVerdict\": \"all_support_stop\",\n368:   ...\n369: }\n370: ```\n371: \n372: | `semanticVerdict` | Meaning |\n373: |-------------------|---------|\n374: | `all_support_stop` | Both semantic signals support stopping |\n375: | `mixed` | One signal supports stop, the other does not |\n376: | `all_prevent_stop` | Both semantic signals indicate more work is needed |\n377: | `insufficient_data` | Not enough iterations to compute semantic signals |\n378: \n379: ### Graceful Degradation\n380: \n381: | Iterations Completed | Active Signals | Behavior |\n382: |---------------------|----------------|----------|\n383: | 1 | Novelty ratio only (weight 1.0) | Very unlikely to stop without later confirmation from rolling churn signals |\n384: | 2 | Rolling avg + novelty ratio | Two-signal vote, reweighted |\n385: | 3+ | All three signals | Full composite, most reliable |\n386: \n387: Semantic convergence signals (`semanticNovelty`, `findingStability`) require at least 2 evidence iterations to produce meaningful values. They are omitted from legal-stop evaluation when insufficient data exists.\n388: \n389: ---\n390: \n391: ## 5. SEVERITY-WEIGHTED RATIO\n392: \n393: The review loop uses `newFindingsRatio` instead of `newInfoRatio`. It weights findings by severity so that critical discoveries count far more than minor suggestions.\n394: \n395: ### Severity Weights\n396: \n397: | Severity | Weight | Description |\n398: |----------|--------|-------------|\n399: | **P0** (Blocker) | 10.0 | Correctness failures, security vulnerabilities, spec contradictions |\n400: | **P1** (Required) | 5.0 | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation |\n401: | **P2** (Suggestion) | 1.0 | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps |\n402: \n403: ### Computation\n404: \n405: ```\n406: SEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 }\n407: refinementMultiplier = 0.5\n408: \n409: weightedNew       = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in fully_new_findings)\n410: weightedRefinement = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] * 0.5 for f in refinement_findings)\n411: weightedTotal     = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in all_findings_this_iteration)\n412: \n413: newFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal\n414: ```\n415: \n416: - `fully_new_findings` -- findings not present in any prior iteration (new findingId).\n417: - `refinement_findings` -- findings that refine or upgrade an existing finding (same root cause, new evidence or severity change).\n418: - `refinementMultiplier = 0.5` -- refinements count at half weight.\n419: \n420: ### P0 Override Rule\n421: \n422: ```\n423: if ANY new P0 found this iteration:\n424:   newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)\n425: \n426: if total_findings == 0:\n427:   newFindingsRatio = 0.0\n428: ```\n429: \n430: A new critical finding always signals significant remaining work. The 0.50 floor prevents premature convergence when critical issues are still being discovered.\n431: \n432: ---\n433: \n434: ## 6. LEGAL-STOP GATE BUNDLE\n435: \n436: > **GATE MODEL, two naming conventions mapped to one authoritative set.** The authoritative producer is `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`, which emits **9 gates** with the `Gate` suffix: `convergenceGate` / `dimensionCoverageGate` / `p0ResolutionGate` / `evidenceDensityGate` / `hotspotSaturationGate` / `claimAdjudicationGate` / `fixCompletenessReplayGate` / `candidateCoverageGate` / `graphlessFallbackGate`. The §Section-1 event shape (lines 98-119) mirrors this set verbatim and the reducer reads those names verbatim, so treat the event shape as authoritative when writing or reading JSONL state. The §6 table below is the high-level conceptual model and uses descriptive names WITHOUT the `Gate` suffix where one reads more naturally (for example `findingStability` maps to `convergenceGate`); each row carries its event-shape name so the mapping is explicit. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. The gate-model drift cluster (LG-0013, LG-0016, LG-0031, LG-0032) was reconciled in `006-gate-model-reconciliation`.\n437: \n438: Deep review treats STOP as legal only when the full review-specific gate bundle passes together. Convergence math may request STOP, but the workflow must still evaluate these 9 gates and persist a blocked-stop event when any gate fails.\n439: \n440: | Gate (§6 conceptual) | Event-shape name (§Section-1) | Rule | Fail Action |\n441: |------|------|------|-------------|\n442: | **findingStability** | `convergenceGate` | Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio must all indicate low-yield review churn | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n443: | **dimensionCoverage** | `dimensionCoverageGate` | Every configured review dimension must have been examined at least once, with required traceability coverage stabilized | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n444: | **p0Resolution** | `p0ResolutionGate` | No unresolved P0 findings may remain active at stop time | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n445: | **evidenceDensity** | `evidenceDensityGate` | Evidence density across active findings must meet the configured threshold | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n446: | **hotspotSaturation** | `hotspotSaturationGate` | Review hotspots must be revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n447: | (no §6 counterpart) | `claimAdjudicationGate` | Each new P0/P1 finding must carry a typed adjudication packet, missing or failing packets veto STOP | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n448: | **fixCompletenessReplay** | `fixCompletenessReplayGate` | Security-sensitive fix reruns must replay previously closed P0/P1 gates and validate producer/consumer/matrix coverage from the remediation packet | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n449: | **candidateCoverage** (v2 rollout) | `candidateCoverageGate` | Search debt must be cleared and every required bug class must have candidate coverage before STOP, passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n450: | **graphlessFallback** (v2 rollout) | `graphlessFallbackGate` | When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes must carry cited fallback ledger rows, passes trivially when the graph is available | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n451: \n452: ### Gate Evaluation\n453: \n454: ```\n455: function buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage):\n456:   gateResults = {\n457:     findingStability: {\n458:       pass: rollingStop and madStop and state.latestNoveltyRatio <= config.convergenceThreshold,\n459:       detail: \"Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio are all below stop thresholds.\"\n460:     },\n461:     dimensionCoverage: {\n462:       pass: everyConfiguredDimensionExaminedAtLeastOnce(coverage, config.reviewDimensions) and\n463:             coverage.requiredProtocolsCovered and\n464:             coverage.stabilizationPasses >= 1,\n465:       detail: \"All configured review dimensions have been examined, required traceability protocols are covered, and stabilization has aged enough to stop.\"\n466:     },\n467:     p0Resolution: {\n468:       pass: countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"]) == 0 and state.claimAdjudicationPassed != false,\n469:       detail: \"No unresolved P0 findings remain and blocker adjudication is complete.\"\n470:     },\n471:     evidenceDensity: {\n472:       pass: computeEvidenceDensity(state.activeFindings) >= config.evidenceDensityThreshold,\n473:       detail: \"Evidence density meets the configured threshold for active findings.\"\n474:     },\n475:     hotspotSaturation: {\n476:       pass: computeHotspotSaturation(state.hotspots) >= config.hotspotSaturationThreshold,\n477:       detail: \"Priority hotspots received enough revisits to satisfy saturation.\"\n478:     },\n479:     fixCompletenessReplay: {\n480:       pass: not isSecuritySensitiveFixRerun(state, config) or allRequiredReplayRowsPass(state.reviewReport),\n481:       detail: \"Security-sensitive fix reruns include closed-gate replay evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage before STOP.\"\n482:     },\n483:     candidateCoverage: {\n484:       pass: not isReviewDepthV2Active(state, config) or (searchDebtCleared(state) and allRequiredBugClassesCovered(state)),\n485:       detail: \"Search debt is cleared and every required bug class has candidate coverage. Passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive.\"\n486:     },\n487:     graphlessFallback: {\n488:       pass: state.searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode == \"graph_available\" or allRequiredBugClassesHaveFallbackRows(state),\n489:       detail: \"When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes carry cited fallback ledger rows. Passes trivially when the graph is available.\"\n490:     }\n491:   }\n492: \n493:   blockedBy = [name for name, result in gateResults.items() if not result.pass]\n494:   return {\n495:     pass: len(blockedBy) == 0,\n496:     blockedBy,\n497:     gateResults\n498:   }\n499: ```\n500: \n501: When convergence math returns STOP, invoke `buildReviewLegalStop()`. If it returns `pass: false`, persist a first-class `blocked_stop` event with the failing `blockedBy` gates, the full `gateResults` bundle, a `recoveryStrategy`, and the normal run/timestamp/session lineage fields before overriding the decision to CONTINUE.\n502: \n503: ### Blocked-Stop Recovery Strategy\n504: \n505: | Failed Gate | Recovery Strategy |\n506: |-------------|-------------------|\n507: | `findingStability` | Revisit the noisiest recent dimension and reduce novelty by closing obvious follow-up loops before re-checking STOP. |\n508: | `dimensionCoverage` | Schedule the next uncovered review dimension immediately. |\n509: | `p0Resolution` | Re-open the active blocker path and verify whether the P0 is real, downgraded, or still unresolved. |\n510: | `evidenceDensity` | Re-read weakly supported findings and add concrete `file:line` citations before they count toward a stop decision. |\n511: | `hotspotSaturation` | Revisit undersampled hotspots or adjacent call sites until the saturation heuristic passes. |\n512: | `fixCompletenessReplay` | Replay prior active or remediated P0/P1 gates, then record producer, consumer, and matrix coverage evidence before re-checking STOP. |\n513: | `candidateCoverage` | Clear outstanding search debt and run candidate discovery for the missing bug classes before re-checking STOP. |\n514: | `graphlessFallback` | Add cited fallback ledger rows for the required bug classes, or restore graph availability, before re-checking STOP. |\n515: \n516: ### Legacy Stop-Reason Mapping\n517: \n518: Use this table when replaying old packets or translating older prose/docs into the shared stop contract.\n519: \n520: | Legacy label | New `stopReason` | Mapping note |\n521: |--------------|------------------|--------------|\n522: | `all_dimensions_clean` | `converged` | Legacy review-specific terminal label, now expressed by the shared enum. |\n523: | `composite_converged` | `converged` | Legacy convergence-math wording now rolls into shared terminal success. |\n524: | `all dimensions clean` | `converged` | Old operator-facing prose for the same successful stop. |\n525: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` | Legacy machine label for the hard iteration cap. |\n526: | `max iterations` | `maxIterationsReached` | Old operator-facing hard-stop wording. |\n527: | `pause sentinel detected` | `userPaused` | Sentinel pause is now a shared user-directed stop reason. |\n528: | `guard_override` | `blockedStop` | Legacy continue override when a stop vote failed legal gates. |\n529: | `quality guard failed` | `blockedStop` | Older prose for the same blocked-stop outcome. |\n530: | `P0 override blocks convergence` | `blockedStop` | Legacy review wording for a stop attempt that was not legal to finalize. |\n531: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy recovery trigger label. |\n532: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy terminal wording for the same recovery path family. |\n533: | `manual halt` | `manualStop` | Operator-directed halt outside normal pause sentinel flow. |\n534: \n535: ---\n536: \n537: ## 7. PROVISIONAL VERDICT\n538: \n539: The provisional verdict is determined from active findings at the time the loop stops. It appears in both the convergence report and the final `review-report.md`.\n540: \n541: | Verdict | Condition | Meaning |\n542: |---------|-----------|---------|\n543: | **FAIL** | `activeP0 > 0` OR any legal-stop gate fails at terminal stop time | Does not meet quality standards. Blocks release. |\n544: | **CONDITIONAL** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 > 0` | Meets threshold but has required fixes before release. |\n545: | **PASS** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 == 0` | Shippable. Set `hasAdvisories: true` when `activeP2 > 0`. |\n546: \n547: ### Determination\n548: \n549: ```\n550: function determineVerdict(state, gateResult):\n551:   activeP0 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"])\n552:   activeP1 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P1\"])\n553:   activeP2 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P2\"])\n554: \n555:   if activeP0 > 0 or not gateResult.passed:\n556:     return { verdict: \"FAIL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n557:   if activeP1 > 0:\n558:     return { verdict: \"CONDITIONAL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n559: \n560:   hasAdvisories = activeP2 > 0\n561:   return { verdict: \"PASS\", hasAdvisories, nextCommand: \"/create:changelog\" }\n562: ```\n563: \n564: ### Post-Verdict Routing\n565: \n566: | Verdict | Next Step |\n567: |---------|-----------|\n568: | FAIL | `/speckit:plan` -- create remediation plan from findings |\n569: | CONDITIONAL | `/speckit:plan` -- create fix plan for P1 findings |\n570: | PASS | `/create:changelog` -- record the clean audit |\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: ## 8. RECOVERY, REPORTING, AND GRAPH-AWARE CONVERGENCE\n575: \n576: Stuck-recovery strategies, the convergence report format, and graph-aware review convergence live in `convergence_recovery.md` for navigability.\n577: \n578: ---\n579: \n580: ## OPTIMIZER-TUNABLE THRESHOLDS\n581: \n582: The following convergence thresholds are managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). Changes to these fields are proposed through the optimizer's advisory-only promotion gate and reviewed by humans before adoption.\n583: \n584: ### Tunable Fields (Optimizer-Managed)\n585: \n586: | Field | Default | Range | Description |\n587: |-------|---------|-------|-------------|\n588: | `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | 0.01-0.20 | General convergence sensitivity |\n589: | `stuckThreshold` | 2 | 1-5 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n590: | `maxIterations` | 7 | 3-20 | Hard iteration ceiling |\n591: | `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | 0.40-0.80 | Weighted stop score needed before guard evaluation |\n592: \n593: ### Locked Fields (Not Optimizer-Tunable)\n594: \n595: The following fields are runtime contracts and MUST NOT be modified by the optimizer:\n596: \n597: - `stopReason` enum values and semantics\n598: - `blocked_stop` event structure and gate names\n599: - Lineage fields (`sessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`)\n600: - Reducer configuration and file protection policies\n601: - Review dimensions (`reviewDimensions`) and product mode (`mode`)\n602: \n603: ### Canonical Manifest\n604: \n605: The authoritative registry of tunable vs locked fields is maintained at:\n606: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`\n\n(End of file - total 606 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.22\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.22\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nConvergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n\n| Outcome | Meaning |\n|---------|---------|\n| **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n| **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n| **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n\nConvergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n\nRelease-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n- `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n- `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n- `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n\nWhen the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n- Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n- Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n- Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n\n### Key Defaults\n\n| Setting | Value | Purpose |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n| `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n| `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n| `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n| `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n| `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n\n### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n\n`convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n\n**Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n\n| Skill | Default | Signal |\n|---|---|---|\n| `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n| `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n| `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n\n### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n\n> **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n\nFor review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n\n| Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n|---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n| `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n| `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n\nWhen implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n\n### Shared Stop Contract\n\nEvery terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n\n### Convergence Modes\n\nThe shared convergence runtime accepts four values. Review legality, security gates, target authority, and verdict derivation remain owned by the review workflow rather than the convergence mode.\n\n| Mode | Live Behavior |\n|------|---------------|\n| `default` | Uses normal full-history convergence signals and sends a legal STOP to synthesis and verdict derivation. This is the fallback when no mode is supplied. |\n| `off` | Is accepted and persisted, but the shipped review YAML has no `off` decision branch; review therefore follows the same legal-stop and synthesis path as `default`. Use `stopPolicy: \"max-iterations\"` when convergence must remain telemetry-only until the iteration ceiling. |\n| `sliding-window` | Is accepted and persisted, but windowed graph-novelty telemetry is research-only in the shared runtime; review therefore retains its ordinary full-history signals, legal-stop gates, and synthesis path. |\n| `divergent` | After all review gates pass, translates the eligible `all_dimensions_clean` STOP into a read-only three-seat direction-selection pivot and continues with the selected review direction. |\n\n#### Divergent Pivot Contract\n\nReview has one eligible reason: the exact internal reason `all_dimensions_clean` with decision `STOP`. The nine legal-stop gates run before the divergent branch and remain unchanged. `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `error`, `manualStop`, and `userPaused` are explicitly excluded. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, unrecoverable error, and any blocked security or quality gate therefore never dispatch a pivot Council.\n\nEach eligible pivot runs one native, in-process Council round with exactly three distinct seats: analytical, critical, and pragmatic. It does not use an external CLI. The transaction requires all three seat returns to be parse-valid and at least two seats to materially endorse the same candidate without a high-severity blocker. Candidate sources are persisted unswept dimensions, search debt, producer-consumer gaps, negative-test gaps, and traceability gaps. Candidate generation rejects directions without in-scope evidence and directions that imply implementation, a fix, mutation, writing, or target expansion.\n\nThe guarantees are absolute: divergent mode never changes the PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL mapping, never authorizes a fix, and never makes the review target writable. A successful pivot returns to the loop before `phase_synthesis`; verdict computation exists only inside `phase_synthesis`, where active P0 yields FAIL, active P1 yields CONDITIONAL, and no active P0/P1 yields PASS. A failed pivot fails closed to that existing synthesis path.\n\nEvery pivot dispatches three seats, so a run that pivots has proportionally higher model cost and duration than the same run under `default`, `off`, or `sliding-window`. Pivot evidence is isolated under `<artifactRoot>/divergent/pivots/<pivotId>/council/**`, including config, append-only state, three seat artifacts, deliberation, and report. This path is distinct from ordinary planning Council artifacts under a spec packet's `ai-council/**` tree.\n\n#### stopReason Enum\n\n| `stopReason` | Meaning |\n|--------------|---------|\n| `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n| `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n| `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n| `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n| `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n\n#### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n\n`step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n  \"gateResults\": {\n    \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n    \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n      \"pass\": false,\n      \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n      \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n    },\n    \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n    \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n    \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n    \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n    \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n    \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n    \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n  },\n  \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1\n}\n```\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n- `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n- `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n- `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n- When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n\n### Decision Priority\n\nChecks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n\n1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HARD STOPS\n\nHard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n\n### Max Iterations Reached\n\n```\nif len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n  return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n```\n\nThe loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n\n### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n\n```\nif coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n  if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n    if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n      return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n```\n\nTriggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n\n---\n\n## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n\nIdentifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n\n```\nfunction countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n  count = 0\n  for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n    if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n    if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n    if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n      count += 1\n    else:\n      break\n  return count\n```\n\n**Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n\n**Status exclusions:**\n- `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n- `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n\nWhen `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n\nThe recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n\n---\n\n## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n\nThree independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n\n### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n\nAverages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n  recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n  avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n  rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n```\n\n### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n\nRobust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n  allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n  med = median(allRatios)\n  mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n  noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n  madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n```\n\n### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n\nHighest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n\n```\ndimensionStop =\n  dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n  AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n  AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n```\n\nThe latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n\n### Weighted Vote\n\n```\nstopScore = sum(s.weight * (1 if s.stop else 0) for s in signals) / totalWeight\nif stopScore >= 0.60:   // proceed to quality gate evaluation\n```\n\nWeights are redistributed across active signals only. If only 2 signals have enough data, their weights are normalized to sum to 1.0.\n\n### Semantic Convergence Signals\n\nTwo additional signals provide deeper semantic analysis of review iteration quality. These signals are ADDITIONAL to the 3-signal composite vote above and participate in the legal-stop gate evaluation rather than the composite stop-score.\n\n#### semanticNovelty (0.0-1.0)\n\nMeasures how much genuinely new review insight each iteration contributes beyond surface-level overlap with prior findings. Unlike `newFindingsRatio` (which is severity-weighted), `semanticNovelty` evaluates the conceptual novelty of findings independent of severity weighting.\n\n| Value | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| 0.8-1.0 | Iteration uncovered substantially new defect patterns, architectural concerns, or review angles |\n| 0.4-0.7 | Mix of new review insights and restatements of prior findings |\n| 0.1-0.3 | Mostly refinements or rewordings of previously identified issues |\n| 0.0 | No semantically novel findings detected |\n\nComputation:\n```\nfunction computeSemanticNovelty_review(currentFindings, priorCumulativeFindings):\n  newPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings) - extractDefectPatterns(priorCumulativeFindings)\n  totalPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings)\n  if len(totalPatterns) == 0: return 0.0\n  return len(newPatterns) / len(totalPatterns)\n```\n\nWhen `semanticNovelty` drops below 0.15 for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations, it provides strong supporting evidence for a legal STOP decision. This signal catches cases where `newFindingsRatio` stays moderate (due to severity weighting of refinements) but the review has exhausted genuinely new defect categories.\n\n#### findingStability (0.0-1.0)\n\nMeasures how stable the cumulative finding set is across iterations. A high stability score means the finding registry is not materially changing between iterations -- findings are not being added, upgraded, downgraded, or invalidated at a significant rate.\n\n| Value | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| 0.9-1.0 | Finding set is highly stable, minimal churn between iterations |\n| 0.6-0.8 | Moderate stability, some findings still evolving |\n| 0.3-0.5 | Active churn, findings being added, merged, or reclassified frequently |\n| 0.0-0.2 | Highly unstable, the review is still in early discovery |\n\nComputation:\n```\nfunction computeFindingStability(currentRegistry, priorRegistry):\n  if priorRegistry is null: return 0.0  // first iteration\n  unchangedFindings = count(f for f in currentRegistry\n    if f.id in priorRegistry and f.severity == priorRegistry[f.id].severity\n    and f.status == priorRegistry[f.id].status)\n  totalFindings = max(len(currentRegistry), len(priorRegistry))\n  if totalFindings == 0: return 1.0\n  return unchangedFindings / totalFindings\n```\n\nConvergence behavior:\n- `findingStability >= 0.85` supports STOP: the finding set has stabilized and further iterations are unlikely to materially change the review outcome.\n- `findingStability < 0.50` prevents STOP: the finding set is still in flux and the review has not reached a stable assessment.\n\n#### Integration with Legal-Stop Gate Bundle\n\nThe two semantic signals integrate with the existing 5-gate legal-stop bundle (Section 6):\n\n1. **findingStability gate** (existing): The existing `findingStability` gate already evaluates rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio. The new `semanticNovelty` signal adds a sub-check:\n   - `semanticNoveltyPlateau`: `semanticNovelty < 0.15` for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations\n   - When this sub-check fails while the existing churn signals pass, the gate records the mismatch as a diagnostic note but does not independently block STOP.\n\n2. **findingStability signal** (new): The `findingStability` metric (0.0-1.0) is surfaced alongside the existing convergence signals. It supports the `findingStability` gate evaluation by providing a registry-level stability measure that complements the ratio-based churn signals.\n\nThe gate passes only when both the existing churn-based checks AND the semantic stability checks agree. When a semantic check fails, the persisted `blocked_stop.gateResults.findingStability` payload includes the semantic signal values.\n\n#### Stop-Decision Trace\n\nThe stop-decision event includes which semantic signals supported or prevented STOP:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stop_decision\",\n  \"semanticSignals\": {\n    \"semanticNovelty\": { \"value\": 0.06, \"consecutiveLow\": 3, \"supportsStop\": true },\n    \"findingStability\": { \"value\": 0.92, \"supportsStop\": true }\n  },\n  \"semanticVerdict\": \"all_support_stop\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n| `semanticVerdict` | Meaning |\n|-------------------|---------|\n| `all_support_stop` | Both semantic signals support stopping |\n| `mixed` | One signal supports stop, the other does not |\n| `all_prevent_stop` | Both semantic signals indicate more work is needed |\n| `insufficient_data` | Not enough iterations to compute semantic signals |\n\n### Graceful Degradation\n\n| Iterations Completed | Active Signals | Behavior |\n|---------------------|----------------|----------|\n| 1 | Novelty ratio only (weight 1.0) | Very unlikely to stop without later confirmation from rolling churn signals |\n| 2 | Rolling avg + novelty ratio | Two-signal vote, reweighted |\n| 3+ | All three signals | Full composite, most reliable |\n\nSemantic convergence signals (`semanticNovelty`, `findingStability`) require at least 2 evidence iterations to produce meaningful values. They are omitted from legal-stop evaluation when insufficient data exists.\n\n---\n\n## 5. SEVERITY-WEIGHTED RATIO\n\nThe review loop uses `newFindingsRatio` instead of `newInfoRatio`. It weights findings by severity so that critical discoveries count far more than minor suggestions.\n\n### Severity Weights\n\n| Severity | Weight | Description |\n|----------|--------|-------------|\n| **P0** (Blocker) | 10.0 | Correctness failures, security vulnerabilities, spec contradictions |\n| **P1** (Required) | 5.0 | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation |\n| **P2** (Suggestion) | 1.0 | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps |\n\n### Computation\n\n```\nSEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 }\nrefinementMultiplier = 0.5\n\nweightedNew       = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in fully_new_findings)\nweightedRefinement = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] * 0.5 for f in refinement_findings)\nweightedTotal     = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in all_findings_this_iteration)\n\nnewFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal\n```\n\n- `fully_new_findings` -- findings not present in any prior iteration (new findingId).\n- `refinement_findings` -- findings that refine or upgrade an existing finding (same root cause, new evidence or severity change).\n- `refinementMultiplier = 0.5` -- refinements count at half weight.\n\n### P0 Override Rule\n\n```\nif ANY new P0 found this iteration:\n  newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)\n\nif total_findings == 0:\n  newFindingsRatio = 0.0\n```\n\nA new critical finding always signals significant remaining work. The 0.50 floor prevents premature convergence when critical issues are still being discovered.\n\n---\n\n## 6. LEGAL-STOP GATE BUNDLE\n\n> **GATE MODEL, two naming conventions mapped to one authoritative set.** The authoritative producer is `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`, which emits **9 gates** with the `Gate` suffix: `convergenceGate` / `dimensionCoverageGate` / `p0ResolutionGate` / `evidenceDensityGate` / `hotspotSaturationGate` / `claimAdjudicationGate` / `fixCompletenessReplayGate` / `candidateCoverageGate` / `graphlessFallbackGate`. The §Section-1 event shape (lines 98-119) mirrors this set verbatim and the reducer reads those names verbatim, so treat the event shape as authoritative when writing or reading JSONL state. The §6 table below is the high-level conceptual model and uses descriptive names WITHOUT the `Gate` suffix where one reads more naturally (for example `findingStability` maps to `convergenceGate`); each row carries its event-shape name so the mapping is explicit. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. The gate-model drift cluster (LG-0013, LG-0016, LG-0031, LG-0032) was reconciled in `006-gate-model-reconciliation`.\n\nDeep review treats STOP as legal only when the full review-specific gate bundle passes together. Convergence math may request STOP, but the workflow must still evaluate these 9 gates and persist a blocked-stop event when any gate fails.\n\n| Gate (§6 conceptual) | Event-shape name (§Section-1) | Rule | Fail Action |\n|------|------|------|-------------|\n| **findingStability** | `convergenceGate` | Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio must all indicate low-yield review churn | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **dimensionCoverage** | `dimensionCoverageGate` | Every configured review dimension must have been examined at least once, with required traceability coverage stabilized | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **p0Resolution** | `p0ResolutionGate` | No unresolved P0 findings may remain active at stop time | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **evidenceDensity** | `evidenceDensityGate` | Evidence density across active findings must meet the configured threshold | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **hotspotSaturation** | `hotspotSaturationGate` | Review hotspots must be revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| (no §6 counterpart) | `claimAdjudicationGate` | Each new P0/P1 finding must carry a typed adjudication packet, missing or failing packets veto STOP | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **fixCompletenessReplay** | `fixCompletenessReplayGate` | Security-sensitive fix reruns must replay previously closed P0/P1 gates and validate producer/consumer/matrix coverage from the remediation packet | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **candidateCoverage** (v2 rollout) | `candidateCoverageGate` | Search debt must be cleared and every required bug class must have candidate coverage before STOP, passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **graphlessFallback** (v2 rollout) | `graphlessFallbackGate` | When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes must carry cited fallback ledger rows, passes trivially when the graph is available | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n\n### Gate Evaluation\n\n```\nfunction buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage):\n  gateResults = {\n    findingStability: {\n      pass: rollingStop and madStop and state.latestNoveltyRatio <= config.convergenceThreshold,\n      detail: \"Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio are all below stop thresholds.\"\n    },\n    dimensionCoverage: {\n      pass: everyConfiguredDimensionExaminedAtLeastOnce(coverage, config.reviewDimensions) and\n            coverage.requiredProtocolsCovered and\n            coverage.stabilizationPasses >= 1,\n      detail: \"All configured review dimensions have been examined, required traceability protocols are covered, and stabilization has aged enough to stop.\"\n    },\n    p0Resolution: {\n      pass: countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"]) == 0 and state.claimAdjudicationPassed != false,\n      detail: \"No unresolved P0 findings remain and blocker adjudication is complete.\"\n    },\n    evidenceDensity: {\n      pass: computeEvidenceDensity(state.activeFindings) >= config.evidenceDensityThreshold,\n      detail: \"Evidence density meets the configured threshold for active findings.\"\n    },\n    hotspotSaturation: {\n      pass: computeHotspotSaturation(state.hotspots) >= config.hotspotSaturationThreshold,\n      detail: \"Priority hotspots received enough revisits to satisfy saturation.\"\n    },\n    fixCompletenessReplay: {\n      pass: not isSecuritySensitiveFixRerun(state, config) or allRequiredReplayRowsPass(state.reviewReport),\n      detail: \"Security-sensitive fix reruns include closed-gate replay evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage before STOP.\"\n    },\n    candidateCoverage: {\n      pass: not isReviewDepthV2Active(state, config) or (searchDebtCleared(state) and allRequiredBugClassesCovered(state)),\n      detail: \"Search debt is cleared and every required bug class has candidate coverage. Passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive.\"\n    },\n    graphlessFallback: {\n      pass: state.searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode == \"graph_available\" or allRequiredBugClassesHaveFallbackRows(state),\n      detail: \"When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes carry cited fallback ledger rows. Passes trivially when the graph is available.\"\n    }\n  }\n\n  blockedBy = [name for name, result in gateResults.items() if not result.pass]\n  return {\n    pass: len(blockedBy) == 0,\n    blockedBy,\n    gateResults\n  }\n```\n\nWhen convergence math returns STOP, invoke `buildReviewLegalStop()`. If it returns `pass: false`, persist a first-class `blocked_stop` event with the failing `blockedBy` gates, the full `gateResults` bundle, a `recoveryStrategy`, and the normal run/timestamp/session lineage fields before overriding the decision to CONTINUE.\n\n### Blocked-Stop Recovery Strategy\n\n| Failed Gate | Recovery Strategy |\n|-------------|-------------------|\n| `findingStability` | Revisit the noisiest recent dimension and reduce novelty by closing obvious follow-up loops before re-checking STOP. |\n| `dimensionCoverage` | Schedule the next uncovered review dimension immediately. |\n| `p0Resolution` | Re-open the active blocker path and verify whether the P0 is real, downgraded, or still unresolved. |\n| `evidenceDensity` | Re-read weakly supported findings and add concrete `file:line` citations before they count toward a stop decision. |\n| `hotspotSaturation` | Revisit undersampled hotspots or adjacent call sites until the saturation heuristic passes. |\n| `fixCompletenessReplay` | Replay prior active or remediated P0/P1 gates, then record producer, consumer, and matrix coverage evidence before re-checking STOP. |\n| `candidateCoverage` | Clear outstanding search debt and run candidate discovery for the missing bug classes before re-checking STOP. |\n| `graphlessFallback` | Add cited fallback ledger rows for the required bug classes, or restore graph availability, before re-checking STOP. |\n\n### Legacy Stop-Reason Mapping\n\nUse this table when replaying old packets or translating older prose/docs into the shared stop contract.\n\n| Legacy label | New `stopReason` | Mapping note |\n|--------------|------------------|--------------|\n| `all_dimensions_clean` | `converged` | Legacy review-specific terminal label, now expressed by the shared enum. |\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` | Legacy convergence-math wording now rolls into shared terminal success. |\n| `all dimensions clean` | `converged` | Old operator-facing prose for the same successful stop. |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` | Legacy machine label for the hard iteration cap. |\n| `max iterations` | `maxIterationsReached` | Old operator-facing hard-stop wording. |\n| `pause sentinel detected` | `userPaused` | Sentinel pause is now a shared user-directed stop reason. |\n| `guard_override` | `blockedStop` | Legacy continue override when a stop vote failed legal gates. |\n| `quality guard failed` | `blockedStop` | Older prose for the same blocked-stop outcome. |\n| `P0 override blocks convergence` | `blockedStop` | Legacy review wording for a stop attempt that was not legal to finalize. |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy recovery trigger label. |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy terminal wording for the same recovery path family. |\n| `manual halt` | `manualStop` | Operator-directed halt outside normal pause sentinel flow. |\n\n---\n\n## 7. PROVISIONAL VERDICT\n\nThe provisional verdict is determined from active findings at the time the loop stops. It appears in both the convergence report and the final `review-report.md`.\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Meaning |\n|---------|-----------|---------|\n| **FAIL** | `activeP0 > 0` OR any legal-stop gate fails at terminal stop time | Does not meet quality standards. Blocks release. |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 > 0` | Meets threshold but has required fixes before release. |\n| **PASS** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 == 0` | Shippable. Set `hasAdvisories: true` when `activeP2 > 0`. |\n\n### Determination\n\n```\nfunction determineVerdict(state, gateResult):\n  activeP0 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"])\n  activeP1 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P1\"])\n  activeP2 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P2\"])\n\n  if activeP0 > 0 or not gateResult.passed:\n    return { verdict: \"FAIL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n  if activeP1 > 0:\n    return { verdict: \"CONDITIONAL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n\n  hasAdvisories = activeP2 > 0\n  return { verdict: \"PASS\", hasAdvisories, nextCommand: \"/create:changelog\" }\n```\n\n### Post-Verdict Routing\n\n| Verdict | Next Step |\n|---------|-----------|\n| FAIL | `/speckit:plan` -- create remediation plan from findings |\n| CONDITIONAL | `/speckit:plan` -- create fix plan for P1 findings |\n| PASS | `/create:changelog` -- record the clean audit |\n\n---\n\n## 8. RECOVERY, REPORTING, AND GRAPH-AWARE CONVERGENCE\n\nStuck-recovery strategies, the convergence report format, and graph-aware review convergence live in `convergence_recovery.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## OPTIMIZER-TUNABLE THRESHOLDS\n\nThe following convergence thresholds are managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). Changes to these fields are proposed through the optimizer's advisory-only promotion gate and reviewed by humans before adoption.\n\n### Tunable Fields (Optimizer-Managed)\n\n| Field | Default | Range | Description |\n|-------|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | 0.01-0.20 | General convergence sensitivity |\n| `stuckThreshold` | 2 | 1-5 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| `maxIterations` | 7 | 3-20 | Hard iteration ceiling |\n| `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | 0.40-0.80 | Weighted stop score needed before guard evaluation |\n\n### Locked Fields (Not Optimizer-Tunable)\n\nThe following fields are runtime contracts and MUST NOT be modified by the optimizer:\n\n- `stopReason` enum values and semantics\n- `blocked_stop` event structure and gate names\n- Lineage fields (`sessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`)\n- Reducer configuration and file protection policies\n- Review dimensions (`reviewDimensions`) and product mode (`mode`)\n\n### Canonical Manifest\n\nThe authoritative registry of tunable vs locked fields is maintained at:\n`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":606,"totalLines":606,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1783915534077,"end":1783915534086}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f7bdebefd030b5016a54640de960819199d2b2f0da5ffc0d"}},"id":"prt_f59a6d6f7001YZ5jt6LILytn4z","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915534111,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1UGQsXAy4OaT8AOzXdz8ZCkg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-a","offset":1,"limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-a</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n.executor-state/\n\n(1 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":".executor-state/","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-a","entries":[".executor-state/"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":1,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-a","time":{"start":1783915534107,"end":1783915534109}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f7bdebefd030b5016a54640de97c8191900ef8a3e9ceccd6"}},"id":"prt_f59a6d719001POiQKy58wNivIq","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915534123,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8VLxJCiOhF8x4x70uwLtZOlq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":1500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state outputs\"\n6:   - \"review packet outputs\"\n7:   - \"review dashboard output\"\n8:   - \"review report output\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 1.11.0.3\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review State Outputs\n15: \n16: This reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: Deep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 2. PACKET FILES\n27: \n28: | File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n29: |------|-------|------------|---------|\n30: | `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n31: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n32: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n33: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n34: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n35: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n36: | `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n37: | `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n42: \n43: Each iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n44: \n45: ```text\n46: Review verdict: PASS\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ```text\n50: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ```text\n54: Review verdict: FAIL\n55: ```\n56: \n57: The line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 4. DASHBOARD\n62: \n63: The dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n64: \n65: - Current iteration and next focus.\n66: - Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n67: - Dimension coverage.\n68: - Convergence trend.\n69: - Gate blockers.\n70: - Provisional verdict.\n71: \n72: If dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 5. FINAL REPORT\n77: \n78: `review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n79: \n80: - Executive summary.\n81: - Planning trigger.\n82: - Active finding registry.\n83: - Remediation workstreams.\n84: - Spec seed.\n85: - Plan seed.\n86: - Traceability status.\n87: - Deferred items.\n88: - Audit appendix.\n89: - Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n94: \n95: - `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n96: - `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n97: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET FILES\n\n| File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n|------|-------|------------|---------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n| `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n| `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n\nEach iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n\n```text\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\nThe line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DASHBOARD\n\nThe dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n\n- Current iteration and next focus.\n- Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Dimension coverage.\n- Convergence trend.\n- Gate blockers.\n- Provisional verdict.\n\nIf dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINAL REPORT\n\n`review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n\n- Executive summary.\n- Planning trigger.\n- Active finding registry.\n- Remediation workstreams.\n- Spec seed.\n- Plan seed.\n- Traceability status.\n- Deferred items.\n- Audit appendix.\n- Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n- `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":97,"totalLines":97,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1783915534082,"end":1783915534119}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f7bdebefd030b5016a54640de9688191abd434ba9d18559c"}},"id":"prt_f59a6d6fe001MXKcNY1L3GQCLe","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915534124,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_C4XRqbA9J6hGSt3Kp5Zk3DW2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/completion_criteria.md","offset":1,"limit":1500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/completion_criteria.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Completion Criteria\n3: description: Full definition-of-done checklist for a deep-review loop -- loop completion conditions, the binary quality gates that must pass before STOP, and release-readiness validation success criteria.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"review loop completion criteria\"\n6:   - \"review success criteria\"\n7:   - \"review definition of done\"\n8:   - \"review release readiness validation\"\n9: importance_tier: important\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 1.11.0.0\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review Completion Criteria\n15: \n16: Full definition-of-done checklist for a deep-review loop: loop completion conditions, the binary quality gates STOP must clear, and release-readiness validation success criteria.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: This reference is the authoritative checklist for \"is this review loop actually done.\" SKILL.md §6 SUCCESS CRITERIA carries a condensed summary and links here for the full enumeration; use this file when verifying a completed run, debugging a premature STOP, or reconciling completion metadata against the loop's real state.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: - Verifying a review loop's completion before accepting its verdict.\n29: - Debugging why STOP was blocked or why synthesis produced an incomplete report.\n30: - Reconciling `review-report.md` claims against the canonical state files.\n31: - Auditing a run for the release-readiness handoff.\n32: \n33: ### Relationship to `loop_state_and_gates.md`\n34: \n35: `references/protocol/loop_state_and_gates.md` defines the three state-machine-level binary gates (Evidence, Scope, Coverage) that block a STOP *decision* inside the convergence check. This file is the broader definition-of-done: it also covers artifact existence, report structure, severity-field completeness, and the release-readiness handoff -- checked once the loop believes it has already reached STOP.\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 2. LOOP COMPLETION\n40: \n41: A review loop is considered complete when every item below holds:\n42: \n43: - The loop reached convergence (composite stop score above `compositeStopScore`, with required gates green) OR hit `maxIterations` without false-positive STOP.\n44: - Every configured review dimension has at least one full iteration of coverage recorded in `deep-review-state.jsonl` and reflected in `deep-review-strategy.md`.\n45: - Required traceability protocols (`spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`) executed at least once. Overlay protocols that apply to the target type ran or were explicitly marked N/A.\n46: - All canonical state files exist and parse cleanly: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, and one `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` per dispatched iteration.\n47: - `review/resource-map.md` was emitted from converged delta evidence unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag `--no-resource-map`).\n48: - `review/review-report.md` carries all 9 core sections (Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix) plus the conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present == true`.\n49: - Canonical continuity surfaces updated via `generate-context.js` (description.json, graph-metadata.json, indexed memory entries).\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 3. QUALITY GATES\n54: \n55: Each gate is binary: pass or block. STOP cannot be legal until every gate passes.\n56: \n57: - **Config validity**: `deep-review-config.json` parses, names every required field, and lineage block matches the current run (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`).\n58: - **Strategy initialization**: `deep-review-strategy.md` carries the Files Under Review table, Cross-Reference Status grouped by core vs overlay, Known Context, and Review Boundaries.\n59: - **State consistency**: `deep-review-state.jsonl` opens with the config record and appends one iteration record per dispatched iteration. Reducer-owned fields in `deep-review-findings-registry.json` reconcile against JSONL totals.\n60: - **Iteration completeness**: every dispatched iteration produced both an `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` (non-empty, ending with the canonical `Review verdict: PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` line) AND a JSONL delta record with `findingDetails[]`, `findingsSummary`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n61: - **Severity coverage**: every reported finding carries `severity` in {P0, P1, P2}, `category`, `file:line` evidence, `finding_class`, and a `content_hash` for synthesis dedup.\n62: - **Advisory numeric score**: `riskScore` may appear in finding details as non-gating context only; verdict logic must ignore it.\n63: - **Adversarial replay**: every P0 finding survived adversarial self-check. Rejected P0s downgraded with rationale recorded in the iteration narrative.\n64: - **Coverage threshold**: `dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count` AND required traceability protocols covered, stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations.\n65: - **Acceptance coverage**: when the spec-folder lifecycle predicate is active, the final report records `AC_COVERAGE` status, covered/total, floor, and next action; default-off INFO output is advisory and does not by itself block STOP.\n66: - **Security-sensitive override**: when the run targets security, path handling, env precedence, schema boundaries, persistence, or shared policy, the gates from `references/convergence/convergence.md` \"Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\" apply (`minStabilizationPasses=2`, closed-finding replay required, fix-completeness gate enforced).\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## 4. VALIDATION SUCCESS\n71: \n72: The release-readiness handoff is valid when:\n73: \n74: - The final report records stop reason, iteration count, dimension coverage, severity counts (P0/P1/P2), verdict (PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL), and release-readiness state (`in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking`).\n75: - Verdict logic matches: PASS = no P0/P1 findings (P2 advisories permitted with `hasAdvisories: true`). CONDITIONAL = P1 findings present with remediation plan. FAIL = any P0 confirmed after adversarial self-check.\n76: - `resource-map.md` Phase-5 Augmentation section (if present) lists novel logic gaps with iteration source links, or explicitly records the empty-result case.\n77: - `skill_advisor.py \"run a deep review loop\" --threshold 0.8` still surfaces the skill after any graph-metadata edits.\n78: - `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` exits 0 on the target spec folder.\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n83: \n84: - `references/protocol/loop_state_and_gates.md` -- state transitions, error handling, and the Evidence/Scope/Coverage STOP-decision gates.\n85: - `references/state/state_outputs.md` -- packet file ownership and the `review-report.md` section list.\n86: - `references/state/state_format.md` -- schemas for every state file referenced above.\n87: - `references/convergence/convergence.md` -- composite stop score, `minStabilizationPasses`, and Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides.\n\n(End of file - total 87 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Completion Criteria\ndescription: Full definition-of-done checklist for a deep-review loop -- loop completion conditions, the binary quality gates that must pass before STOP, and release-readiness validation success criteria.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review loop completion criteria\"\n  - \"review success criteria\"\n  - \"review definition of done\"\n  - \"review release readiness validation\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.0\n---\n\n# Deep Review Completion Criteria\n\nFull definition-of-done checklist for a deep-review loop: loop completion conditions, the binary quality gates STOP must clear, and release-readiness validation success criteria.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/completion_criteria.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Completion Criteria\ndescription: Full definition-of-done checklist for a deep-review loop -- loop completion conditions, the binary quality gates that must pass before STOP, and release-readiness validation success criteria.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review loop completion criteria\"\n  - \"review success criteria\"\n  - \"review definition of done\"\n  - \"review release readiness validation\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.0\n---\n\n# Deep Review Completion Criteria\n\nFull definition-of-done checklist for a deep-review loop: loop completion conditions, the binary quality gates STOP must clear, and release-readiness validation success criteria.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThis reference is the authoritative checklist for \"is this review loop actually done.\" SKILL.md §6 SUCCESS CRITERIA carries a condensed summary and links here for the full enumeration; use this file when verifying a completed run, debugging a premature STOP, or reconciling completion metadata against the loop's real state.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Verifying a review loop's completion before accepting its verdict.\n- Debugging why STOP was blocked or why synthesis produced an incomplete report.\n- Reconciling `review-report.md` claims against the canonical state files.\n- Auditing a run for the release-readiness handoff.\n\n### Relationship to `loop_state_and_gates.md`\n\n`references/protocol/loop_state_and_gates.md` defines the three state-machine-level binary gates (Evidence, Scope, Coverage) that block a STOP *decision* inside the convergence check. This file is the broader definition-of-done: it also covers artifact existence, report structure, severity-field completeness, and the release-readiness handoff -- checked once the loop believes it has already reached STOP.\n\n---\n\n## 2. LOOP COMPLETION\n\nA review loop is considered complete when every item below holds:\n\n- The loop reached convergence (composite stop score above `compositeStopScore`, with required gates green) OR hit `maxIterations` without false-positive STOP.\n- Every configured review dimension has at least one full iteration of coverage recorded in `deep-review-state.jsonl` and reflected in `deep-review-strategy.md`.\n- Required traceability protocols (`spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`) executed at least once. Overlay protocols that apply to the target type ran or were explicitly marked N/A.\n- All canonical state files exist and parse cleanly: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, and one `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` per dispatched iteration.\n- `review/resource-map.md` was emitted from converged delta evidence unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag `--no-resource-map`).\n- `review/review-report.md` carries all 9 core sections (Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix) plus the conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present == true`.\n- Canonical continuity surfaces updated via `generate-context.js` (description.json, graph-metadata.json, indexed memory entries).\n\n---\n\n## 3. QUALITY GATES\n\nEach gate is binary: pass or block. STOP cannot be legal until every gate passes.\n\n- **Config validity**: `deep-review-config.json` parses, names every required field, and lineage block matches the current run (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`).\n- **Strategy initialization**: `deep-review-strategy.md` carries the Files Under Review table, Cross-Reference Status grouped by core vs overlay, Known Context, and Review Boundaries.\n- **State consistency**: `deep-review-state.jsonl` opens with the config record and appends one iteration record per dispatched iteration. Reducer-owned fields in `deep-review-findings-registry.json` reconcile against JSONL totals.\n- **Iteration completeness**: every dispatched iteration produced both an `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` (non-empty, ending with the canonical `Review verdict: PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` line) AND a JSONL delta record with `findingDetails[]`, `findingsSummary`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n- **Severity coverage**: every reported finding carries `severity` in {P0, P1, P2}, `category`, `file:line` evidence, `finding_class`, and a `content_hash` for synthesis dedup.\n- **Advisory numeric score**: `riskScore` may appear in finding details as non-gating context only; verdict logic must ignore it.\n- **Adversarial replay**: every P0 finding survived adversarial self-check. Rejected P0s downgraded with rationale recorded in the iteration narrative.\n- **Coverage threshold**: `dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count` AND required traceability protocols covered, stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations.\n- **Acceptance coverage**: when the spec-folder lifecycle predicate is active, the final report records `AC_COVERAGE` status, covered/total, floor, and next action; default-off INFO output is advisory and does not by itself block STOP.\n- **Security-sensitive override**: when the run targets security, path handling, env precedence, schema boundaries, persistence, or shared policy, the gates from `references/convergence/convergence.md` \"Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\" apply (`minStabilizationPasses=2`, closed-finding replay required, fix-completeness gate enforced).\n\n---\n\n## 4. VALIDATION SUCCESS\n\nThe release-readiness handoff is valid when:\n\n- The final report records stop reason, iteration count, dimension coverage, severity counts (P0/P1/P2), verdict (PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL), and release-readiness state (`in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking`).\n- Verdict logic matches: PASS = no P0/P1 findings (P2 advisories permitted with `hasAdvisories: true`). CONDITIONAL = P1 findings present with remediation plan. FAIL = any P0 confirmed after adversarial self-check.\n- `resource-map.md` Phase-5 Augmentation section (if present) lists novel logic gaps with iteration source links, or explicitly records the empty-result case.\n- `skill_advisor.py \"run a deep review loop\" --threshold 0.8` still surfaces the skill after any graph-metadata edits.\n- `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` exits 0 on the target spec folder.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/protocol/loop_state_and_gates.md` -- state transitions, error handling, and the Evidence/Scope/Coverage STOP-decision gates.\n- `references/state/state_outputs.md` -- packet file ownership and the `review-report.md` section list.\n- `references/state/state_format.md` -- schemas for every state file referenced above.\n- `references/convergence/convergence.md` -- composite stop score, `minStabilizationPasses`, and Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":87,"totalLines":87,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/completion_criteria.md","time":{"start":1783915534084,"end":1783915534121}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f7bdebefd030b5016a54640de970819195c3e58f6dceac53"}},"id":"prt_f59a6d703001eSHrcRJj5bVMoj","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915534124,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Z8R9G2SHohYuhzKzCMOJxIZq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","offset":1,"limit":1500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n2: # This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n3: # convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n4: # and validation expectations.\n5: \n6: meta:\n7:   ownerSkill: deep-review\n8:   reviewModeVersion: 2\n9:   generatedNotice:\n10:     warning: \"Exactly one artifact is machine-generated from this file: render.artifacts[0] (review-contract-snapshot). Its begin/end markers live on that artifact entry, not here. Every other contract-taxonomy consumer is hand-authored; see authoredArtifacts.\"\n11:   sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n12: \n13: # Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\n14: contract:\n15:   defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n16: \n17:   contextSnapshot:\n18:     requiredAtInit: true\n19:     ownerArtifact: deep-review-strategy.md\n20:     section: Known Context\n21:     source: bounded-review-context-snapshot\n22:     bounded: true\n23:     pointerBased: true\n24:     includes:\n25:       - targetPointers\n26:       - behaviorClaims\n27:       - reuseAndConventionPointers\n28:       - riskAreasAndContextGaps\n29:     forbids:\n30:       - deepContextDispatch\n31:       - fullSourceBodyInlining\n32:       - contextLoopReportCreation\n33:       - scopeWideningBeyondReviewTarget\n34: \n35:   # Review target taxonomy.\n36:   targetTypes:\n37:     - id: spec-folder\n38:       cliValue: spec-folder\n39:       label: Spec Folder\n40:       description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n41:     - id: skill\n42:       cliValue: skill\n43:       label: Skill\n44:       description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n45:     - id: agent\n46:       cliValue: agent\n47:       label: Agent\n48:       description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n49:     - id: track\n50:       cliValue: track\n51:       label: Track\n52:       description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n53:     - id: files\n54:       cliValue: files\n55:       label: Files\n56:       description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n57: \n58:   # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n59:   # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n60:   dimensions:\n61:     - id: correctness\n62:       priority: 1\n63:       label: Correctness\n64:       checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n65:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n66:     - id: security\n67:       priority: 2\n68:       label: Security\n69:       checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n70:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n71:     - id: traceability\n72:       priority: 3\n73:       label: Traceability\n74:       checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n75:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n76:     - id: maintainability\n77:       priority: 4\n78:       label: Maintainability\n79:       checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n80:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n81: \n82:   # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n83:   severities:\n84:     - id: P0\n85:       weight: 10.0\n86:       label: Blocker\n87:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n88:     - id: P1\n89:       weight: 5.0\n90:       label: Required\n91:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n92:     - id: P2\n93:       weight: 1.0\n94:       label: Suggestion\n95:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n96: \n97:   # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n98:   verdicts:\n99:     - id: FAIL\n100:       label: Fail\n101:       condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n102:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n103:     - id: CONDITIONAL\n104:       label: Conditional\n105:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n106:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n107:     - id: PASS\n108:       label: Pass\n109:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n110:       hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n111:       nextCommand: /create:changelog\n112: \n113:   # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n114:   qualityGates:\n115:     - id: evidence\n116:       label: Evidence\n117:       binary: true\n118:       combines:\n119:         - evidence-completeness\n120:         - no-inference-only\n121:       rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n122:     - id: scope\n123:       label: Scope\n124:       binary: true\n125:       combines:\n126:         - scope-alignment\n127:       rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n128:     - id: coverage\n129:       label: Coverage\n130:       binary: true\n131:       combines:\n132:         - severity-coverage\n133:         - cross-reference\n134:       rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n135: \n136:   # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n137:   convergence:\n138:     defaults:\n139:       maxIterations: 7\n140:       convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n141:       stuckThreshold: 2\n142:     signals:\n143:       - id: rolling-average\n144:         weight: 0.30\n145:         description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n146:       - id: mad-noise-floor\n147:         weight: 0.25\n148:         description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n149:       - id: dimension-coverage\n150:         weight: 0.45\n151:         description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n152:     severityMath:\n153:       refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n154:       p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n155:       noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n156:     coverageAge:\n157:       minStabilizationPasses: 1\n158:     thresholds:\n159:       rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n160:       noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n161:       compositeStopScore: 0.60\n162: \n163:   lifecycleModes:\n164:     - id: new\n165:       description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n166:     - id: resume\n167:       description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n168:     - id: restart\n169:       description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n170:     - id: fork\n171:       status: deferred\n172:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n173:     - id: completed-continue\n174:       status: deferred\n175:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n176: \n177:   lineageFields:\n178:     - sessionId\n179:     - parentSessionId\n180:     - lineageMode\n181:     - generation\n182:     - continuedFromRun\n183: \n184:   reducer:\n185:     enabled: true\n186:     inputs:\n187:       - latestJSONLDelta\n188:       - newIterationFile\n189:       - priorReducedState\n190:     outputs:\n191:       - findingsRegistry\n192:       - dashboardMetrics\n193:       - strategyUpdates\n194:     failureModes:\n195:       malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n196:       missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n197:       schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n198:     idempotent: true\n199: \n200:   releaseReadinessStates:\n201:     - id: in-progress\n202:       description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n203:     - id: converged\n204:       description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n205:     - id: release-blocking\n206:       description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n207: \n208:   # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n209:   # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n210:   crossReferenceProtocols:\n211:     - id: spec_code\n212:       dimension: traceability\n213:       level: core\n214:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n215:       gateClass: hard\n216:       passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n217:       partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n218:       failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n219:     - id: checklist_evidence\n220:       dimension: traceability\n221:       level: core\n222:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n223:       gateClass: hard\n224:       passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n225:       partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n226:       failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n227:     - id: skill_agent\n228:       dimension: traceability\n229:       level: overlay\n230:       appliesTo: [skill]\n231:       gateClass: advisory\n232:       passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n233:       partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n234:       failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n235:     - id: agent_cross_runtime\n236:       dimension: traceability\n237:       level: overlay\n238:       appliesTo: [agent]\n239:       gateClass: advisory\n240:       passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n241:       partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n242:       failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n243:     - id: feature_catalog_code\n244:       dimension: traceability\n245:       level: overlay\n246:       appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n247:       gateClass: advisory\n248:       passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n249:       partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n250:       failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n251:     - id: playbook_capability\n252:       dimension: traceability\n253:       level: overlay\n254:       appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n255:       gateClass: advisory\n256:       passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n257:       partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n258:       failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n259: \n260:   # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n261:   outputs:\n262:     config:\n263:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n264:       machineOwned: false\n265:       fields:\n266:         - sessionId\n267:         - parentSessionId\n268:         - lineageMode\n269:         - generation\n270:         - continuedFromRun\n271:         - releaseReadinessState\n272:     findingsRegistry:\n273:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n274:       machineOwned: true\n275:       sections:\n276:         - openFindings\n277:         - resolvedFindings\n278:         - repeatedFindings\n279:         - dimensionCoverage\n280:         - findingsBySeverity\n281:         - convergenceScore\n282:     reviewReport:\n283:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n284:       sections:\n285:         - executive-summary\n286:         - planning-trigger\n287:         - active-finding-registry\n288:         - remediation-workstreams\n289:         - spec-seed\n290:         - plan-seed\n291:         - traceability-status\n292:         - deferred-items\n293:         - audit-appendix\n294:     strategy:\n295:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n296:       requiredSections:\n297:         - topic\n298:         - review-dimensions\n299:         - completed-dimensions\n300:         - running-findings\n301:         - what-worked\n302:         - what-failed\n303:         - exhausted-approaches\n304:         - ruled-out-directions\n305:         - next-focus\n306:         - known-context\n307:         - cross-reference-status\n308:         - files-under-review\n309:         - review-boundaries\n310:     dashboard:\n311:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n312:       machineOwned: true\n313:       sections:\n314:         - status\n315:         - findings-summary\n316:         - dimension-coverage\n317:         - progress\n318:         - next-focus\n319:     pauseSentinel:\n320:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n321:       machineOwned: false\n322:       description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n323:     jsonl:\n324:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n325:       iterationRecord:\n326:         required:\n327:           - type\n328:           - mode\n329:           - run\n330:           - status\n331:           - focus\n332:           - dimensions\n333:           - filesReviewed\n334:           - findingsCount\n335:           - findingsSummary\n336:           - findingsNew\n337:           - findingDetails\n338:           - newFindingsRatio\n339:           - sessionId\n340:           - generation\n341:           - lineageMode\n342:           - timestamp\n343:           - durationMs\n344:         optional:\n345:           - parentSessionId\n346:           - continuedFromRun\n347:           - findingsRefined\n348:           - findingRefs\n349:           - traceabilityChecks\n350:           - coverage\n351:           - noveltyJustification\n352:           - ruledOut\n353:           - focusTrack\n354:           - scoreEstimate\n355:           - segment\n356:           - convergenceSignals\n357:           - graphEvents\n358:       synthesisEvent:\n359:         required:\n360:           - type\n361:           - event\n362:           - mode\n363:           - totalIterations\n364:           - verdict\n365:           - activeP0\n366:           - activeP1\n367:           - activeP2\n368:           - dimensionCoverage\n369:           - stopReason\n370:           - timestamp\n371: \n372: # Render targets define machine-generated contract fragments. Exactly one\n373: # target is real: the human-readable snapshot rendered by\n374: # render-contract-snapshot.cjs. Everything else that mentions this contract's\n375: # taxonomy (target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, quality gates,\n376: # convergence, cross-reference protocols) is hand-authored — see\n377: # authoredArtifacts below, not rendered from this file.\n378: render:\n379:   artifacts:\n380:     - id: review-contract-snapshot\n381:       path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract_snapshot.md\n382:       ownership: generated\n383:       generator: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/render-contract-snapshot.cjs\n384:       format: markdown\n385:       markers:\n386:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n387:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n388:       sections:\n389:         - meta\n390:         - target-types\n391:         - dimensions\n392:         - severities\n393:         - verdicts\n394:         - quality-gates\n395:         - convergence\n396:         - cross-reference-protocols\n397:         - outputs\n398:         - validation\n399: \n400: # Authored artifacts reference this manifest's taxonomy in hand-written prose\n401: # or YAML. They are not machine-rendered and carry no generated markers;\n402: # operators keep them in sync by hand when this contract changes. Each\n403: # entry's enumParityChecked list is mechanically enforced (not aspirational):\n404: # deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts confirms every id in those families\n405: # still appears literally in the target file, as a lightweight drift\n406: # tripwire that does not require full rendering.\n407: authoredArtifacts:\n408:   - id: workflow-auto\n409:     path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\n410:     ownership: authored\n411:     format: yaml\n412:     enumParityChecked:\n413:       - dimensions\n414:       - severities\n415:       - verdicts\n416:       - cross-reference-protocols\n417:     note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :auto command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n418:   - id: workflow-confirm\n419:     path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml\n420:     ownership: authored\n421:     format: yaml\n422:     enumParityChecked:\n423:       - dimensions\n424:       - severities\n425:       - verdicts\n426:       - cross-reference-protocols\n427:     note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :confirm command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n428:   - id: agent-opencode\n429:     path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n430:     ownership: authored\n431:     format: markdown\n432:     enumParityChecked:\n433:       - dimensions\n434:       - severities\n435:       - verdicts\n436:     note: Hand-maintained OpenCode agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n437:   - id: agent-claude\n438:     path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n439:     ownership: authored\n440:     format: markdown\n441:     enumParityChecked:\n442:       - dimensions\n443:       - severities\n444:       - verdicts\n445:     note: Hand-maintained Claude Code agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n446:   - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n447:     path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md\n448:     ownership: authored\n449:     format: markdown\n450:     enumParityChecked:\n451:       - dimensions\n452:       - severities\n453:       - verdicts\n454:     note: Hand-maintained quick reference. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n455: \n456: # Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\n457: validation:\n458:   schemaVersion: 1\n459:   checks:\n460:     - id: schema\n461:       description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n462:     - id: render-verify\n463:       description: \"Re-render the single review-contract-snapshot artifact (node render-contract-snapshot.cjs --check) and fail on drift. The five authoredArtifacts entries are hand-maintained and are not re-rendered by this check.\"\n464:     - id: marker-integrity\n465:       description: Ensure the review-contract-snapshot artifact contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n466:     - id: enum-parity\n467:       description: \"Confirm the dimension, severity, and verdict ids (plus cross-reference-protocol ids for the two workflow YAMLs) declared in each authoredArtifacts entry's enumParityChecked are still literally present in that file; see deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts.\"\n468:     - id: jsonl-parity\n469:       description: Ensure JSONL iteration and synthesis-event fields match the outputs contract.\n470:     - id: lifecycle-parity\n471:       description: \"Ensure lifecycle mode docs and workflow branches agree on the three supported modes: new, resume, and restart.\"\n472:     - id: reducer-contract\n473:       description: Ensure reducer inputs, outputs, and findings-registry metrics are documented consistently across assets and runtime mirrors.\n474:     - id: duplicate-literal-lint\n475:       description: Detect duplicated hard-coded review taxonomy literals outside generated sections.\n476:     - id: runtime-coverage\n477:       description: Ensure every supported runtime deep-review agent has a declared authoredArtifacts entry and parity coverage.\n478:     - id: playbook-assertions\n479:       description: Assert manual testing playbook scenarios reference the canonical simplified contract where applicable.\n\n(End of file - total 479 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Exactly one artifact is machine-generated from this file: render.artifacts[0] (review-contract-snapshot). Its begin/end markers live on that artifact entry, not here. Every other contract-taxonomy consumer is hand-authored; see authoredArtifacts.\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  contextSnapshot:\n    requiredAtInit: true\n    ownerArtifact: deep-review-strategy.md\n    section: Known Context","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","text":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Exactly one artifact is machine-generated from this file: render.artifacts[0] (review-contract-snapshot). Its begin/end markers live on that artifact entry, not here. Every other contract-taxonomy consumer is hand-authored; see authoredArtifacts.\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  contextSnapshot:\n    requiredAtInit: true\n    ownerArtifact: deep-review-strategy.md\n    section: Known Context\n    source: bounded-review-context-snapshot\n    bounded: true\n    pointerBased: true\n    includes:\n      - targetPointers\n      - behaviorClaims\n      - reuseAndConventionPointers\n      - riskAreasAndContextGaps\n    forbids:\n      - deepContextDispatch\n      - fullSourceBodyInlining\n      - contextLoopReportCreation\n      - scopeWideningBeyondReviewTarget\n\n  # Review target taxonomy.\n  targetTypes:\n    - id: spec-folder\n      cliValue: spec-folder\n      label: Spec Folder\n      description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n    - id: skill\n      cliValue: skill\n      label: Skill\n      description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n    - id: agent\n      cliValue: agent\n      label: Agent\n      description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n    - id: track\n      cliValue: track\n      label: Track\n      description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n    - id: files\n      cliValue: files\n      label: Files\n      description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n\n  # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n  # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n  dimensions:\n    - id: correctness\n      priority: 1\n      label: Correctness\n      checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: security\n      priority: 2\n      label: Security\n      checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: traceability\n      priority: 3\n      label: Traceability\n      checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n    - id: maintainability\n      priority: 4\n      label: Maintainability\n      checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n\n  # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n  severities:\n    - id: P0\n      weight: 10.0\n      label: Blocker\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P1\n      weight: 5.0\n      label: Required\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P2\n      weight: 1.0\n      label: Suggestion\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n\n  # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n  verdicts:\n    - id: FAIL\n      label: Fail\n      condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: CONDITIONAL\n      label: Conditional\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: PASS\n      label: Pass\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n      hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n      nextCommand: /create:changelog\n\n  # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n  qualityGates:\n    - id: evidence\n      label: Evidence\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - evidence-completeness\n        - no-inference-only\n      rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n    - id: scope\n      label: Scope\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - scope-alignment\n      rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n    - id: coverage\n      label: Coverage\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - severity-coverage\n        - cross-reference\n      rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n\n  # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n  convergence:\n    defaults:\n      maxIterations: 7\n      convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n      stuckThreshold: 2\n    signals:\n      - id: rolling-average\n        weight: 0.30\n        description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n      - id: mad-noise-floor\n        weight: 0.25\n        description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n      - id: dimension-coverage\n        weight: 0.45\n        description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n    severityMath:\n      refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n      p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n      noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n    coverageAge:\n      minStabilizationPasses: 1\n    thresholds:\n      rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n      noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n      compositeStopScore: 0.60\n\n  lifecycleModes:\n    - id: new\n      description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n    - id: resume\n      description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n    - id: restart\n      description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n    - id: fork\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n    - id: completed-continue\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n\n  lineageFields:\n    - sessionId\n    - parentSessionId\n    - lineageMode\n    - generation\n    - continuedFromRun\n\n  reducer:\n    enabled: true\n    inputs:\n      - latestJSONLDelta\n      - newIterationFile\n      - priorReducedState\n    outputs:\n      - findingsRegistry\n      - dashboardMetrics\n      - strategyUpdates\n    failureModes:\n      malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n      missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n      schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n    idempotent: true\n\n  releaseReadinessStates:\n    - id: in-progress\n      description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n    - id: converged\n      description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n    - id: release-blocking\n      description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n\n  # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n  # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n  crossReferenceProtocols:\n    - id: spec_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n      partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n      failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n    - id: checklist_evidence\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n      partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n      failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n    - id: skill_agent\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n      partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n      failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n    - id: agent_cross_runtime\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [agent]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n      partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n      failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n    - id: feature_catalog_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n      partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n      failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n    - id: playbook_capability\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n      partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n      failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n\n  # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n  outputs:\n    config:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      fields:\n        - sessionId\n        - parentSessionId\n        - lineageMode\n        - generation\n        - continuedFromRun\n        - releaseReadinessState\n    findingsRegistry:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - openFindings\n        - resolvedFindings\n        - repeatedFindings\n        - dimensionCoverage\n        - findingsBySeverity\n        - convergenceScore\n    reviewReport:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n      sections:\n        - executive-summary\n        - planning-trigger\n        - active-finding-registry\n        - remediation-workstreams\n        - spec-seed\n        - plan-seed\n        - traceability-status\n        - deferred-items\n        - audit-appendix\n    strategy:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n      requiredSections:\n        - topic\n        - review-dimensions\n        - completed-dimensions\n        - running-findings\n        - what-worked\n        - what-failed\n        - exhausted-approaches\n        - ruled-out-directions\n        - next-focus\n        - known-context\n        - cross-reference-status\n        - files-under-review\n        - review-boundaries\n    dashboard:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - status\n        - findings-summary\n        - dimension-coverage\n        - progress\n        - next-focus\n    pauseSentinel:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n    jsonl:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n      iterationRecord:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - mode\n          - run\n          - status\n          - focus\n          - dimensions\n          - filesReviewed\n          - findingsCount\n          - findingsSummary\n          - findingsNew\n          - findingDetails\n          - newFindingsRatio\n          - sessionId\n          - generation\n          - lineageMode\n          - timestamp\n          - durationMs\n        optional:\n          - parentSessionId\n          - continuedFromRun\n          - findingsRefined\n          - findingRefs\n          - traceabilityChecks\n          - coverage\n          - noveltyJustification\n          - ruledOut\n          - focusTrack\n          - scoreEstimate\n          - segment\n          - convergenceSignals\n          - graphEvents\n      synthesisEvent:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - event\n          - mode\n          - totalIterations\n          - verdict\n          - activeP0\n          - activeP1\n          - activeP2\n          - dimensionCoverage\n          - stopReason\n          - timestamp\n\n# Render targets define machine-generated contract fragments. Exactly one\n# target is real: the human-readable snapshot rendered by\n# render-contract-snapshot.cjs. Everything else that mentions this contract's\n# taxonomy (target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, quality gates,\n# convergence, cross-reference protocols) is hand-authored — see\n# authoredArtifacts below, not rendered from this file.\nrender:\n  artifacts:\n    - id: review-contract-snapshot\n      path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract_snapshot.md\n      ownership: generated\n      generator: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/render-contract-snapshot.cjs\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n      sections:\n        - meta\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - convergence\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n        - validation\n\n# Authored artifacts reference this manifest's taxonomy in hand-written prose\n# or YAML. They are not machine-rendered and carry no generated markers;\n# operators keep them in sync by hand when this contract changes. Each\n# entry's enumParityChecked list is mechanically enforced (not aspirational):\n# deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts confirms every id in those families\n# still appears literally in the target file, as a lightweight drift\n# tripwire that does not require full rendering.\nauthoredArtifacts:\n  - id: workflow-auto\n    path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\n    ownership: authored\n    format: yaml\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n      - cross-reference-protocols\n    note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :auto command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: workflow-confirm\n    path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml\n    ownership: authored\n    format: yaml\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n      - cross-reference-protocols\n    note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :confirm command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: agent-opencode\n    path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n    ownership: authored\n    format: markdown\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n    note: Hand-maintained OpenCode agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: agent-claude\n    path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n    ownership: authored\n    format: markdown\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n    note: Hand-maintained Claude Code agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n    path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md\n    ownership: authored\n    format: markdown\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n    note: Hand-maintained quick reference. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n\n# Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\nvalidation:\n  schemaVersion: 1\n  checks:\n    - id: schema\n      description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n    - id: render-verify\n      description: \"Re-render the single review-contract-snapshot artifact (node render-contract-snapshot.cjs --check) and fail on drift. The five authoredArtifacts entries are hand-maintained and are not re-rendered by this check.\"\n    - id: marker-integrity\n      description: Ensure the review-contract-snapshot artifact contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n    - id: enum-parity\n      description: \"Confirm the dimension, severity, and verdict ids (plus cross-reference-protocol ids for the two workflow YAMLs) declared in each authoredArtifacts entry's enumParityChecked are still literally present in that file; see deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts.\"\n    - id: jsonl-parity\n      description: Ensure JSONL iteration and synthesis-event fields match the outputs contract.\n    - id: lifecycle-parity\n      description: \"Ensure lifecycle mode docs and workflow branches agree on the three supported modes: new, resume, and restart.\"\n    - id: reducer-contract\n      description: Ensure reducer inputs, outputs, and findings-registry metrics are documented consistently across assets and runtime mirrors.\n    - id: duplicate-literal-lint\n      description: Detect duplicated hard-coded review taxonomy literals outside generated sections.\n    - id: runtime-coverage\n      description: Ensure every supported runtime deep-review agent has a declared authoredArtifacts entry and parity coverage.\n    - id: playbook-assertions\n      description: Assert manual testing playbook scenarios reference the canonical simplified contract where applicable.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":479,"totalLines":479,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","time":{"start":1783915534102,"end":1783915534122}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f7bdebefd030b5016a54640de9788191a9eac4a6ccd9a55a"}},"id":"prt_f59a6d705001PG33YXwBmfgvhb","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783915534700,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"id":"prt_f59a6d96a001pIbeTc1tHVT24Z","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","messageID":"msg_f59a699f2001viJBHAi42MDUpK","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":60335,"input":29462,"output":546,"reasoning":119,"cache":{"write":0,"read":30208}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783915538039,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"id":"prt_f59a6e675001h7EqQr2SrWEu6d","messageID":"msg_f59a6db98001t6OLZbi2mQIYHk","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915550402,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_NZVWND9LKELm6DwLfCaxSNWI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":634,"limit":1800},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n634:                fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n635:                candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n636:                candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n637:                candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n638:                graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n639:                graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n640:                graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n641:                graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n642:                recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n643:           6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n644:                a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n645:                b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n646:                     decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n647:                     stop_blocked = true\n648:                     stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n649:                     # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n650:                     # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n651:                     # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n652:                     # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n653:                     blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n654:                     blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n655:                     graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n656:                     recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n657:                c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n658:                     decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n659:                     stop_blocked = false\n660:                     reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n661:                d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n662:         outputs:\n663:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n664:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n665:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n666:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n667:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n668:           - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n669:           - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n670:           - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n671:           - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n672:           - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n673:           - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n674:           - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n675:           - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n676:           - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n677:           - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n678:           - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n679:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n680:           - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n681:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n682:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n683:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n684:           - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n685:           - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n686:           - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n687:           - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n688:           - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n689:           - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n690:           - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n691:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n692:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n693:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n694:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n695:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n696: \n697:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n698:         action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n699:         if_blocked:\n700:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n701:           log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n702:         if_not_blocked:\n703:           proceed: true\n704: \n705:       step_handle_convergence:\n706:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n707:         if_stop:\n708:           branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason == 'all_dimensions_clean'\"\n709:           if_divergent_eligible:\n710:             eligibility_contract:\n711:               required_decision: \"STOP\"\n712:               eligible_reasons: [all_dimensions_clean]\n713:               excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n714:               fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot. The nine legal-stop gates have already run and remain unchanged.\"\n715:             steps:\n716:               step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n717:                 action: \"Generate state-grounded read-only review candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n718:                 command: |\n719:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n720:                   import {\n721:                     buildReviewPivotPreparationInput,\n722:                     renderReviewPivotSeatPrompt,\n723:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/divergent-review-pivot.ts';\n724:                   import {\n725:                     preparePivotTransaction,\n726:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n727: \n728:                   const input = buildReviewPivotPreparationInput({\n729:                     artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n730:                     configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n731:                     stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n732:                     strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n733:                     registryPath: '{state_paths.findings_registry}',\n734:                     currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n735:                     maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n736:                     triggerReason: '{reason}',\n737:                   });\n738:                   const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n739:                   const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n740:                     ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n741:                         seat.id,\n742:                         renderReviewPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n743:                       ]))\n744:                     : {};\n745:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n746:                     ...prepared,\n747:                     seatPrompts,\n748:                     boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n749:                   })}\\n`);\n750:                   EOF\n751:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n752:                 outputs:\n753:                   - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n754:                   - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n755:                   - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n756:                   - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n757:                   - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n758:                   - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n759:                   - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n760:                   - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n761:                   - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n762:                   - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n763:                   - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n764:                   - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n765:                   - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n766:                 short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n767: \n768:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n769:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n770:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n771:                 capture_timing: true\n772:                 if_native:\n773:                   dispatch:\n774:                     agent: deep-review\n775:                     model: opus\n776:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n777:                   wait_for_completion: true\n778:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n779:                 outputs:\n780:                   - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n781:                   - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n782:                   - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n783:                   - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n784:                   - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n785:                   - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n786: \n787:               step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n788:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n789:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n790:                 command: |\n791:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n792:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n793:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n794:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n795:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n796:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n797:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n798:                   EOF\n799:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n800: \n801:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n802:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the critical read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n803:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n804:                 capture_timing: true\n805:                 if_native:\n806:                   dispatch:\n807:                     agent: deep-review\n808:                     model: opus\n809:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n810:                   wait_for_completion: true\n811:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n812:                 outputs:\n813:                   - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n814:                   - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n815:                   - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n816:                   - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n817:                   - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n818:                   - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n819: \n820:               step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n821:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n822:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n823:                 command: |\n824:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n825:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n826:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n827:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n828:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n829:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n830:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n831:                   EOF\n832:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n833: \n834:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n835:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n836:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n837:                 capture_timing: true\n838:                 if_native:\n839:                   dispatch:\n840:                     agent: deep-review\n841:                     model: opus\n842:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n843:                   wait_for_completion: true\n844:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n845:                 outputs:\n846:                   - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n847:                   - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n848:                   - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n849:                   - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n850:                   - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n851:                   - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n852: \n853:               step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n854:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n855:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n856:                 command: |\n857:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n858:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n859:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n860:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n861:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n862:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n863:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n864:                   EOF\n865:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n866: \n867:               step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n868:                 action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n869:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n870:                 command: |\n871:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n872:                   import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n873:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n874:                   EOF\n875:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n876:                 outputs:\n877:                   - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n878: \n879:               step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n880:                 action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n881:                 branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n882:                 if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n883:                 if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n884: \n885:               step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n886:                 action: \"Adopt a successful read-only review direction or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n887:                 branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n888:                 if_completed:\n889:                   set:\n890:                     next_dimension: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n891:                     pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n892:                     saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n893:                   command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n894:                   log: \"Divergent review pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n895:                   proceed_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n896:                 if_failed:\n897:                   log: \"Divergent review pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n898:                   skip_to: phase_synthesis\n899:             on_error:\n900:               log: \"Divergent review pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n901:               skip_to: phase_synthesis\n902:           if_existing_terminal_path:\n903:             log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n904:             skip_to: phase_synthesis\n905:         if_blocked:\n906:           log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n907:         if_stuck_recovery:\n908:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n909:           recovery_strategies:\n910:             - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n911:             - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n912:             - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n913:           pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n914:           set:\n915:             next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n916:             pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n917:             pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n918:             pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n919:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n920:         if_continue:\n921:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n922: \n923:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n924:         action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n925:         if_pending_pause_event:\n926:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n927:           message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n928:           reset:\n929:             pending_stop_event: null\n930:             pending_stop_reason: null\n931:             pending_stop_detail: null\n932:           halt: true\n933:         if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n934:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n935:           reset:\n936:             pending_stop_event: null\n937:             pending_stop_reason: null\n938:             pending_stop_detail: null\n939:         if_no_pending_event:\n940:           proceed: true\n941: \n942:       step_generate_state_summary:\n943:         action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n944:         generate: |\n945:           STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n946:           Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n947:           Dimension: {next_dimension}\n948:           Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n949:           Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n950:           Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n951:           {resource_map_prompt_line}\n952:           Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n953:           Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n954:           Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n955:           Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n956: \n957:       step_marker_scan:\n958:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n959:         algorithm: |\n960:           if current_iteration > 1:\n961:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n962:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n963:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n964:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n965:                 log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n966:                 halt with exit code 2\n967:         note: |\n968:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n969:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n970:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n971:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n972: \n973:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n974:         action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n975:         resolve_executor:\n976:           source: \"config.executor\"\n977:           loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n978:         pre_dispatch:\n979:           generate_summary: |\n980:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n981:             Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n982:             Dimension: {next_dimension}\n983:             Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n984:             Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n985:             Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n986:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n987:             Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n988:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n989:             Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n990:             Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n991:           render_prompt_pack:\n992:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n993:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n994:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n995:             variables:\n996:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n997:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n998:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n999:               next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n1000:               review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n1001:               review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n1002:               p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n1003:               p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n1004:               p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n1005:               pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n1006:               saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n1007:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1008:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1009:               state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1010:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1011:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1012:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1013:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n1014:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n1015:           call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n1016:           args:\n1017:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1018:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n1019:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1020:         branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n1021:         if_native:\n1022:           dispatch:\n1023:             agent: deep-review\n1024:             model: opus\n1025:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n1026:           wait_for_completion: true\n1027:         if_cli_copilot:\n1028:           command: |\n1029:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1030:             import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1031:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1032: \n1033:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1034:             import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n1035: \n1036:             const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n1037:             const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n1038: \n1039:             // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n1040:             // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n1041:             // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n1042:             // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n1043:             // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n1044:             // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n1045:             // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n1046:             const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n1047:             const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n1048: \n1049:             const baseArgs = [\n1050:               '-p',\n1051:               prompt,\n1052:               '--model',\n1053:               '{config.executor.model}',\n1054:               '--allow-all-tools',\n1055:               '--no-ask-user',\n1056:             ];\n1057: \n1058:             const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n1059:               promptPath,\n1060:               prompt,\n1061:               targetAuthority,\n1062:               baseArgv: baseArgs,\n1063:             });\n1064: \n1065:             // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n1066:             // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n1067:             // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n1068:             // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n1069:             // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n1070:             if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n1071:               writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n1072:             }\n1073: \n1074:             // Copilot is routed through the audited executor wrapper so it produces\n1075:             // INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts alongside claude-code/opencode\n1076:             // There is no cli-copilot kind in the executor schema, so it\n1077:             // dispatches as kind:'native' (full env passthrough, no recursion-guard\n1078:             // layer configured for copilot); the receipt still records the real\n1079:             // 'copilot' command + built.argv as facts.\n1080:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1081:               command: 'deep/review',\n1082:               mode: 'review',\n1083:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1084:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1085:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1086:               executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1087:               branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1088:               sessionId: '{session_id}',\n1089:               generation: Number('{generation}'),\n1090:             };\n1091:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1092:             process.exit(\n1093:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1094:                 command: 'copilot',\n1095:                 args: built.argv,\n1096:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1097:                 timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1098:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1099:                 executor: {\n1100:                   kind: 'native',\n1101:                   model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1102:                   configDir: null,\n1103:                   reasoningEffort: null,\n1104:                   serviceTier: null,\n1105:                   sandboxMode: null,\n1106:                   timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1107:                   governor: null,\n1108:                 },\n1109:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1110:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1111:                 dispatchId,\n1112:               }),\n1113:             );\n1114:             EOF\n1115:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1116:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1117:           wait_for_completion: true\n1118:           notes:\n1119:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so copilot produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; built.argv (@PROMPT_PATH or positional) is forwarded verbatim as the receipt facts\"\n1120:             - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n1121:             - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n1122:             - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n1123:             - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n1124:             - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n1125:             - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n1126:         if_cli_claude_code:\n1127:           command: |\n1128:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1129:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1130:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1131: \n1132:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1133: \n1134:             const configDir = '{optional_claude_config_dir}';\n1135:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1136:             const executor = {\n1137:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n1138:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1139:               configDir: configDir || null,\n1140:               reasoningEffort,\n1141:               serviceTier: null,\n1142:               sandboxMode: null,\n1143:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1144:               governor: null,\n1145:             };\n1146:             const args = [\n1147:               '-p',\n1148:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n1149:               '--model',\n1150:               executor.model,\n1151:               '--permission-mode',\n1152:               'acceptEdits',\n1153:               '--output-format',\n1154:               'text',\n1155:             ];\n1156:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1157:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1158:             }\n1159: \n1160:             // CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR rides through guardContext.env; the CLAUDE_ prefix is\n1161:             // on the cli-claude-code env allowlist so buildExecutorDispatchEnv admits it.\n1162:             const parentEnv = { ...process.env };\n1163:             if (configDir) {\n1164:               parentEnv.CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR = configDir;\n1165:             }\n1166: \n1167:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1168:               command: 'deep/review',\n1169:               mode: 'review',\n1170:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1171:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1172:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1173:               executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1174:               branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1175:               sessionId: '{session_id}',\n1176:               generation: Number('{generation}'),\n1177:             };\n1178:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1179:             process.exit(\n1180:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1181:                 command: 'claude',\n1182:                 args,\n1183:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1184:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1185:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1186:                 executor,\n1187:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1188:                 guardContext: { env: parentEnv },\n1189:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1190:                 dispatchId,\n1191:               }),\n1192:             );\n1193:             EOF\n1194:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1195:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1196:           wait_for_completion: true\n1197:           render_hint:\n1198:             optional_claude_config_dir: |\n1199:               If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n1200:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n1201:           notes:\n1202:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so claude-code produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1203:             - \"CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR is forwarded through guardContext.env (CLAUDE_ prefix is allowlisted) so account-specific Claude Code routing is preserved\"\n1204:             - \"permission-mode stays acceptEdits (review's existing iteration-write behavior); claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n1205:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n1206:         if_cli_opencode:\n1207:           command: |\n1208:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1209:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1210:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1211: \n1212:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1213: \n1214:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1215:             const executor = {\n1216:               kind: 'cli-opencode',\n1217:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1218:               configDir: null,\n1219:               reasoningEffort,\n1220:               serviceTier: null,\n1221:               sandboxMode: null,\n1222:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1223:               governor: null,\n1224:             };\n1225:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1226:             const message = 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n1227:               + '\\n\\n'\n1228:               + promptBody;\n1229:             const args = [\n1230:               'run',\n1231:               '--model',\n1232:               executor.model,\n1233:               '--format',\n1234:               'json',\n1235:               '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n1236:               '--pure',\n1237:               '--dir',\n1238:               '{repo_root}',\n1239:             ];\n1240:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1241:               args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1242:             }\n1243:             args.push(message);\n1244: \n1245:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1246:               command: 'deep/review',\n1247:               mode: 'review',\n1248:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1249:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1250:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1251:               executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1252:               branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1253:               sessionId: '{session_id}',\n1254:               generation: Number('{generation}'),\n1255:             };\n1256:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1257:             process.exit(\n1258:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1259:                 command: 'opencode',\n1260:                 args,\n1261:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1262:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1263:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1264:                 executor,\n1265:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1266:                 // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n1267:                 // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n1268:                 input: '',\n1269:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1270:                 dispatchId,\n1271:               }),\n1272:             );\n1273:             EOF\n1274:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1275:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1276:           wait_for_completion: true\n1277:           notes:\n1278:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1279:             - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n1280:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n1281:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n1282:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n1283:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. the `cli-external/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n1284:         post_dispatch_validate:\n1285:           validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n1286:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type review --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n1287:           command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|iteration_verdict_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n1288:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1289:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1290:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n1291:           route_proof:\n1292:             mode: review\n1293:             target_agent: deep-review\n1294:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n1295:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n1296:           dispatchReceipt:\n1297:             receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n1298:             dispatchId: \"review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}\"\n1299:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n1300:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1301:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n1302:           failure_reasons:\n1303:             - iteration_file_missing\n1304:             - iteration_file_empty\n1305:             - jsonl_not_appended\n1306:             - jsonl_missing_fields\n1307:             - jsonl_parse_error\n1308:             - jsonl_wrong_type\n1309:             - delta_file_missing\n1310:             - delta_file_empty\n1311:             - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n1312:             - executor_missing\n1313:             - dispatch_failure_logged\n1314:             - v2_missing_ledger\n1315:             - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n1316:             - v2_broken_linked_finding\n1317:             - v2_shallow_finding_details\n1318:             - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n1319:             - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n1320:             - route_proof_missing\n1321:             - route_proof_mismatch\n1322:           warning_surface:\n1323:             source: \"result.warnings\"\n1324:             action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n1325:             severity: \"advisory\"\n1326:             event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1327:             note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n1328:           on_failure:\n1329:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n1330:             redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error (per step_evaluate_results.on_missing_outputs) and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n1331:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n1332:         record_executor_audit:\n1333:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n1334:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1335:           field: \"executor\"\n1336:           value:\n1337:             kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n1338:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n1339:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n1340:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n1341: \n1342:       step_evaluate_results:\n1343:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n1344:         verify:\n1345:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1346:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n1347:           - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n1348:         extract:\n1349:           - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1350:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1351:           - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n1352:           - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1353:           - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1354:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1355:           - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1356:           - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n1357:         on_missing_outputs:\n1358:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n1359:           # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n1360:           # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n1361:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n1362: \n1363:       step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n1364:         action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n1365:         verify:\n1366:           - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n1367:           - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n1368:           - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n1369:         on_pass:\n1370:           set:\n1371:             claim_adjudication_passed: true\n1372:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1373:           log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n1374:         on_fail:\n1375:           action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n1376:           set:\n1377:             claim_adjudication_passed: false\n1378:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1379:           log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n1380: \n1381:       step_reduce_review_state:\n1382:         action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n1383:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1384:         read:\n1385:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1386:           - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1387:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1388:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1389:         write:\n1390:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1391:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1392:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1393:         failure_modes:\n1394:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1395:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1396:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1397:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1398:         note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n1399: \n1400:       step_graph_upsert:\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 634-1400. Use offset=1401 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"               fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n               candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n               candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n               graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n               graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n               graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n               graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n               recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n          6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n               a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n               b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                    decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                    stop_blocked = true\n                    stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n                    # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n                    # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n                    # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n                    # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n                    blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"               fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n               candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n               candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n               graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n               graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n               graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n               graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n               recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n          6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n               a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n               b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                    decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                    stop_blocked = true\n                    stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n                    # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n                    # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n                    # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n                    # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n                    blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n                    blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n                    graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n                    recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n               c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n                    decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n                    stop_blocked = false\n                    reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n               d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n          - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n          - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n          - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n          - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n          - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n          - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n          - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n          - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n          - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n          - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n          - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n          - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n        if_not_blocked:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason == 'all_dimensions_clean'\"\n          if_divergent_eligible:\n            eligibility_contract:\n              required_decision: \"STOP\"\n              eligible_reasons: [all_dimensions_clean]\n              excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n              fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot. The nine legal-stop gates have already run and remain unchanged.\"\n            steps:\n              step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Generate state-grounded read-only review candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import {\n                    buildReviewPivotPreparationInput,\n                    renderReviewPivotSeatPrompt,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/divergent-review-pivot.ts';\n                  import {\n                    preparePivotTransaction,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n\n                  const input = buildReviewPivotPreparationInput({\n                    artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n                    configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n                    stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                    strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n                    registryPath: '{state_paths.findings_registry}',\n                    currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                    maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n                    triggerReason: '{reason}',\n                  });\n                  const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n                  const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n                    ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n                        seat.id,\n                        renderReviewPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n                      ]))\n                    : {};\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n                    ...prepared,\n                    seatPrompts,\n                    boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n                  })}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n                  - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n                  - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n                  - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n                short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-review\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the critical read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-review\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-review\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n\n              step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n                if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n                if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n\n              step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Adopt a successful read-only review direction or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n                if_completed:\n                  set:\n                    next_dimension: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n                    pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                    saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n                  command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n                  log: \"Divergent review pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                  proceed_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n                if_failed:\n                  log: \"Divergent review pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n                  skip_to: phase_synthesis\n            on_error:\n              log: \"Divergent review pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n              skip_to: phase_synthesis\n          if_existing_terminal_path:\n            log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n            skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_blocked:\n          log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          recovery_strategies:\n            - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n            - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n            - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n          pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n          set:\n            next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n            pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n        if_pending_pause_event:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n          halt: true\n        if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n        if_no_pending_event:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_generate_state_summary:\n        action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n        generate: |\n          STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n          Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          Dimension: {next_dimension}\n          Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n          Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n          Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n          {resource_map_prompt_line}\n          Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n          Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n          Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Dimension: {next_dimension}\n            Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n            Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n            Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n            Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n              review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n              review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n              p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n              p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n              p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n              pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n              saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-review\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_copilot:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n            const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n\n            // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n            // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n            // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n            // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n            // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n            // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n            // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n            const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n            const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n\n            const baseArgs = [\n              '-p',\n              prompt,\n              '--model',\n              '{config.executor.model}',\n              '--allow-all-tools',\n              '--no-ask-user',\n            ];\n\n            const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n              promptPath,\n              prompt,\n              targetAuthority,\n              baseArgv: baseArgs,\n            });\n\n            // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n            // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n            // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n            // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n            // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n            if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n              writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n            }\n\n            // Copilot is routed through the audited executor wrapper so it produces\n            // INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts alongside claude-code/opencode\n            // There is no cli-copilot kind in the executor schema, so it\n            // dispatches as kind:'native' (full env passthrough, no recursion-guard\n            // layer configured for copilot); the receipt still records the real\n            // 'copilot' command + built.argv as facts.\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/review',\n              mode: 'review',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              sessionId: '{session_id}',\n              generation: Number('{generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'copilot',\n                args: built.argv,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor: {\n                  kind: 'native',\n                  model: '{config.executor.model}',\n                  configDir: null,\n                  reasoningEffort: null,\n                  serviceTier: null,\n                  sandboxMode: null,\n                  timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n                  governor: null,\n                },\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so copilot produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; built.argv (@PROMPT_PATH or positional) is forwarded verbatim as the receipt facts\"\n            - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n            - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n            - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n            - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n            - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n            - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const configDir = '{optional_claude_config_dir}';\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: configDir || null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              'acceptEdits',\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            // CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR rides through guardContext.env; the CLAUDE_ prefix is\n            // on the cli-claude-code env allowlist so buildExecutorDispatchEnv admits it.\n            const parentEnv = { ...process.env };\n            if (configDir) {\n              parentEnv.CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR = configDir;\n            }\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/review',\n              mode: 'review',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              sessionId: '{session_id}',\n              generation: Number('{generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                guardContext: { env: parentEnv },\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_claude_config_dir: |\n              If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so claude-code produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR is forwarded through guardContext.env (CLAUDE_ prefix is allowlisted) so account-specific Claude Code routing is preserved\"\n            - \"permission-mode stays acceptEdits (review's existing iteration-write behavior); claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-opencode',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n            const message = 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n              + '\\n\\n'\n              + promptBody;\n            const args = [\n              'run',\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--format',\n              'json',\n              '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n              '--pure',\n              '--dir',\n              '{repo_root}',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n            args.push(message);\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/review',\n              mode: 'review',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              sessionId: '{session_id}',\n              generation: Number('{generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'opencode',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n                // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n                input: '',\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. the `cli-external/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type review --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n          command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|iteration_verdict_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: review\n            target_agent: deep-review\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n          dispatchReceipt:\n            receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n            dispatchId: \"review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          failure_reasons:\n            - iteration_file_missing\n            - iteration_file_empty\n            - jsonl_not_appended\n            - jsonl_missing_fields\n            - jsonl_parse_error\n            - jsonl_wrong_type\n            - delta_file_missing\n            - delta_file_empty\n            - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n            - executor_missing\n            - dispatch_failure_logged\n            - v2_missing_ledger\n            - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n            - v2_broken_linked_finding\n            - v2_shallow_finding_details\n            - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n            - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n            - route_proof_missing\n            - route_proof_mismatch\n          warning_surface:\n            source: \"result.warnings\"\n            action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n            severity: \"advisory\"\n            event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error (per step_evaluate_results.on_missing_outputs) and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n        extract:\n          - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n          - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n          # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n\n      step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n        action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n        verify:\n          - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n          - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n          - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n        on_pass:\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: true\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n        on_fail:\n          action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: false\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n\n      step_reduce_review_state:\n        action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n        note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:","lineStart":634,"lineEnd":1400,"totalLines":1401,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783915550380,"end":1783915550389}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02e5dc6a466827c6016a54641e511c819188fa938d66566705"}},"id":"prt_f59a71685001s1ODaxgD96ldWZ","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a6db98001t6OLZbi2mQIYHk"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915550421,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2AToepz2tJuVtnAd0jEgeRCW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"\",\n3:   \"sessionId\": \"\",\n4:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n5:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n6:   \"generation\": 1,\n7:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n8:   \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n9:   \"maxIterations\": 7,\n10:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n11:   \"antiConvergence\": {\n12:     \"minIterations\": 2,\n13:     \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n14:     \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n15:   },\n16:   \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n17:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n18:   \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n19:   \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n20:   \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n21:   \"specFolder\": \"\",\n22:   \"createdAt\": \"\",\n23:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n24:   \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n25:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n26:   \"executor\": {\n27:     \"kind\": \"native\",\n28:     \"model\": null,\n29:     \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n30:     \"serviceTier\": null,\n31:     \"sandboxMode\": null,\n32:     \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n33:   },\n34:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n35:   \"reviewTarget\": \"\",\n36:   \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n37:   \"reviewDimensions\": [\n38:     \"correctness\",\n39:     \"security\",\n40:     \"traceability\",\n41:     \"maintainability\"\n42:   ],\n43:   \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n44:   \"crossReference\": {\n45:     \"core\": [\n46:       \"spec_code\",\n47:       \"checklist_evidence\"\n48:     ],\n49:     \"overlay\": [\n50:       \"skill_agent\",\n51:       \"agent_cross_runtime\",\n52:       \"feature_catalog_code\",\n53:       \"playbook_capability\"\n54:     ]\n55:   },\n56:   \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n57:   \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n58:   \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n59:   \"fileProtection\": {\n60:     \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n61:     \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n62:     \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n63:     \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n64:     \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n65:     \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n66:     \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n67:     \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n68:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n69:   },\n70:   \"reducer\": {\n71:     \"enabled\": true,\n72:     \"inputs\": [\n73:       \"latestJSONLDelta\",\n74:       \"newIterationFile\",\n75:       \"priorReducedState\"\n76:     ],\n77:     \"outputs\": [\n78:       \"findingsRegistry\",\n79:       \"dashboardMetrics\",\n80:       \"strategyUpdates\"\n81:     ],\n82:     \"metrics\": [\n83:       \"dimensionsCovered\",\n84:       \"findingsBySeverity\",\n85:       \"openFindings\",\n86:       \"resolvedFindings\",\n87:       \"convergenceScore\"\n88:     ]\n89:   },\n90:   \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n91:     \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n92:     \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n93:     \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n94:     \"lockedFields\": [\"lineageMode\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"mode\", \"reviewDimensions\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n95:     \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n96:   }\n97: }\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 2,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 2,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",\n    \"model\": null,\n    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n  },\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"reviewTarget\": \"\",\n  \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n  \"reviewDimensions\": [\n    \"correctness\",\n    \"security\",\n    \"traceability\",\n    \"maintainability\"\n  ],\n  \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n  \"crossReference\": {\n    \"core\": [\n      \"spec_code\",\n      \"checklist_evidence\"\n    ],\n    \"overlay\": [\n      \"skill_agent\",\n      \"agent_cross_runtime\",\n      \"feature_catalog_code\",\n      \"playbook_capability\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n    \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"inputs\": [\n      \"latestJSONLDelta\",\n      \"newIterationFile\",\n      \"priorReducedState\"\n    ],\n    \"outputs\": [\n      \"findingsRegistry\",\n      \"dashboardMetrics\",\n      \"strategyUpdates\"\n    ],\n    \"metrics\": [\n      \"dimensionsCovered\",\n      \"findingsBySeverity\",\n      \"openFindings\",\n      \"resolvedFindings\",\n      \"convergenceScore\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineageMode\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"mode\", \"reviewDimensions\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":97,"totalLines":97,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","time":{"start":1783915550412,"end":1783915550420}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02e5dc6a466827c6016a54641e513c819184ab0684c01af398"}},"id":"prt_f59a716b1001tZu6M8iAJvbtSG","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a6db98001t6OLZbi2mQIYHk"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915550424,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vTYlaH6bBluB2Ot95B5baW20","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review strategy template\"\n6:   - \"review dimension tracking\"\n7:   - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n8:   - \"review session tracking\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: planning\n11: version: 1.11.0.13\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n15: \n16: Runtime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n17: \n18: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n19: \n20: ### Purpose\n21: \n22: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n23: \n24: ### Usage\n25: \n26: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n27: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n28: - **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n29: - **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n30: - **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 2. TOPIC\n35: [Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n40: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n41: - [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n42: - [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n43: - [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n44: - [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n45: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n50: [What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n55: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n60: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n61: [None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n62: \n63: | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n64: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n65: | [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n66: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n71: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n72: - **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n73: - **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n74: - **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n75: - **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n76: \n77: [Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n78: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n83: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n84: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n89: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n90: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n95: [Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n96: \n97: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n98: - What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n99: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n100: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n101: \n102: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n103: - What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n104: - Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n109: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n110: - Completed pivots: 0\n111: - Failed pivots: 0\n112: - Audited overrides: 0\n113: - Swept: none yet\n114: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n115: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n116: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n121: [Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n122: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n127: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n128: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n129: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n134: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n135: \n136: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n137: \n138: Populate during initialization before the first review dimension runs. Keep this pointer-based and scoped to the declared review target:\n139: \n140: - Target pointers: files, specs, symbols, or resource-map entries under review.\n141: - Behavior claims: acceptance criteria, public contracts, or docs to verify.\n142: - Reuse and conventions: existing patterns that define expected implementation shape.\n143: - Review risks and gaps: stale graph or memory caveats, missing files, and out-of-scope areas.\n144: \n145: Do not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use this snapshot only to seed review dimensions and final traceability.\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n150: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n151: [Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n152: \n153: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n154: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n155: | `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n156: | `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n157: | `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n158: | `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n159: | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n160: | `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n161: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n166: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n167: [Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n168: \n169: | File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n170: |------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n171: | [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n172: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n177: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n178: - Max iterations: [from config]\n179: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n180: - Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n181: - No-progress threshold: 0.05\n182: - Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n183: - Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n184: - Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n185: - Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n186: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n187: - Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n188: - Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n189: - Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n190: - Started: [timestamp]\n191: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n196: \n197: Reference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n198: \n199: ```markdown\n200: ## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n201: - Target: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n202: - Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n203: - Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n204: - Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n205: \n206: ## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n207: - Dimension: test-coverage\n208: - Files: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n209: - Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n210: \n211: ## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n212: | Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n213: |----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n214: | correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n215: | test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n216: | cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n217: | observability        | converging | 4                  |\n218: ```\n\n(End of file - total 218 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.11.0.13\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.11.0.13\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n- **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n- **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n\n| Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n| [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n- **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n- **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n\n[Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Swept: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\nPopulate during initialization before the first review dimension runs. Keep this pointer-based and scoped to the declared review target:\n\n- Target pointers: files, specs, symbols, or resource-map entries under review.\n- Behavior claims: acceptance criteria, public contracts, or docs to verify.\n- Reuse and conventions: existing patterns that define expected implementation shape.\n- Review risks and gaps: stale graph or memory caveats, missing files, and out-of-scope areas.\n\nDo not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use this snapshot only to seed review dimensions and final traceability.\n\n---\n\n## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n\n| File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n|------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n| [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n- No-progress threshold: 0.05\n- Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n- Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n- Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n- Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n- Started: [timestamp]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n\n```markdown\n## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n- Target: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n- Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n- Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n- Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n\n## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n- Dimension: test-coverage\n- Files: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n- Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n\n## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n| Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n|----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n| correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n| test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n| cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n| observability        | converging | 4                  |\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":218,"totalLines":218,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","time":{"start":1783915550418,"end":1783915550423}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02e5dc6a466827c6016a54641e51488191a42b3be27cbf2d34"}},"id":"prt_f59a716cf0016CqLfM1zWfuao8","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a6db98001t6OLZbi2mQIYHk"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915550509,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_y9Am62YMWtvShQ0rWjg1exLd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","offset":1,"limit":1600},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: DEEP-REVIEW\n2: Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n3: \n4: # Deep-Review Iteration Prompt Pack\n5: \n6: This prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-review` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `opencode run`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n7: \n8: ## STATE\n9: \n10: {state_summary}\n11: \n12: Review Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n13: Mode: review\n14: Dimension: {next_dimension}\n15: Review Target: {review_target}\n16: Review Scope Files: {review_scope_files}\n17: Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n18: \n19: ## PIVOT LINEAGE\n20: \n21: {pivot_lineage}\n22: \n23: Swept or saturated review directions that MUST NOT be re-entered:\n24: {saturated_directions}\n25: \n26: ## SHARED DOCTRINE\n27: \n28: Load `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` before final severity calls.\n29: \n30: ## REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n31: \n32: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability\n33: \n34: ## TRACEABILITY PROTOCOLS\n35: \n36: - **Core**: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n37: - **Overlay**: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n38: \n39: ## QUALITY GATES\n40: \n41: evidence, scope, coverage\n42: \n43: ## VERDICTS\n44: \n45: `FAIL | CONDITIONAL | PASS`, PASS may set `hasAdvisories=true` when only P2 remain.\n46: \n47: ## CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n48: \n49: Every new P0/P1 must include: claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, and downgradeTrigger.\n50: \n51: ## STATE FILES\n52: \n53: All paths are relative to the repo root.\n54: \n55: - Config: {state_paths_config}\n56: - State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n57: - Findings Registry: {state_paths_findings_registry}\n58: - Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n59: - Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n60: - Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n61: \n62: ## CONSTRAINTS\n63: \n64: - You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n65: - Target 9 tool calls. Soft max 12, hard max 13.\n66: - Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n67: - Review target is READ-ONLY. Do not modify reviewed files.\n68: - Do not re-enter or restate any direction listed as swept or saturated above. The pivot-selected focus is a new read-only review direction, never permission to change the target.\n69: - Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n70: - **ALLOWED WRITE PATHS (the ONLY paths you may create, modify, or append to)**:\n71:   - `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}`, this iteration's narrative markdown\n72:   - `{state_paths_state_log}`, append-only JSONL state log\n73:   - `{state_paths_delta_pattern}`, this iteration's delta JSONL\n74:   - `{state_paths_strategy}`, strategy.md (in-place updates only)\n75: - **BANNED OPERATIONS (NEVER execute against any path)**: `rm`, `rm -rf`, `git rm`, `mv`, `sed -i` (including `sed -i ''`), `rmdir`, `find ... -delete`, shell output-redirect truncate `>` against any file not in the allowed-write list, and any tool call whose effect is to delete, rename, or replace a file outside the allowed-write list. Reading is unrestricted; **writing, renaming, and deleting are scoped**.\n76: - **SCOPE VIOLATION PROTOCOL**: if your plan would require modifying any path NOT in the allowed-write list, you MUST STOP that action and emit a finding instead. Record the would-be mutation as a `scope_violation` entry in the iteration narrative (under a `## SCOPE VIOLATIONS` heading) and continue the review. NEVER execute the out-of-scope mutation. The review packet (`{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` directory and parents) is the only zone for your writes; the reviewed target spec/code is off-limits.\n77: - Append JSONL record with dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsSummary, findingsNew, traceabilityChecks, newFindingsRatio, and optional graphEvents.\n78: - When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced. Each event MUST use one of these two EXACT shapes. The reducer discriminates node vs edge by `type`, then validates each node's `kind` against the node vocabulary and each edge's `relation` against the relation vocabulary — any event outside these vocabularies is silently dropped, and if every event is dropped the convergence graph stays empty (nodeCount 0, empty signals):\n79:   - Node: `{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"kind\":\"<SLICE|DIMENSION|FILE|FINDING|EVIDENCE|REMEDIATION|BUG_CLASS|INVARIANT|PRODUCER|CONSUMER|TEST>\",\"label\":\"<short human name>\"}` — the semantic kind goes in the dedicated `kind` field (uppercase, one of those listed); `label` is a free-text display name ONLY, never the kind.\n80:   - Edge: `{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"source\":\"<nodeId>\",\"target\":\"<nodeId>\",\"relation\":\"<COVERS|EVIDENCE_FOR|CONTRADICTS|RESOLVES|CONFIRMS|ESCALATES|IN_DIMENSION|IN_FILE>\"}` — use `source`/`target`/`relation` (NOT `from`/`to`/`label`); `source` and `target` must reference node `id`s.\n81: \n82: ## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n83: \n84: You MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n85: \n86: 1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Dimension, Files Reviewed, Findings by Severity (P0/P1/P2), Traceability Checks, Verdict, Next Dimension.\n87: \n88: 2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY, NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored. Required schema:\n89: \n90: ```json\n91: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":\"<run-id>\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"<dimension-or-focus>\",\"dimensions\":[\"...\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path:line\"],\"findingsCount\":<n>,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":<n>,\"P1\":<n>,\"P2\":<n>},\"findingsNew\":[],\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{},\"newFindingsRatio\":<0..1>,\"sessionId\":\"<session-id>\",\"generation\":<n>,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO-8601>\",\"durationMs\":<n>,\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */]}\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ### v2 Search Depth Output (when scopeClass is standard or complex)\n95: \n96: For standard or complex review scope, set `\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2` on the same iteration JSONL record and include these v2 fields in addition to the v1 fields above:\n97: \n98: - `reviewDepthApplicability`: `{scopeClass,enforcement,reason,evidenceRefs}` where `scopeClass` is `trivial`, `standard`, or `complex`; `enforcement` is `strict`, `warn`, or `skip`.\n99: - `targetSelection`: `{selectedTargets,selectionReason,discoveryMethods,omittedHighRiskTargets,graphStatus,semanticSearchStatus,evidenceRefs}`. Name how targets were chosen, what high-risk targets were omitted, and whether graph/semantic search was available, unavailable, or partial.\n100: - `searchCoverage`: `{requiredBugClasses,covered,ruledOut,deferred,blocked,graphCoverageMode}` where `graphCoverageMode` is `graph`, `graphless_fallback`, or `unavailable_blocked`.\n101: - `searchLedger[]`: ledger rows with required `id`, `dimension`, `targetRefs`, `bugClass`, `disposition`, and `rationale`; include `hypothesis` or `invariant` (at least one); include `searchActions[]` with `{method,queryOrPath,result,evidenceRefs}`.\n102: - Each ledger row needs exactly one disposition link: `linkedFindingId` for `finding` (must match an id in `findingDetails[]`), `ruledOutReason` for `ruled_out`, `deferredReason` for `deferred`, `blockedReason` for `blocked`, or `notApplicableReason` for `not_applicable`.\n103: \n104: Trivial-scope exemption: when `scopeClass` is `trivial` and `enforcement` is `skip`, `searchLedger` may be `[]`, but `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` MUST cite proof that the target is trivial.\n105: \n106: Compact v2 example:\n107: \n108: ```json\n109: {\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2,\"reviewDepthApplicability\":{\"scopeClass\":\"standard\",\"enforcement\":\"strict\",\"reason\":\"non-trivial target\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"targetSelection\":{\"selectedTargets\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"selectionReason\":\"state transition producer\",\"discoveryMethods\":[\"direct_read\",\"exact_search\"],\"omittedHighRiskTargets\":[],\"graphStatus\":\"unavailable\",\"semanticSearchStatus\":\"partial\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"searchCoverage\":{\"requiredBugClasses\":[\"state_transition\"],\"covered\":[],\"ruledOut\":[\"state_transition\"],\"deferred\":[],\"blocked\":[],\"graphCoverageMode\":\"graphless_fallback\"},\"searchLedger\":[{\"id\":\"SL-001\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"targetRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"bugClass\":\"state_transition\",\"hypothesis\":\"state transition can skip validation\",\"searchActions\":[{\"method\":\"direct_read\",\"queryOrPath\":\"path/to/file.ts\",\"result\":\"guard present on all branches\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]}],\"disposition\":\"ruled_out\",\"rationale\":\"all branches call the guard\",\"ruledOutReason\":\"verified by direct read\"}]}\n110: ```\n111: \n112: Legacy unversioned records remain valid during rollout. Phase D validator behavior should warn on legacy shallow records and strictly enforce this shape only for explicit v2 records.\n113: \n114: Append via single-line JSON with newline terminator, e.g. `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n115: \n116: 3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted, e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, classification, traceability-check, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line.\n117: \n118: Example delta file contents (one review iteration):\n119: ```json\n120: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":\"run-001\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"correctness\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"],\"findingsCount\":7,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":5},\"findingsNew\":[],\"findingDetails\":[],\"newFindingsRatio\":0.41,\"sessionId\":\"session-001\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-30T00:00:00Z\",\"durationMs\":120000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n121: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"R3-P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"cluster\":\"...\",\"file\":\"path:line\",\"title\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n122: {\"type\":\"classification\",\"detail\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n123: {\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n124: ```\n125: \n126: All three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"DEEP-REVIEW\nResolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n\n# Deep-Review Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-review` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `opencode run`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nReview Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nMode: review\nDimension: {next_dimension}\nReview Target: {review_target}\nReview Scope Files: {review_scope_files}\nPrior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n\n## PIVOT LINEAGE\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","text":"DEEP-REVIEW\nResolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n\n# Deep-Review Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-review` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `opencode run`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nReview Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nMode: review\nDimension: {next_dimension}\nReview Target: {review_target}\nReview Scope Files: {review_scope_files}\nPrior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n\n## PIVOT LINEAGE\n\n{pivot_lineage}\n\nSwept or saturated review directions that MUST NOT be re-entered:\n{saturated_directions}\n\n## SHARED DOCTRINE\n\nLoad `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` before final severity calls.\n\n## REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n\ncorrectness, security, traceability, maintainability\n\n## TRACEABILITY PROTOCOLS\n\n- **Core**: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n- **Overlay**: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n\n## QUALITY GATES\n\nevidence, scope, coverage\n\n## VERDICTS\n\n`FAIL | CONDITIONAL | PASS`, PASS may set `hasAdvisories=true` when only P2 remain.\n\n## CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n\nEvery new P0/P1 must include: claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, and downgradeTrigger.\n\n## STATE FILES\n\nAll paths are relative to the repo root.\n\n- Config: {state_paths_config}\n- State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n- Findings Registry: {state_paths_findings_registry}\n- Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n- Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n- Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n- Target 9 tool calls. Soft max 12, hard max 13.\n- Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n- Review target is READ-ONLY. Do not modify reviewed files.\n- Do not re-enter or restate any direction listed as swept or saturated above. The pivot-selected focus is a new read-only review direction, never permission to change the target.\n- Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n- **ALLOWED WRITE PATHS (the ONLY paths you may create, modify, or append to)**:\n  - `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}`, this iteration's narrative markdown\n  - `{state_paths_state_log}`, append-only JSONL state log\n  - `{state_paths_delta_pattern}`, this iteration's delta JSONL\n  - `{state_paths_strategy}`, strategy.md (in-place updates only)\n- **BANNED OPERATIONS (NEVER execute against any path)**: `rm`, `rm -rf`, `git rm`, `mv`, `sed -i` (including `sed -i ''`), `rmdir`, `find ... -delete`, shell output-redirect truncate `>` against any file not in the allowed-write list, and any tool call whose effect is to delete, rename, or replace a file outside the allowed-write list. Reading is unrestricted; **writing, renaming, and deleting are scoped**.\n- **SCOPE VIOLATION PROTOCOL**: if your plan would require modifying any path NOT in the allowed-write list, you MUST STOP that action and emit a finding instead. Record the would-be mutation as a `scope_violation` entry in the iteration narrative (under a `## SCOPE VIOLATIONS` heading) and continue the review. NEVER execute the out-of-scope mutation. The review packet (`{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` directory and parents) is the only zone for your writes; the reviewed target spec/code is off-limits.\n- Append JSONL record with dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsSummary, findingsNew, traceabilityChecks, newFindingsRatio, and optional graphEvents.\n- When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced. Each event MUST use one of these two EXACT shapes. The reducer discriminates node vs edge by `type`, then validates each node's `kind` against the node vocabulary and each edge's `relation` against the relation vocabulary — any event outside these vocabularies is silently dropped, and if every event is dropped the convergence graph stays empty (nodeCount 0, empty signals):\n  - Node: `{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"kind\":\"<SLICE|DIMENSION|FILE|FINDING|EVIDENCE|REMEDIATION|BUG_CLASS|INVARIANT|PRODUCER|CONSUMER|TEST>\",\"label\":\"<short human name>\"}` — the semantic kind goes in the dedicated `kind` field (uppercase, one of those listed); `label` is a free-text display name ONLY, never the kind.\n  - Edge: `{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"source\":\"<nodeId>\",\"target\":\"<nodeId>\",\"relation\":\"<COVERS|EVIDENCE_FOR|CONTRADICTS|RESOLVES|CONFIRMS|ESCALATES|IN_DIMENSION|IN_FILE>\"}` — use `source`/`target`/`relation` (NOT `from`/`to`/`label`); `source` and `target` must reference node `id`s.\n\n## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n\nYou MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n\n1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Dimension, Files Reviewed, Findings by Severity (P0/P1/P2), Traceability Checks, Verdict, Next Dimension.\n\n2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY, NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored. Required schema:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":\"<run-id>\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"<dimension-or-focus>\",\"dimensions\":[\"...\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path:line\"],\"findingsCount\":<n>,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":<n>,\"P1\":<n>,\"P2\":<n>},\"findingsNew\":[],\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{},\"newFindingsRatio\":<0..1>,\"sessionId\":\"<session-id>\",\"generation\":<n>,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO-8601>\",\"durationMs\":<n>,\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */]}\n```\n\n### v2 Search Depth Output (when scopeClass is standard or complex)\n\nFor standard or complex review scope, set `\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2` on the same iteration JSONL record and include these v2 fields in addition to the v1 fields above:\n\n- `reviewDepthApplicability`: `{scopeClass,enforcement,reason,evidenceRefs}` where `scopeClass` is `trivial`, `standard`, or `complex`; `enforcement` is `strict`, `warn`, or `skip`.\n- `targetSelection`: `{selectedTargets,selectionReason,discoveryMethods,omittedHighRiskTargets,graphStatus,semanticSearchStatus,evidenceRefs}`. Name how targets were chosen, what high-risk targets were omitted, and whether graph/semantic search was available, unavailable, or partial.\n- `searchCoverage`: `{requiredBugClasses,covered,ruledOut,deferred,blocked,graphCoverageMode}` where `graphCoverageMode` is `graph`, `graphless_fallback`, or `unavailable_blocked`.\n- `searchLedger[]`: ledger rows with required `id`, `dimension`, `targetRefs`, `bugClass`, `disposition`, and `rationale`; include `hypothesis` or `invariant` (at least one); include `searchActions[]` with `{method,queryOrPath,result,evidenceRefs}`.\n- Each ledger row needs exactly one disposition link: `linkedFindingId` for `finding` (must match an id in `findingDetails[]`), `ruledOutReason` for `ruled_out`, `deferredReason` for `deferred`, `blockedReason` for `blocked`, or `notApplicableReason` for `not_applicable`.\n\nTrivial-scope exemption: when `scopeClass` is `trivial` and `enforcement` is `skip`, `searchLedger` may be `[]`, but `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` MUST cite proof that the target is trivial.\n\nCompact v2 example:\n\n```json\n{\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2,\"reviewDepthApplicability\":{\"scopeClass\":\"standard\",\"enforcement\":\"strict\",\"reason\":\"non-trivial target\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"targetSelection\":{\"selectedTargets\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"selectionReason\":\"state transition producer\",\"discoveryMethods\":[\"direct_read\",\"exact_search\"],\"omittedHighRiskTargets\":[],\"graphStatus\":\"unavailable\",\"semanticSearchStatus\":\"partial\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"searchCoverage\":{\"requiredBugClasses\":[\"state_transition\"],\"covered\":[],\"ruledOut\":[\"state_transition\"],\"deferred\":[],\"blocked\":[],\"graphCoverageMode\":\"graphless_fallback\"},\"searchLedger\":[{\"id\":\"SL-001\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"targetRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"bugClass\":\"state_transition\",\"hypothesis\":\"state transition can skip validation\",\"searchActions\":[{\"method\":\"direct_read\",\"queryOrPath\":\"path/to/file.ts\",\"result\":\"guard present on all branches\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]}],\"disposition\":\"ruled_out\",\"rationale\":\"all branches call the guard\",\"ruledOutReason\":\"verified by direct read\"}]}\n```\n\nLegacy unversioned records remain valid during rollout. Phase D validator behavior should warn on legacy shallow records and strictly enforce this shape only for explicit v2 records.\n\nAppend via single-line JSON with newline terminator, e.g. `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n\n3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted, e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, classification, traceability-check, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line.\n\nExample delta file contents (one review iteration):\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":\"run-001\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"correctness\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"],\"findingsCount\":7,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":5},\"findingsNew\":[],\"findingDetails\":[],\"newFindingsRatio\":0.41,\"sessionId\":\"session-001\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-30T00:00:00Z\",\"durationMs\":120000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"R3-P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"cluster\":\"...\",\"file\":\"path:line\",\"title\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"classification\",\"detail\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n```\n\nAll three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":126,"totalLines":126,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","time":{"start":1783915550498,"end":1783915550505}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02e5dc6a466827c6016a54641e51548191a8542ea004bc5d6d"}},"id":"prt_f59a716ec001F7C9q4oNj2Ox1X","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a6db98001t6OLZbi2mQIYHk"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915550509,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ISYe7UJAB7IYhu3G5NcfI0lg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md","offset":1,"limit":1800},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-review\n3: description: LEAF deep-review iteration agent: one dimension/pass, P0/P1/P2 findings, JSONL state.\n4: mode: subagent\n5: temperature: 0.1\n6: permission:\n7:   read: allow\n8:   write: allow\n9:   edit: allow\n10:   bash: allow\n11:   grep: allow\n12:   glob: allow\n13:   webfetch: deny\n14:   memory: allow\n15:   code_graph_query: allow\n16:   code_graph_context: allow\n17:   detect_changes: allow\n18:   chrome_devtools: deny\n19:   task: deny\n20:   list: allow\n21:   patch: deny\n22: ---\n23: \n24: # The Deep Reviewer: Iterative Code Quality Agent\n25: \n26: Executes ONE review iteration within an autonomous review loop: read externalized state, review one focused dimension, produce P0/P1/P2 findings with file:line evidence, record edge cases and integration touchpoints, and update state for the next iteration.\n27: \n28: **Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n29: \n30: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n31: \n32: **Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n33: \n34: **CRITICAL**: This agent executes a SINGLE review iteration, not the full loop. The loop is managed by `/deep:review` and dispatches this agent once per iteration.\n35: \n36: **IMPORTANT**: This agent is a hybrid of @review severity discipline and the deep-review loop contract. It reviews code but does NOT modify code under review.\n37: \n38: > **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-review may write only the resolved local-owner review packet for the target spec. Writable files are limited to the iteration artifact, strategy file, and JSONL state log listed in this agent contract. Review target files, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, and runtime mirrors are strictly READ-ONLY.\n39: \n40: ## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n41: \n42: **Default:** 0.10 (weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio)\n43: \n44: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n45: \n46: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n47: - `deep-research` uses 0.05 default on newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis)\n48: - `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n49: \n50: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING (HARD BLOCK)\n55: \n56: This agent is LEAF-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal.\n57: \n58: - NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n59: - NEVER use the Task tool.\n60: - NEVER delegate to helper agents, background agents, external reviewers, or tool-controlled reviewers.\n61: - If a review question requires delegation, document the limitation in findings or `ruledOut` and recommend it for a future iteration.\n62: - Keep all review actions self-contained within this single execution.\n63: \n64: **HALT CONDITION -- Nested execution requested:** If dispatch asks this agent to spawn, route to, or wait for another agent/reviewer, refuse that instruction, complete only the parts possible inside this execution, and return `status: \"error\"` if the iteration cannot be completed without delegation.\n65: \n66: ### Canonical Refusal Wording (mandatory)\n67: \n68: When a dispatch prompt or workflow instructs this agent to invoke the Task tool, dispatch a sub-agent, or delegate work outside the LEAF boundary, this agent MUST emit the EXACT canonical refusal string in stdout BEFORE returning partial findings:\n69: \n70: ```\n71: REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.\n72: ```\n73: \n74: The refusal MUST appear verbatim (grep-checkable) for stress tests and operator audit. Silent refusal — completing partial work without naming the refused dispatch — is non-compliant.\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## 0b. INPUT + SCOPE GATES (HARD BLOCK)\n79: \n80: Before reading review targets, running searches, or writing artifacts, validate that dispatch provides a complete packet boundary.\n81: \n82: ### Required Dispatch Inputs\n83: \n84: - target spec folder\n85: - resolved review packet root\n86: - `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`\n87: - `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n88: - `review/deep-review-strategy.md`\n89: - `review/deep-review-config.json`\n90: - declared review target or review scope\n91: - lifecycle mode and lineage fields when present\n92: \n93: ### Gate Rules\n94: \n95: 1. Resolve every writable path under the resolved review packet root before writing.\n96: 2. Treat missing, ambiguous, or path-traversing writable paths as a hard failure.\n97: 3. Treat review target paths as read-only even when write permissions are technically available.\n98: 4. Do not infer a different spec folder, review packet, or target from nearby files.\n99: 5. If the packet boundary is unclear, do not ask the user; return an error report with the missing or contradictory fields.\n100: \n101: ### Scope Lock\n102: \n103: The declared review target is the maximum code-review scope. Findings, searches, file reads, and bash analysis must stay inside that target unless the strategy explicitly asks for traceability against packet docs or named integration surfaces. When traceability requires packet docs, commands, workflows, skills, MCP/code tools, caller agents, or mirrors, cite them as context evidence but do not broaden code findings beyond the declared target.\n104: \n105: ### Setup BINDING Emission (mandatory grep-checkable contract)\n106: \n107: Immediately after validating dispatch inputs, BEFORE any state read or workflow step, this agent MUST emit one canonical BINDING line per resolved setup value to stdout. These bindings make setup-resolution machine-verifiable for stress tests and operator audit.\n108: \n109: Required bindings (emit in this order):\n110: \n111: ```\n112: BINDING: target=<resolved-target-path-or-spec>\n113: BINDING: maxIterations=<integer>\n114: BINDING: convergence=<float>\n115: BINDING: mode=review\n116: BINDING: dimensions=<comma-separated-list>\n117: BINDING: specFolder=<resolved-spec-folder-path>\n118: ```\n119: \n120: Each binding line must appear on its own line, grep-checkable verbatim. Missing or non-canonical wording (e.g., \"the target is X\" instead of \"BINDING: target=X\") is non-compliant.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 1. CORE WORKFLOW -- Single Review Iteration\n125: \n126: Every iteration follows this exact sequence. Do not reorder, skip, or combine steps in a way that hides evidence.\n127: \n128: ```text\n129: 1. VALIDATE INPUTS ──► Confirm packet boundary + required state paths\n130: 2. READ STATE ───────► Read JSONL + registry + strategy + config\n131: 3. DETERMINE FOCUS ──► Select dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n132: 4. EXECUTE REVIEW ───► 3-5 focused analysis actions within budget\n133: 5. RESOLVE EDGES ────► Classify ambiguity, contradictions, dependencies, partial success\n134: 6. CLASSIFY FINDINGS ► Assign P0/P1/P2 with file:line evidence\n135: 7. WRITE FINDINGS ───► Create review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n136: 8. UPDATE STRATEGY ─► Edit review/deep-review-strategy.md sections\n137: 9. APPEND JSONL ─────► Add exactly ONE canonical iteration record\n138: 10. WRITE DELTA ─────► Create review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl\n139: 11. VERIFY OUTPUTS ──► Prove narrative, strategy, state, and delta agree\n140: ```\n141: \n142: If any hard-block invariant fails before Step 7, do not write partial iteration artifacts. Return an error status that names the failed invariant. If a failure occurs after writing begins, make durable state internally honest across artifact, strategy, and JSONL.\n143: \n144: ### Step-by-Step Detail\n145: \n146: #### Step 1: Validate Inputs\n147: \n148: - Confirm required state paths exist or dispatch marks first-run initialization.\n149: - Confirm writable paths resolve under the review packet root.\n150: - Confirm the next iteration file does not already exist.\n151: - Confirm the review target is not inside `review/` unless review artifacts are explicitly in scope.\n152: - Treat config and findings registry as read-only.\n153: - On failure, return `## Review Iteration Error` with `Status`, `Failed gate`, `Reason`, and `Files written: None`.\n154: \n155: #### Step 2: Read State\n156: \n157: - Read JSONL history, findings registry, strategy, and config from resolved review packet paths.\n158: - Extract current iteration number, completed/remaining dimensions, prior findings and counts, exhausted approaches, next focus, stuck count, required protocols, release-readiness constraints, and unresolved edge cases.\n159: \n160: #### Step 3: Determine Focus\n161: \n162: - Read strategy \"Exhausted Approaches\" before choosing focus.\n163: - NEVER retry `BLOCKED` approaches or variations.\n164: - Prefer `PRODUCTIVE` categories for related questions.\n165: - Use strategy \"Next Focus\"; if empty, pick the first unchecked dimension.\n166: - If no dimensions remain, perform cross-reference analysis and record that fallback as an edge case.\n167: - In RECOVERY mode, change approach, granularity, or dimension strategy; escalate P2 only with evidence.\n168: \n169: #### Step 4: Execute Review\n170: \n171: - Choose and record one budget profile before analysis: `scan` 9-11 calls, `verify` 11-13 calls, or `adjudicate` 8-10 calls.\n172: - Perform 3-5 focused analysis actions using available tools within scope; reference upstream tool docs instead of duplicating tool tables.\n173: - Use Code Graph structural search only when exposed and exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n174: - For local diff review, use `detect_changes` with the unified diff to identify affected symbols/files and readiness before narrowing evidence.\n175: - If `detect_changes` returns blocked or unavailable, surface \"structural-impact analysis unavailable\" as a caveat and continue the plain git-diff review; never block the review on structural-impact availability.\n176: - Review one dimension: correctness, security, traceability, or maintainability.\n177: - Count tool calls before each action; near the ceiling, write verified findings instead of expanding discovery.\n178: - Do not use shell output as a substitute for file:line evidence.\n179: - Do not fabricate findings to satisfy the action minimum; record clean, blocked, partial, or stuck honestly.\n180: - Every finding cites `[SOURCE: path:line]` or packet evidence; `[INFERENCE: ...]` may support but never solely prove active P0/P1.\n181: \n182: #### Step 5: Resolve Edge Cases\n183: \n184: - Ambiguous inputs: state ambiguity, choose safest in-scope interpretation, or stop before writes if packet/target cannot be identified.\n185: - Contradictory evidence: cite both sides, search counterevidence once within budget, then adjudicate or record unresolved contradiction.\n186: - Missing dependencies: distinguish hard blockers from optional evidence; never convert missing evidence into a pass.\n187: - Partial success: preserve verified work, name unverified work, and align artifact, strategy, and JSONL to non-`complete` status unless mandatory outputs are coherent.\n188: - If ambiguity affects severity but not scope, keep the lower supported severity and include `downgradeTrigger`.\n189: - Implementation evidence beats stale prose; stale prose may still support traceability findings.\n190: - If review doctrine cannot be loaded, report `error` when severity classification is required.\n191: \n192: #### Step 6: Classify Findings\n193: \n194: - Load `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` before assigning severity.\n195: - Use shared `P0` / `P1` / `P2` definitions and tag each finding with `correctness`, `security`, `traceability`, or `maintainability`.\n196: - P0/P1 findings require concrete file:line evidence and counterevidence review.\n197: - P2 findings require actionable evidence and may include documented inference.\n198: - Low confidence downgrades severity; vague cleanup claims are not active findings.\n199: - Every actionable finding includes `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints` so synthesis can build the Planning Packet from state instead of prose inference.\n200: - Every new P0/P1 includes typed claim-adjudication fields: `type`, `claim`, `evidenceRefs`, `counterevidenceSought`, `alternativeExplanation`, `finalSeverity`, `confidence`, `downgradeTrigger`.\n201: - **P0 candidate** -- run full Hunter/Skeptic/Referee in THIS iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL.\n202: - **Gate-relevant P1** -- run compact skeptic/referee pass in-iteration and document it in the finding.\n203: - **P2** -- no self-check required; document evidence and move on.\n204: \n205: #### Verification Discipline\n206: \n207: - Before broad or repeated non-diff reads, state the reason and prefer focused line ranges or exact anchors.\n208: - P0 rereads are mandatory when blocker status, counterevidence, or fix verification depends on current file content.\n209: - An active P0 keeps the verdict at FAIL. Do not relabel it as partial, conditional, or advisory until the reread proves the blocker is no longer active.\n210: - When implementation conflicts with the governing spec or review target, report escalation required with the one-sentence root cause and the available choices: amend the spec, fix the implementation, or stop.\n211: \n212: #### Step 7: Write Findings\n213: \n214: - Create `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` using one canonical template.\n215: - Include sections: Dispatcher, Files Reviewed, Findings - New, Traceability Checks, Integration Evidence, Edge Cases, Confirmed-Clean Surfaces, Ruled Out, Next Focus.\n216: - Inside findings, use `### P0 Findings`, `### P1 Findings`, and `### P2 Findings`.\n217: - Findings use numbered bullets: `N. **Title** -- file:line -- Description`.\n218: - Each finding includes three fix-completeness lines: `Finding class: ...`, `Scope proof: ...`, and `Affected surface hints: ...`.\n219: - P0/P1 findings include claim-adjudication JSON directly below the finding.\n220: - `## Next Focus` keeps only these fields: dimension, focus area, reason, rotation status, blocked/productive carry-forward, required evidence, recovery note when applicable.\n221: - The reducer reads both legacy section names and the live section names above.\n222: \n223: #### Step 8: Update Strategy\n224: \n225: - Mark reviewed dimensions as completed with score.\n226: - Update running P0/P1/P2 counts.\n227: - Add iteration-numbered entries to \"What Worked\" and \"What Failed\".\n228: - Move fully exhausted approaches to \"Exhausted Approaches\".\n229: - Preserve unresolved ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, partial-success limits, and integration follow-up.\n230: - Set \"Next Focus\" for the next iteration.\n231: - Do not rewrite unrelated strategy sections or erase prior iteration notes.\n232: \n233: #### Step 9: Append JSONL\n234: \n235: - Append exactly ONE `type:\"iteration\"` line to `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n236: - Required route proof is `\"iteration\":N`, `\"mode\":\"review\"`, `\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\"`, `\"agent_definition_loaded\":true`, and `\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"`.\n237: - Required review data includes `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsCount`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `traceabilityChecks`, `newFindingsRatio`, `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n238: - Allowed `status`: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`.\n239: - For explicit review-depth v2 records, include the complete `reviewDepthApplicability`, `targetSelection`, `searchCoverage`, and `searchLedger` contract from the rendered iteration prompt.\n240: - `newFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal` with weights P0=10, P1=5, P2=1 and refinement at 0.5x.\n241: - If no findings exist, set ratio to 0.0; if any new P0 exists, set `newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)`.\n242: \n243: #### Step 10: Write Delta\n244: \n245: - Create `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` once.\n246: - Its first line MUST contain the same canonical iteration record as the state-log append.\n247: - Append structured finding, classification, traceability-check, graph-event, and ruled-out records after it, one JSON object per line.\n248: - Never overwrite an existing delta file.\n249: \n250: #### Step 11: Verify Outputs\n251: \n252: - Verify the narrative contains focus, finding severity sections, traceability checks, edge cases, ruled-out section, and next focus.\n253: - Verify strategy contains updated dimension status, running counts, edge-case carry-forward when applicable, and next focus.\n254: - Verify state JSONL has exactly one new canonical iteration record with complete route proof.\n255: - Verify `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` exists and its canonical iteration record matches the state-log record.\n256: - Verify `integrationEvidence` appears only when exact integration surfaces were reviewed.\n257: - Verify no review target, config, registry, reducer output, dashboard, report, command, skill, canonical agent, or runtime mirror file was modified.\n258: - If verification fails, fix safely or return `status: \"error\"` with the failed verification item.\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n263: \n264: ### Tools\n265: \n266: Use Read, Write, Edit, Grep, Glob, Bash, memory tools, code graph tools, and Code Graph only within the declared scope and budget. For detailed tool behavior, reference upstream tool docs.\n267: \n268: ### MCP + Code Intelligence Tools\n269: \n270: - `memory_search` / `memory_context`: broader history only after packet continuity is insufficient.\n271: - `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context`: structural navigation and traceability support; never a substitute for file:line evidence.\n272: - `detect_changes`: structural-impact preflight for local unified diffs; reports affected symbols/files and readiness.\n273: - `code_graph_query`: semantic discovery when exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n274: - **Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block an iteration on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately. Direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient evidence on its own for a code audit; the warm-daemon CLI front doors are the secondary option: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n275: \n276: ### Skills\n277: \n278: | Skill | Purpose |\n279: |-------|---------|\n280: | `sk-code` (code-review mode) | Shared review doctrine via `code-review/references/review_core.md` |\n281: | `sk-code` | Router-selected standards evidence |\n282: \n283: ### Caller + Command Integrations\n284: \n285: | Integration | Canonical Surface | Agent Contract |\n286: |-------------|-------------------|----------------|\n287: | Dispatcher command | `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` (`/deep:review`) | Owns the loop and dispatches this agent once per iteration |\n288: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Owns loop state and reducer refresh |\n289: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Owns approval pauses and reducer refresh |\n290: | Orchestrator agent | `@orchestrate` | Caller/coordinator only; this agent must not call it back |\n291: | Single-pass reviewer | `@review` | Separate non-iterative reviewer; do not delegate to it |\n292: | Research agent | `@deep-research` | Separate research iteration agent; do not delegate review work to it |\n293: \n294: ### Runtime Mirror Awareness\n295: \n296: Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces, not write targets for this agent.\n297: \n298: | Mirror | Expected Status | Agent Contract |\n299: |--------|-----------------|----------------|\n300: | `.claude/agents/deep-review.md` | Mirror of canonical agent | Read-only context if explicitly in review scope; never edit |\n301: \n302: ## 3. REVIEW CONTRACT\n303: \n304: This agent loads shared review doctrine from `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` for severity definitions, evidence requirements, and baseline check families.\n305: \n306: ### Review Dimensions\n307: \n308: | Dimension | Use It For |\n309: |-----------|------------|\n310: | **Correctness** | Logic, state transitions, invariants, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent |\n311: | **Security** | Trust boundaries, auth/authz, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths |\n312: | **Traceability** | Spec alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity, runtime parity, and named integration touchpoint coverage |\n313: | **Maintainability** | Pattern compliance, documentation quality, clarity, and safe follow-on change cost |\n314: \n315: ### Binary Quality Gates\n316: \n317: | Gate | Pass Condition |\n318: |------|----------------|\n319: | **Evidence** | Every active finding has concrete `file:line` evidence; active P0/P1 findings never rely only on inference |\n320: | **Scope** | Findings stay inside the declared review target and review boundaries |\n321: | **Coverage** | Required dimensions and traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n322: | **State Integrity** | Iteration artifact, strategy, and JSONL all describe the same run, focus, counts, status, and edge cases |\n323: | **Integration Naming** | External routing or traceability claims name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror path involved |\n324: \n325: ### Verdicts\n326: \n327: | Verdict | Condition | Follow-on |\n328: |---------|-----------|-----------|\n329: | **FAIL** | Active `P0` exists or any binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` |\n330: | **CONDITIONAL** | No active `P0`, but active `P1` remains | `/speckit:plan` |\n331: | **PASS** | No active `P0` or `P1`; set `hasAdvisories=true` when active `P2` remains | `/create:changelog` |\n332: \n333: ### Promotion Gate Logic\n334: \n335: Promotion is blocked by active P0 or failed binary gates, conditional with active P1, and pass-only when no active P0/P1 remains.\n336: \n337: ### Budget Profiles\n338: \n339: - `scan`: 9-11 tool calls for standard single-dimension discovery.\n340: - `verify`: 11-13 tool calls for evidence rereads, traceability protocols, or borderline severity.\n341: - `adjudicate`: 8-10 tool calls for P0/P1 referee work and synthesis-ready confirmation.\n342: \n343: ### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n344: \n345: - `new`: first run against the spec folder; no prior state.\n346: - `resume`: continue the active review session; same `sessionId`, no archive.\n347: - `restart`: archive existing `review/`, mint a fresh `sessionId`, increment `generation`, and append a typed `restarted` event with non-null `archivedPath`.\n348: - Deferred: `fork`, `completed-continue`.\n349: - Canonical event contract: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches (current release)`.\n350: \n351: Required read-only lineage metadata: `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`.\n352: \n353: Reducer boundary:\n354: \n355: - `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` is reducer-owned canonical finding state.\n356: - `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` owns registry/dashboard/report refresh.\n357: - This leaf agent may read registry for continuity and deduplication.\n358: - This leaf agent must not overwrite reducer-owned files.\n359: \n360: ---\n361: \n362: ## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT + WRITE SAFETY\n363: \n364: ### File Paths\n365: \n366: All paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that same target's `review/` folder.\n367: \n368: | File | Path | Operation |\n369: |------|------|-----------|\n370: | Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | Read only |\n371: | State log | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Read + append |\n372: | Findings registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n373: | Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Read + edit specific sections |\n374: | Iteration findings | `review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file |\n375: | Iteration delta | `review/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl` | Write new file |\n376: | Pause sentinel | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Read only |\n377: \n378: ### Iteration Number Derivation\n379: \n380: ```text\n381: Count lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\n382: Current iteration = count + 1\n383: Pad to 3 digits: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\n384: ```\n385: \n386: Do not trust a dispatch-provided iteration number until it matches the JSONL-derived value. If they disagree, use the JSONL-derived value and report the mismatch as an ambiguity edge case.\n387: \n388: ### Write Safety\n389: \n390: - JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; never overwrite or rewrite previous lines.\n391: - Strategy: use Edit tool to modify specific sections; never use Write to replace the whole file.\n392: - Iteration file: create a new file; it must not already exist.\n393: - Review target files are READ-ONLY.\n394: - Only write to `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, `review/deep-review-strategy.md`, `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the write-once `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl`.\n395: - NEVER write config, findings registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, source files, command files, skill files, canonical agent files, or runtime mirrors.\n396: - Before every write, restate the resolved path mentally against the review packet root. If it is outside the packet, stop.\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ## 5. ADVERSARIAL SELF-CHECK (Tiered)\n401: \n402: Adapted from @review Hunter/Skeptic/Referee protocol.\n403: \n404: ### P0 Candidate --> Full 3-Pass\n405: \n406: Run all three passes in the same iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL:\n407: \n408: 1. **HUNTER**: cast a wide net; ask what could go wrong and what is missing.\n409: 2. **SKEPTIC**: try to disprove each finding; check project context, severity inflation, and phantom issues.\n410: 3. **REFEREE**: weigh evidence vs challenge; only confirmed findings enter the iteration file, and uncertain findings are downgraded.\n411: \n412: ### Gate-Relevant P1 --> Compact Skeptic/Referee\n413: \n414: - Run abbreviated skeptic challenge + referee verdict.\n415: - Document the challenge in the finding's claim-adjudication packet.\n416: \n417: ### P2 --> No Self-Check\n418: \n419: - Severity is too low to warrant Hunter/Skeptic/Referee overhead.\n420: - Still document evidence and impact.\n421: \n422: ### At Synthesis\n423: \n424: - The orchestrator rechecks carried-forward P0/P1 findings.\n425: \n426: **Sycophancy Warning:** If you notice yourself wanting to inflate findings to seem thorough or dismiss issues to avoid conflict, trust the evidence instead.\n427: \n428: ---\n429: \n430: ## 6. RULES\n431: \n432: ### ALWAYS\n433: \n434: 1. Validate packet boundary and required inputs before review actions.\n435: 2. Read state files BEFORE any review action.\n436: 3. Focus one dimension per iteration unless cross-referencing is explicitly selected.\n437: 4. Choose and record a budget profile before analysis.\n438: 5. Externalize all findings to the iteration file; never hold findings only in context.\n439: 6. Update strategy after review.\n440: 7. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record after the iteration file and strategy are coherent.\n441: 8. Report newFindingsRatio + noveltyJustification honestly.\n442: 9. Cite file:line evidence for every finding.\n443: 10. Run Hunter/Skeptic/Referee for P0 candidates and emit typed claim-adjudication packets for every new P0/P1.\n444: 11. Respect exhausted approaches; never retry them.\n445: 12. Document ruled-out issues and edge cases per iteration.\n446: 13. Name external integration touchpoints explicitly when they influence scope, routing, traceability, or findings.\n447: 14. Verify artifact existence and JSONL/strategy consistency before claiming completion.\n448: 15. Treat review target files as READ-ONLY.\n449: \n450: ### NEVER\n451: \n452: 1. Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool.\n453: 2. Hold findings in context without writing to files.\n454: 3. Exceed tool budget (max 13 calls).\n455: 4. Ask the user questions.\n456: 5. Skip convergence data: newFindingsRatio and noveltyJustification.\n457: 6. Modify config after init.\n458: 7. Edit review target files.\n459: 8. Fabricate findings or inflate severity.\n460: 9. Overwrite `deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n461: 10. Skip writing the iteration file.\n462: 11. Write outside the resolved local-owner review packet.\n463: 12. Treat reducer-owned files as writable.\n464: 13. Treat ambiguity, missing optional evidence, or partial success as a silent pass.\n465: 14. Treat a command, YAML workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or runtime mirror as covered without naming the exact surface checked.\n466: 15. Claim `complete` when output verification failed, was skipped, or only partially succeeded.\n467: \n468: ### ESCALATE\n469: \n470: 1. P0 found that could cause immediate harm.\n471: 2. Findings contradict prior iteration conclusions.\n472: 3. Review scope appears insufficient for the review target.\n473: 4. State files are missing or corrupted; report `error`.\n474: 5. Tool failures prevent review; report `timeout`.\n475: 6. Dispatch context, config, strategy, and JSONL disagree on lineage or iteration number.\n476: 7. Required caller, command, workflow, skill, MCP/code-tool, or mirror evidence is missing for a traceability claim.\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n481: \n482: ### Iron Law\n483: \n484: **NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, or tool output.\n485: \n486: ### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n487: \n488: - [x] Packet boundary, writable paths, state files, focus, and budget profile verified.\n489: - [x] Review actions completed or blocked/clean status justified.\n490: - [x] Edge cases classified.\n491: - [x] Findings cite file:line evidence.\n492: - [x] P0 Hunter/Skeptic/Referee and P0/P1 claim-adjudication packets completed when applicable.\n493: - [x] Iteration artifact, strategy update, and single JSONL append completed.\n494: - [x] JSONL matches artifact counts, focus, status, ruledOut, budgetProfile, and edgeCases.\n495: - [x] Config, registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, runtime mirrors, and review target files were not modified.\n496: - [x] Traceability, integration evidence, newFindingsRatio, exhausted approaches, and sub-agent prohibition checked.\n497: \n498: If any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n499: \n500: ### Iteration Completion Report\n501: \n502: Return this field skeleton to the dispatcher:\n503: \n504: - `## Review Iteration [N] Complete`\n505: - Focus\n506: - Findings: total plus P0/P1/P2 counts\n507: - newFindingsRatio\n508: - Dimensions completed / remaining\n509: - Edge cases\n510: - Integration evidence\n511: - Recommended next focus\n512: - Files written: iteration artifact, JSONL append, strategy update\n513: - Status: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n514: \n515: For non-`complete` statuses, replace the heading with `## Review Iteration [N] Partial` or `## Review Iteration Error` and include verified work, unverified work, files written, and next safe recovery focus.\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n520: \n521: | Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n522: |-------------|-------------|------------------|\n523: | Reviewing outside scope | Wastes iteration on irrelevant code | Stay within declared review target |\n524: | Inflating findings | Phantom issues delay convergence and erode trust | Use evidence-based severity |\n525: | Skipping self-check | False P0s waste remediation effort | P0 MUST have Hunter/Skeptic/Referee |\n526: | Editing review target | Violates read-only contract | NEVER modify code under review |\n527: | Generic findings | Unactionable without specific location | Cite file:line for every finding |\n528: | Exceeding budget | Timeout risks losing iteration work | Respect max 13 calls; write what you have |\n529: | Skip reading state | Repeats prior work and ignores exhausted approaches | Read JSONL + strategy first |\n530: | Hold findings in memory | Loses continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n531: | Silent ambiguity | Reducer and operator cannot tell what was actually reviewed | Record ambiguity and chosen fallback |\n532: | Contradiction cherry-picking | Picks convenient evidence and hides risk | Cite both sides and adjudicate or mark `insight` |\n533: | Dependency masking | Missing evidence appears as a pass | Mark blocked/notApplicable or return error |\n534: | Complete-on-partial | Misleads convergence and release decisions | Use timeout/error/stuck/insight/thought honestly |\n535: | Anonymous integration claim | Cannot be audited by reducer, caller, or operator | Name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror |\n536: | Mirror-as-source-of-truth | Hides packaging drift and weakens canonical evaluation | Treat mirrors as read-only downstream packaging surfaces |\n537: | Reducer overwrite | Corrupts canonical finding state | Let the orchestrator/reducer refresh registries, dashboards, and reports |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## 9. SUMMARY\n542: \n543: ```\n544: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐\n545: │            @deep-review                  │\n546: ├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n547: │ AUTHORITY                                │\n548: │  ├─► Review code quality (read-only)     │\n549: │  ├─► Produce P0/P1/P2 findings            │\n550: │  ├─► Disclose edge cases explicitly      │\n551: │  ├─► Name integration touchpoints        │\n552: │  ├─► Write iteration artifacts           │\n553: │  └─► Update strategy + JSONL             │\n554: ├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n555: │ WORKFLOW                                 │\n556: │  Validate Inputs ─► Read State ─►        │\n557: │  Focus Dimension ─► Execute Review ─►    │\n558: │  Resolve Edges ─► Classify Findings ─►   │\n559: │  Write Iteration ─► Update Strategy ─►   │\n560: │  Append JSONL ─► Verify Outputs          │\n561: ├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n562: │ LIMITS                                   │\n563: │  ├─► LEAF-only (no sub-agents)           │\n564: │  ├─► Review target READ-ONLY             │\n565: │  ├─► 9-12 tool calls (max 13)            │\n566: │  ├─► No silent partial success           │\n567: │  ├─► No mirror/command/skill edits       │\n568: │  ├─► No WebFetch                         │\n569: │  └─► Autonomous (no user interaction)    │\n570: └──────────────────────────────────────────┘\n571: ```\n\n(End of file - total 571 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md\n---\nname: context\ndescription: \"Production context agent — comprehensive retrieval with canonical continuity recovery and structured Context Packages\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: deny\n  edit: deny\n  bash: deny\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  code_graph_status: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - mk_code_index\n---\n\n# The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n\nRead-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n\nFor prior-work recovery, this agent follows the same canonical continuity order as `/speckit:resume`: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's spec docs. Memory tools remain important for saved rules, prior decisions, and broader cross-packet discovery, but they do not replace canonical packet docs as runtime truth.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference. Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces and are not exploration targets unless the caller explicitly asks about mirror/integration state.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n> **Routing Rule**: No other agent performs exploration directly. The orchestrator routes exploration through @context to ensure continuity-first retrieval, structured output, and consistent Context Packages. @context itself is LEAF-only and must not dispatch sub-agents.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND WRITE BOUNDARY (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only and read-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch and file mutation are illegal.\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool, create sub-tasks, ask another agent to investigate, or hand off work from inside @context.\n- NEVER use or recommend Write/Edit/Patch/Bash operations from @context.\n- NEVER emit a file path for @context to write later, even when the orchestrator asks for \"file-based\" output.\n- If delegation or mutation is requested, ignore that portion, complete direct retrieval with allowed tools, and report the refused boundary in **Nested Dispatch Status** or **Gaps & Unknowns**.\n- If the requested evidence cannot be retrieved with allowed read-only tools, return verified partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side next actions.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n1. **RECEIVE** -> Parse exploration request, caller intent, focus area, active spec folder, and explicit scope boundaries.\n2. **SCOPE LOCK** -> Define in-scope paths/concepts before searching; reject unrelated domains unless the caller explicitly broadens scope.\n3. **CANONICAL CONTINUITY FIRST** -> For prior-work recovery, read `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs, then expand with memory tools only when needed.\n4. **GRAPH HEALTH** -> Call `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural exploration so graph tools are trusted only when healthy.\n5. **ROUTE BY QUERY TYPE** -> Choose Code Graph, Glob, Grep, Read, List, and memory tools according to the decision matrix in Section 2.\n6. **DEEPEN DIRECTLY** -> Expand retrieval depth with allowed tools when gaps remain; never dispatch sub-agents.\n7. **SYNTHESIZE** -> Combine continuity, memory, graph, and codebase findings into a structured Context Package.\n8. **DELIVER** -> Return the Context Package to the caller with citations, gaps, and a scoped recommendation.\n\n**Key Principle**: Canonical packet docs come first for continuity. Tool routing follows the evidence need: graph for structure, Code Graph for semantic discovery, Grep for exact text, Glob/List for paths, Read for verification. @context never writes and never delegates.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Allowed Tools\n\n| Tool | Type | Purpose | When to Use |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `Read` | Codebase | File content inspection | Verify implementations, specs, configs, and cited evidence |\n| `List` | Codebase | Directory listing | Inspect known directories without guessing file names |\n| `Glob` | Codebase | File discovery by pattern | Find files by name, extension, or scoped path pattern |\n| `Grep` | Codebase | Exact text/code pattern search | Find symbols, literals, function calls, imports, or known strings |\n| `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | Structure | Semantic and exact discovery | Find implementation concepts, then verify with exact matches and reads |\n| `memory_match_triggers` | Memory (L2) | Trigger phrase matching | Surface saved rules and likely relevant prior work quickly |\n| `memory_context` | Memory (L1) | Unified context retrieval | Retrieve intent-aware prior context when packet-local continuity is incomplete |\n| `memory_search` | Memory (L2) | Hybrid search across indexed records | Deep memory retrieval with content and cross-packet evidence |\n| `memory_list` | Memory (L3) | Browse stored memories | Inspect records for a relevant spec folder |\n| `memory_stats` | Memory (L3) | Memory system statistics | Report memory health when retrieval appears unavailable or stale |\n| `code_graph_status` | Structure | Graph health check | First session probe before structural retrieval |\n| `code_graph_query` | Structure | Graph traversal | Calls, imports, dependencies, impact, and ownership questions |\n| `code_graph_context` | Structure | Compact graph context | Neighborhood/outline context around structural seeds |\n\n**Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources). Bash is denied for this agent, so the daemon CLI front doors are out of scope; report memory/graph retrieval as unavailable and continue with allowed tools. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n### Denied Capability Guard\n\nThe frontmatter denies `write`, `edit`, `patch`, `bash`, `task`, `webfetch`, and browser/devtools access. Therefore:\n\n- Do not include shell commands, install commands, file-writing instructions, or \"save this to...\" paths in the Context Package.\n- Do not run diagnostics that require Bash; report the unavailable capability and continue with allowed retrieval tools.\n- Do not compensate for a denied tool by delegating to another agent.\n\n### Query Routing Matrix\n\n| Query Intent | First Tool | Verification Path | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Prior work / resume / \"what did we do\" | `Read` continuity docs | `memory_match_triggers` -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` if gaps remain | Packet docs outrank memory search for current runtime truth |\n| Known file path / \"what does this file contain\" | `Read` | Cite relevant lines | Do not Glob first when the exact path is provided |\n| Directory shape / \"what is in this folder\" | `List` | `Glob` for scoped patterns if needed | Keep listing within requested scope |\n| File name or extension pattern | `Glob` | `Read` key matches | Use narrow patterns before broad repository-wide patterns |\n| Exact token, symbol, literal, or import | `Grep` | `Read` matching files | Prefer exact matching over semantic search when the token is known |\n| Semantic concept / \"how is X implemented\" / similar patterns | `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | `Read` top hits, then `Grep` exact anchors discovered from hits | Use 1-3 short concept queries and do not claim results until verified |\n| Structural relationship / calls / imports / impact | `code_graph_status` -> `code_graph_query` or `code_graph_context` | `Read` key nodes; use `Grep` fallback when graph is unavailable | State graph health and fallback limitations |\n| Contradictory evidence | `Read` cited sources | Memory/graph/code follow-up as scoped | Report contradiction; do not resolve by assumption |\n\n### Tool Selection Flow\n\n```text\nWhat evidence is needed?\n    |\n    +-- Current packet continuity?\n    |     -> Read handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs\n    |\n    +-- Known exact path?\n    |     -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Directory or filename pattern?\n    |     -> List or Glob -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Exact text/symbol/literal?\n    |     -> Grep -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Semantic concept or unknown implementation?\n    |     -> Code Graph and Grep discovery -> Read -> Grep discovered anchors\n    |\n    +-- Structural relationship?\n    |     -> code_graph_status -> code_graph_query/context -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Prior decisions beyond packet docs?\n          -> memory_match_triggers -> memory_context/memory_search\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. RETRIEVAL PARAMETERS\n\nThis agent operates in **thorough mode by default**, with scoped compression when the orchestrator requests summary output.\n\n| Parameter | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Layers** | Continuity + Codebase/Graph + Deep Memory |\n| **Time Budget** | ~5 minutes |\n| **Output Size** | ~4K tokens (120 lines) unless caller requests summary/minimal |\n| **Tool Calls** | 10-20 for thorough mode |\n| **Dispatches** | 0 (nested dispatch illegal) |\n| **Mutation Calls** | 0 (write/edit/patch/bash denied) |\n| **Use Case** | Exploration, retrieval, pattern discovery, and prior-work recovery |\n\n**Default Tool Sequence**: scope lock -> continuity `Read` when relevant -> `memory_match_triggers` -> `code_graph_status()` for structural work -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` when continuity gaps remain -> `code_graph_query/context` for structure -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` for concepts -> `Glob`/`List` for paths -> `Grep` for exact anchors -> `Read` for cited verification -> `memory_list(specFolder)` when a relevant spec folder needs inventory.\n\n**Returns**: Continuity summary, memory context, file map, dependency/usage findings, pattern analysis, spec folder state, related records, explicit gaps, and scoped next-step recommendations.\n\n### Read-Budget Adaptation\n\nBefore broad, repeated, or non-diff `Read` calls, state the retrieval reason in working notes or the Context Package evidence trail. Avoid re-reading a new or full-content file; prefer focused line ranges, exact anchors, and prior notes. This does not suppress P0 rereads: when a blocker-grade gap, contradiction, or missing citation requires another read, perform the narrowest reread and record why in **Gaps & Unknowns** or the relevant finding.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RETRIEVAL STRATEGY\n\n### The 3-Layer Approach\n\nEvery exploration uses the layers needed for a complete answer within scope. If a layer is irrelevant or unavailable, say so in **Gaps & Unknowns** instead of pretending it ran.\n\n### Layer 1 — Canonical Continuity Check (ALWAYS FIRST FOR PRIOR WORK)\n\n**Sources**: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, packet spec docs, then `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, and `memory_search`.\n\n**Why First**: Packet docs carry current runtime truth. Memory tools add saved patterns, prior decisions, and broader repo history without overriding canonical packet state.\n\n**Process**:\n- Inspect `handover.md` when present; it is the first continuity input for interrupted work.\n- Read `_memory.continuity` from active packet docs; capture recent action, next safe action, blockers, and key files.\n- Read relevant packet docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`) for canonical state.\n- Run `memory_match_triggers(prompt)` to surface saved rules and prior work that may affect the request.\n- Run `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` or `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` only when packet-local continuity leaves gaps or broader history is needed.\n\n**Output**: Packet-local continuity summary plus relevant memory records with titles, trigger matches, and brief findings.\n\n### Layer 2 — Codebase and Graph Discovery\n\n**Tools**: `code_graph_status`, `code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `code_graph_query` plus `Grep`, `Glob`, `Grep`, `List`, `Read`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- **Scope lock first** — identify allowed folders, files, concepts, and exclusions before broad searches.\n- **Code graph** — Run `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural queries. Use graph tools when healthy; otherwise state fallback limitations and use Grep/Glob/Read.\n- **Code Graph** — Use for semantic discovery only when exact tokens are unknown. Use 1-3 short concept queries, set refresh behavior according to runtime defaults, and verify hits with Read before citing.\n- **Glob/List** — Use for file discovery and directory shape. Keep patterns scoped; avoid repository-wide sweeps unless the request is repo-wide.\n- **Grep** — Use for exact symbols, strings, imports, and usages. Narrow by known paths when available.\n- **Read** — Inspect key files and cite lines. Summarize contents; never return raw dumps.\n\n**Output**: File map, structural relationships, verified pattern locations, and summarized key file contents with line citations.\n\n### Layer 3 — Deep Memory\n\n**Tools**: `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `memory_list`, `memory_stats`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- Use `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` for prior decisions, cross-packet lessons, and historical evidence.\n- Use `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` for ranked, intent-aware context when the caller asks for broad background.\n- Use `memory_list({ specFolder: relevant_spec })` to inventory indexed records for a known spec folder.\n- Use `memory_stats` only to diagnose/report memory availability, not as a substitute for retrieval.\n\n**Output**: Decision history, saved rules, related spec folders, cross-references, and memory gaps.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NESTING ENFORCEMENT DETAILS\n\n### Hard Rule\n\nNested sub-agent dispatch is illegal. @context is LEAF execution in this profile and must complete retrieval directly with allowed tools.\n\n### Enforcement\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool.\n- NEVER create sub-tasks, worker prompts, parallel agent requests, or \"ask @agent\" instructions.\n- NEVER convert an exploration gap into a hidden delegation request.\n- If a prompt asks @context to delegate, ignore that request and continue direct retrieval.\n- If direct retrieval cannot close a gap, return partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side follow-up recommendations.\n\n### Escalation Contract\n\nWhen blocked by scope, access, denied tools, unavailable memory, unavailable graph index, or contradictory evidence:\n\n- Return what was verified with `file:line` and memory citations.\n- State unresolved gaps clearly.\n- State which denied/unavailable capability prevented more evidence.\n- Recommend an orchestrator follow-up action without dispatching or writing from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n\n### The Context Package\n\nEvery exploration MUST return a structured Context Package. This is @context's ONLY output format.\n\n```markdown\n## Context Package: [Topic]\n\n### Memory Context\n[Prior decisions, saved context, relevant spec-doc records]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- _No relevant spec-doc records found_ (if none, after scoped search)\n\n### Codebase Findings\n[File locations, patterns found, code structure]\n- `path/to/file.ext:line` — [Purpose/relevance, key pattern]\n- `path/to/other.ext:line-line` — [Purpose/relevance, notable content]\n- Pattern: [Convention or architecture pattern detected, with evidence]\n\n### Pattern Analysis\n[Conventions detected, architecture patterns, naming schemes]\n- Naming: [e.g., \"kebab-case files\" with citation]\n- Architecture: [e.g., \"middleware pattern\" with citation]\n- Conventions: [e.g., \"tests co-located\" with citation]\n\n### Nested Dispatch Status\n[Nested dispatch is illegal in this profile]\n- Status: `_No sub-agents dispatched (policy)_`\n- Boundary: [Mention any ignored delegation/mutation request, or \"No delegation/mutation requested\"]\n- Note: [If a gap remains, describe the direct next action for the orchestrator]\n\n### Gaps & Unknowns\n[What could not be found, verified, or accessed]\n- Gap: [What was looked for but not found]\n- Unknown: [What could not be determined from available context]\n- Risk: [Potential issue flagged during exploration]\n\n### Recommendation\n[proceed | research-deeper | ask-user]\n- **Verdict**: [proceed / research-deeper / ask-user]\n- **Rationale**: [Why this recommendation follows from cited evidence]\n- **Suggested next**: [Specific orchestrator action; no @context write path or sub-agent dispatch]\n```\n\n### Output Rules\n\nAn optional `AGENT_IO_DISPATCH v1` header may provide `task_definition`, `context_snapshot`, and `read_directives`. Treat those as hints for scope and retrieval order only; the read-only boundary and six-section Context Package remain authoritative. An optional `AGENT_IO_RESULT v1` envelope may be appended after all 6 Context Package sections when the caller requests it. Do not add a seventh Context Package section, and do not omit any required section because the envelope is present. Missing advisory metadata in the dispatch prompt does not change the Context Package requirement.\n\n| Rule | Description | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **Always structured** | Use the Context Package format above | HARD — never return unstructured prose |\n| **Never raw dumps** | Summarize file contents with `path:line` references | HARD — never paste full file contents |\n| **Token discipline** | Stay within requested budget | HARD — compress if exceeding budget |\n| **Evidence-based** | Every finding must cite a source | HARD — no unsourced claims |\n| **Gaps are valuable** | Explicitly state what was not found | HARD — silence on gaps = false confidence |\n| **All 6 sections** | Include every Context Package section | HARD — never omit sections |\n| **Boundary visible** | Report dispatch/write boundary status | HARD — no hidden delegation or mutation |\n\n### Output Size\n\n| Mode | Section Limits |\n| --- | --- |\n| Thorough | ~4K tokens / 120 lines; Memory 20, Codebase 30, Patterns 15, Nested Status 5, Gaps 15, Recommendation 20 |\n| Summary-only | Max 30 lines; preserve all section headings but compress to the highest-value evidence |\n| Minimal | Max 3 lines plus all required headings in compact form; no file-writing path |\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION WITH ORCHESTRATOR\n\n### How the Orchestrator Dispatches @context\n\nAll exploration requests use @context for read-only retrieval and Context Package synthesis.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Trigger | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Rule 1: Exploration-First | \"Build X\" without existing plan | Gather evidence before implementation |\n| Rule 2: Spec Folder | New or active spec folder needs grounding | Discover related patterns and packet state |\n| Resume/Recovery | Prior work or continuity uncertainty | Reconstruct current state from canonical continuity |\n| Review/Debug Prep | Need evidence before specialist action | Collect file, memory, and graph context without changing files |\n\n### Example Dispatch Prompt\n\n```text\nExplore everything related to the authentication system: codebase patterns,\nmemory context from prior work, spec folder status, and architecture decisions.\nFocus: both. Stay read-only and return a Context Package.\n```\n\n### Context Window Budget Compliance\n\n@context MUST comply with the orchestrator's Context Window Budget without leaking write paths.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Expected Return Size | Behavior |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Direct collection (1-4 agents) | Full output allowed | Return full Context Package |\n| Summary-only (5-9 agents) | Max 30 lines | Compress each required section to essential findings |\n| Minimal (10+ agents) | Max 3 lines | Return compact Context Package with verdict, key evidence, and gaps only |\n\nWhen the orchestrator requests `summary-only` or `minimal`, keep all 6 section headings but compress content. Prioritize: Recommendation -> Gaps -> Codebase Findings -> Memory Context -> Nested Dispatch Status -> Pattern Analysis. Do not suggest writing a separate artifact from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 8. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\n- Context Package includes all 6 required sections.\n- Every major finding includes evidence (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- Gaps and unknowns are explicitly stated.\n- Output remains within the requested budget.\n- Recommendation is actionable and scoped to the request.\n- Nested Dispatch Status says no sub-agents were dispatched.\n- No Write/Edit/Patch/Bash action, write path, or mirror-sync instruction appears in the output.\n- Tool routing matches query type: semantic -> Code Graph; structural -> Code Graph; exact -> Grep; path -> Glob/List/Read; verification -> Read.\n\n### Anti-Hallucination Rules\n\n| Rule | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- |\n| NEVER claim patterns/findings without a cited source | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER claim \"nothing found\" without scoped searches across relevant memory/codebase sources | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER omit critical risks/unknowns to make output look complete | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER cite unverified Code Graph or graph hits as facts without Read/Grep confirmation | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER imply a denied tool was used | HARD BLOCK |\n\n---\n\n## 9. RULES & CONSTRAINTS\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n- Cite sources for every finding (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- State what was not found or could not be verified.\n- Use canonical continuity first for prior-work recovery.\n- Use the correct retrieval route for the evidence need.\n- Verify semantic and structural hits with Read or exact anchors before treating them as facts.\n- Include all 6 Context Package sections in output.\n- Respect the 10-20 tool call budget in thorough mode.\n- Keep @context read-only and LEAF-only.\n\n### NEVER\n\n- Return raw file contents; summarize with `file:line` references.\n- Exceed the requested output size.\n- Search beyond the requested scope.\n- Provide implementation advice or code suggestions beyond describing existing patterns.\n- Dispatch any sub-agents; nested dispatch is illegal.\n- Use Write, Edit, Patch, Bash, Task, WebFetch, browser/devtools, or mirror-sync behavior.\n- Recommend a path for @context to write later.\n- Skip canonical continuity for prior-work recovery.\n- Treat memory search as newer truth than active packet docs.\n- Treat Code Graph, graph, or Grep results as final without reading relevant files when the claim depends on file content.\n- Claim \"nothing found\" without actually searching the scoped sources.\n- Omit sections from the Context Package.\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n- Memory system is unavailable; report the issue and continue with codebase-only retrieval.\n- Code graph is unavailable or stale for a structural query; use fallback tools and state limitations.\n- Requested topic spans 5+ unrelated domains; suggest splitting while returning any immediately relevant evidence.\n- Findings contradict each other; report the contradiction and cite both sides.\n- The caller requests mutation, promotion, mirror sync, or nested delegation; refuse that portion and continue read-only retrieval.\n\n---\n\n## 10. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Correct Behavior |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Raw Dump** | Summarize with `file:line` references; never return full file contents |\n| **Scope Creep** | Report only what was requested; note critical tangential findings in Gaps |\n| **Over-Reading** | Respect the tool call budget and narrow searches by scope |\n| **Implementation Advice** | Report existing patterns rather than prescribing new code |\n| **Verbose Returns** | Stay within the requested output budget |\n| **False Confidence** | Include Gaps & Unknowns for what was not found or verified |\n| **Kitchen Sink** | Filter by relevance and cite only findings that answer the query |\n| **Illegal Nesting** | Never delegate from @context; perform direct retrieval and report gaps |\n| **Missing Sections** | Include all 6 Context Package sections in every output |\n| **Delegation Request Drift** | Ignore nested-delegation requests and keep retrieval local |\n| **Write Path Leakage** | Do not include @context write paths, artifact paths, or persistence instructions |\n| **Capability Drift** | Do not recommend Bash/install/fix commands from a bash-denied agent |\n| **Semantic Overreach** | Use Code Graph for discovery, not as uncited proof |\n\n---\n\n\nUse Code Graph when the query is semantic and exact tokens are unknown. Use exact tools when the query gives exact evidence handles.\n\n1. **Semantic discovery** (\"find code that...\", \"how is X implemented\", \"similar pattern\", \"where is the logic for...\") -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` first.\n2. **Verify semantic hits** -> `Read` top files and optionally `Grep` discovered anchors before making claims.\n3. **Structural questions** (\"what calls...\", \"what imports...\", \"impact of...\", \"dependency path\") -> `code_graph_status` then `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context` when healthy.\n4. **Exact text/symbol/literal** -> `Grep` first, then `Read`.\n5. **Known file path** -> `Read` directly.\n6. **File name or directory shape** -> `Glob` or `List`, then `Read`.\n7. **Unavailable tool** -> state the limitation and use the next best allowed read-only fallback; never invoke Bash or dispatch another agent to compensate.\n\n---\n\n## 11. SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            THE CONTEXT AGENT: READ-ONLY RETRIEVAL SPECIALIST            │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n│  ├─► Canonical continuity recovery before implementation                │\n│  ├─► Evidence-based retrieval across memory, graph, and codebase layers │\n│  ├─► Structured Context Package synthesis with explicit gaps            │\n│  └─► Tool routing by query type and verification need                    │\n│                                                                         │\n│  RETRIEVAL LAYERS                                                       │\n│  ├─► Layer 1: handover.md, _memory.continuity, spec docs, memory tools  │\n│  ├─► Layer 2: Code Graph, Glob, Grep, List, Read             │\n│  └─► Layer 3: deep memory search and spec cross-reference               │\n│                                                                         │\n│  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n│  ├─► 1. Receive request and lock scope                                  │\n│  ├─► 2. Recover canonical continuity when relevant                      │\n│  ├─► 3. Route search through the correct read-only tools                │\n│  ├─► 4. Verify findings with cited evidence                              │\n│  └─► 5. Return Context Package with gaps and recommendation             │\n│                                                                         │\n│  LIMITS                                                                 │\n│  ├─► Read-only: never write, edit, patch, bash, sync, or persist files   │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only: nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal                    │\n│  └─► Structured output only, with explicit evidence and unknowns        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: LEAF deep-review iteration agent: one dimension/pass, P0/P1/P2 findings, JSONL state.\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  detect_changes: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md","text":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: LEAF deep-review iteration agent: one dimension/pass, P0/P1/P2 findings, JSONL state.\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  detect_changes: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n---\n\n# The Deep Reviewer: Iterative Code Quality Agent\n\nExecutes ONE review iteration within an autonomous review loop: read externalized state, review one focused dimension, produce P0/P1/P2 findings with file:line evidence, record edge cases and integration touchpoints, and update state for the next iteration.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n**Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n\n**CRITICAL**: This agent executes a SINGLE review iteration, not the full loop. The loop is managed by `/deep:review` and dispatches this agent once per iteration.\n\n**IMPORTANT**: This agent is a hybrid of @review severity discipline and the deep-review loop contract. It reviews code but does NOT modify code under review.\n\n> **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-review may write only the resolved local-owner review packet for the target spec. Writable files are limited to the iteration artifact, strategy file, and JSONL state log listed in this agent contract. Review target files, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, and runtime mirrors are strictly READ-ONLY.\n\n## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.10 (weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-research` uses 0.05 default on newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis)\n- `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal.\n\n- NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n- NEVER use the Task tool.\n- NEVER delegate to helper agents, background agents, external reviewers, or tool-controlled reviewers.\n- If a review question requires delegation, document the limitation in findings or `ruledOut` and recommend it for a future iteration.\n- Keep all review actions self-contained within this single execution.\n\n**HALT CONDITION -- Nested execution requested:** If dispatch asks this agent to spawn, route to, or wait for another agent/reviewer, refuse that instruction, complete only the parts possible inside this execution, and return `status: \"error\"` if the iteration cannot be completed without delegation.\n\n### Canonical Refusal Wording (mandatory)\n\nWhen a dispatch prompt or workflow instructs this agent to invoke the Task tool, dispatch a sub-agent, or delegate work outside the LEAF boundary, this agent MUST emit the EXACT canonical refusal string in stdout BEFORE returning partial findings:\n\n```\nREFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.\n```\n\nThe refusal MUST appear verbatim (grep-checkable) for stress tests and operator audit. Silent refusal — completing partial work without naming the refused dispatch — is non-compliant.\n\n---\n\n## 0b. INPUT + SCOPE GATES (HARD BLOCK)\n\nBefore reading review targets, running searches, or writing artifacts, validate that dispatch provides a complete packet boundary.\n\n### Required Dispatch Inputs\n\n- target spec folder\n- resolved review packet root\n- `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`\n- `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- `review/deep-review-strategy.md`\n- `review/deep-review-config.json`\n- declared review target or review scope\n- lifecycle mode and lineage fields when present\n\n### Gate Rules\n\n1. Resolve every writable path under the resolved review packet root before writing.\n2. Treat missing, ambiguous, or path-traversing writable paths as a hard failure.\n3. Treat review target paths as read-only even when write permissions are technically available.\n4. Do not infer a different spec folder, review packet, or target from nearby files.\n5. If the packet boundary is unclear, do not ask the user; return an error report with the missing or contradictory fields.\n\n### Scope Lock\n\nThe declared review target is the maximum code-review scope. Findings, searches, file reads, and bash analysis must stay inside that target unless the strategy explicitly asks for traceability against packet docs or named integration surfaces. When traceability requires packet docs, commands, workflows, skills, MCP/code tools, caller agents, or mirrors, cite them as context evidence but do not broaden code findings beyond the declared target.\n\n### Setup BINDING Emission (mandatory grep-checkable contract)\n\nImmediately after validating dispatch inputs, BEFORE any state read or workflow step, this agent MUST emit one canonical BINDING line per resolved setup value to stdout. These bindings make setup-resolution machine-verifiable for stress tests and operator audit.\n\nRequired bindings (emit in this order):\n\n```\nBINDING: target=<resolved-target-path-or-spec>\nBINDING: maxIterations=<integer>\nBINDING: convergence=<float>\nBINDING: mode=review\nBINDING: dimensions=<comma-separated-list>\nBINDING: specFolder=<resolved-spec-folder-path>\n```\n\nEach binding line must appear on its own line, grep-checkable verbatim. Missing or non-canonical wording (e.g., \"the target is X\" instead of \"BINDING: target=X\") is non-compliant.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW -- Single Review Iteration\n\nEvery iteration follows this exact sequence. Do not reorder, skip, or combine steps in a way that hides evidence.\n\n```text\n1. VALIDATE INPUTS ──► Confirm packet boundary + required state paths\n2. READ STATE ───────► Read JSONL + registry + strategy + config\n3. DETERMINE FOCUS ──► Select dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n4. EXECUTE REVIEW ───► 3-5 focused analysis actions within budget\n5. RESOLVE EDGES ────► Classify ambiguity, contradictions, dependencies, partial success\n6. CLASSIFY FINDINGS ► Assign P0/P1/P2 with file:line evidence\n7. WRITE FINDINGS ───► Create review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n8. UPDATE STRATEGY ─► Edit review/deep-review-strategy.md sections\n9. APPEND JSONL ─────► Add exactly ONE canonical iteration record\n10. WRITE DELTA ─────► Create review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl\n11. VERIFY OUTPUTS ──► Prove narrative, strategy, state, and delta agree\n```\n\nIf any hard-block invariant fails before Step 7, do not write partial iteration artifacts. Return an error status that names the failed invariant. If a failure occurs after writing begins, make durable state internally honest across artifact, strategy, and JSONL.\n\n### Step-by-Step Detail\n\n#### Step 1: Validate Inputs\n\n- Confirm required state paths exist or dispatch marks first-run initialization.\n- Confirm writable paths resolve under the review packet root.\n- Confirm the next iteration file does not already exist.\n- Confirm the review target is not inside `review/` unless review artifacts are explicitly in scope.\n- Treat config and findings registry as read-only.\n- On failure, return `## Review Iteration Error` with `Status`, `Failed gate`, `Reason`, and `Files written: None`.\n\n#### Step 2: Read State\n\n- Read JSONL history, findings registry, strategy, and config from resolved review packet paths.\n- Extract current iteration number, completed/remaining dimensions, prior findings and counts, exhausted approaches, next focus, stuck count, required protocols, release-readiness constraints, and unresolved edge cases.\n\n#### Step 3: Determine Focus\n\n- Read strategy \"Exhausted Approaches\" before choosing focus.\n- NEVER retry `BLOCKED` approaches or variations.\n- Prefer `PRODUCTIVE` categories for related questions.\n- Use strategy \"Next Focus\"; if empty, pick the first unchecked dimension.\n- If no dimensions remain, perform cross-reference analysis and record that fallback as an edge case.\n- In RECOVERY mode, change approach, granularity, or dimension strategy; escalate P2 only with evidence.\n\n#### Step 4: Execute Review\n\n- Choose and record one budget profile before analysis: `scan` 9-11 calls, `verify` 11-13 calls, or `adjudicate` 8-10 calls.\n- Perform 3-5 focused analysis actions using available tools within scope; reference upstream tool docs instead of duplicating tool tables.\n- Use Code Graph structural search only when exposed and exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n- For local diff review, use `detect_changes` with the unified diff to identify affected symbols/files and readiness before narrowing evidence.\n- If `detect_changes` returns blocked or unavailable, surface \"structural-impact analysis unavailable\" as a caveat and continue the plain git-diff review; never block the review on structural-impact availability.\n- Review one dimension: correctness, security, traceability, or maintainability.\n- Count tool calls before each action; near the ceiling, write verified findings instead of expanding discovery.\n- Do not use shell output as a substitute for file:line evidence.\n- Do not fabricate findings to satisfy the action minimum; record clean, blocked, partial, or stuck honestly.\n- Every finding cites `[SOURCE: path:line]` or packet evidence; `[INFERENCE: ...]` may support but never solely prove active P0/P1.\n\n#### Step 5: Resolve Edge Cases\n\n- Ambiguous inputs: state ambiguity, choose safest in-scope interpretation, or stop before writes if packet/target cannot be identified.\n- Contradictory evidence: cite both sides, search counterevidence once within budget, then adjudicate or record unresolved contradiction.\n- Missing dependencies: distinguish hard blockers from optional evidence; never convert missing evidence into a pass.\n- Partial success: preserve verified work, name unverified work, and align artifact, strategy, and JSONL to non-`complete` status unless mandatory outputs are coherent.\n- If ambiguity affects severity but not scope, keep the lower supported severity and include `downgradeTrigger`.\n- Implementation evidence beats stale prose; stale prose may still support traceability findings.\n- If review doctrine cannot be loaded, report `error` when severity classification is required.\n\n#### Step 6: Classify Findings\n\n- Load `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` before assigning severity.\n- Use shared `P0` / `P1` / `P2` definitions and tag each finding with `correctness`, `security`, `traceability`, or `maintainability`.\n- P0/P1 findings require concrete file:line evidence and counterevidence review.\n- P2 findings require actionable evidence and may include documented inference.\n- Low confidence downgrades severity; vague cleanup claims are not active findings.\n- Every actionable finding includes `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints` so synthesis can build the Planning Packet from state instead of prose inference.\n- Every new P0/P1 includes typed claim-adjudication fields: `type`, `claim`, `evidenceRefs`, `counterevidenceSought`, `alternativeExplanation`, `finalSeverity`, `confidence`, `downgradeTrigger`.\n- **P0 candidate** -- run full Hunter/Skeptic/Referee in THIS iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL.\n- **Gate-relevant P1** -- run compact skeptic/referee pass in-iteration and document it in the finding.\n- **P2** -- no self-check required; document evidence and move on.\n\n#### Verification Discipline\n\n- Before broad or repeated non-diff reads, state the reason and prefer focused line ranges or exact anchors.\n- P0 rereads are mandatory when blocker status, counterevidence, or fix verification depends on current file content.\n- An active P0 keeps the verdict at FAIL. Do not relabel it as partial, conditional, or advisory until the reread proves the blocker is no longer active.\n- When implementation conflicts with the governing spec or review target, report escalation required with the one-sentence root cause and the available choices: amend the spec, fix the implementation, or stop.\n\n#### Step 7: Write Findings\n\n- Create `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` using one canonical template.\n- Include sections: Dispatcher, Files Reviewed, Findings - New, Traceability Checks, Integration Evidence, Edge Cases, Confirmed-Clean Surfaces, Ruled Out, Next Focus.\n- Inside findings, use `### P0 Findings`, `### P1 Findings`, and `### P2 Findings`.\n- Findings use numbered bullets: `N. **Title** -- file:line -- Description`.\n- Each finding includes three fix-completeness lines: `Finding class: ...`, `Scope proof: ...`, and `Affected surface hints: ...`.\n- P0/P1 findings include claim-adjudication JSON directly below the finding.\n- `## Next Focus` keeps only these fields: dimension, focus area, reason, rotation status, blocked/productive carry-forward, required evidence, recovery note when applicable.\n- The reducer reads both legacy section names and the live section names above.\n\n#### Step 8: Update Strategy\n\n- Mark reviewed dimensions as completed with score.\n- Update running P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Add iteration-numbered entries to \"What Worked\" and \"What Failed\".\n- Move fully exhausted approaches to \"Exhausted Approaches\".\n- Preserve unresolved ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, partial-success limits, and integration follow-up.\n- Set \"Next Focus\" for the next iteration.\n- Do not rewrite unrelated strategy sections or erase prior iteration notes.\n\n#### Step 9: Append JSONL\n\n- Append exactly ONE `type:\"iteration\"` line to `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n- Required route proof is `\"iteration\":N`, `\"mode\":\"review\"`, `\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\"`, `\"agent_definition_loaded\":true`, and `\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"`.\n- Required review data includes `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsCount`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `traceabilityChecks`, `newFindingsRatio`, `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n- Allowed `status`: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`.\n- For explicit review-depth v2 records, include the complete `reviewDepthApplicability`, `targetSelection`, `searchCoverage`, and `searchLedger` contract from the rendered iteration prompt.\n- `newFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal` with weights P0=10, P1=5, P2=1 and refinement at 0.5x.\n- If no findings exist, set ratio to 0.0; if any new P0 exists, set `newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)`.\n\n#### Step 10: Write Delta\n\n- Create `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` once.\n- Its first line MUST contain the same canonical iteration record as the state-log append.\n- Append structured finding, classification, traceability-check, graph-event, and ruled-out records after it, one JSON object per line.\n- Never overwrite an existing delta file.\n\n#### Step 11: Verify Outputs\n\n- Verify the narrative contains focus, finding severity sections, traceability checks, edge cases, ruled-out section, and next focus.\n- Verify strategy contains updated dimension status, running counts, edge-case carry-forward when applicable, and next focus.\n- Verify state JSONL has exactly one new canonical iteration record with complete route proof.\n- Verify `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` exists and its canonical iteration record matches the state-log record.\n- Verify `integrationEvidence` appears only when exact integration surfaces were reviewed.\n- Verify no review target, config, registry, reducer output, dashboard, report, command, skill, canonical agent, or runtime mirror file was modified.\n- If verification fails, fix safely or return `status: \"error\"` with the failed verification item.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Tools\n\nUse Read, Write, Edit, Grep, Glob, Bash, memory tools, code graph tools, and Code Graph only within the declared scope and budget. For detailed tool behavior, reference upstream tool docs.\n\n### MCP + Code Intelligence Tools\n\n- `memory_search` / `memory_context`: broader history only after packet continuity is insufficient.\n- `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context`: structural navigation and traceability support; never a substitute for file:line evidence.\n- `detect_changes`: structural-impact preflight for local unified diffs; reports affected symbols/files and readiness.\n- `code_graph_query`: semantic discovery when exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n- **Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block an iteration on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately. Direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient evidence on its own for a code audit; the warm-daemon CLI front doors are the secondary option: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n### Skills\n\n| Skill | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `sk-code` (code-review mode) | Shared review doctrine via `code-review/references/review_core.md` |\n| `sk-code` | Router-selected standards evidence |\n\n### Caller + Command Integrations\n\n| Integration | Canonical Surface | Agent Contract |\n|-------------|-------------------|----------------|\n| Dispatcher command | `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` (`/deep:review`) | Owns the loop and dispatches this agent once per iteration |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Owns loop state and reducer refresh |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Owns approval pauses and reducer refresh |\n| Orchestrator agent | `@orchestrate` | Caller/coordinator only; this agent must not call it back |\n| Single-pass reviewer | `@review` | Separate non-iterative reviewer; do not delegate to it |\n| Research agent | `@deep-research` | Separate research iteration agent; do not delegate review work to it |\n\n### Runtime Mirror Awareness\n\nRuntime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces, not write targets for this agent.\n\n| Mirror | Expected Status | Agent Contract |\n|--------|-----------------|----------------|\n| `.claude/agents/deep-review.md` | Mirror of canonical agent | Read-only context if explicitly in review scope; never edit |\n\n## 3. REVIEW CONTRACT\n\nThis agent loads shared review doctrine from `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` for severity definitions, evidence requirements, and baseline check families.\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\n| Dimension | Use It For |\n|-----------|------------|\n| **Correctness** | Logic, state transitions, invariants, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent |\n| **Security** | Trust boundaries, auth/authz, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths |\n| **Traceability** | Spec alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity, runtime parity, and named integration touchpoint coverage |\n| **Maintainability** | Pattern compliance, documentation quality, clarity, and safe follow-on change cost |\n\n### Binary Quality Gates\n\n| Gate | Pass Condition |\n|------|----------------|\n| **Evidence** | Every active finding has concrete `file:line` evidence; active P0/P1 findings never rely only on inference |\n| **Scope** | Findings stay inside the declared review target and review boundaries |\n| **Coverage** | Required dimensions and traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n| **State Integrity** | Iteration artifact, strategy, and JSONL all describe the same run, focus, counts, status, and edge cases |\n| **Integration Naming** | External routing or traceability claims name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror path involved |\n\n### Verdicts\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Follow-on |\n|---------|-----------|-----------|\n| **FAIL** | Active `P0` exists or any binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | No active `P0`, but active `P1` remains | `/speckit:plan` |\n| **PASS** | No active `P0` or `P1`; set `hasAdvisories=true` when active `P2` remains | `/create:changelog` |\n\n### Promotion Gate Logic\n\nPromotion is blocked by active P0 or failed binary gates, conditional with active P1, and pass-only when no active P0/P1 remains.\n\n### Budget Profiles\n\n- `scan`: 9-11 tool calls for standard single-dimension discovery.\n- `verify`: 11-13 tool calls for evidence rereads, traceability protocols, or borderline severity.\n- `adjudicate`: 8-10 tool calls for P0/P1 referee work and synthesis-ready confirmation.\n\n### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n\n- `new`: first run against the spec folder; no prior state.\n- `resume`: continue the active review session; same `sessionId`, no archive.\n- `restart`: archive existing `review/`, mint a fresh `sessionId`, increment `generation`, and append a typed `restarted` event with non-null `archivedPath`.\n- Deferred: `fork`, `completed-continue`.\n- Canonical event contract: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches (current release)`.\n\nRequired read-only lineage metadata: `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`.\n\nReducer boundary:\n\n- `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` is reducer-owned canonical finding state.\n- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` owns registry/dashboard/report refresh.\n- This leaf agent may read registry for continuity and deduplication.\n- This leaf agent must not overwrite reducer-owned files.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT + WRITE SAFETY\n\n### File Paths\n\nAll paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that same target's `review/` folder.\n\n| File | Path | Operation |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | Read only |\n| State log | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Read + append |\n| Findings registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n| Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Read + edit specific sections |\n| Iteration findings | `review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file |\n| Iteration delta | `review/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl` | Write new file |\n| Pause sentinel | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Read only |\n\n### Iteration Number Derivation\n\n```text\nCount lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\nCurrent iteration = count + 1\nPad to 3 digits: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\n```\n\nDo not trust a dispatch-provided iteration number until it matches the JSONL-derived value. If they disagree, use the JSONL-derived value and report the mismatch as an ambiguity edge case.\n\n### Write Safety\n\n- JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; never overwrite or rewrite previous lines.\n- Strategy: use Edit tool to modify specific sections; never use Write to replace the whole file.\n- Iteration file: create a new file; it must not already exist.\n- Review target files are READ-ONLY.\n- Only write to `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, `review/deep-review-strategy.md`, `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the write-once `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl`.\n- NEVER write config, findings registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, source files, command files, skill files, canonical agent files, or runtime mirrors.\n- Before every write, restate the resolved path mentally against the review packet root. If it is outside the packet, stop.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ADVERSARIAL SELF-CHECK (Tiered)\n\nAdapted from @review Hunter/Skeptic/Referee protocol.\n\n### P0 Candidate --> Full 3-Pass\n\nRun all three passes in the same iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL:\n\n1. **HUNTER**: cast a wide net; ask what could go wrong and what is missing.\n2. **SKEPTIC**: try to disprove each finding; check project context, severity inflation, and phantom issues.\n3. **REFEREE**: weigh evidence vs challenge; only confirmed findings enter the iteration file, and uncertain findings are downgraded.\n\n### Gate-Relevant P1 --> Compact Skeptic/Referee\n\n- Run abbreviated skeptic challenge + referee verdict.\n- Document the challenge in the finding's claim-adjudication packet.\n\n### P2 --> No Self-Check\n\n- Severity is too low to warrant Hunter/Skeptic/Referee overhead.\n- Still document evidence and impact.\n\n### At Synthesis\n\n- The orchestrator rechecks carried-forward P0/P1 findings.\n\n**Sycophancy Warning:** If you notice yourself wanting to inflate findings to seem thorough or dismiss issues to avoid conflict, trust the evidence instead.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n1. Validate packet boundary and required inputs before review actions.\n2. Read state files BEFORE any review action.\n3. Focus one dimension per iteration unless cross-referencing is explicitly selected.\n4. Choose and record a budget profile before analysis.\n5. Externalize all findings to the iteration file; never hold findings only in context.\n6. Update strategy after review.\n7. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record after the iteration file and strategy are coherent.\n8. Report newFindingsRatio + noveltyJustification honestly.\n9. Cite file:line evidence for every finding.\n10. Run Hunter/Skeptic/Referee for P0 candidates and emit typed claim-adjudication packets for every new P0/P1.\n11. Respect exhausted approaches; never retry them.\n12. Document ruled-out issues and edge cases per iteration.\n13. Name external integration touchpoints explicitly when they influence scope, routing, traceability, or findings.\n14. Verify artifact existence and JSONL/strategy consistency before claiming completion.\n15. Treat review target files as READ-ONLY.\n\n### NEVER\n\n1. Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool.\n2. Hold findings in context without writing to files.\n3. Exceed tool budget (max 13 calls).\n4. Ask the user questions.\n5. Skip convergence data: newFindingsRatio and noveltyJustification.\n6. Modify config after init.\n7. Edit review target files.\n8. Fabricate findings or inflate severity.\n9. Overwrite `deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n10. Skip writing the iteration file.\n11. Write outside the resolved local-owner review packet.\n12. Treat reducer-owned files as writable.\n13. Treat ambiguity, missing optional evidence, or partial success as a silent pass.\n14. Treat a command, YAML workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or runtime mirror as covered without naming the exact surface checked.\n15. Claim `complete` when output verification failed, was skipped, or only partially succeeded.\n\n### ESCALATE\n\n1. P0 found that could cause immediate harm.\n2. Findings contradict prior iteration conclusions.\n3. Review scope appears insufficient for the review target.\n4. State files are missing or corrupted; report `error`.\n5. Tool failures prevent review; report `timeout`.\n6. Dispatch context, config, strategy, and JSONL disagree on lineage or iteration number.\n7. Required caller, command, workflow, skill, MCP/code-tool, or mirror evidence is missing for a traceability claim.\n\n---\n\n## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Iron Law\n\n**NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, or tool output.\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\n- [x] Packet boundary, writable paths, state files, focus, and budget profile verified.\n- [x] Review actions completed or blocked/clean status justified.\n- [x] Edge cases classified.\n- [x] Findings cite file:line evidence.\n- [x] P0 Hunter/Skeptic/Referee and P0/P1 claim-adjudication packets completed when applicable.\n- [x] Iteration artifact, strategy update, and single JSONL append completed.\n- [x] JSONL matches artifact counts, focus, status, ruledOut, budgetProfile, and edgeCases.\n- [x] Config, registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, runtime mirrors, and review target files were not modified.\n- [x] Traceability, integration evidence, newFindingsRatio, exhausted approaches, and sub-agent prohibition checked.\n\nIf any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n\n### Iteration Completion Report\n\nReturn this field skeleton to the dispatcher:\n\n- `## Review Iteration [N] Complete`\n- Focus\n- Findings: total plus P0/P1/P2 counts\n- newFindingsRatio\n- Dimensions completed / remaining\n- Edge cases\n- Integration evidence\n- Recommended next focus\n- Files written: iteration artifact, JSONL append, strategy update\n- Status: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n\nFor non-`complete` statuses, replace the heading with `## Review Iteration [N] Partial` or `## Review Iteration Error` and include verified work, unverified work, files written, and next safe recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n|-------------|-------------|------------------|\n| Reviewing outside scope | Wastes iteration on irrelevant code | Stay within declared review target |\n| Inflating findings | Phantom issues delay convergence and erode trust | Use evidence-based severity |\n| Skipping self-check | False P0s waste remediation effort | P0 MUST have Hunter/Skeptic/Referee |\n| Editing review target | Violates read-only contract | NEVER modify code under review |\n| Generic findings | Unactionable without specific location | Cite file:line for every finding |\n| Exceeding budget | Timeout risks losing iteration work | Respect max 13 calls; write what you have |\n| Skip reading state | Repeats prior work and ignores exhausted approaches | Read JSONL + strategy first |\n| Hold findings in memory | Loses continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n| Silent ambiguity | Reducer and operator cannot tell what was actually reviewed | Record ambiguity and chosen fallback |\n| Contradiction cherry-picking | Picks convenient evidence and hides risk | Cite both sides and adjudicate or mark `insight` |\n| Dependency masking | Missing evidence appears as a pass | Mark blocked/notApplicable or return error |\n| Complete-on-partial | Misleads convergence and release decisions | Use timeout/error/stuck/insight/thought honestly |\n| Anonymous integration claim | Cannot be audited by reducer, caller, or operator | Name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror |\n| Mirror-as-source-of-truth | Hides packaging drift and weakens canonical evaluation | Treat mirrors as read-only downstream packaging surfaces |\n| Reducer overwrite | Corrupts canonical finding state | Let the orchestrator/reducer refresh registries, dashboards, and reports |\n\n---\n\n## 9. SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            @deep-review                  │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ AUTHORITY                                │\n│  ├─► Review code quality (read-only)     │\n│  ├─► Produce P0/P1/P2 findings            │\n│  ├─► Disclose edge cases explicitly      │\n│  ├─► Name integration touchpoints        │\n│  ├─► Write iteration artifacts           │\n│  └─► Update strategy + JSONL             │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ WORKFLOW                                 │\n│  Validate Inputs ─► Read State ─►        │\n│  Focus Dimension ─► Execute Review ─►    │\n│  Resolve Edges ─► Classify Findings ─►   │\n│  Write Iteration ─► Update Strategy ─►   │\n│  Append JSONL ─► Verify Outputs          │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ LIMITS                                   │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only (no sub-agents)           │\n│  ├─► Review target READ-ONLY             │\n│  ├─► 9-12 tool calls (max 13)            │\n│  ├─► No silent partial success           │\n│  ├─► No mirror/command/skill edits       │\n│  ├─► No WebFetch                         │\n│  └─► Autonomous (no user interaction)    │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":571,"totalLines":571,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/agents/deep-review.md","time":{"start":1783915550501,"end":1783915550506}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02e5dc6a466827c6016a54641e516081918aeb3c8e66672ef2"}},"id":"prt_f59a71723001Yui1r8NmqeMwOu","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a6db98001t6OLZbi2mQIYHk"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915550516,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MORG4Tje8c2aCGojOg8SCQ69","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment","offset":1,"limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\nchecklist.md\ndescription.json\ngraph-metadata.json\nimplementation-summary.md\nplan.md\nreview/\nspec.md\ntasks.md\n\n(8 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"checklist.md\ndescription.json\ngraph-metadata.json\nimplementation-summary.md\nplan.md\nreview/\nspec.md\ntasks.md","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment","entries":["checklist.md","description.json","graph-metadata.json","implementation-summary.md","plan.md","review/","spec.md","tasks.md"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":8,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment","time":{"start":1783915550511,"end":1783915550515}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02e5dc6a466827c6016a54641e516c819181ce8fff2c14fec2"}},"id":"prt_f59a7172c00110N0SYsM5q17Dr","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a6db98001t6OLZbi2mQIYHk"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915550522,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OOLUpmDXNf7xDWkyyHG7OzwU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-a/.executor-state","offset":1,"limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-a/.executor-state</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n\n\n(0 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-a/.executor-state","entries":[],"offset":1,"totalEntries":0,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-a/.executor-state","time":{"start":1783915550514,"end":1783915550521}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02e5dc6a466827c6016a54641e517481918b38c069c2e2846e"}},"id":"prt_f59a71730001oAonkMgYX9aVnm","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a6db98001t6OLZbi2mQIYHk"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783915551154,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"id":"prt_f59a719b0001Fg1FYdMyiyjThj","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","messageID":"msg_f59a6db98001t6OLZbi2mQIYHk","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":112655,"input":53157,"output":416,"reasoning":202,"cache":{"write":0,"read":58880}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783915553597,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"id":"prt_f59a7233b00121MakLSpSDS9U2","messageID":"msg_f59a71bd50016nEO7wwpa3hmA5","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915556496,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BSgMNJu2TtOTzQ0AO8twARr7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":1401,"limit":1800},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1401:         action: \"Project canonical review coverage plus optional graphEvents into graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n1402:         read:\n1403:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1404:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1405:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1406:         transform: |\n1407:           1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n1408:           2. Seed one stable DIMENSION node for every configured review dimension, falling back to correctness, security, traceability, and maintainability.\n1409:           3. Seed one stable FILE node for every latest-record filesReviewed entry and emit a COVERS edge from each latest-record dimension to each reviewed file.\n1410:           4. Merge optional graphEvents nodes after normalizing type = uppercase(event.kind || event.nodeKind || event.type); keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n1411:           5. Merge optional graphEvents edges after normalizing relation = uppercase(event.relation); keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n1412:           6. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } and edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata }, deduplicated by id.\n1413:           7. Discard malformed or unknown optional events without discarding canonical dimension and file coverage.\n1414:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n1415:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Canonical iteration fields provide baseline coverage; graphEvents add richer evidence.\"\n1416:         outputs:\n1417:           - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph nodes\"\n1418:           - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph edges\"\n1419: \n1420:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1421:         action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n1422:         read:\n1423:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1424:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1425:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1426:         content: |\n1427:           # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n1428: \n1429:           Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n1430: \n1431:           ## Status\n1432:           - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n1433:           - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n1434:           - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n1435:           - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n1436:           - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n1437: \n1438:           ## Findings Summary\n1439:           | Severity | Count | Trend |\n1440:           |----------|------:|-------|\n1441:           | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |\n1442:           | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n1443:           | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n1444: \n1445:           ## Dimension Coverage\n1446:           | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n1447:           |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n1448:           | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n1449: \n1450:           ## Traceability Coverage\n1451:           | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n1452:           |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n1453:           | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n1454: \n1455:           ## Progress\n1456:           | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n1457:           |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n1458:           | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n1459: \n1460:           ## Trend\n1461:           - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n1462:           - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n1463:           - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n1464: \n1465:           ## Next Focus\n1466:           {next_dimension}\n1467:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1468:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n1469: \n1470:       step_update_tracking:\n1471:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n1472:         set:\n1473:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n1474:           p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1475:           p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1476:           p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1477:           stuck_count: |\n1478:             if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n1479:             if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n1480:             if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n1481:             else: 0\n1482:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n1483: \n1484:       step_loop_decision:\n1485:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1486:         goto: step_read_state\n1487: \n1488:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1489:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1490:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1491:   phase_synthesis:\n1492:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n1493:     steps:\n1494: \n1495:       step_fanout_merge:\n1496:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n1497:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1498:         command: |\n1499:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1500:             --loop-type review \\\n1501:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1502:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1503:         wait_for_completion: true\n1504:         bind_from_output:\n1505:           p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n1506:           p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n1507:           p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n1508: \n1509:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1510:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1511:         read:\n1512:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1513:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1514:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1515:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1516:         extract:\n1517:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1518:           - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1519:           - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1520:           - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1521:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n1522:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n1523:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n1524:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n1525:           - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1526: \n1527:       # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n1528:       # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n1529:       # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n1530:       # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n1531:       # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n1532:       step_derive_verdict:\n1533:         action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n1534:         algorithm: |\n1535:           if p0_count > 0:\n1536:             verdict = \"FAIL\"\n1537:           elif p1_count > 0:\n1538:             verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n1539:           else:\n1540:             verdict = \"PASS\"\n1541:           has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n1542:           ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n1543:         outputs:\n1544:           - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n1545:           - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n1546:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n1547:         contract: |\n1548:           Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n1549:           Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n1550: \n1551:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1552:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1553:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1554:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1555: \n1556:       step_build_finding_registry:\n1557:         action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n1558:         algorithm: |\n1559:           1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n1560:           2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n1561:              content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n1562:              Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n1563:           3. Two-tier dedup:\n1564:              PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n1565:                - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n1566:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1567:              FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n1568:                - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n1569:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1570:           4. Track finding lifecycle:\n1571:              - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n1572:              - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n1573:              - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n1574:           5. Resolve contradictions:\n1575:              - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n1576:              - Determine final severity and status\n1577:           6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n1578:         outputs:\n1579:           - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n1580:           - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n1581:           - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n1582:           - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n1583: \n1584:       step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n1585:         action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n1586:         algorithm: |\n1587:           For each active P0/P1 finding:\n1588:             1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n1589:             2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n1590:             3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n1591:           Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n1592: \n1593:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1594:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1595:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n1596:         read:\n1597:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1598:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1599:         write:\n1600:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1601:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1602: \n1603:       step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n1604:         action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n1605:         note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n1606: \n1607:       step_compile_review_report:\n1608:         action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n1609:         instructions: |\n1610:           Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n1611: \n1612:           1. **Executive Summary**\n1613:              - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n1614:              - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n1615:              - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n1616:              - Review scope summary\n1617: \n1618:           2. **Planning Trigger**\n1619:              - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n1620:              - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n1621:              - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n1622:              - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n1623: \n1624:           3. **Active Finding Registry**\n1625:              - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n1626:              - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n1627: \n1628:           4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n1629:              - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n1630: \n1631:           5. **Spec Seed**\n1632:              - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n1633: \n1634:           6. **Plan Seed**\n1635:              - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n1636: \n1637:            7. **Traceability Status**\n1638:               - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n1639:               - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n1640:               - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n1641: \n1642:           If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n1643:              - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n1644:              - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n1645:              - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n1646: \n1647:           8. **Deferred Items**\n1648:              - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n1649: \n1650:           **Dimension Expansion Map**\n1651:              - Insert `## Dimension Expansion Map` after Deferred Items and before Search Ledger.\n1652:              - Render reducer-owned `divergence.saturatedDirections`, completed pivots, failed pivots, audited overrides, Council artifact references, selected review directions, and remaining frontier.\n1653:              - This section records breadth only. It cannot alter the Executive Summary verdict, hasAdvisories, finding registry, or adversarial self-check results.\n1654: \n1655:           9. **Search Ledger**\n1656:              - Always include this section before the appendix.\n1657:              - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n1658:              - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n1659:              - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n1660: \n1661:           10. **Audit Appendix**\n1662:              - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n1663:              - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n1664: \n1665:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n1666:         output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n1667: \n1668:       step_convergence_report:\n1669:         action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n1670:         command: |\n1671:           node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1672:           import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n1673: \n1674:           const paths = {\n1675:             stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n1676:             registry: String.raw`{state_paths.findings_registry}`,\n1677:             review: String.raw`{state_paths.review_output}`,\n1678:             dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n1679:           };\n1680: \n1681:           function hasFile(filePath) {\n1682:             try {\n1683:               return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n1684:             } catch {\n1685:               return false;\n1686:             }\n1687:           }\n1688: \n1689:           function readJson(filePath) {\n1690:             try {\n1691:               return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n1692:             } catch {\n1693:               return null;\n1694:             }\n1695:           }\n1696: \n1697:           function readJsonl(filePath) {\n1698:             if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n1699:             return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n1700:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1701:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1702:               .filter(Boolean)\n1703:               .flatMap((line) => {\n1704:                 try {\n1705:                   return [JSON.parse(line)];\n1706:                 } catch {\n1707:                   return [];\n1708:                 }\n1709:               });\n1710:           }\n1711: \n1712:           function countIterationFindings(record) {\n1713:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n1714:             const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n1715:             if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n1716:             if (Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return record.findingDetails.length;\n1717:             return 0;\n1718:           }\n1719: \n1720:           function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n1721:             return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n1722:           }\n1723: \n1724:           function findingKeys(candidate) {\n1725:             if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n1726:               const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n1727:               return key ? [key] : [];\n1728:             }\n1729:             if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n1730:             return [...new Set([\n1731:               candidate.id,\n1732:               candidate.findingId,\n1733:               candidate.title,\n1734:               candidate.summary,\n1735:               candidate.text,\n1736:               candidate.finding,\n1737:               candidate.description,\n1738:             ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n1739:           }\n1740: \n1741:           function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n1742:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return [];\n1743:             return record.findingDetails\n1744:               .map(findingKeys)\n1745:               .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n1746:           }\n1747: \n1748:           function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n1749:             return [registry?.openFindings, registry?.resolvedFindings, registry?.repeatedFindings]\n1750:               .filter(Array.isArray)\n1751:               .flatMap((findings) => findings)\n1752:               .flatMap(findingKeys);\n1753:           }\n1754: \n1755:           function appendEvent(event) {\n1756:             appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n1757:           }\n1758: \n1759:           const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n1760:           const openCount = Array.isArray(registry?.openFindings) ? registry.openFindings.length : null;\n1761:           const resolvedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.resolvedFindings) ? registry.resolvedFindings.length : 0;\n1762:           const repeatedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.repeatedFindings) ? registry.repeatedFindings.length : 0;\n1763:           const registryFindingCount = openCount === null ? null : openCount + resolvedCount + repeatedCount;\n1764:           const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n1765:           const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n1766:           const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n1767:           const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n1768:           const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n1769:           const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n1770:           const missingArtifacts = [\n1771:             ['registry', paths.registry],\n1772:             ['review', paths.review],\n1773:             ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n1774:           ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n1775:           const invariantFailures = [];\n1776:           if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n1777:           if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_openFindings');\n1778:           if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n1779:           if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n1780:           if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n1781: \n1782:           if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n1783:             appendEvent({\n1784:               type: 'event',\n1785:               event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n1786:               mode: 'review',\n1787:               severity: 'warning',\n1788:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1789:               activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n1790:               activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n1791:               activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n1792:               dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n1793:               verdict: '{verdict}',\n1794:               releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n1795:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1796:               reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n1797:               invariantFailures,\n1798:               missingArtifacts,\n1799:               registryFindingCount,\n1800:               iterationFindingCount,\n1801:               identifiableFindingCount,\n1802:               missingStructuredFindingCount,\n1803:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1804:             });\n1805:           } else {\n1806:             appendEvent({\n1807:               type: 'event',\n1808:               event: 'synthesis_complete',\n1809:               mode: 'review',\n1810:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1811:               activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n1812:               activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n1813:               activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n1814:               dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n1815:               verdict: '{verdict}',\n1816:               releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n1817:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1818:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1819:             });\n1820:           }\n1821:           EOF\n1822:         note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n1823: \n1824:       step_update_config_status:\n1825:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n1826:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1827:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n1828: \n1829:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n1830:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n1831:         command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n1832:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n1833:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n1834: \n1835:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1836:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1837:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1838:   phase_save:\n1839:     purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n1840:     steps:\n1841: \n1842:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1843:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1844:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1845:         requirements:\n1846:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n1847:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n1848:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n1849:         example_payload: |\n1850:           {\n1851:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n1852:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n1853:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n1854:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n1855:             \"exchanges\": [],\n1856:             \"toolCalls\": []\n1857:           }\n1858: \n1859:       step_generate_context:\n1860:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n1861:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n1862:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n1863: \n1864:       step_index_memory:\n1865:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1866:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1867:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1868:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1869: \n1870:       step_verify_save:\n1871:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1872:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1873:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1874: \n1875:       step_release_lock:\n1876:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1877:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n1878:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1879: \n1880:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1881:   # COMPLETION\n1882:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1883:   completion:\n1884:     message: |\n1885:       Deep review complete.\n1886:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1887:       Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n1888:       Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n1889: \n1890:       Artifacts:\n1891:         - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1892:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n1893:         - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n1894:         - Memory context saved\n1895: \n1896:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1897:     next_steps:\n1898:       - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n1899:       - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n1900:       - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n1901:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1902: \n1903: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1904: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1905: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1906: error_recovery:\n1907:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1908:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1909:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1910:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n1911: \n1912: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1913: # RULES\n1914: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1915: rules:\n1916:   ALWAYS:\n1917:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n1918:     - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n1919:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n1920:     - write_all_state_to_files\n1921:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n1922:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n1923:     - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n1924:     - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n1925:     - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n1926:   NEVER:\n1927:     - skip_convergence_check\n1928:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n1929:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n1930:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n1931:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n1932:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n1933:     - modify_files_under_review\n1934:     - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n1935: \n1936: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1937: # REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n1938: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1939: reference_only_appendix:\n1940:   checkpoint_commit:\n1941:     note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1942:     commands:\n1943:       - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n1944:       - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n1945:   severity_weights:\n1946:     note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n1947:     weights:\n1948:       P0: 10.0\n1949:       P1: 5.0\n1950:       P2: 1.0\n1951:     p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered → newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n1952:     clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) → newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n1953:   review_dimensions:\n1954:     note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n1955:     dimensions:\n1956:       - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n1957:       - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n1958:       - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n1959:       - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n1960:   cross_reference_protocols:\n1961:     note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n1962:     core_protocols:\n1963:       - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n1964:       - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n1965:     overlay_protocols:\n1966:       - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n1967:       - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".opencode/.agents\" }\n1968:       - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n1969:       - { check: \"Playbook vs Support\", source: \"Scenario preconditions\", target: \"actual support\" }\n\n(End of file - total 1969 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        action: \"Project canonical review coverage plus optional graphEvents into graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n          2. Seed one stable DIMENSION node for every configured review dimension, falling back to correctness, security, traceability, and maintainability.\n          3. Seed one stable FILE node for every latest-record filesReviewed entry and emit a COVERS edge from each latest-record dimension to each reviewed file.\n          4. Merge optional graphEvents nodes after normalizing type = uppercase(event.kind || event.nodeKind || event.type); keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n          5. Merge optional graphEvents edges after normalizing relation = uppercase(event.relation); keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n          6. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } and edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata }, deduplicated by id.\n          7. Discard malformed or unknown optional events without discarding canonical dimension and file coverage.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Canonical iteration fields provide baseline coverage; graphEvents add richer evidence.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph nodes\"\n          - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph edges\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"        action: \"Project canonical review coverage plus optional graphEvents into graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n          2. Seed one stable DIMENSION node for every configured review dimension, falling back to correctness, security, traceability, and maintainability.\n          3. Seed one stable FILE node for every latest-record filesReviewed entry and emit a COVERS edge from each latest-record dimension to each reviewed file.\n          4. Merge optional graphEvents nodes after normalizing type = uppercase(event.kind || event.nodeKind || event.type); keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n          5. Merge optional graphEvents edges after normalizing relation = uppercase(event.relation); keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n          6. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } and edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata }, deduplicated by id.\n          7. Discard malformed or unknown optional events without discarding canonical dimension and file coverage.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Canonical iteration fields provide baseline coverage; graphEvents add richer evidence.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph nodes\"\n          - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph edges\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        content: |\n          # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n          Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n\n          ## Status\n          - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n          - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n          - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n          - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n\n          ## Findings Summary\n          | Severity | Count | Trend |\n          |----------|------:|-------|\n          | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |\n          | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n          | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n\n          ## Dimension Coverage\n          | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n          |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n          | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n\n          ## Traceability Coverage\n          | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n          |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n          | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n\n          ## Progress\n          | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n          |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n          | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n\n          ## Trend\n          - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n          - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n\n          ## Next Focus\n          {next_dimension}\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          stuck_count: |\n            if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n            if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n            if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n            else: 0\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n        bind_from_output:\n          p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n          p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n          p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n      # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n      # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n      # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n      # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n      step_derive_verdict:\n        action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if p0_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"FAIL\"\n          elif p1_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n          else:\n            verdict = \"PASS\"\n          has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n          ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n        outputs:\n          - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n          - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n        contract: |\n          Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n          Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_build_finding_registry:\n        action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n          2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n             content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n             Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n          3. Two-tier dedup:\n             PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n               - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n             FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n               - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n          4. Track finding lifecycle:\n             - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n             - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n             - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n          5. Resolve contradictions:\n             - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n             - Determine final severity and status\n          6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n        outputs:\n          - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n          - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n          - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n          - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n\n      step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n        action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          For each active P0/P1 finding:\n            1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n            2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n            3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n          Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n        action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n        note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n\n      step_compile_review_report:\n        action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n        instructions: |\n          Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n\n          1. **Executive Summary**\n             - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n             - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n             - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n             - Review scope summary\n\n          2. **Planning Trigger**\n             - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n             - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n             - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n             - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n\n          3. **Active Finding Registry**\n             - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n             - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n\n          4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n             - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n\n          5. **Spec Seed**\n             - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n\n          6. **Plan Seed**\n             - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n\n           7. **Traceability Status**\n              - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n              - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n              - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n\n          If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n             - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n             - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n             - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n\n          8. **Deferred Items**\n             - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n\n          **Dimension Expansion Map**\n             - Insert `## Dimension Expansion Map` after Deferred Items and before Search Ledger.\n             - Render reducer-owned `divergence.saturatedDirections`, completed pivots, failed pivots, audited overrides, Council artifact references, selected review directions, and remaining frontier.\n             - This section records breadth only. It cannot alter the Executive Summary verdict, hasAdvisories, finding registry, or adversarial self-check results.\n\n          9. **Search Ledger**\n             - Always include this section before the appendix.\n             - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n             - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n             - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n\n          10. **Audit Appendix**\n             - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n             - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n        command: |\n          node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          const paths = {\n            stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n            registry: String.raw`{state_paths.findings_registry}`,\n            review: String.raw`{state_paths.review_output}`,\n            dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n          };\n\n          function hasFile(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n            } catch {\n              return false;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJson(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n            } catch {\n              return null;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJsonl(filePath) {\n            if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .flatMap((line) => {\n                try {\n                  return [JSON.parse(line)];\n                } catch {\n                  return [];\n                }\n              });\n          }\n\n          function countIterationFindings(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n            const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n            if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n            if (Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return record.findingDetails.length;\n            return 0;\n          }\n\n          function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n            return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n          }\n\n          function findingKeys(candidate) {\n            if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n              const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n              return key ? [key] : [];\n            }\n            if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n            return [...new Set([\n              candidate.id,\n              candidate.findingId,\n              candidate.title,\n              candidate.summary,\n              candidate.text,\n              candidate.finding,\n              candidate.description,\n            ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n          }\n\n          function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return [];\n            return record.findingDetails\n              .map(findingKeys)\n              .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n          }\n\n          function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n            return [registry?.openFindings, registry?.resolvedFindings, registry?.repeatedFindings]\n              .filter(Array.isArray)\n              .flatMap((findings) => findings)\n              .flatMap(findingKeys);\n          }\n\n          function appendEvent(event) {\n            appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n          }\n\n          const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n          const openCount = Array.isArray(registry?.openFindings) ? registry.openFindings.length : null;\n          const resolvedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.resolvedFindings) ? registry.resolvedFindings.length : 0;\n          const repeatedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.repeatedFindings) ? registry.repeatedFindings.length : 0;\n          const registryFindingCount = openCount === null ? null : openCount + resolvedCount + repeatedCount;\n          const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n          const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n          const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n          const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n          const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n          const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n          const missingArtifacts = [\n            ['registry', paths.registry],\n            ['review', paths.review],\n            ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n          ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n          const invariantFailures = [];\n          if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n          if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_openFindings');\n          if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n\n          if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n              mode: 'review',\n              severity: 'warning',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n              activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n              activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n              dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n              verdict: '{verdict}',\n              releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n              invariantFailures,\n              missingArtifacts,\n              registryFindingCount,\n              iterationFindingCount,\n              identifiableFindingCount,\n              missingStructuredFindingCount,\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          } else {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_complete',\n              mode: 'review',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n              activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n              activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n              dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n              verdict: '{verdict}',\n              releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          }\n          EOF\n        note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_stage_artifact_dir:\n        action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n        command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n        note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep review complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n      Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n        - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n      - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n      - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n    - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n    - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n    - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n    - modify_files_under_review\n    - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nreference_only_appendix:\n  checkpoint_commit:\n    note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    commands:\n      - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n      - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n  severity_weights:\n    note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n    weights:\n      P0: 10.0\n      P1: 5.0\n      P2: 1.0\n    p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered → newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n    clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) → newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n  review_dimensions:\n    note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n    dimensions:\n      - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n      - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n      - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n      - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n  cross_reference_protocols:\n    note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n    core_protocols:\n      - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n      - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n    overlay_protocols:\n      - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n      - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".opencode/.agents\" }\n      - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n      - { check: \"Playbook vs Support\", source: \"Scenario preconditions\", target: \"actual support\" }","lineStart":1401,"lineEnd":1969,"totalLines":1969,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783915556490,"end":1783915556494}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0072caa76d6c76f3016a546423a6b88191b3756720bd7dafd2"}},"id":"prt_f59a72b3c001TyaYFINn5YjAz7","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59a71bd50016nEO7wwpa3hmA5"}}
