{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915647335,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_YooXOmGoABF8VJOxPf8LbE3w","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"F001|F002|Purpose|broken link|0 broken|duplicate","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 48 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/lineages/gpt56-sol-high/iterations/iteration-002.md:\n  Line 22: 1. **F001: Twenty-one conformed references duplicate the intro in Purpose** -- `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/implementation_workflows/validation_minification_and_cdn.md:16-24` -- The intro and Purpose are identical in this representative file, and the same class appears in 21 target references. The governing template explicitly says not to duplicate intro content in Section 1 at `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md:84-87`.\n\n  Line 24:    - Scope proof: all 163 Git-tracked target files were parsed; 21 exact/containment duplicates were found.\n\n  Line 28: {\"findingId\":\"F001\",\"claim\":\"Twenty-one target references duplicate the H1 intro in Section 1 Purpose despite the canonical template explicitly forbidding that duplication.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md:84-87\",\".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/implementation_workflows/validation_minification_and_cdn.md:16-24\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Ran validate_document.py and the complete section matrix over all 163 files; those checks pass but do not enforce semantic duplication.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Mechanical wrapper generation may have treated repeated Purpose prose as acceptable, but the na