{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915823840,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_BWCAxC4p8mj37Ahh3D5mYJUm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh --help","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"validate-spec.sh - Spec Folder Validation Orchestrator (v2.0)\n\nUSAGE: ./validate-spec.sh <folder-path> [OPTIONS]\n\nOPTIONS:\n    --help, -h     Show help     --version, -v  Show version\n    --json         JSON output   --strict       Warnings as errors\n    --verbose      Detailed      --quiet, -q    Results only\n    --recursive    Validate parent + all [0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/ child phase folders\n    --no-recursive Disable auto-recursive validation when phase children exist\n\nEXIT CODES: 0=pass, 1=user error, 2=validation error, 3=system error\n\nRULES BY CATEGORY:\n  authored_template:\n    FILE_EXISTS [error] - Validates required spec documents for the declared documentation level.\n    PLACEHOLDER_FILLED [error] - Rejects unfilled template placeholders in authored spec documents.\n    COMMENT_HYGIENE_MARKER [error] - Rejects ephemeral finding markers inside HTML comments in authored spec documents.\n    SCAFFOLD_NEVER_TOUCHED [error] - Rejects scaffold-signature markers in required docs when spec.md claims Complete status.\n    STATUS_CROSS_DOC_CONSISTENCY [warn] - Advisory-by-default check that spec.md and implementation-summary.md status fields classify to the same delivery state.\n    SECTIONS_PRESENT [warn] - Checks that required high-level markdown sections are present.\n    LEVEL_DECLARED [info] - Reports whether the documentation level was declared or inferred.\n    PRIORITY_TAGS [warn] - Validates P0/P1/P2 priority tags on checklist items.\n    EVIDENCE_CITED [warn] - Checks completed checklist/tasks items for evidence citations.\n    AC_COVERAGE [info] - Opt-in advisory scan for acceptance-criteria traceability coverage.\n    ANCHORS_VALID [error] - Validates anchor syntax, pairing, order, and uniqueness.\n    FRONTMATTER_MEMORY_BLOCK [error] - Validates canonical _memory continuity frontmatter blocks.\n    SPEC_DOC_SUFFICIENCY [error] - Checks implementation-summary sufficiency after save/write flows.\n    TOC_POLICY [error] - Enforces table-of-contents placement policy.\n    PHASE_LINKS [warn] - Checks parent/child phase-link consistency.\n    PHASE_PARENT_CONTENT [warn] - Warns when phase-parent spec.md includes migration-history narrative tokens.\n    CURRENT_STATE_DISCIPLINE [info] - Advises when implementation-summary.md includes migration-history narrative tokens.\n    AI_PROTOCOLS [error] - Validates AI execution protocol sections in high-governance specs.\n    COMPLEXITY_MATCH [error] - Checks declared level against content complexity signals.\n    FOLDER_NAMING [error] - Validates numbered spec-folder naming conventions.\n    FRONTMATTER_VALID [error] - Validates YAML frontmatter structure and required semantic values.\n    LEVEL_MATCH [error] - Checks required files match the declared documentation level.\n    SECTION_COUNTS [error] - Checks section-count expectations for authored spec documents.\n    SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY [error] - Verifies inline markdown references resolve within spec docs.\n    TEMPLATE_SOURCE [error] - Checks SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE provenance markers.\n    TEMPLATE_HEADERS [error] - Checks required template header order and naming.\n  operational_runtime:\n    MERGE_LEGALITY [error] - Validates generated merge payloads against target anchor shape.\n    CROSS_ANCHOR_CONTAMINATION [error] - Detects route/category mismatches before generated content is merged.\n    POST_SAVE_FINGERPRINT [error] - Verifies post-save fingerprints for generated writes.\n    GRAPH_METADATA_PRESENT [warn] - Checks generated description and graph metadata are present.\n    GRAPH_METADATA_CHILD_DRIFT [warn] - Flags graph-metadata.json children_ids missing on-disk phase children the writer would add (advisory unless SPECKIT_CHILD_DRIFT_ENFORCE=true).\n    NORMALIZER_LINT [error] - Strict-only lint for duplicated runtime normalizer helpers.\n    LINKS_VALID [warn] - Validates cross-skill wikilinks when explicitly enabled.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_ROOT_SPEC_REQUIRED [error] - Ensures canonical saves include a root spec reference.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_SOURCE_DOCS_REQUIRED [error] - Ensures canonical saves include source document references.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_LINEAGE_REQUIRED [error] - Ensures canonical save lineage metadata is present.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_PACKET_IDENTITY_NORMALIZED [error] - Checks canonical save packet identity normalization.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_DESCRIPTION_GRAPH_FRESHNESS [error] - Checks generated description/graph freshness for canonical saves.\n    CONTINUITY_FRESHNESS [warn strict-only] - Strict-mode freshness check for continuity frontmatter.\n    EVIDENCE_MARKER_LINT [warn strict-only] - Strict-mode lint for evidence marker formatting.\n\nLEVELS: 1=spec+plan+tasks+impl-summary*, 2=+checklist, 3=+decision-record\n        review=spec+review/review-report (lean review record, marker-gated)\n        *impl-summary required after tasks completed\n","metadata":{"output":"validate-spec.sh - Spec Folder Validation Orchestrator (v2.0)\n\nUSAGE: ./validate-spec.sh <folder-path> [OPTIONS]\n\nOPTIONS:\n    --help, -h     Show help     --version, -v  Show version\n    --json         JSON output   --strict       Warnings as errors\n    --verbose      Detailed      --quiet, -q    Results only\n    --recursive    Validate parent + all [0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/ child phase folders\n    --no-recursive Disable auto-recursive validation when phase children exist\n\nEXIT CODES: 0=pass, 1=user error, 2=validation error, 3=system error\n\nRULES BY CATEGORY:\n  authored_template:\n    FILE_EXISTS [error] - Validates required spec documents for the declared documentation level.\n    PLACEHOLDER_FILLED [error] - Rejects unfilled template placeholders in authored spec documents.\n    COMMENT_HYGIENE_MARKER [error] - Rejects ephemeral finding markers inside HTML comments in authored spec documents.\n    SCAFFOLD_NEVER_TOUCHED [error] - Rejects scaffold-signature markers in required docs when spec.md claims Complete status.\n    STATUS_CROSS_DOC_CONSISTENCY [warn] - Advisory-by-default check that spec.md and implementation-summary.md status fields classify to the same delivery state.\n    SECTIONS_PRESENT [warn] - Checks that required high-level markdown sections are present.\n    LEVEL_DECLARED [info] - Reports whether the documentation level was declared or inferred.\n    PRIORITY_TAGS [warn] - Validates P0/P1/P2 priority tags on checklist items.\n    EVIDENCE_CITED [warn] - Checks completed checklist/tasks items for evidence citations.\n    AC_COVERAGE [info] - Opt-in advisory scan for acceptance-criteria traceability coverage.\n    ANCHORS_VALID [error] - Validates anchor syntax, pairing, order, and uniqueness.\n    FRONTMATTER_MEMORY_BLOCK [error] - Validates canonical _memory continuity frontmatter blocks.\n    SPEC_DOC_SUFFICIENCY [error] - Checks implementation-summary sufficiency after save/write flows.\n    TOC_POLICY [error] - Enforces table-of-contents placement policy.\n    PHASE_LINKS [warn] - Checks parent/child phase-link consistency.\n    PHASE_PARENT_CONTENT [warn] - Warns when phase-parent spec.md includes migration-history narrative tokens.\n    CURRENT_STATE_DISCIPLINE [info] - Advises when implementation-summary.md includes migration-history narrative tokens.\n    AI_PROTOCOLS [error] - Validates AI execution protocol sections in high-governance specs.\n    COMPLEXITY_MATCH [error] - Checks declared level against content complexity signals.\n    FOLDER_NAMING [error] - Validates numbered spec-folder naming conventions.\n    FRONTMATTER_VALID [error] - Validates YAML frontmatter structure and required semantic values.\n    LEVEL_MATCH [error] - Checks required files match the declared documentation level.\n    SECTION_COUNTS [error] - Checks section-count expectations for authored spec documents.\n    SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY [error] - Verifies inline markdown references resolve within spec docs.\n    TEMPLATE_SOURCE [error] - Checks SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE provenance markers.\n    TEMPLATE_HEADERS [error] - Checks required template header order and naming.\n  operational_runtime:\n    MERGE_LEGALITY [error] - Validates generated merge payloads against target anchor shape.\n    CROSS_ANCHOR_CONTAMINATION [error] - Detects route/category mismatches before generated content is merged.\n    POST_SAVE_FINGERPRINT [error] - Verifies post-save fingerprints for generated writes.\n    GRAPH_METADATA_PRESENT [warn] - Checks generated description and graph metadata are present.\n    GRAPH_METADATA_CHILD_DRIFT [warn] - Flags graph-metadata.json children_ids missing on-disk phase children the writer would add (advisory unless SPECKIT_CHILD_DRIFT_ENFORCE=true).\n    NORMALIZER_LINT [error] - Strict-only lint for duplicated runtime normalizer helpers.\n    LINKS_VALID [warn] - Validates cross-skill wikilinks when explicitly enabled.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_ROOT_SPEC_REQUIRED [error] - Ensures canonical saves include a root spec reference.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_SOURCE_DOCS_REQUIRED [error] - Ensures canonical saves include source document references.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_LINEAGE_REQUIRED [error] - Ensures canonical save lineage metadata is present.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_PACKET_IDENTITY_NORMALIZED [error] - Checks canonical save packet identity normalization.\n    CANONICAL_SAVE_DESCRIPTION_GRAPH_FRESHNESS [error] - Checks generated description/graph freshness for canonical saves.\n    CONTINUITY_FRESHNESS [warn strict-only] - Strict-mode freshness check for continuity frontmatter.\n    EVIDENCE_MARKER_LINT [warn strict-only] - Strict-mode lint for evidence marker formatting.\n\nLEVELS: 1=spec+plan+tasks+impl-summary*, 2=+checklist, 3=+decision-record\n        review=spec+review/review-report (lean review record, marker-gated)\n        *impl-summary required after tasks completed\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh --help","time":{"start":1783915823837,"end":1783915823839}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0370d16f82751bd8016a54652fb064819194d5964083731935"}},"id":"prt_f59ab42a2001CWsq6q7iWAx8XQ","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac46dffebja9CFmlcvrGJ0","messageID":"msg_f59aaa9ca001t3HL5XTur253w5"}}
